INSERT INTO `reviews` VALUES (211,'Chuck',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,3.0,'Also losing feathers','I\'ve had the shirt/jacket for a couple of week now and just wear it to work and client meetings. Like another reviewer, I\'m seeing more feathers poking out of this garment than any other Patagonia jacket I\'ve owned. It\'s a great looking alternative to a typical jacket style. I recommend it for the looks. I am, however, hesitant',35,'2020-06-15'),(212,'Brian K.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Couldn\'t be happier: soft, light weight, warm, stylish','I am a huge fan of Patagonia\'s down jackets, particularly the Hi-Loft Down Hoody which I\'ve had for years. I got this Silent Down Shirt (which is absolutely a jacket and not a shirt) recently and love it. As with the Hi-Loft Hoody, this jacket can keep you very warm in cold temps but I very rarely, if ever, get too hot in it. It\'s so',35,'2020-06-15'),(213,'YUIKO K.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,5.0,'Great customer service !!','We purchased it for Christmas gift. One item was missing in time for Christmas, but the customer service was great !! That\'s why we love this company.',35,'2020-06-15'),(214,'Amy B.',NULL,'None','5T',NULL,5.0,'All Good','Fits well. Good color. Love the snaps.',35,'2020-06-15'),(215,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket','Purchased as a gift for my husband. He likes it very much. The style is unique as it looks like a shirt but has the functionality of a down jacket. Warm enough, he says no need for extra layering in 30-40 degree weather. Blends in really nicely. Trendy style for the typical NYC commuter. He is happy with his purchase.',35,'2020-06-15'),(216,'Foster K.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Toasty warm','Super light weight, comfortable',35,'2020-06-15'),(217,'Jorge H.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,4.0,'Almost perfect','I love the overall fit of the jacket. It\'s warm without being too puffy.',35,'2020-06-15'),(218,'Jakob K.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Amazing product as expected, with a caveat','A small amount of down feathers will poke through the jacket infrequently.',35,'2020-06-15'),(219,'Andrew M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Magnificent','Words cannot really express how stoked I am on this jacket. All the soft, cozy, and functional chops of a technical piece with some casual/streetwear aesthetic. Beautiful color in the sage khaki. Signature eco and socially responsible Patagonia foundations. Perfect fit. Simply cannot lose with this piece....and I’m critical and picky as hell!',35,'2020-06-15'),(220,'Vincent S.',NULL,'None','XS',NULL,3.0,'Good quality, fits a bit big.','Overall the quality is great. It keeps me warm, its silent and very easy to wear. However it is a bit big and the black color is not as black as my other Patagonia jackets.',35,'2020-06-15'),(221,'Robina P.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,5.0,'Great shirt!','Great price, arrived on time, perfect fit!',35,'2020-06-15'),(222,'Fletcher C.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Runs a tiny bit big.','Runs a tiny bit big. I\'m between a M and LG and went M for casual wear (not layering underneath).',35,'2020-06-15'),(223,'Alexander F.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','NB-7lb',NULL,4.0,'Not silent','Its a fine jacket, it is just nowhere near silent.',35,'2020-06-15'),(224,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Good jacket','I gave 4 star only for the reaaon it has buttons instead of zip, rest everyrhing is good. Nixe cozy jacket.',35,'2020-06-15'),(225,'Benjamin D.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','NB-7lb',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket!','Is well made, breathes well, and keeps me warm in Chicago! What I\'ve come to expect from this great brand :)',35,'2020-06-15'),(226,'Dan E.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'insulation and fit','got this late in the season so not a full winter\'s use yet. the insulation works great; very versatile as a layer and overall; the cut of the sleeves and collar are comfortable and the pockets are adequate - would be nice to have an inside breast pocket, or zipper seam one - the only improvement to suggest',35,'2020-06-15'),(227,'Me',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Solid','Best jacket I own. Dresses up for work and functional and warm for early morning east coast surf checks',35,'2020-06-15'),(228,'Ron G.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XXL',NULL,5.0,'spot on','No complaints from me, its really comfortable and very warm. I will mos likely get another one soon in another color.',35,'2020-06-15'),(229,'Matt L.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,3.0,'Losing feathers','I love the warmth of this jacket and the shirt-style look, but I\'ve never had a Patagonia down garment that lost feathers at such an alarming rate (I\'ve had multiple Down Sweaters, a Fitz Roy Parka, and and Ultralight Down Hoody ). I\'m just wearing this casually to walk the dog and to/from the car at work, and there are always feathe',35,'2020-06-15'),(230,'Mitchell P.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,4.0,'Warm, Comfy & Stylish','I love jackets styled after button-up shirts, so this was a no-brainer for me. Fit is on the money, it runs longer than typical Patagonia down jackets which suits tall guys well. Super cozy and the collar stands nicely when flipped for extra protection. While still lightweight like most down jackets, it isn\'t as light & packable as the cla',35,'2020-06-15'),(231,'Andrew J.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Excellent style','Great retro styling and perfect within the bulk.',35,'2020-06-15'),(232,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,3.0,'Not as described (it’s a jacket not a shirt)','This garment is very nice, but it is a jacket, not a shirt. A down “shirt” would be rather thin, like a shirt, even down filled, and appropriate to have on under a jacket. This “shirt” is very puffy, bulky, and runs quite large. Putting a jacket over this “shirt” would be ridiculous. I love the products but just call this one a jacket with front po',35,'2020-06-15'),(233,'william',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'w','bout his down shirt under arm bit tight but overall very comfortable snaps bit to stiff to open and close',35,'2020-06-15'),(234,'Rich',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Versatile','I purchased this jacket to use on a trip to Iceland and Norway. Light weight, very packable, surprisingly warm (Iceland is cold, even in July). I did a lot of climbing and hiking and was very happy to have this jacket along. Another fine Patagonia product.',48,'2020-06-15'),(235,'Stephen S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,3.0,'Pocket zipper teeth rip arm stitches','Ive been buying and wearing the Nano Puff Jacket since it was originally introduced. Its very versatile, works well in a broad range of temps, and is excellent as both insulation and outerwear. At a certain point Patagonia streamlined the fit making it more fitted which I very much prefer. However, it does have a big DESIGN FLAW; the POCKET ZIPPERS',48,'2020-06-15'),(236,'Ed',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Very warm, yet comfortable.','Great jacket. True to size, yet because of my beer gut, a bit tight. BUT, even though it is not breathable(I think), walking around when temps are in the mid to upper 30s, with only a t underneath, I am very comfortable. I have a Pat, Wanaker Down jacket, and with only a t, sweat like a pig, even with temps in the 20s. So the NP is a great, comfort',48,'2020-06-15'),(237,'Matt',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,3.0,'Little too tight','Just got a Nano puff Fall 19 size M and its really tight in chest, back and arm holes. Fits well everywhere else. Im 57 about 170lbs. Feels like jacket is going to rip in back if I move my arms too much. If you have narrow shoulders and chest might work for you. Will probably return it.',48,'2020-06-15'),(238,'Alvin',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Great for casual uses!','I am from Georgia but go to school in Connecticut so I see a pretty big variety of winter weather. The price was a bit of a shock but man it was worth it. On campus, I can wear only a cotton tshirt and the Nano Puff on the way to class and be comfortable down to ~