ling effort Patagonia tries to employ.',48,'2020-06-15'),(441,'Kong V.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,5.0,'Amazing!!!','Awesome quality and I couldn’t be more excited then to finally get my hands on this attire! I love Love this classic navy color way as well!',48,'2020-06-15'),(442,'John B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Compact but warm','The product was exactly what I was looking for in a packable, light jacket. I can\'t wait for the weather to get cold.',48,'2020-06-15'),(443,'Brant',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Everyone needs at least one','I personally feel everyone needs at least one puff jacket in their inventory. The nano puff is my new go to as a light outer layer and low impact base layer. Very packable and perfect for minimizing weight and space. Regulates body temp well across a range of moderate temps...you don\'t have to take it off if you go in somewhere warm for a whil',48,'2020-06-15'),(444,'charles C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Nice casual jacket','Lightweight jacket yet very warm considering how thin it is. Very packable. Warm. Blocks wind. Comfortable. Heavy enough to keep you warm on most occasions. I\'ve only had mine a few weeks but wore it in the Sierras on a breezy 30 degree morning walking our dog. Stayed warm and comfortable. If you\'re in colder weather, I\'d recommend p',48,'2020-06-15'),(445,'Vincent B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket that fits perfectly.','Great jacket that fits perfectly.',48,'2020-06-15'),(446,'Scott L.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Great travel option','The jacket is great for travel to areas where the weather can change temperatures quickly. Can easily be packed and layers well.',48,'2020-06-15'),(447,'Kent P.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Lightweight warmth.','Since 1977 I have always been pleased with Patagonia’s design and quality. The Nanopuff jacket provides warmth and mobility for Minnesota’s chores. Great stuff.',48,'2020-06-15'),(448,'Armand L.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Best snuggly sweater/jacket ever!','This is my second nano puff - I received my 1st as a gift 3 years ago and it became my every day \'grab\'. It is bright green (which was great for Ireland) but my friends and family though it high time to get a new one so I could rotate the colors!',48,'2020-06-15'),(449,'Jasper R.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Combines easily the Patagonia products','Combines easily the Patagonia products ( jackets, fleece, etc). that already own. Plus it’s ability to be compressed into its pocket for packing.',48,'2020-06-15'),(450,'Cassie C.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,5.0,'Ladies can wear them too!','I jumped on to one of the annual 50% off sales and did not see a women\'s puff in the color or size I liked, so I decided to try a \"men\'s\" puff. I wear a M in women\'s and decided to try a S in men\'s. It does fit a bit differently than the women\'s jacket with longer arms, but the rest of the measurements are pretty',48,'2020-06-15'),(451,'Rufino V.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'A versatile swiss army knife','A versatile swiss army knife of a jacket.',48,'2020-06-15'),(452,'Kishan G.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Good jacket','The jacket is very light but warm, making it a good outer layer for temperatures in the 50s/60s.',48,'2020-06-15'),(453,'User',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Awesome Jacket','Best all-around jacket I have ever owned. Great for fall and winter adventures. Easy to pack and can be layered for just about any weekend activity.',48,'2020-06-15'),(454,'Robert M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'waiting for winter','Pleased so far, but it is still quite warm here, so waiting for winter to see how I really like it. I like that it is made from 75% recycled materials, is light weight, water resistant, and stuffs into its own pocket and that I caught it on sale.',48,'2020-06-15'),(455,'Diane H.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Nano puff jacket','looks great, good fit, still summer, so can\'t vouch for warmth',48,'2020-06-15'),(456,'Alex S.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Nano Puff Repeat','Love love the product- it’s my fourth nano puff- and our whole family of 6 wears them!! Keep the colors coming',48,'2020-06-15'),(457,'Jacob J.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'The best!','Comfortable, Incredible quality and great performance. Definitely a product that will last a life time. A great investment!',48,'2020-06-15'),(458,'Steve',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Under layer or over layer','I bought this jacket to use under a Micro Puff Storm Jacket I bought last March. The storm jacket was warm enough for temps in the 30’s and 40’s in upstate NY in March, but I sensed it wouldn’t be adequate on a 10 degree day in January without a warm under layer. The Nano Puff jacket has a slim fit and works perfectly under the more roomy fit of th',48,'2020-06-15'),(459,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Great jacket','My son loves the jacket and color!',48,'2020-06-15'),(460,'Jimmie W.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Nice lightweight jacket','Perfect weight jacket for Arizona weather. Fits as advertised.',48,'2020-06-15'),(461,'Jacob M.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Awesome','Light weight, packable, comfy, funky inner lining which actually allows you to use it backwards! For real! (Brick color). It fits a little odd though, sleeves to long and tide body on a 6’2” 205 lbs guy (on the slim to normal build) the down sweater fits way better but left lots of feathers on clothes.',48,'2020-06-15'),(462,'John M.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Patagonia as usual','Always a great product. Stylish, well made, comfortable, effective.',48,'2020-06-15'),(463,'Scott H.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Nano Puff Jacket','First one was so great, I bought a second one so that my son would stop borrowing mine! Lightweight, packs small, and comes in handy on our camping trips.',48,'2020-06-15'),(464,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great Jacket','I live in Alaska and having a warm jacket that is easy to layer with is essential. This jacket does the trick for temps as low as 30 below!!',48,'2020-06-15'),(465,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great Jacket','Fits true to size and is a great addition to the closet. Warm when you need it to be warm and surprisingly breathable otherwise',48,'2020-06-15'),(466,'Eugene S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','NB-7lb',NULL,5.0,'great versatile jacket','great versatile jacket for Bay Area climate. this is my daily go-to jacket that I take to work in case it gets chilly at night.',48,'2020-06-15'),(467,'Clare D.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Pretty good','For a light weight insulating layer it’s pretty good. I bought this to replace a basic 650 fill down puffy that was at the end of its life. The Nano isn’t quite as warm but it packs about as small and doesn’t weigh much. The fit is just ok for me. it’s a little more boxy in the shoulders than I need and the waist has a tendency to ride up kinda wei',48,'2020-06-15'),(468,'William B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Ecellent','Comfortable, Light Weight, Warm. Perfect.',48,'2020-06-15'),(469,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,3.0,'Nano Puff','This is the second Patagonia jacket I\'ve had in green. Both have shown dark discoloring around the inside of the collar. So weird. It\'s not like I sweat profusely or don\'t bathe. I don\'t get it. Maybe it happens on my black puffer but I just can\'t see it.',48,'2020-06-15'),(470,'Noah K.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Trail Harbor Pocket Shirt','I absolutely love these shirts. They are comfortable and help keep me cool on hot days. They fit great too',48,'2020-06-15'),(471,'Keith L.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Handsome','Great comfort and style. Love the fun interior of the rust red jacket.',48,'2020-06-15'),(472,'Brad C.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Well worth it','I knew you had a good product but was always scared off by the price. Well now that I got past that mental block I know why they cost a bit more is because that are worth it. You get what you pay for. A great jacket worth every penny. I will buy more Patagonia products as I have a need. Love them.',48,'2020-06-15'),(473,'John G.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,2.0,'Too tight in the armpits','I had to return the jacket as it was too tight in the arm pits.',48,'2020-06-15'),(474,'Rafael G.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'The perfect layer!!! And travel jacket.','Packable. Warm. Comfortable. This is the perfect layer. Heavy enough to keep you warm on most occasions. If you find yourself in very cold weather, pair this jacket with proper layering and you’ll find yourself warm without the feeling of being weighed down. Oh yeah, it also packs into a nice pillow for traveling!',48,'2020-06-15'),(475,'Joe S.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Outstanding garment','This is a re-review. I have now had the jacket for several months, with some serious hiking and backpacking, along with multiple bike commutes in PNW winter. It is amazing in warmth to weight! Stuffs away in pack or travel bag to almost nothing, but keeps me warm and dry. Great under a rainshell or by itself in light rain. Pockets big enough for an',48,'2020-06-15'),(476,'Daniel S.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Light but Warm','Lightweight jacket yet very warm considering how thin it is.',48,'2020-06-15'),(477,'Edward T.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Mens Nano Puff jacket','This jacket is the best of both worlds...its super light, super warm, and very compact. I would recommend it to anyone!',48,'2020-06-15'),(478,'Tom S.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Good for active pursuits','This is not an insta-cozy winter coat and I always start out a little too cold, but it\'s great for active pursuits in cold weather. It warms up well without overheating. Fits slim overall. I really like the low profile hood for under a helmet.',48,'2020-06-15'),(479,'Randel R.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Very warm the fit is','Very warm the fit is perfect and it also stows very easily in a very compact way',48,'2020-06-15'),(480,'Roopak P.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Nice versatile jacket','Works for mild winters. Looks great! Easy to clean and maintain.',48,'2020-06-15'),(481,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket','Perfect jacket for all kinds of weather! It’s cozy but not hot. True to sizing.',48,'2020-06-15'),(482,'Kate W.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Light weight and tough','I take my Nano Puff everywhere as it is breathable yet protective against all weather situations and packs down very small. Great all around jacket for city our outdoor use!',48,'2020-06-15'),(483,'Zac B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Easiest on-off jacket ever!','Love the moderate warmth, great fit, and easy transitions from on-off!',48,'2020-06-15'),(484,'Canaan C.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Nano Puff Jacket','I love this jacket, it is the most versatile jacket I own and extremely warm for how light it is! Patagonia makes the utmost amazing products and clothing and this is a piece everyone should own.',48,'2020-06-15'),(485,'Tamara C.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Lightweight quilted jacket','Nothing is better for traveling than this jacket. In unpredictable spring weather this jacket is as welcome as a satin edged toodler’s security blankie!',48,'2020-06-15'),(486,'Nancy M.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'The Best Jacket Ever!','I was looking for a jacket for our Zion hiking trip and this jacket was perfect for all weather conditions!!',48,'2020-06-15'),(487,'Casey M.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Super comfortable and light. Will','Super comfortable and light. Will be great for future backpacking trips!',48,'2020-06-15'),(488,'Anh H.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','NB-7lb',NULL,3.0,'Great fabric innovation - Need to re-examine fit','I wear size XS and found the body and sleeve\'s length too long while width-wise everything fits nicely.',48,'2020-06-15'),(489,'Alec M.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Awesome Stuff','Great product. Had an issue with a hole in a recently purchased qzip and they replaced it immediately. Would recommend',48,'2020-06-15'),(490,'Betsy F.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Picky husband','Patagonia didn’t disappoint. My husband is always having trouble finding the right fit and this was perfect.',48,'2020-06-15'),(491,'Elisabeth H.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Wear a Cloud','I love everything about this garment. Light as a puff of air, color, pockets and washability- washing necessary and easy because I wear it so often',48,'2020-06-15'),(492,'Helen H.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Love every outfit I bought.','Love every outfit I bought. Use them daily!',48,'2020-06-15'),(493,'Kathryn C.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Slim cut','Fit is quite slim. My husband exchanged his usual medium for a large. It is a bit too large in shoulders and long in arms. He is slim, but the jacket cut is not for him. Otherwise just what he wanted.',48,'2020-06-15'),(494,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Perfect!','Works great, in cold or warm weather. This will be your go to, and without the hood allows for more wear.',48,'2020-06-15'),(495,'Mark H.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Perfect for sports','I bought this for playing golf on chilly fall days. It is a perfect jacket for this, lightweight and with full arm movement - other than being warm, it feels like nothing’s on!',48,'2020-06-15'),(496,'Eric F.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,1.0,'The jacket is AWESOME but...','It was a fit thing for me. The large was too big and the medium too small. I’m a “normal” build 5’10 180 lbs. I was surprised , and bummed, I couldn’t find a fit.',48,'2020-06-15'),(497,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Love It','It\'s my favorite and most functional jacket I own.',48,'2020-06-15'),(498,'John W.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,1.0,'XXL was too small.','Wanted to keep it, but due to size had to return items.',48,'2020-06-15'),(499,'Kevin',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'No Micro Green?','I have a very old version of this jacket. Looks nothing like this one (mines a half-zip, non-pleated insulation, with zippered chest pocket - at least 20 years old I would say). I was thinking of upgrading but I see there\'s no Micro Green color any more. That color is what inspired me to possibly upgrade. Please bring back the Micro Green colo',48,'2020-06-15'),(500,'Krish C.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,2.0,'Great jacket, but definitely won\'t last very long','Nano puff is a great jacket, its super light weight, easily packable. Unfortunately, it rips super easily on any kind of contact - brush against a door and you\'ve torn a thread, brush against a branch and you\'ve ripped it. I originally bought it to wear during activity but I don\'t think it\'ll last even a few months like that. Ca',48,'2020-06-15'),(501,'Thomas S.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'Versatile jacket','My first Patagonia.',48,'2020-06-15'),(502,'Ray',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,2.0,'Not durable','Warm, light, yes. Durable, no. Material is very delicate. Insulation popping out everywhere from micro-tears. Zipper broke.',48,'2020-06-15'),(503,'John S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,3.0,'It\'s aight','5\'11\" 200 lbs athletic build. This jacket does what its intended for, which is to be part of a layering system. If you aren\'t an outdoor athlete/sportsman this jacket is probably not for you. It is not an around town jacket by itself if it\'s below 30-40 but held up in below zero temps on lake Superior with 20mph gust as part of',48,'2020-06-15'),(504,'Jacob H.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Good enough','I bought it on sale so the price was more agreeable. The jacket is great down to 32 F for me, and it packs away super tight, so that’s nice. Only problem is that it snags kinda easy, even on its own zipper, but that can be avoided if you’re careful enough.',48,'2020-06-15'),(505,'Melissa R.',NULL,'6\'7 or above','S',NULL,5.0,'Perfect','This jacket fit as described. My son loves it!',48,'2020-06-15'),(506,'Greg',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,2.0,'Love the jacket. Lot\'s of fraying.','Got this jacket at a gift at Christmas and love it. Very light weight and comfortable while providing great warmth. Unfortunately I have a hard time recommending it because within two months of wearing it there is a lot of fraying through the exterior of the jacket. I\'m constantly noticing threads hanging from various spots on the jacket, to t',48,'2020-06-15'),(507,'Peter',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,4.0,'GO TO JACKET','Wear the jacket all the time. Usually under gorex. I live in Juneau. Wet and an on the coldish side. Light weight. Fabric durable for me but the zipper comes off the track. I see these thin plastic zipper\'s',48,'2020-06-15'),(508,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Best jacket i’ve ever owned','This was the greatest jacket I have ever owned. I wore this pretty much every single day and it kept me very warm. I highly recommend this to everyone, but unfortunately mine was stolen at a bar the other night and now I do not own the nano puff. I am very very sad about this loss :(',48,'2020-06-15'),(509,'Dean',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Compliments','I bought this jacket in micro green last December. It fits great and is more than warm enough for most winter weather in Georgia. I receive compliments from coworkers almost every time I wear it. Great quality and worth the price.',48,'2020-06-15'),(510,'Luis C.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,2.0,'Perfectly Imperfect','Let me start off by saying that this is ALMOST the best jacket I have ever bought. It is warm, light weight, and such an amazing all around jacket with a horrible side effect. The stitching and threads come off with just about any contact. Patagonia was amazing enough to replace it because my first one was already tearing after two months of use an',48,'2020-06-15'),(511,'Sergey',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XXL',NULL,1.0,'Try first in store before buying on line','New Nano puffs changed in way it is fit now. And if you like me a long time fan of Nano Puffs, and have two-three jackets of older generation.....it is true, the fit changed for the worse. Size XXL is no longer fit me in chest and way, way too tight in the armpit, very tight. And I am pretty comfortable in similar jackets size XL in MHW or NF. So t',48,'2020-06-15'),(512,'Brett',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,4.0,'Nice Jacker but...','This is a really nice jacket it was 26 and windy today and kept me warm with a tee shirt and hoody on under it. My only complaint is that when the side pockets are unzipped the teeth of the zipper grabs the stitching on the arms and pulls the string out. The same thing is happening to my wife’s jacket. Overall love the jacket just hope it stands th',48,'2020-06-15'),(513,'Sean M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,3.0,'Fit has changed for the worse','Just purchased new Nano Puff to replace my old one. Bought same M size - much too tight in shoulders/armpits and sleeves too long. I know a lot of Patagonia customers are lanky climbers, but a lot more aren\'t at this point! I\'m 6\'1\" 180 lbs and unfortunately large would be too big because I\'d have to roll up the cuffs.',48,'2020-06-15'),(514,'Jason',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,2.0,'Not very durable','The Nano puff will keep you warm but I would not plan on using this for real outdoor activities. The shell material is very lightweight but is prone to snags. I wouldn\'t go hiking in this jacket because after an hour the shell would be wreaked. Also, the jacket does run small. I am 5\' 9\" and had to get a large.',48,'2020-06-15'),(515,'Matt B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,4.0,'I wish it was more durable','I have had this jacket for two years and I love it. The fit is great and it is surprisingly warm down to 0°F. I’ve even worn it sailing wear I was soaking wet. My only complaint is that it is not very durable. Within the first year, I had to send it in to repair a torn sleeve and I just sent it in again with 5 smaller tears. One of which is from th',48,'2020-06-15'),(516,'Tom H.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Looks sleek','Just got my new nano puff last week and wore it to work right away. I am in and out of a vehicle all day, so I need to dress for the winter weather. This jacket looks really nice so I like that. Very light weight and packable. Good for layering under or over. It was 28F in the early morning with a breeze, and I had a sweatshirt under this, and it w',48,'2020-06-15'),(517,'Dennis',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Good midweight jacket','I\'m 5-11 and 180 and the fit is fine and it looks great. Comfortable and super light in weight. When worn as midweight jacket it\'s warm into the 30s if you\'re active but not if stationary. I wear it as my mid-layer over fleece when skiing and its warm to the teens and not restrictive. I bought it on sale at a considerable discount; I',48,'2020-06-15'),(518,'Dirk',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,2.0,'Not a \"Regular Fit\" - Fit has changed.','I\'ve owned a couple of Nano Puff jackets over the years and they have been great for all outdoor activities with lengthy sleeves and looser fit. In addition to the OLD R1, the older styles Nano Puff were my favorite outdoor piece. I recently purchased this newer version and boy has the fit changed. I am tall and slim and the new fitting is too',48,'2020-06-15'),(519,'Sue',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'My 17 year old son LOVES this jacket!','My son is an outdoor enthusiast, skier, hiker and wears this everyday to school in the Northeast. He absolutely LOVES this jacket, however he has had it for about a year, and the zipper is broken-',48,'2020-06-15'),(520,'Wesley W.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,5.0,'Best Jacket Ever...!!!1','Read some of the 1 and 2 star reviews and couldn\'t believe what I was reading so I decided write this review. This is the most amazing jacket I have ever owned. For anyone sitting on the fence about buying it...BUY IT !!!! First of all, it is for me the absolutely the warmest jacket for it\'s weight. I live in the San Francisco Bay Area wh',48,'2020-06-15'),(521,'Thomas N.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,1.0,'Poor material choice','I have had this jacket for less than four months. It is falling apart. The very first time I wore it it, filling pulled out in front. Since, small tears opened up in the sleeves and on the back of the jacket.',48,'2020-06-15'),(522,'Ben H.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,2.0,'The fit changed for the worse','I didn’t want to believe it...but it’s true, the fit has changed for the worse. I ALWAYS wear a medium in Patagonia, and have owned two Nano Puffs and countless other Patty items. Keep in mind, I am a tall, slender musician who prefers to wear form fitting clothes...but the fit on the new Nano Puffs has gone too far. Way too tight in the armpits (i',48,'2020-06-15'),(523,'Sean B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Incredibly versatile, incredibly stylish','This is the best outerwear purchase I’ve ever made. It can be worn in such a wide range of temps all while keeping you incredibly comfortable. It’s also very stylish and I receive compliments all the time. Great quality, this jacket checks all the boxes!',48,'2020-06-15'),(524,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'It’s Great','I’m 5’10” 180 lbs and the medium fits great. I can wear it with either a t or base layer and a light fleece. It’s surprisingly warm, due to being wind proof and is very lightweight. It packs down very small too. Highly recommend.',48,'2020-06-15'),(525,'David',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,2.0,'Nice jacket but poor fit for a tall average build male.','I have an original Nano jacket in size large and purchased a new one in my size large. It did not fit like the original. It was tight around the chest and neck. I reordered a size XL and it was hugh. Felt like I was wearing a poncho. I’m 6’5” and 200 pounds and normally wear a size large in regular fit and size XL in a slim fit. It has been a hassl',48,'2020-06-15'),(526,'Seacoast H.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,1.0,'Nano Puffs,R1 Pants, R1 pullovers etc etc','I have purchased a few items over the past 15 years from Patagonia to include a 2005 Primo ski jacket, R1 pants, R1 zipped pullovers and Nano puff jackets. I have been happy with the ski jacket over the years but the R1 pants and tops have changed not only in materials & weight but sizing. The Nano puff jacket has gotten slimmer in the body and',48,'2020-06-15'),(527,'Serge B.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,1.0,'I will never buy Patagonia product again','This afternoon I bough Patagonia Nano Puff jacket from REI. The jacket looked very good and put it on right in the store and then drove home. At home when put it off I noticed that the seam got loose on my shoulder. I read several negative reviews, but I was loyal to Patagonia and inspected every inch of the jacked at the store -- there were no def',48,'2020-06-15'),(528,'Drew',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,3.0,'Pocket zipper design flaw','I am new to Patagonia, this Nano Puff jacket is my first purchase and I didn’t know much about the brand prior to purchasing. After I did some research, I liked what Patagonia represents from an environmental and reputation aspect. I love how functional this jacket is for all the reasons that most have talked about. However, I have had the jacket f',48,'2020-06-15'),(529,'Pradeep J.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,1.0,'Design flaw','I have used this jacket for the last couple of months and am about to return the product. First of all, it is not very warm and secondly the front end of the collar is higher than the rest of the collar and is constantly chafing my jaw/ cheeks/ ears depending on standing/ sitting position. Highly irritating.',48,'2020-06-15'),(530,'Tyler B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,3.0,'Light and warm, very fragile','I’ve got both a pull over and jacket in the nanopuff line. The good about them is they pack very small and the weight to warmth ratio is very good. The bad, the coats are very fragile, the stitching along the baffles and cuffs snag on nearly everything that passes over the fabric. The coats don’t stay attractive looking for long, becoming misshapen',48,'2020-06-15'),(531,'Zachary C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,1.0,'I expected better quality: jacket has loose threads all over','I love the cut, the warmth, the material, the recycled-ness… but the workmanship on this jacket is the worst of any piece of gear I’ve used. I’ve had it for 6 months and maybe worn for 1, and it’s got pulled threads all over. One of the baffle threads on the jacket front pulled loose the very first week, and the recommendation from Patagonia custom',48,'2020-06-15'),(532,'Kala E.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'1 Jacket = all temps','This jacket is perfect for all temperatures. I have gone snowboarding in this jacket and used it under my shell. It kept me warm in -10 degree weather. This jacket has also kept me comfortable all the way up to the mid 60’s. Anything 70’s and above this jacket will be too warm for you.',48,'2020-06-15'),(533,'Calitosway',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,5.0,'The last jacket you will ever need!','Absolutely the best I have replaced every single jacket with just three of these a black a regular color like a grayish and of course you need a vest that’s all you ever need in your wardrobe. Patagonia makes really nice stuff whether you want to dress up or simply use a pair jeans !! Is worth every penny I bought one for every person in my house.',48,'2020-06-15'),(534,'rcthompson',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,3.0,'Warm Jacket, Strange Size','So I ordered a Medium after looking at the size guide, putting in my dimensions online, and reading through the reviews. Holy cow, this thing is HUGE. I\'m ~175lbs, 5\'10, and the size dwarfs my athletic frame. It\'s especially strange after going back through and reading the reviews mentioning the more slim fit others are receiving. Ho',48,'2020-06-15'),(535,'Bearcat85',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Best layering insulted jacket you can get','The nanopuff jacket and hoodie is the insulated layer of choice for Alaskan fishing guides. So I got one myself. You can\'t beat the weight/utility/comfort combo on this jacket. It seems to have the inate ability to adjust to the elements, and not be too hot or cold. Throw a high quality shell on top and you are set for any situation above 20°',48,'2020-06-15'),(536,'Greg',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Greg','I work with the military and we are always traveling to different places for training. In between training and traveling I\'ve been through just about every sort of weather. When it gets cold I\'m always looking for my green nano puff jacket to keep me warm. This jacket is excellent, perfect size, weight, and fit. When I\'m wearing civi',48,'2020-06-15'),(537,'James',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,2.0,'James','I washed a down sweater, meticulously following Patagonia\'s instructions, and it was ruined. But, true to their history and character, Patagonia offered to replace it, but with a Nano-Puff (as they didn\'t consider another down sweater \'suitable\' for me - even though I swore never to wash it.). I assumed it would perform close to',48,'2020-06-15'),(538,'Bodie H.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Best jacket ever made','Living in Arizona this jacket is perfect for everything, fits great, extremely durrable, looks great, and the primaloft has the perfect balance of warmth and wind blocker for all my adventures in the city or the mountains. Im 6\'2 and wear a large as i have a 6\'4 wing span and prefer the longer sleeves and shoulder movement.',48,'2020-06-15'),(539,'Bob',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,3.0,'Good but not great','The insulation comes out of the seems pretty easily and the cuffs get worn pretty easily. On the positive side, it fits great and it really warm. You may just want to use a lint roller to collect the insulation that comes out.',48,'2020-06-15'),(540,'Jay C.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Outstanding Jacket for a wide range of temps','This is my everything jacket. I wear it and am comfortable in temps from 30- low 60s. After two years of regular wear, it is in the same condition as when I bought it, no issues with ripped squares or pulled threading. It is true to size but slim-fitting, which makes it easy to layer when necessary.',48,'2020-06-15'),(541,'Andy N.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,2.0,'Not even close to a regular fit','Purchased to replace an old nanopuff.... the sizing has gone down by at least 1 size... it is a slim fit, and regardless of the sizing assistance on the website go up at least a size. Shoulders so snug that if I move to dramatically, they will tear... I’m a very fit XL, and an outdoor professional... it’s a great jacket, the sizing is just way off.',48,'2020-06-15'),(542,'Joe',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Just What I Needed','I was looking for a jacket that could be used throughout the year. I need a mid-layer for skiing, a hiking jacket that would keep me warm on night hikes, and cool on spring/fall hikes, a jacket that was perfect around the campfire, and one that could be packed super small, lightweight, and could double as a pillow. This jackets covers them all. It ',48,'2020-06-15'),(543,'E',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,2.0,'Good. Just wish Patagonia would make sturdier products.','As a poor undergraduate geology student I used to lust over Patagonia\'s gear. Their stuff seemed so practical and useful but at that time I just couldn\'t afford the price tag associated with them. Years and years down the line I\'ve owned a number of Patagonia garments all across the line. Recently I have been pretty disappointed with',48,'2020-06-15'),(544,'John',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,1.0,'Sizing is terrible','Patagonia needs to greatly improve their seriously flawed sizing system. Im 5 11 and 170 pounds. Im a solid medium in everything that I wear. A medium in Patagonia puff jackets cuts off circulation around my armpits, and is weirdly tight around my waist. when zippered, I can\'t even swing my arms sideward because Im afraid it would rip the jack',48,'2020-06-15'),(545,'Stephen S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Finally: Classic Navy w/o Contrast!!','My 10 year old Nano has been a go to jacket and this one is even better. It has a great temperature range on it’s own, is great for layering under shells or insulated jackets, and packs small. It’s warmer than my old one; either better insulation or age, I don’t know. THANK YOU for finally issuing in CLASSIC NAVY W/O THE ANNOYING CONTRAST. Classic',48,'2020-06-15'),(546,'JD113',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,4.0,'My Favorite Jacket Ever But Why Mess with it?','I have 3 older versions. I can wear them all year long. Absolutely perfect. Warm,dry,packable. Layer perfection for skiing. Just nailed it. I\'m a fairly new Patagonia lover,I have a closet full,but lately I am worried that this can\'t last too long because they seem to be shrinking the jackets. Everything is Slim fit now. I\'m not fat,',48,'2020-06-15'),(547,'Archer70',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,4.0,'Great Jack. Only One Gripe.','Love this jacket. Only wish it wasn\'t so tight/narrow in the armpit area where the body of the jacket connects to the arm. Patagonia please fix this so i can buy another!',48,'2020-06-15'),(548,'Scotty2014',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,2.0,'Seams a little weak.','I\'ve had two of these jackets since November and both of them have had a seam on one of the boxes pull out,I\'m very careful with the jacket,but it still happened twice. If this was fixed somehow on a future model I would get another one. Until then I would have a tough time recommending this jacket,which is unfortunate because I love ever',48,'2020-06-15'),(549,'Tim D.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,2.0,'Love the product poor sizing','I have an older version of this jacket and love it but this latest version isn\'t even close to the sizing of the older one. I am 6\' 2\' and weight 183 lbs and the sizing calculator told me I was a large. My older Nano Puff was a large and fit me perfectly. This one is way smaller in the shoulders and not close to fitting. I tried an X',48,'2020-06-15'),(550,'John T.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Must Have Jacket','I purchased this jacket in the winter of 2016 and it has easily been one of the best purchases I\'ve made. It is deceptively lightweight,which makes you think the slightest cold breeze would make its way to your core. Boy,is that a lie. Not only is it wind proof,it is quite warm as well. It is great for just about any activity and I frequently',48,'2020-06-15'),(551,'12hjyu76',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Versatile','This jacket is light and packable but adds serious warmth. I use it daily around town and it keeps me comfortable in moderate temperatures. I then wore it XC skiing in 10* F and overheated to the point I soaked the jacket with sweat and ended up skiing home in my T-shirt. I also wore this alpine skiing in some pretty nasty weather at 13.5k and agai',48,'2020-06-15'),(552,'Disappointed D.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,2.0,'Beware: New Nano Puff\'s Smaller than the Old.','I have owned and loved one of these jackets for several years; and liked the one I own so much that I decided to purchase another one in a different color. The new jacket I just received is significantly more tailored than the one I now have - to the point it almost looks like a women\'s jacket and I can\'t begin to get it zipped up even th',48,'2020-06-15'),(553,'Anonymous',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Great upgrade','I have about a 10 or so year old version of this type of jack that was before nano puff but also not down that was getting a little long in the tooth. The material was starting to show its age. I didn\'t really need a new one but grab one of these last year when they were discontinuing a color. What a great coat and it is an upgrade,fit is a li',48,'2020-06-15'),(554,'David L.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Just a great jacket','I decided to retire my first Nano puff after 4+ years of wear,thorn snags,and campfire sparks,even though it was still holding up great. I got the same exact jacket again because it\'s awesome. Light,warm,and easily packs down for travel. The old one is either getting passed on,or going to the Patagonia recycle program.',48,'2020-06-15'),(555,'Art V.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Yet another great product','Wanted one of this for a long tie and finally got one for a trekking trip to Torres del Paine. Jacket did not disappoint... it packs up light and easy and was perfect after long days on the trail... or during some of the inclement weather we encountered. Jacket has enough features for what you need but is sleek enough to fit under a shell or other ',48,'2020-06-15'),(556,'Rollo002',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Not just a climbing or skiing jacket!','A fantastic,versatile jacket that performs very much as stated. It is warm without being too warm or constricting,fits well and layers without adding excessive bulk.',48,'2020-06-15'),(557,'Chappyboy1',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Perfect every day ski baselayer under shell','This is my go-to piece under any shell jacket 10-35 degrees. Enough insulation to keep you warm on the lift and not overheat on a hike. Stays warm if damp as well. I\'m comfortable in a large. I\'m 6ft,195 and usually use a 42R suit jacket.',48,'2020-06-15'),(558,'Linney',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Great all around cool weather jacket','I have had this jacket for a year and a half,it was my go to jacket at least 3 times a week. The fit was perfect for me,5\'8,150,31 waist,a small was just barely tight in the waist and hip but loose enough towards the chest and shoulders that it gave me good movement,maybe a bit loose in the forearms but I almost always had it pulled up my fore',48,'2020-06-15'),(559,'Nick123456',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Get the next size up unless u are a string bean','Very nice coat however the size chart is misleading. Ordered the Large because of my shoulder size and the coat fits my shoulder witdth of 44 but is too small in the arms and body. I lift weights and am not overweight,my arms do not fit in the sleeves and the body is also slim. Tried the XL in another color and that fit great. Very disappointed to',48,'2020-06-15'),(560,'Deweyphan',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,2.0,'not warm or versatile enough','First off,jacket fit is not regular. I\'m 5\'8 160 lbs. the small is way too tight at the pits,and the medium is way too loose and long in the arms. I can care less about the fit but it\'s not warm enough. With a t-shirt underneath and this jacket around 45-50 degree,I was beyond cold. I used the Nano puff as a mid-layer and when the te',48,'2020-06-15'),(561,'Cmcenearney',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,3.0,'wear all the time but should be better for the $','Since getting this I wear it as the go-to daily jacket for autumn-winter-spring,in NYC. I find it does just fine on the coldest days with a sweater or thick shirt underneath (1 hour plus at the playground,standing around). So that is awesome. And very comfortable.',48,'2020-06-15'),(562,'John',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,2.0,'Nice jacket but very slim fit','I just received my Nano Puff. I ordered it to have a jacket similar to the down sweater (which I love) but useful for more active things like hiking and bicycle commuting. I like it BUT it fits so snug that I\'m probably going to have to send it back. It\'s advertised as \"regular fit\" but it\'s definitely a slim fit. I am 5&#x',48,'2020-06-15'),(563,'Dragonia',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'New Nano Puff Replaced 2013 model','I brought my 2013 purched at the Soho store into the Pasadena store for a repair. The filling was compressed,I had a few small holes in front,the stitching was coming out. And the associate san me through the repair process but then decided the jacket hadn\'t lived up to it\'s expectations. So he offered to replace it with brand new Black s',48,'2020-06-15'),(564,'Henderson',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great Jacket with one small limitation....','Bought this during the yearly sales push and just began wearing it today (weather finally dropped into the low 50s). Overall impressions are very positive. It is pretty cold and windy here and this jacket blocks the wind effectively and keeps the body warm. Zippers all work well and the pockets are deep enough to carry items comfortably. The collar',48,'2020-06-15'),(565,'Daniel A.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,3.0,'Very packable,not sure about durability long term','I like my Nano puff,although I haven\'t had the opportunity to wear it much. I was fortunate to purchase it at 40% off,probably wouldn\'t buy it all full price when you could get an Icebreaker Merino equivalent for pretty much the same price.',48,'2020-06-15'),(566,'Nagano B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,3.0,'Weak stitching?','My first Nano Puff,but hopefully not my last. I really like the lightweight warmth and fit of this jacket,but after wearing it for about two hours the stitching started to unravel at 5\'6 points along the length of the waist hem. Patagonia in Tokyo where I bought it is repairing the stitching for free,and will replace the jacket if it happens a',48,'2020-06-15'),(567,'Linda B.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'Light weight & warm','Bought this for my son and he loves that it can be shoved in his backpack when he gets to school and he doesn\'t notice the weight. Kept him warm this weekend at 29f while at camp',48,'2020-06-15'),(568,'Wilsondallas',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Super light and easy to travel!!!','Works great by itselt or layered. Real light and easy to pack!',48,'2020-06-15'),(569,'Casstucks',NULL,'5\'0 or less','XS',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket','Bought this in men\'s xs for my daughter. It\'s very cute love the color and lightweight of the jacket. Wish they had the old one with the red zippers',48,'2020-06-15'),(570,'Robininn',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Perfect for all kinds of weather','I bought this for my husband before heading to the Netherlands and it was a perfect choice as we have encountered torrential rains and wind and he has been dry,warm and comfirtable!',48,'2020-06-15'),(571,'Lore J.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'Light weight,easy to pack and warm!','I bought this jacket for my son who works for the National Park Service doing backcountry trail work. I hiked in to visit him and he was totally thrilled with his birthday present! It was starting to get cold and he really needed the extra layer of warmth!',48,'2020-06-15'),(572,'Bruce4848',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'My 3rd Nano Puff','I got this one on sale and the xl was gigantic. I brouht it into the store and they',48,'2020-06-15'),(573,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Love this Jacket!','Just bought my second Nano Puff (for a bit of colour variety). Best jacket I\'ve ever owned. Lightweight and warm on its own,and an excellent insulation layer under a goretex shell for winter. I wear it all the time,for all activities.',48,'2020-06-15'),(574,'Kjh1123',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Perfect for crisp fall weather.','Lightweight and easy to pack for a weekend getaway,',48,'2020-06-15'),(575,'bo n.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Awesome color!','I got the Mojave Khaki color. It\'s less Khaki,and more like C3PO,in a good way. Really digging the color.',48,'2020-06-15'),(576,'Daniel H.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Chilly Hike? Nope','Great for those chilly nights out on the trail where a heavier jacket wouldn\'t make sense.',48,'2020-06-15'),(577,'Christine G.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'Super warm super packable','This jacket is super warm and awesome,the color nouveau green looks grey in the photo but it is very unique in person (a mix of green,grey,and blue) and fits my style perfectly.',48,'2020-06-15'),(578,'Wmsy',NULL,'5\'1 - 5\'3','S',NULL,5.0,'Great for international travel','I got this jacket mainly for travel. It is warm,lightweight and packagable down to the size of a pouch that fits inside my hand carries Or laptop backpack bag within making it crowded or bulky.',48,'2020-06-15'),(579,'Hornbeam',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Small Updates Required','I bought this as a midlayer for skiing as well as general wear. The only thing I am left wanting is for some stretch in the pit area,hybriding the sides would result in a bomb of a jacket,in my humble opinion. The other reason I gave 4 stars is that the fit was just a teensy bit snug,compared to the other Patagucci stuff I\'ve purchased.',48,'2020-06-15'),(580,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'great jacket','bought this jacket on sale. Definitely my go to jacket in spring and late fall. Insulation is amazing and the weightless feel is awesome. More importantly,it breathes well esp in a poorly-ventilated and over-heated subway. Great product!',48,'2020-06-15'),(581,'Lbarone',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,4.0,'great but fragile','light,classy,warm but too fragile.',48,'2020-06-15'),(582,'Scott B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Love and loss','I had my Nano Puff for a few happy months of late spring cool camping and river trips. Sadly it was in a bag that fell off a trailer of boring gear a couple weeks ago. Looks like I need to buy another one now :-/',48,'2020-06-15'),(583,'Bearcat85',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Best all weather insulating jacket out there','Perfect multi-weather insulating jacket out there. Seems to have unique ability to sense what temperature it is and adapt. If it gets too warm you can stuff it in your pocket. If it gets windy and cold,does its job. Good to about freezing on its own. Great under waders,pretty much standard apparel for Alaska guides for good reason. Only drawback is',48,'2020-06-15'),(584,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Love this jacket!','I bought this for my son who is going to spend the summer in the Boundary Waters in Ontario Canada. His first week there it snowed,and he told me that he used this jacket layered with a fleece underneath and his rain jacket on top and he stayed toasty warm. I love that this is a synthetic fiber since he will be canoeing all summer and that material',48,'2020-06-15'),(585,'Peter L.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Hard To Believe How Warm This Little Thing Is','This is a birthday present from my wife. Big points for her. I can\'t believe how warm this lightweight jacket is. Not sure how they do it but I never seem to get too warm in it. Every other lightweight jacket or hoodie I have makes me sweat at some point. Also the wind resistance or wind proofing is incredible. I tried it out on my motorcycle',48,'2020-06-15'),(586,'Lisa H.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Light and Warm and Packable!','We love our Nanopuffs so much I made up a little chorus to sing about them. The name is a adorable as the jacket is functional!',48,'2020-06-15'),(587,'Pete57',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Spring,fall or winter base.','Perfect weight base layer,stylish,and still being used into 2017 mid May because Northern Maine can still get frost this time of year',48,'2020-06-15'),(588,'Jackie 2.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Returned','Great piece but it was too tight under my arms so I returned it. So sorry I had to do so. I would have exchanged for xl but the L sleeves were pretty long do I figured the xl would be too long.',48,'2020-06-15'),(589,'Nippon B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Excellent,as expected','In total between my husband and myself,we own 5 nano puff jackets. I can\'t say enough positive things about this product. It is lightweight,which is perfect for traveling. It washes very well and air dries in a flash. It is surprisingly warm,given how lightweight it is. The style is also flattering for both men and women.',48,'2020-06-15'),(590,'Kyle B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,1.0,'New fit is way too small :(','First off,I own 5 Nano puffs. Second,I will note that they are all the models from last year prior to the \"overhaul.\" I am so in love with these jackets but not anymore. I ripped my black one that I use for work and Patagonia sent me a replacement. The nano puffs now are so incredibly tight. They hike up in the arm pits and all around the',48,'2020-06-15'),(591,'Tough M.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'Good Layering Option','This is one of my go-to jackets! It\'s very lightweight and packs down into a pretty small square. It\'s very easy to shove in my pack when I\'m not sure if I will need another layer or not for the day. I can even clip it to the outside of my pack if I don\'t room inside. I would say though that the jacket is a little tight around t',48,'2020-06-15'),(592,'H2ocamping',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Light and packable','The biggest reason I purchased the nano,compactablility,wether I\'m backpacking,skiing,or on the motorcycle I know i will have room. The nano as well as all the jackets I have from Patagonia fit to size. The nano is also light so it can be used as a layer or alone.',48,'2020-06-15'),(593,'derkle07',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Awesome product here!','This jacket is perfect for the high alpine environment as an in-between layer when you really need it.',48,'2020-06-15'),(594,'Jake5280',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Just love it!','Perfect weight and warmth so exactly what I was expecting',48,'2020-06-15'),(595,'Terrific J.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Great Combination','Remarkable combination of warmth and light weight. Very happy with the jacket and glad that I consulted with one of the advisors regarding the intended use of this jacket. I would have made the wrong choice had I not called.',48,'2020-06-15'),(596,'Amy S.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,4.0,'Great Midweight Synthetic Staple','A great substitute for a the Down Sweater when temperatures are in the 40\'s & 50\'s The fit is slightly slimmer & form fitting that the older Nano Puff jackets. I do wish Patagonia would go back to the older more roomy cut.',48,'2020-06-15'),(597,'Nano H.',NULL,'None','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Men\'s Nani puff jacket','Love the jacket so much. But your products run small . I wish they were a tad bigger. It\'s not just me ,our entire patrol complains about this .',48,'2020-06-15'),(598,'Casey B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Best Jacket','Perfect jacket for travel and convenience anywhere. Awesome on flight as well as performance in the field. From a blanket',48,'2020-06-15'),(599,'Ilgava I.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,3.0,'Great jacket with a minor problem ( sewings)','Bought 2 months ago e used 4/5 times. Perfect in Italy for mid-season. Good cover and internal lining. The zipper finally works perfectly ( i\'m a Patagonia aficionado From more than 25 Years, and in the recent past i found myself in trouble with the zipper of a couple of jackets ). The problem with the sewings is emerged ( or i noticed) after',48,'2020-06-15'),(600,'Denny V.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Light & Warm','Purchased this for the warmer days of skiing,I was surprised of the warmth this garment produces. No need to layer up much,this jacket looks great and produces. Best of all it doesn\'t wrinkle after being stuffed in a day pack or a carry-on back pack',48,'2020-06-15'),(601,'Jjomsky',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Best Everyday Jacket!','I love this jacket. It is an excellent everyday jacket. Keeps me warm in the morning and doesn\'t overheat me in the afternoons.',48,'2020-06-15'),(602,'Cmcintyre',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,1.0,'Tears and holes','Bought this jacket over winter and have only worn it about 5 times and theres already has two huge holes in the back.. Two of my family members also bought them and they both have holes.. Patagonia is getting bigger and bigger and their clothes are getting worse and worse.',48,'2020-06-15'),(603,'Dan R.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,4.0,'A bit snug in body','I own two of these jackets (both size med) and the one I bought a few years ago definitely has a looser fit in the torso area. The new one has been tapered a bit - shoulders and waist fit great but it is a little snug across the middle of the jacket. I prefer the old fit better but still a great jacket.',48,'2020-06-15'),(604,'Roscoe2',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'All Purpose','Wear this in any environment. Wore this as a winter coat in Minnesota with a nice base and kept me warm.',48,'2020-06-15'),(605,'The G.',NULL,'5\'1 - 5\'3','XS',NULL,5.0,'Warm,Light,and Good Looking','I finally decided to get a Nano Puff when I saw the \"Sporty Orange.\" I\'ve usually worn my Ultralight Down jacket,but the color was irresistible. I\'m so glad I got it. While I still pack the ultralight down for excursions,the Nano Puff has become my daily jacket for everything else. I liked it so much that I bought a second on in',48,'2020-06-15'),(606,'Tony S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'looks great','Bought this at my local out-door gear store. The Jacket looks great and is very comfortable. The only thing is for the price I wish it was a bit warmer. I realize this jacket is\'nt suppose to be as warm as some of the goose down jackets but I guess I didnt realize that when I bought it considering they are very simular price . It gets very col',48,'2020-06-15'),(607,'James11',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Extremely Versatile','I now own two of these wonderful jackets,because I wanted one to wear around town and one to pack for hiking trips. I may even add another in the future!',48,'2020-06-15'),(608,'Eric W.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XS',NULL,4.0,'Warm and Stylish','This product embodies why I buy Patagonia products. It\'s warm,travels well,and looks great! I throw this on over a t-shirt and it\'s good down to 40 degrees. It packs down fairly easily and I can throw it in my bag if it\'s too warm. The fit is true to size and it looks like a refined down jacket - just the right amount of puff.',48,'2020-06-15'),(609,'Dick',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XL',NULL,5.0,'Freaking love it lol','Ok it\'s 45 out and just got this n the mail opened it put it on and instant warmth. Love the black being in gonna wear it with everything. I love the fact I can also wear it under my down sweater if it gets to chilly',48,'2020-06-15'),(610,'David',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,3.0,'Great jacket but front zipper problems.','I also own the hooded version and love these jackets but both front zippers are always catching wheather it\'s zipping it down or up. Finally had to send my jacket in for repairs or replacement because the front zippered failed and tore the fabic. Waiting for the same thing to happen to my hooded version. Need to come up with a different zipper',48,'2020-06-15'),(611,'Jason M.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,2.0,'Was a great Jacket...','I bought the Nano Puff late last winter and now less than a year later the threads are coming free and falling out of the outside of the jacket. I have maybe worn this jacket for 3 months or so total. I have another warmer/bigger coat from Patagonia that I love and I like this coat also but the quality of mine is horrible for the minimal amount of',48,'2020-06-15'),(612,'Dave C.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Simple function','I pair my Nano Puff with a R1 pullover and find this combination perfect for most winter days in Bend,Oregon. I am 5\' 7\",150#,and fit a medium with a relaxed fit.',48,'2020-06-15'),(613,'Zjc2',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,4.0,'Great Jacket that is functional and classic style','I have had my nano puff jacket for over 3 years and it is perfect for the weather in the PNW. It is great for layering,looks good and when folded up in the inside pocket has been my camping pillow on several occasions.',48,'2020-06-15'),(614,'Nmorrill25',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Awesome Jacket When Layered','Wore this jacket everyday for 3 months straight on a NOLS course. When layered correctly with a capilene base layer and an R4 fleece it is quite warm. Nice and lightweight for backpacking. Have worn for anything from walking to get coffee on a cold morning to windy days on the Deschutes chasing native red sides and have always been satisfied. Again',48,'2020-06-15'),(615,'Rob U.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Sizing','I really wanted the Nano Puff Jacket,but wasn\'t sure of the size. I used the online chat to ask a customer service representative and she came to the conclusion that I\'d need a medium (she even sent me the measurements of the garment,which was nice).',48,'2020-06-15'),(616,'Brendan',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,3.0,'Tight neck','I had an older version for 3-4 years. It was perfect. I\'m 5\'9\",185 pounds. Athletic build but putting on the pounds in my mid 40s. Unfortunately,I lost my jacket over the summer and ordered a new one online (from REI). I knew it changed the second I zipped it up and it hit my chin. I recommend you try on this jacket before ordering.',48,'2020-06-15'),(617,'Panccho',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'\"Sculptured fit\" is right,but it\'s good','Just picked up a new Nano Puff in the carbon color. Fit is great...I got an L. I\'m 6\'0\" 190 and it\'s perfect. Sleeves are slightly long,but I\'m a 34\" sleeve. I have two down sweaters and I think this is warmer,and I like the quilted pattern that allows no slippage. One thing...the carbon color is a brighter green than',48,'2020-06-15'),(618,'CHRIS',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,3.0,'Doesnt fit me','I want to love this coat. The material, light insulation, pockets-all of it is sweet. It just was too short in the arms and tight in the shoulders. I am not normally a large, but I would be interested in a large, but the chest was already pretty baggy on me. If it fits you, I think you will be really happy with this coat.',23,'2020-06-15'),(619,'SM',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,4.0,'Bought for commute but use in the Mountains!','Honestly I bought this because I have experience with the nano air and it wanted to mimic the warmth level for my daily driver jacket and combine it with the storms h2no layer. This past weekend I did 20 miles in the white mountains in 0-15 degree F weather and grabbed this instead of the regular nano puff and goretex jacket combo. I did not expect',23,'2020-06-15'),(620,'Nan W.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,4.0,'Love the materials used, design could be modified for casual use','Love the silent waterproof shell that doesn\'t crinkle when I walk, and the breathable full range insulation material used. I would personally prefer a more closely fit non helmet size hood like the micropuff hoody, and a longer visor for rain visibility. If this could be made into pants I would buy in a heartbeat, just don\'t make them too',23,'2020-06-15'),(621,'Marcos C.',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,3.0,'Great jacket, just definitely not for climbing','I own the first generation of this jacket and love it more than any other piece of outerwear I own. It fits me extraordinarily well with some of the best articulation had in piece of clothing I\'ve put on. This can be hard since I\'m 6\'2\" with narrow shoulders and long arms. It was clearly designed for climbing and a full range of',23,'2020-06-15'),(622,'JW',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,5.0,'The End of Layering','My go to ski jacket this year. I\'m 5\' 11\' and 205 lbs. I bought an XL and it\'s just what I wanted. Goes over anything and fits loose. L is probably the \'proper\' size but I wanted the big. Breathable is the concept here, it works. Stormproof. It has taped seams that the web site does not mention. I often wear this over',23,'2020-06-15'),(623,'charles f.',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,5.0,'Better than anything else','For that magical \"single quiver\" jacket this takes the prize. I really like my dead bird AR but the lining feels clammy and the face fabric isnt bomber. This jacket outshines the competition in both categories. I used to wear shells due to sweating and how the jacket\'s lining feels. The lining on this jacket is comfortable and instan',23,'2020-06-15'),(624,'Sam A.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,4.0,'Awesome jacket but too fitted in armpits','I ordered this for my husband because I have the womens and LOVE it! He has been wishing he had one because I am always dry and warm without all the bulk. I ordered him a MEDIUM because that is his size in all other jackets, both Patagonia and other top brands. This was too snug in the armpit area wearing just a T-shirt. He felt he could not wear a',23,'2020-06-15'),(625,'Brian M.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket for 40-65 degrees','The jacket is perfect for 40-65 degrees, though with long sleeve t shirt, hat, hood on, and synched Waist I was comfortable below 30 degrees. I haven’t been able to test waterproofing, but it is amazing on windy days. While it doesn’t compress as much as a down coat, you can stuff it easily into the hood. The hood has two Adjustments that made it f',23,'2020-06-15'),(626,'Beau M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Just what I needed','Great jacket',23,'2020-06-15'),(627,'Todd H.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'The Best-','I would recommend this jacket for brisk mornings and any wet weather needs where you need to be active comfortable and warm. Love it!',23,'2020-06-15'),(628,'Carl N.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Love this Jacket','Just finished a week of skiing in Colorado and truly enjoyed this jacket. Totally waterproof, wind proof, yet soft and comfortable to wear. It was especially thoughtful that they included soft material at the top of the inside zipper against your face when you need the full length of the jacket to stay warm in bitter, 40 mph wind while skiing. Plen',23,'2020-06-15'),(629,'Richard S.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,4.0,'Very Satisfied','I purchased this jacket for downhill skiing and ski touring. I am 5\'-11\" and weigh 190 lbs. The large fits perfectly with just enough room for a \"puffy\" layer under it. Having received the jacket this week I took the opportunity to see how well it worked in a strenuous situation. I threw it on over a lightweight long-sleeve wool',23,'2020-06-15'),(630,'Mac J.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'My go-to jacket','Simply the best. Winter steelheading, everyday travel, dog walking, in the shower...seriously, I love this jacket. It’s true to size, breathable, impervious to most weather, and warm enough for a t shirt underneath in 20 degrees. Home run, Patagonia.',23,'2020-06-15'),(631,'Bobby S.',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,5.0,'Patagonia Nano Storm Jacket','I am 6\'-0\", 190 lbs. I have the XL and it fits perfectly. I am a bass fisherman and it is hard to find outerwear that fits our needs. We are out in the wind, rain, and cold a ton. When you add the 70 MPH windchill driving down the lake in a tournament at 25 degrees, the right gear is everything. The Nano Storm has far exceeded my expectat',23,'2020-06-15'),(632,'Paula A.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','L',NULL,3.0,'I like everything about this','I like everything about this jacket except that it has the tightest hips of any coat I have ever worn. I debated sizes and would have had too long arms and too big shoulders had I gone with a larger size. I\'m a 12-14 and the large should have been right. Now I\'m finding it a little too snug, unlike all other coats I have. So, I wish the p',23,'2020-06-15'),(633,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Warm and comfortable','Great, comfortable jacket. Perfect for mild winter weather or add layer underneath for the colder days.',23,'2020-06-15'),(634,'cody f.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,2.0,'Poor fit.','And the zipper bulges when sitting or bending over even slightly. Returned and purchased an Arcteryx jacket. Patagonia\'s sizing and quality is off as of late - super disappointing.',23,'2020-06-15'),(635,'Sean',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'My new favorite jacket!','Another great piece from Patagonia! I just purchased this and it\'s already my new favorite jacket. The quality, material and feeling of the jacket is excellent. The fit and cut is also excellent, it\'s not baggy at all. I\'m 6\'1\" and 175 lbs and size Large is literally perfect. It\'s very warm, light and not too puffy/ bu',61,'2020-06-15'),(636,'Daniel',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','0',NULL,5.0,'Perfect Lite-Weight Sweater Jacket','Light, I normally wear an XL but they were oversized so I dropped into a large - perfect fit and still room enough. Weather\'s warmed up already so I might get one chance of spring chill to wear it before next season. From initial try-on was very happy to have this added to my kit, but I still think this piece needs a separate travel and pack s',61,'2020-06-15'),(637,'Barry M.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,1.0,'BOO HISS on the new slim fit!!','I bought this jacket four, maybe five years ago. It is probably my all time favorite Patagonia purchase. I love everything about it -- the quality, the weight and most importantly the FIT. And it\'s still going strong. In Feb 2020 I bought a second one in Peppergrass Green. Same size (M). The color did not disappoint. Unfortunately, the most im',61,'2020-06-15'),(638,'Rebekah M.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,3.0,'Great Jacket, but....','I bought this jacket in November and have been using it as my primary layer this winter with a sweater underneath. With moderate to heavy use already this garment is already showing signs of wear, small rips/tears, lost stitching on one of the arms, and most recently a broken zipper. Although I love this jacket and Patagonia I am deeply saddened by',61,'2020-06-15'),(639,'Chong X.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,1.0,'Neck Area Turned Dark After Normal Wear','The neck area turned dark after normal/light wear. I tried use down detergent to wash and clean, but did not work. This doesn\'t happen to my other down jackets with similar material. Very disappointed.',61,'2020-06-15'),(640,'Michael C.',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,4.0,'Decent down Sweater','Have an older model from ~3 years back but still good.',61,'2020-06-15'),(641,'Jim',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','0',NULL,5.0,'Go to jacket','Perfect for Spring and Fall seasons',61,'2020-06-15'),(642,'Renee E.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Perfect Jacket','I have a HARD to shop for dad, who is very particular about cuts and fabrics and breathability etc. He LOVES this jacket, and said it protected him perfectly from the wind on a walk in the neighborhood. He also said it’s the perfect amount of warmth on a Brisk California winter day. I would highly recommend.',61,'2020-06-15'),(643,'Jay P.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,4.0,'Perfect for our MT fall/winter.','Perfect for our MT fall/winter. If I layer with MWT Capilene and a sweater, it\'s comfortable down to single digits. Then it\'s time for the 10 year old Fitzroy.',61,'2020-06-15'),(644,'Gene C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Awesome down sweater','Finally replaced my old, repaired many times down sweater. The new sweater is awesome except for the loss of the hook loop. It is \"replaced\" with the size label loop that does not work well with fatter hooks or branches. Other than that, a great product.',61,'2020-06-15'),(645,'Breanne J.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Comfortable, Stylish, Lighweight and perfect for Layering','Very pleased with my purchase of this Down Sweater. It came in the mail very quickly, and just as described on the site. Definitely worth the price tag! Thanks!',61,'2020-06-15'),(646,'sergio m.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Great experience','I got a jacket for my husband for Christmas. I could not find the package when it was delivered so i panicked and contacted patagonias customer service. They immediately understood and send me another one one day delivery.. Im so grateful you saved my Christmas! My husband loved the jacket sooo much',61,'2020-06-15'),(647,'Diane B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Light & exceptionally very warm!!','Light & exceptionally very warm!!',61,'2020-06-15'),(648,'Mark J.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Lightweight, warm jacket','Always wanted a down jacket, did a ton of research and this one performed well in the reviews. Couldn’t be happier. Now if the weather would just turn cold enough to wear it more often, I’d be set',61,'2