 the races. I wear it skiing underneath a goretex rain jacket and the cold doesnt bother me. Also the soft cushion has held up well when owning it for the past few years. W',61,'2020-06-15'),(784,'Matt',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','S',NULL,5.0,'BEST JACKET EVER','The Down Sweater is, far and away, the best jacket ever made. It\'s light, breathable, packable, and just SUPER awesome. YAY.',61,'2020-06-15'),(785,'Switheyw',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'Down Sweater Love circa 2000','Last winter I purchased one of your current generation down sweaters. Prior to that,I had owned the same Patagonia down sweater for more than fifteen years. The original down sweater had no side pockets,no draft closure,no inner liner. I loved it; lived in it from fall through spring. It was like the Dire Straits song,comfort for nothing and your w',61,'2020-06-15'),(786,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Exactly what I was looking for','This is so warm and nice. I run hot but it breaths so well. It also looks very fashionable and minimalist,which I love. I also love what the company stands for,politically and environmentally,so that is a huge plus.',61,'2020-06-15'),(787,'Colonel L.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'Maybe the best outdoor gear purchase in the galaxy','Keeps you really warm. Is light. Packs easy. Best thing I bought - if you hike or live in cold weather,even if it hurts your wallet,still buy it because it is unbeatable.',61,'2020-06-15'),(788,'Lcolsant',NULL,'None','None',NULL,1.0,'Multiple Issues - Holes and Zipper Snags','I received jacket with a small hole in the back of the jack and feathers coming out. I returned the jacket and got a new one. For the new one,when the left pocket zipper is unzipped,the zipper snags the fine stitching on the underside of the left arm when it rubs (e.g. every time i sit down to drive my car). Now the left arm has multiple stitching ',61,'2020-06-15'),(789,'Toe B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XXL',NULL,4.0,'Built for Girly Men?','Dear Patagonia,',61,'2020-06-15'),(790,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Perfect!','Have several puffy jackets but all are too fragile to wear on their own. This one fit the bill: durable,yet soft,ripstop exterior which I am not afraid to roam about the woods in. It is both windproof and waterproof (up to a point). The fit is true-to-size,roomy but not too boxy. With just a long-sleeve shirt under,is good to 32F+/-. Nice drawstrin',61,'2020-06-15'),(791,'Bherren3',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Awesome coat','If you\'re like me,you might live in a state that can go from 50 degrees one day to below 0 and snowing the next. This is a coat that you could wear in either condition or anywhere in between. If you\'re looking for a coat with versatility,comfort,style,and practicality,then look no further. This coat is versatile in a sense that it can be',61,'2020-06-15'),(792,'1222',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,1.0,'3 Holes after wearing about 2 months','Bought it in Hong Kong,with daily use,get 3 holes and i send them back to patagonia for repair,won\'t recommend it,because i only wear about 2 months and they charged for repair.',61,'2020-06-15'),(793,'br',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,5.0,'Best down jacket?','This is the real deal. 800 full power down is amazingly warm and compact. When you\'re traveling the jacket turns into a comfy pillow.',61,'2020-06-15'),(794,'Kwhylee32',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Down is my new favorite','I got this jacket around early winter this year,as I live in the appalachians,and go through brutal winters. This Jacket has done nothing but impressed me. Even in temps below 30 degrees,I always stay warm. The elastic cuffed sleeves are a blessing,and allow for layering. I\'ve used this as my secondary layer under goretex for skiing,and I&#x27',61,'2020-06-15'),(795,'Mark5404',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Perfect for travel','I travel frequently and this is the jacket that I carry all winter. It is warm enough for most of the places I go. My favorite part is the ability to stuff it into its own small pocket,which makes it fit perfectly into a carry on bag.',61,'2020-06-15'),(796,'Phishflies',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,4.0,'Good but maybe don\'t wash it','Super warm and lightweight,actually found myself too warm in a lot of situations (but that\'s me and not the jacket).',61,'2020-06-15'),(797,'Guy B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Warm and comfortable','I was looking for something light,warm and comfortable and the Down Sweater has met all my expectations. I wrestled with laying for the first week but now have the right combination. I\'ll 100 miles north of Toronto and this time of year it does get \'fresh\'',61,'2020-06-15'),(798,'Ronnieayres',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'if you can only have one..','4 years and still going strong. From Tahoe to Maui to New Jersey,this is the one jacket that has got me through all seasons on all coasts. Just add a different base layer for the temps. from Fall Surf checks to Winter shoveling,pack it and go anywhere. Got some burn holes from bonfires but nothing some super glue could fix. Worn Wear On!',61,'2020-06-15'),(799,'Darn',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,1.0,'Loosing down','I\'ve only worn this four a week or two and it\'s loosing down from multiple places very disappointed I was literally planning on getting all my jackets patagonia but now I\'m not so sure...',61,'2020-06-15'),(800,'Ryan',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Pretty Close to Perfect','This jacket is super comfortable to wear,and you have excellent mobility in it. I never feel restricted in my movement. It\'s very warm relative to the weight,and not a struggle to stuff it in the stuff-sack. I wear this under a Torrentshell parka and they fit together beautifully.',61,'2020-06-15'),(801,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Love it!','I bought this for my husband. He loves the color and the fit! Lightweight jacket but lots of warmth!',61,'2020-06-15'),(802,'Mike',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Fits 