ep me warm now in Tennessee. If the size is right he should love the jacket.',61,'2020-06-15'),(809,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Men\'s Down Sweater','Awesome jacket. Extremely warm for the weight. Packs easily.',61,'2020-06-15'),(810,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Love it!','This is the 4th down sweater I\'ve bought for family. My husband usually takes a M but the L is a better fit if he\'s wearing a chunky sweater. We absolutely love these jackets and see it as a \"must own\" item.',61,'2020-06-15'),(811,'Extroller 1.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'My go to coat','I like this coat so much I bought 2! Different sizes for more or less layers.',61,'2020-06-15'),(812,'Gus C.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Very well designed,as expected','Excellent jacket,with the usual array of well thought out features. Zippers are quality. Packs down small if needed. Warm without being hot. Wear alone on a chilly morning or layer under a shell for a cold downhill ski day. You can use this jacket in any season in the backcountry. Re: fit...I\'m 6\' 1\" and about 198 and an XL was just',61,'2020-06-15'),(813,'Russell V.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','None',NULL,5.0,'service','returned previous garment for repair. it was beyond. issued a new garment!!',61,'2020-06-15'),(814,'Namruts',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Patagonia is the best.','This is my second down sweater. I wear them all the time. Great materials and workmanship. I may buy a third!',61,'2020-06-15'),(815,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Perfect','I bought one of these on sale in February 2017 and loved it so much I bought three more for my family a few days later. Super lite weight at 13 oz. Deceptively warm with only a t-shirt underneath. Once you are to warm with it simply stuff the entire jacket in the inside pocket and zip it up. End result is a 6\" X 12\" soft pillow that easil',61,'2020-06-15'),(816,'Number 6.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Brilliant bit of kit: shame about the creases','Up there with the best Patagonia stuff I\'ve ever bought over 40 years. But the transit packing leaves it with sharp-edged creases: two on each sleeve; two down the front and two running the length of the back. They\'re unsightly,unnatural and prevent it from hanging well. Washing and tumble-drying it hasn\'t helped. Anyone got any bett',61,'2020-06-15'),(817,'Brad M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Happy after looking for warm coat','Like this,switched to it from the lighter coat. Warm but not super warm. Good to 40 degrees. Wish it was a little trimmer.',61,'2020-06-15'),(818,'Hpad',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,3.0,'Great Quality but Bad Sizing','No doubt the quality of this product is superb but there is too much difference between the small and the medium sizes. Medium is too boxy for me and small I can barely close the zipper.',61,'2020-06-15'),(819,'Alia R.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Compactable Warmth','I bought this for my father who always comments on my down sweaters. I have 4 down sweaters and love them. They keep me warm under my ski shell. Spring and fall hikes provide warmth but squish down to nothing in my pack. Have even used it as a pillow when packing after I forgot my pillow-',61,'2020-06-15'),(820,'Usfd301',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,4.0,'Next step beyond my nanopuff','I\'m a big fan of my nanopuff jacket but I wanted more insulation and the down sweater clearly fits the bill. It is a great addition to my layering strategy but doesn\'t replace my nanopuff as my everyday choice.',61,'2020-06-15'),(821,'Drum',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,3.0,'Different design','This did not fit as well as my previous down sweater. The sizing has changed so I returned it and will get more use out of my patched old down sweater.',61,'2020-06-15'),(822,'Frankss8',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Nice pocket placment. Kept me warm but never hot.','I bought this two months ago and used it to our trip to Vail.',61,'2020-06-15'),(823,'Jerzy S