otten from Patagonia. Fit is good,glad I got the XL.',61,'2020-06-15'),(855,'Sauvant',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Great,light-weight,jacket','This jacket is warm and very convenient for casual wear. I also plan to use it for travel since it stuffs so easily into its pocket.',61,'2020-06-15'),(856,'B B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Outstanding!','At 71,I\'ve become pretty retro and minimalist. But my old down coat of 50 years(!) finally got to looking pretty shabby with frayed sleeves and stains that don\'t wash out. So,I reluctantly bought a Patagonia down sweater. But,then I was pleasantly surprised that I liked it better than my old jacket. The down doesn\'t shift around like',61,'2020-06-15'),(857,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XL',NULL,5.0,'Great Product','I have had my Men\'s Down Sweater for about 4 weeks. I find that it is perfect tor temperatures between 30 and 50 as an over-garment with a shirt underneath . The materials and workmanship are excellent,as I would expect from Patagonia. The warmth to weight ratio is perfect. I camp in the high desert area of the United States,mostly in Utah,and',61,'2020-06-15'),(858,'Fishnut',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,5.0,'Great features!','Bought this about a month ago,great fit,I\'m 6\'5 and the sleeves are plenty long and the body is too. Light enough but also very warm,one of many Patagonia jackets and vests I own and my new favorite!',61,'2020-06-15'),(859,'Dennis M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Perfect all around jacket. Any season.','My third down sweater. I work at a ski area and it is my go to jacket.',61,'2020-06-15'),(860,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket','Just what I was after - windproof,warm,lightweight,and a good color. Enough room to put a light layer underneath,which makes this really warm. The internal chest pocket and zip up side pockets are also appreciated. I absolutely recommend this jacket.',61,'2020-06-15'),(861,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket','Light weight and very warm. Great jacket,great value.',61,'2020-06-15'),(862,'John R.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,4.0,'Storage pocket misplaced','In my new down sweater purchased in Feb17 vs the old one purchased in Aug15 there is a noticeable difference in the placement of the storage pocket. On the 2017 version the stow pocket is on the left hand side chest high near the zipper. when using the pocket for other items like a toboggan,sunglasses,etc,it hangs heavy and bulky. On the 2015 versi',61,'2020-06-15'),(863,'Jack503',NULL,'None','M',NULL,1.0,'No Durability,Loosing lots of down','I was so excited to buy this jacket originally. It is great looking,extremely comfortable and very warm for its weight. The price is high but I felt okay with that thinking I was buying a quality and durable product... However,it has no durability whatsoever. This is my special occasion causal wear coat that I wear when it is cold and still want to',61,'2020-06-15'),(864,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Love this jacket!','Bought this about a month ago and it\'s been keeping me warm ever since. Very comfy,enough space to layer other clothing too. Stuff sack pocket is awesome,makes throwing it in a suitcase super easy,without taking up much space!',61,'2020-06-15'),(865,'Anjulian',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Just right!','I bought this in light grey for my husband. It\'s lightweight,yet keeps him cozy on the coldest of days. It\'s casual,but is so nicely shaped,he can wear it on dressier occasions in order to stay warm.',61,'2020-06-15'),(866,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XL',NULL,5.0,'Great Sweater','I bought this about a month ago...wore it a few times...fuits great,nice feel and does keep me warm.',61,'2020-06-15'),(867,'Rich S.',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,5.0,'Awesome and warm!','I\'m a newcomer to Patagonia and love this jacket. It\'s warm and easy to store in my backpack. I am 6\',220 and the XL is good for me!!',61,'2020-06-15'),(868,'Kyle P.',NULL,