y warm and super soft.',61,'2020-06-15'),(921,'Kalechipz',NULL,'5\'1 - 5\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Best Lightweight Jacket','This is my first Patagonia jacket. I love this jacket. It\'s lightweight and it\'s warm. I love that i don\'t need to wear so many layers to stay warm.',61,'2020-06-15'),(922,'Mjms',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Awesome men\'s down jacket!','I bought this jacket for my boyfriend for xmas and he is obsessed with it! It is very warm and comfortable and can be worn for many different occasions. Thanks Patagonia!',61,'2020-06-15'),(923,'Grainguy',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Love the Color combo','I wanted another light weight Down piece to wear under a shell for winter and this is just perfect.',61,'2020-06-15'),(924,'Mmlm',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Just the best jacket','I bought this about three months ago and I haven\'t stopped wearing in. Light enough to be packable and not weigh me down,but also incredibly warm.',61,'2020-06-15'),(925,'Brad123',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Lightweight,warm,packs easily','This works well for temps down to about 20 with another layer underneath. Very lightweight,packs easily,looks great,and seems well made.',61,'2020-06-15'),(926,'Gleta',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Men\'s Down Sweater/for a Woman','I have a home in the high desert of Joshua Tree,Ca. and it is great for the winter months,then I have a home in the mountains of Big Bear Lake,Ca. lots of snow in the winter and the weight of the sweater is perfect for both climates!!!',61,'2020-06-15'),(927,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Awesome jacket!','Very warm and comfortable! Wear it casually,hiking,backpacking,and skiing! I love it!',61,'2020-06-15'),(928,'Orlo J.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Sets the Standard','This down piece really is the best out there for fit,weight,and warmth.',61,'2020-06-15'),(929,'John D.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,4.0,'super light and warm at elevation','I\'ve worn the hoody version at 11,000\',in zero degrees,with a nano puff underneath. Its a trade off as your bindings will rip open the down,but its a great jacket. The downside is the toddler front zipper on an adult jacket. Not replaceable. It would be smart to beef up the zipper as it tends to \'fail\' on a regular basis. Patago',61,'2020-06-15'),(930,'Jflinville1002',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Fully satisfied!!','Got this for Christmas,but had been wanting one for a while. Quality is what I have come to expect from Patagonia: superb!! Very warm too!!',61,'2020-06-15'),(931,'S G.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Good warmth for the weight','Picked up this jacket for commuting and to wear for my various snow sport activities. I am pleased with the fit and finish of this jacket,I do with the material was a bit more abrasion resistant. All in all I am pleased.',61,'2020-06-15'),(932,'Skier R.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Best mid layer ever','I have two of these. My wife has one and two of my kids have one. This \"jacket\",is light,highly packable,very warm as a layer under a shell,and a great stand alone jacket in moderate conditions. I\'ve been using Patagonia gear for almost 40 years for skiing,climbing,and all around use. This jacket is my favorite piece of clothing ever',61,'2020-06-15'),(933,'Beau13',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Keeps me warm','Although it fits a bit snug for a size small around the waist,there is ample room in the arms and chest. I often feel this is comfy and quite warm compared to my Canada Goose.',61,'2020-06-15'),(934,'Jeff K.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Light,warm,and awesome','I must admit,this is one fine garment. I wear it in the wee hours of the morning when I go on my morning walks,usually 5 to 8 miles. This sweater is perfect over a thermal layer,and keeps me warm down to 10 degrees. Moderate winds aren\'t an issue. Below 10,I use an additional layer. If it\'s above 30,I use only a light cotton layer under i',61,'2020-06-15'),(935,'Pms999y',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,3.0,'Good but fit is slightly fifferent','I have owned several of these over the past decade and where through them once every other year or so. This latest one seems snigger around he chest and abdomen,I even lost weight this year and yet it is noticeably smaller than jackets of the past. I do like it hat the interior poscket was moved from the abdomen area to the chest.',61,'2020-06-15'),(936,'Davis C.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Perfect for what I need it to be','Lightweight and warm. Good between 40 and 10 degrees. Perfect as an outer layer most of the time and under a shell when the temp drops into the low teens and single digits. Fits trim without being too tight. Would definitely recommend.',61,'2020-06-15'),(937,'Tk90',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Love the colors','I use this under my skiing shell and it works great and looks good enough to wear around the big city too.',61,'2020-06-15'),(938,'Dimo',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XS',NULL,5.0,'Excellent!','I bought this a month ago and can\'t recommend it enough. It has been perfect for mild winter days,and is an excellent layer on colder and windy ones. I strongly recommend it as an excellent basic Patagonia item to own. Versatile,effective,and stylish.',61,'2020-06-15'),(939,'Isdaman',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Performs awesome!','This coat has been a great addition for me. Superior warmth and comfortable temperature range. Way warmer than my last \"puffy down\" coat. Only dislike and reason for 4 stars instead of 5 is the fit,like the older versions fit better. But heck it might work better for you,just not me. Luckily I tried one first. I get medium everything Pata',61,'2020-06-15'),(940,'Z D.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Warm compact','Wearing this jacket for years,love the brand,live the product.',61,'2020-06-15'),(941,'Johnny L.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Warm,Comfortable,Great Jacket','I bought this jacket for skiing a month ago. I found it very warm and comfortable to wear under my Pantagonia Shell. This jacket is also great to take to the office on those cold mornings. I have the micro jacket as well and find this to be warmer and the perfect jacket for the cold winter.',61,'2020-06-15'),(942,'Tweety 2.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Great weight','Gave this to my husband and he\'s worn it everyday!',61,'2020-06-15'),(943,'Johngmolloy',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Good Looking Down Sweater Jacket','I bought 16 of these as a Christmas gifts for my sales staff. As a Subaru dealership,we wanted to look uniform,and good,as well as mimic a majority of our customers. All the Salespeople absolutely love them. Unfortunately,one of them got snagged on a corner and has already torn,but other than that ,they are awesome. Thanks for making my sales staff',61,'2020-06-15'),(944,'Andrew1',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,1.0,'Returned for Fabric Issues','I purchased this a month ago and am disappointed. The fabric tore through normal wear and began losing down. I have returned the item and am not confident I would purchase a replacement. Has this been an issue for this item?',61,'2020-06-15'),(945,'D C.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Best packable jacket','Bought this for my husband who hates wearing winter jackets and he loves this one because is warm and not bulky. Can\'t go wrong with Patagonia',61,'2020-06-15'),(946,'ddddd',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'I love the coat!','The coat is perfect for day to day use in Wisconsin!',61,'2020-06-15'),(947,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket','I bought this Jacket four weeks ago. I have nothing bad to say about the jacket keep you warm even the Temp was down to 15F with New York wind.',61,'2020-06-15'),(948,'Lisa',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Men\'s Down Sweater','My son loves it! Fits perfectly!! Color is beautiful!',61,'2020-06-15'),(949,'Ashley A.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Warm and coxy','I bought a large Patagonia dow sweater abou