ay with the exterior chest zip pocket - I really miss this! Otherwise this is a beautiful jacket, love it. Im 60/175# and sized right between M and L - went with the large as the medium is just a bit too snug but the large is really a bit too big. Patagonia, please bring back the exterio',85,'2020-06-15'),(1186,'colin',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'good fabrick but i needs a few tweeks','i think the cuffs should be like the techface r2 where there is a seam that is tighter to keep it from always falling over your hands and i like the hood on the r2 better .. it makes for a better underlayer that way.. atleast fix the cuffs please.',85,'2020-06-15'),(1187,'David',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Perfect Jacket','Great for runs and walks. Fits perfect and super comfortable. Nice as a stand alone jacket in cooler weather and work weak as a layer. Best jacket Ive owned.',85,'2020-06-15'),(1188,'Forrest F.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'4 season perfect','I brought this hoodie right before the winter holidays 2019....it has been snowshoeing, winter hiking, road trips from Vancouver Wa to Boise ID. it was a great layer under a puffy now that it is warmer it is a breathable warm outer layer. With corvid-19 I have only worn it in neighborhood walks. I highly recommend this gear for any one kit.',85,'2020-06-15'),(1189,'Jack',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','0',NULL,5.0,'Great companion for urban and outdoor.','A great multi purpose jacket that blocks wind n light rain. I love its comfortable fabric with some elastic element. I own the previous version which has the chest pocket outside of the jacket. Worn for a year n have absolutely no complaints!! I m 172cm broad shoulder muscle build and M is perfect for me. The sleeve is a bit too long but can be rol',85,'2020-06-15'),(1190,'Justin',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Amazing jacket for mountain biking and much more!','This jacket is amazing for mountain biking and much more! It has a wide range of temperatures from 10-40 and is breathable enough to keep you comfortable and dry. The fit is amazing and the breathability to warmth ratio is second to none. This jacket is great for mountain biking or any other sport where you put off a lot of heat in cool weather. My',85,'2020-06-15'),(1191,'Albert',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Holds Up in Severe Weather','This jacket is great. I work as a photojournalist where the risk of shooting video during inclement weather is just part of the job. I got burned by breaking news one day: my camera had rain gear but I didn\'t! Immediately after drying myself off, I looked online for some rain gear, found the Calcite Gore-tex jacket from Patagonia and the rest',67,'2020-06-15'),(1192,'David',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,2.0,'Not waterproof','I liked what I heard about Patagonia\'s environmental policies, and the notion of buying a good product that lasts a while rather than buying cheaper stuff and throwing it away. I was also hoping to get a better quality product by spending a bit more.',67,'2020-06-15'),(1193,'Sardar',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','0',NULL,5.0,'Versatile gear','I bought the Calcite because it checked multiple boxes for me. It was my first attempt at buying a nicer shell-only jacket (and also my very first piece of gear from Patagonia!). I wanted something waterproof that I could use for a variety of outdoor adventures and it fit the bill - especially with the close out sale price in a great color. In deci',67,'2020-06-15'),(1194,'Jeff G.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Perfect Shell','I replaced a worn Torrentshell jacket with this. Works perfect, Lighter, dry, correct fit. Patagonia did a great job updated the Torrentshell with the Calcite jacket.',67,'2020-06-15'),(1195,'Stephen S.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Rain?, what rain!!','Excellent lightweight waterproof layer. I’ve needed this essential outer skin for years, and finally got it. Perfect size, breathable Gore-Tex, nice adjustable hood, sweet waterproof zippers all around (even under the pits). Best jacket ever, feel asleep in it on Christmas.',67,'2020-06-15'),(1196,'Eileen M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Calcite Jacket','This is a gift for my grandson. His Mother looked at the jacket before wrapping. Great color and fit looks perfect.',67,'2020-06-15'),(1197,'Aiden F.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Freaking love this jacket. The','Freaking love this jacket. The best price for Gore Tex around!!',67,'2020-06-15'),(1198,'Timothy B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'very light','surprised by how light a storm jacket can be, great for packing. Improved pit zips from the old style, very pleased with my purchase.',67,'2020-06-15'),(1199,'Jon V.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Shell yeah baby','This is a bomb proof rain jacket as well as a good Gore shell for touring and resort riding. Fit is great and very lightweight.',67,'2020-06-15'),(1200,'Carolyn R.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Beautiful Jacket','Great for wind and rain! Looks fabulous',67,'2020-06-15'),(1201,'Ethan P.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Extremely impressed','I am super impressed with this jacket. It’s 100% waterproof and fits very well. It has giant armpit vents and good pockets. It’s not designed to keep you warm, but it will keep you dry.',67,'2020-06-15'),(1202,'Francis W.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'the perfect light weight waterproof','the perfect light weight waterproof jacket I was looking for.',67,'2020-06-15'),(1203,'Mike F.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,4.0,'Great shell for layering as','Great shell for layering as needed',67,'2020-06-15'),(1204,'Mcpherson',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Calcite','I haven’t had it long enough to comment on performance much but I really like the fit. I’m 6’0” and 165 lbs and medium fits perfectly.',67,'2020-06-15'),(1205,'Ray C.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Your products never fail to','Your products never fail to impress.',67,'2020-06-15'),(1206,'Arthur S.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,5.0,'Nicely Made','This is generously cut for layering and has high quality features that justify its price. I stay completely dry while wearing it in the rain.',67,'2020-06-15'),(1207,'Andy22',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M/L',NULL,5.0,'Awesome jacket!','Originally purchased for a shell for AT touring and can’t wait to use it for that but it’s fantastic for hiking in wet weather. Love the full pit vents for staying cool!',67,'2020-06-15'),(1208,'Corey P.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Best lightweight rain jacket','This is the best lightweight rain jacket I have ever owned. It is fully waterproof even in a downpour. The fit is perfect for daily and activewear. It also has enough room for a climbing or biking helmet. If this thing hold up for the long haul I will never need another jacket.',67,'2020-06-15'),(1209,'Joseph C.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Always a solid choice','I had a jacket that I loved but had seen too many days on the trail. Upgraded to the Calcite and I am stokked. Patagonia remains at the Pinnacle of the industry.',67,'2020-06-15'),(1210,'David',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Go-To Jacket','I needed a jacket that looks decent, but fun for travel. I have long arms and a tall torso, but this jacket fits really well. I dont know if Id really layer with it, besides having a small base layer. Layering really isnt necessary. This jacket keeps the wind out because of the inner liner and the outer fabric. The only problem I now have is not be',80,'2020-06-15'),(1211,'Joe',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,4.0,'Amazing feel and material but too small','When I first opened the package the feel and material are fantastic... I could live in this and never take it off... but sadly the fit is off compared to other Patagonia items I have.... this is super tight across the back and under the arms.... also on the shoulders the my make like a point so it looks like a square when wearing it.... I would rec',80,'2020-06-15'),(1212,'James W.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'One of my favorites!','One of my favorite Patagonia purchases! I was surprised at how warm this flannel is.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1213,'Kerry S.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,4.0,'Casual Jacket','My husband liked this jacket. He uses it as a double layer or even under a tshirt as it’s pretty warm. The only downside was that the sleeves are a litttttle short on him as with all clothes as he is 6’1”. However, no too short that made it return. Overall, it’s a handsome piece to add to your wardrobe.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1214,'Jessica D.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Husband loves it','Exactly what he was looking for, which is an extremely hard task to meet! He is very particular on how a piece of clothing should fit and look. It’s warm, but thin enough to move comfortably. The fit is attractive. This will be his go to. He will be wearing this for years to come. Fantastic job Patagonia!',80,'2020-06-15'),(1215,'Hilde A.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Cool shirt','Love this black flannel shirt. Great for the bar.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1216,'Julie G.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','ML',NULL,5.0,'My dad loved it!','The perfect jacket for three seasons. Fit is great and the pattern is beautiful.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1217,'Nate R.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Ms Insulated Fjord Fannel Jacket','Great “Flacket”, super warm, fits nice, love the look.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1218,'Jacob S.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','XL',NULL,5.0,'Ridiculous!','I saw where one of my friends had this jacket on and as soon as I saw it I wanted to get one. I wanted something that was a bit more casual but also still did a job of insulating me and keeping me warm. This jacket does exactly that and it’s just crazy comfortable. I’ll throw it on at the house even when I’m sitting inside because it’s that comfort',80,'2020-06-15'),(1219,'Natalie H.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Can be worn as a','Can be worn as a jacket or shirt. Really comfortable and warm',80,'2020-06-15'),(1220,'Delores B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'love the jacket','love the jacket',80,'2020-06-15'),(1221,'Jim M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Go to piece for cold morning','Tried the \"Insulated\" version for the first time and it\'s amazingly toast for those chilly mornings. Fit was spot on and I would not change a thing!',80,'2020-06-15'),(1222,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Great Quality','Fits true to size, super cozy',80,'2020-06-15'),(1223,'Justin S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Super Warm','This is a great flannel for just throwing on and heading out to work in the yard or garage. The lining is super warm and the feel of the flannel is super soft--so glad that I got this.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1224,'SHAWN C.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L/XL',NULL,3.0,'Super Soft exterior and very comfortable interior','I would love to give this piece of outdoor gear a 5 star rating, but alas I can not. As far as the style, comfort, warmth, design, and craftsmanship I gladly give it 5 stars all day. Due to the fit I have to give it a 3 star rating. I wear a L in both the fjord light and heavy weight flannels. Both of those fit me fairly good, but still far from pe',80,'2020-06-15'),(1225,'Steven G.',NULL,'None','M/L',NULL,5.0,'Perfect, fall piece','Just bought it.. live in Colorado but brought this along on a trip to the Rhode Island coast. Brisk, windy, clear fall weather and this Fjord (insulated) Flannel is cozy, warm and looks great. Wears a little longer than the standard Fjord flannel as it has convenient hand pockets and overall makes this a warmer shirt/jacket. Another note: this wear',80,'2020-06-15'),(1226,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'It’s great!','Super versatile. I have worn it pretty much every day since purchase. The perfect thing as my house gets a little colder in the fall/winter.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1227,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Love it!','Love it!',80,'2020-06-15'),(1228,'Bruce N.',NULL,'5\'0 or less','L/XL',NULL,5.0,'Love the big side pockets','Love the big side pockets for your keys, cell phone or dog treats. Great for grabbing on the way out the door or walking the dog.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1229,'Bruce L.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Fjord flannel jacket','After reading reviews I took a chance with size large my normal size. I was concerned with the fit through the shoulder. It fit true to size.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1230,'Quinton',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'Best jacket/sweater ever','I swear by my Patagonia gear, and this is no exception. Out of all my technical and casual gear, this is my most worn piece. It’s warm, light, packable, and generally formal enough for me to bring on ANY travel trip (work or pleasure). The insulation is warm but not puffy enough to look like you’re wearing a puffer jacket, it looks like an over shi',80,'2020-06-15'),(1231,'Roldan A.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great looking, yet very effective','Jacket looks and feels great. Light enough to wear during a brisk morning and just the right amount of layering to hang by the campfire as temperatures drop.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1232,'Kevin M.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,3.0,'Nice Shirt, not a great fit','I bought this shirt as a medium, which is what I have in the Fjord non insulated flannels and it is too tight. The medium fits great with my other shirts but not this time. Unfortunately this is a problem I find with ordering online from Patagonia from time to time.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1233,'Michael W.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Mens Bivy Down Jacket','Great jacket but zipper needs to be moved back to the correct side. More earth tone and dark colors should be added.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1234,'Zilich',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'New Favorite','So stoked to finally score a flannel jacket. It\'s my go-to for my evening 2mi hikes carrying my newborn in a baby bjorn pack. Keeps both him and myself warm on these 40-50F windy spring New England days.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1235,'Christopher R.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Insulated shirt','Great quality, super soft and good fit.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1236,'Jack E.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Too small.','I have five Fjord flannel shirts, and this jacket seems to be exactly the same size, but with an insulated lining. After a few washings, all of my shirts have shrunk to the point that they are almost too small. I returned the jacket, which was already too tight, knowing it would not fit after the first washing. I\'m still waiting for my refund.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1237,'Josh S.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Insulated Fjord Flannel Jacket','Really like the flannel. Very warm and isn\'t so poofy.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1238,'Thomas D.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Love this thing!','The fabric is soft, but durable. The quilt lining provides warmth without being too bulky. The sizing is good. It allows for a shirt or two to be worn underneath, but not something bulky like a sweater. Easily one of my favorite work shirts.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1239,'Marc',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'useful either alone or with','useful either alone or with rain jacket. Light and packable to take anytime just in case it is needed.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1240,'Chris Y.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','XS',NULL,5.0,'One of the most comfortable things I ever put on my body','I was surprised with how comfortable and warm this jacket was when I tried it on for the first time. The inside lining is super smooth and soft, like silk. The outer shell is incredibly soft as well. In terms of fashion, it is very versatile, as it can range from casual to more formal depending on what you wear with it. I wear the XS size and it fi',80,'2020-06-15'),(1241,'Tom H.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Just what I needed','After an initial wash, I\'m now wearing this insulated flannel shirt and it is nice and warm, looks good and fits just right. And it has hand warming side pockets. I bought it to replace another brand\'s similar item that is wearing out. Hard to find a good one that fits me well. I appreciate that Patagonia doesn\'t skimp on sleeve leng',80,'2020-06-15'),(1242,'Colin',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XXL',NULL,4.0,'Last Year','I bought last years model of this and I love mine. The XXL fits me perfectly. Not too loose, not too tight. If you have a bigger mid section, it might be too tight on some.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1243,'Kwetzel B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Amazing product','Bought one of these around the holidays, I am around 5’9” so I copped the large, fits good and looks good too, kept me warm on a 2hr30min, 7.4mi walk home from a party on New Year’s Eve 2019 all the way back to my house in sub freezing weather with light frozen rain! I was shocked at the insulation’s effectiveness, great buy.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1244,'Willie',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Love. LOVE this shirt/jacket!','Instant favorite! This shirt/jacket is super comfortable and warm, and it looks great. Perfect for habitat surveys, around town, beer gardens, birding, apres surf and other activities on cool days when you don\'t need or want a technical piece. Layers easily over a Pima cotton or long sleeved daily henley shirt or wool baselayer hoody. The real',80,'2020-06-15'),(1245,'Dick',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XL',NULL,5.0,'Watch ur sizes','Loved the look feel and weight but in most Patagonia I wear a large to and xl n this I had to send back n and return for a xxl',80,'2020-06-15'),(1246,'Grimeydog',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Nnnnnnice','Grabbed the Tom’s navy flannel and super glad I did. Very nice fit and finish... plenty warm for me. Fits great even with a sweatshirt underneath. I’m 6’1 190 and got the XL. This one might run slightly small compared to my other Patagonia stuff ... the XL is perfect for me.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1247,'Schmidty1891',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Best casual jacket ever','I only really own \"outdoors\" technical clothing and was looking to have a nice shirt to wear on colder days for around town and out for dinner. This flannel checked all the boxes and I look pretty damn good in it. You can tell the construction is solid. Love Patagonia!',80,'2020-06-15'),(1248,'Brandon',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XS',NULL,5.0,'Love at first button','Since first buttoning this jacket, I loved it, this is a iniatil impression after just a couple of days, but the inseltation and flannel are supple. The double articulation at the back is really nice when reaching and moving around and doesn’t feel restricting at all. I got the size I usually wear and though it is form fitting expected that, if you',80,'2020-06-15'),(1249,'Dphresh',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'best flannel ever.','bring back that color scheme shown in the video. its the best looking flannel out there',80,'2020-06-15'),(1250,'Ryan',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Nice and warm for all day wear','The model I bought was a Fall 2017 (FA17 on the tag). I\'m 5\'11\",about 165 pounds. Many people were saying that the fit of this ran small,so I bought a Large at first,even though I typically wear a Medium in everything. When I got the Large,though the space beneath the armpits and back behind the armpits was more roomy,the arm length',80,'2020-06-15'),(1251,'Pnw L.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XS',NULL,5.0,'Can\'t Stop Wearing It','I love this jacket. I wear it all the time. I wear it with tees,base layers,sweaters,and even double up with another flannel. It fits perfectly as a sturdy over layer. Great length and cut. I\'m 5\'7\",athletic build,+2.5 ape index,and the xs is everything I\'d dream it to be. Perfect for Seattle drizzle or shine. I\'ve layered',80,'2020-06-15'),(1252,'Heady T.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,5.0,'Awesome','6\'4\" 195 originally bought a large. Too tight in the shoulders. Re-ordered a XL and it\'s perfect. Big enough for a sweatshirt to go underneath or wear with just a t-shirt.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1253,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Perfect Fit','Sizing adjusted? I own a regular Fjord Flannel that runs short in the arms and torso. This insulated version is longer and fits perfectly. It\'s warm,and the hand warmer pockets are deep and cozy.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1254,'Ebin',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Wonderful jacket','this jacket is warm and cozy. I\'m wearing it right now since some cold weather has come.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1255,'Hornbeam',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Not warm? Heresy!','I am pretty much good t go in the jacket department,but when I saw one of these guys in a dark blue for 50% off in my local store I had to grab it. I\'ve always had a standby blue shirt/jacket of sorts and this filled a void that had been open a few years.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1256,'B B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,1.0,'Not warm','I gave a few Patagonia items. After this I will not purchase anything else. Not as advertised',80,'2020-06-15'),(1257,'Acp',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Go To Jacket','As many others have stated,these skew toward the small size. I\'m 5\' 10\" about 185 lbs. and I usually wear a Medium with Patagonia (Down Better Sweater,Hybrid Better Sweater,other coats...) and I had to return the Medium and purchase a Large. After that,great fit,sleeve length is perfect and the cotton really is one of the softest thi',80,'2020-06-15'),(1258,'Fiveightandten',NULL,'None','XS',NULL,4.0,'Warmer than expected,could use a shirt hem.','This is impressively warm. I planned on it being a transitional jacket for spring or fall. But it\'s actually been standing in for my Down Sweater at times this winter,and keeps me warm down into the 25\'F range. It\'s a bit more burly than a heavy flannel shirt,due to the insulation,but not overly bulky. Still,I think it could really u',80,'2020-06-15'),(1259,'Big5safari',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Warm,comfortable and great fit','Nice and warm...I wear this jacket down to 15-20\'F with a base layer without any problem. It fits comfortably in all range of motion. Definitely recommend it if you are in the market for one.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1260,'Yapp',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,3.0,'Great Quality. Misleading Sizing.','I bought this jacket recently and i was impressed by the quality and build of it. Sizing is very inaccurate. I am usually a medium in most regular-fit Patagonia products and a large in slim-fit. This product should be considered slim-fit. Definitely recommend going up a size.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1261,'Craycray77',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Cozy warm flannel','I love this flannel. First of all it\'s a great looking flannel. The rusty gold is just plain cool looking. Second it\'s so comfortable cozy and warm. It feels just like it looks,like golden sunshine. I\'ve throughly enjoyed wearing this exceptional flannel.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1262,'I N.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,4.0,'great insulated flannel','This is a great layer for winter in Maine. I live in Bar Harbor and this work inside when chilly and outside as top layer when not super cold. The size runs small so go one up. A little disappointed that one button has come off already. Quality control is not what it used to be! Otherwise,5 stars!',80,'2020-06-15'),(1263,'Blue L.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Great casual','Perfect for breakfast at Tootsies in Thayne Wyoming .',80,'2020-06-15'),(1264,'Key33',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,4.0,'Comfy','Great fit. Warm and comfy. Looks sweet! Only reason this review is 4/5 and not 5/5 is simply because of the high price point.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1265,'Kevin',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Nice mid weight button down.','Perfect for 20 deg pond hockey,followed by bring a cord a wood in the house on the same day. Burly.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1266,'Martin C.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,5.0,'Fantastic all round multi-function piece','I am quite hard on gear and travel to remote and often cold climates. I love this jacket. I\'ve been using it this winter in Vermont on weekends and NYC during the week and I can\'t find any fault with it. It is warm but not hot or sweaty,about 80% windproof,looks tremendous and is quite rugged. I\'ve used it with a baselayer and the Pa',80,'2020-06-15'),(1267,'Peipert',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,2.0,'Not what I expected.','Ordered this online in the brownish color. Looked more like yellow when I got it. Ran small despite other Patagonia products in size S fitting me well. Also didn\'t seem to hit the right spot between shirt and jacket.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1268,'Jwpercy',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Great Fit,Very Comfortable','Love this \"jacket\". More like a wearable blanket. I\'ve had this for a few weeks now,and have worn it every day. I\'m 6\'2\",165 lbs. size Medium fits like a glove. Great as a light weight jacket,or a mid layer when extra warmth or shell is called for. Dark blue colour is very nice. Only complaint is I wish there was more',80,'2020-06-15'),(1269,'Mike T.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Great product!','I bought this product about 2 months ago and absolutely love it. It\'s great for layering under in the winter when you don\'t want to wear a bulky jacket (I live in Chicago) and it is the perfect fall temperature jacket.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1270,'Alex123',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'Perfect Flannel','Can be used as casual wear or for doing something active. Warm and durable. I wear it practically every day because it just works no matter what I am doing.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1271,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Warm','This insulated flannel is impressively warm,the pockets are a nice add',80,'2020-06-15'),(1272,'Zachipoo',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'jacket was just what I thought','I was given this jacket for Christmas and like it very much.',80,'2020-06-15'),(1273,'Panzer7',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Cool look with outstanding insulation','I purchased this jacket based on the appearance and the preview provided by Patagonia. I was very impressed the quality of material and the insulation it provided,in addition to the stylish look. I now own 3 variants of the Fjord Flannel Jacket. It\'s good-to-go.',80,