,'Great Jacket','Kept me dry at the UM vs ND game on my top half, worked like a charm.',26,'2020-06-15'),(1413,'Charlie',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Flawless crosslayer for just about anything','I have three of these. My wife thinks Im nuts. But I wear them every day in Colorado shoulder season. I hike, boulder, ice climb, ski, snowshoe, bike, and run in them. I never took my black one off in September in Iceland. Theyre comfortable from about 40 to the mid-50s while on the move. They shed wind, but not so much a breeze doesnt cool you dow',84,'2020-06-15'),(1414,'Chris',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','12-18m',NULL,5.0,'Perfect for Spring running','I usually wear large, but since this is listed as slim fit, I went with an XL, Im glad I did. Its a little baggy on me, but I love it; Im able to wrap the sleeves around my hands and not bring gloves. I use this in Anchorage Alaska where the weather in mid-April is mid 30s to low 40s in the afternoon. This jacket has blocked the wind and rain, kept',84,'2020-06-15'),(1415,'eric s.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','6-12m',NULL,5.0,'Light, Warm, wind and rain resistant','I have two R1s now one with the hood in one not. These are fantastic layering pieces. I use a Merino underlayer for warmth and wicking and this as an outer layer. The full zip allows me to cool down or warm up depending upon what I’m doing. I really like the fact that it’s wind resistant and good in light spring shower situations and layers well.',84,'2020-06-15'),(1416,'Deb R.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Awesome athletic fit','Husband 6’2” , 180 lbs with Extra long arms, the athletic fit works well for him & his arms!',84,'2020-06-15'),(1417,'Laura O.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,5.0,'Love it.','Great color and fit. Perfect for colder weather, but not too heavy. Would purchase again.',84,'2020-06-15'),(1418,'Jay D.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S/M',NULL,5.0,'Service','Excellent product and the service to match. Thank you!',84,'2020-06-15'),(1419,'Pascal D.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0