r back, but black will suffice. Arms ar',84,'2020-06-15'),(1434,'Jan A.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','0',NULL,5.0,'Terre Planer','This is a great piece of gear for me. I enjoy mine mostly when traveling to warmer than my SoCal home. Firstly, it is the BEST thing to surf travel with. It\'s like having your own personal isolation tent on an airliner, talk about a perfect breathable curtain! Liberal hood, tall collar plus light amount of warmth. Then when you are at your tem',72,'2020-06-15'),(1435,'Carrie',NULL,'None','XS',NULL,5.0,'Love this','Can you please make this for women!!!',72,'2020-06-15'),(1436,'Epooni P.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Purchase this as a gift','Purchase this as a gift for my son-in-law and he loves it!',72,'2020-06-15'),(1437,'Justin O.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Perfect all around jacket','I\'ve owned multiple iterations of this jacket and I continue to love it. I\'ve done everything in it from traversing glaciers in Alaska to just casual wear around town. Somehow it balances breathability, wind resistance, quick drying, and water resistance in one package. I always throw it in my pack because it\'s one of my favorite pie',72,'2020-06-15'),(1438,'Donald J.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Planning hoodie.','Great layer for a German summer morning with a cool gray mist. Thoughtfully designed jacket.',72,'2020-06-15'),(1439,'Robb K.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Always Incredible','As usual the quality and fit of the Patagonia items I received did NOT disappoint. The thought and attention to detail will make these items timeless additions to the gear I use for loving the outdoors!',72,'2020-06-15'),(1440,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket','I bought this jacket for something a little thicker than a Houdini for spring skiing. Glad I did. Packs small for touring and great for spring laps at the resort. It’s summer and I have used it a couple times mountain biking. Great jacket',72,'2020-06-15'),(1441,'Matthew L.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Planing hoodie','Very lightweight but just enough coverage to take the chill out of cardio activity',72,'2020-06-15'),(1442,'Randall R.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Awesome jacket','I am recently stationed in American Samoa and needed extra protection from the sun. The SPF 40 jacket is amazing and also keeps me cool in the hot weather.',72,'2020-06-15'),(1443,'Kris M.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Fits great and kept me','Fits great and kept me cool all summer',72,'2020-06-15'),(1444,'Evan',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Best piece of patagonia (or any brand) gear that I own','I love this thing, I use it for any activity outside in the sun, but particularly watersports (kiting , surfing , wakeboard). It dries super fast, the lighter color doesn\'t get hot when in the sun, and its way faster and less messy than completely covering up with sun screen. I use the kite harness feature a lot, though I wish that had put the',72,'2020-06-15'),(1445,'David K.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,2.0,'Tall not fat','I loved the fabric and the simplicity but the cut was so baggy through the belly I returned it. To get a piece that is long enough in the sleeves or broad enough across the shoulders, I am almost always a large. Especially if I am going to wear something in the water I need it to have more of a slim fit. If the hoodie gets slimmer for next year I w',72,'2020-06-15'),(1446,'Mark L.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great for mountain biking','Even though it was designed for water sports, I use this hooding for summer rides in the sun. It gives me UV protection and allows me to avoid sunscreen on my arms. This keeps the sunscreen off the seat in my pick up truck: a real Pain to clean off. Bet the designers didn’t think of that benefit!',72,'2020-06-15'),(1447,'Ar D.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Versatile and good looking','I picked this up hoping for lightweight sun protection. It serves that purpose well and has served as my go-to jacket on cool spring and su