hs of light use and the zipper broke after 12 months. Seems pretty rugged but casual use wore it out in 12 months.',55,'2020-06-15'),(1517,'Dan S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Great Products and Great Service','I have bought many Patagonia products and enjoy all of them. The quality is exceptional and the styling is respected.',55,'2020-06-15'),(1518,'Brandon S.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L/XL',NULL,5.0,'Jacket','Husband loves it!',55,'2020-06-15'),(1519,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Awesome jacket','I bought this jacket for my son for Christmas. He loves it! He will use it under his shell when skiing and as a stand alone jacket. The jacket material appears to be heavier than the Fitz Roy Down Parka, which we recently purchased for my husband. The blue and beige color combination is really sharp!',55,'2020-06-15'),(1520,'Korty',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,4.0,'Love this jacket but it stains very easily','I love this jacket but I bought it in the tan/olive color and am noticing how easily it shows stains. Next time I\'ll stick with black!',55,'2020-06-15'),(1521,'Morgan T.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great casual all around outdoor','Great casual all around outdoor jacket. warm,light. Protects from elements.',55,'2020-06-15'),(1522,'Richard B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,4.0,'Nice jacket','This is my first piece of Patagonia gear. I have not had enough time to really put it to work yet but what it has done has been great. I am not a real gear guy so may not be the best to review, but, its a jacket, so not that big of deal. I would say buy a smaller size than you need. Not totally sold on the elastic waist, but thats not a jacket issu',55,'2020-06-15'),(1523,'Dyan B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Good Jacket','It\'s light and comfy.',55,'2020-06-15'),(1524,'Mae A.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,3.0,'Gift for grandson. He loves','Gift for grandson. He loves it. He is 6’5” and slim and XL works well for him.',55,'2020-06-15'),(1525,'Chandra B.',NULL,'