',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XXL',NULL,5.0,'excellent','great',63,'2020-06-15'),(1881,'Dejaentendu247',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'JUST BUY IT.','This is by far the best jacket I\'ve ever owned. I live in Wisconsin and this was one of our coldest winters yet with temps reaching -50, no joke. This jacket has completely blown me away, it keeps your body just the right temperature and the inside pocket is really helpful as well. I can literally wear a t-shirt underneath it and be completely',63,'2020-06-15'),(1882,'Roarke',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,3.0,'Please make a LT and XLT size','Love this jacket except that it doesn\'t fit my XLT frame. I am 6’5 XL in the shoulders and arm lenth and M-L in the waist. This means if I wear a M or L its good in the torso but tight around my shoulders and short on the arms. It also means if I wear a XL its fits my shoulders and arm length but also has way too much material in the torso and',63,'2020-06-15'),(1883,'Al',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Like my favorite comforter in jacket form','I’m 5’9” and 200lbs and the Large size fits me perfectly. I’m really impressed with this jacket. To be honest I initially blew off the “silent down” line name as a gimmick (despite the fact that I’ve been a Pata customer for over a decade and should know better than the fact that they don’t do gimmicks for sales numbers, so far as I can tell).',63,'2020-06-15'),(1884,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great!','I love my new Silent Down Jacket. Already had a Nano Puff and this is a nice step up for cold, windy days. Bulky, but not obnoxiously so, actually a slimmer profile than I expected. Medium size, 5\'10\" 155lb, can have a vest or sweatshirt layer under with no trouble. Great for dawn patrol dog walks. :-)',63,'2020-06-15'),(1885,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket','I spent about a month in Europe during January where the weather was between 37-46 degrees and drizzling and this jacket kept me really warm. Not to mentioned how comfortable it was. Another thing I really liked was the interior zipper pocket that allowed me to securely store my important travel documents such as my passport. A must have.',63,'2020-06-15'),(1886,'Montana D.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Excellent with a minor suggestion','I bought this jacket after several send backs to Patagonia because of the constant inconsistent sizing with everything Patagonia. This Medium jacket fits me perfect. I live in Bozeman MT where it can be bone chilling cold and this is my go to piece when I don’t want to be cold. There’s plenty of room for a heavy sweater and layering underneath.',63,'2020-06-15'),(1887,'Ronkie',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Super comfortable','For noodling around town or for \"easy\" camping and hiking, this jacket can\'t be beat. I wore it when last December throughout the Southwest, when it got down into the 20s at night and with an ooold Capaline thermal weight, it was plenty warm. The most comfortable Patagonia I\'ve owned.',63,'2020-06-15'),(1888,'Justin',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,3.0,'Justin','I\'ve also received one in Forge Grey medium that has the duck/goose filling coming out of it on the first day. It\'s like some one poked a bunch of. micro holes in the outer fabric. I\'m going to give Patagonia one more chance and exchange for one that\'s hopefully not defective. If the exchange is defective as well, I\'m afrai',63,'2020-06-15'),(1889,'Glen W.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,2.0,'Just not warm enough.','I purchased this as a daily wear jacket for winters in Fairbanks, Alaska. Tried it on over a long sleeve cotton shirt and walked down my driveway in -15 degree weather. Total fail for this type of use. Definitely need layers for anything below 0 and the slim fit will make that tough. I love Patagonia but this is not a good choice for my needs. Will',63,'2020-06-15'),(1890,'Patyguy',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Truly silent','I tried this jacket on in-store, so this review is for those who don\'t have easy access to try Patagonia items locally and are thinking of taking the plunge online.',63,'2020-06-15'),(1891,'Gary H.',NULL,'5\'0 or less','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Awesome Jacket','Have only used jacket in 40 degree weather so far in Las Vegas, NV. Quality and design elements make this jacket from Patagonia my favorite go to jacket when it is cold. Yes, I have been in sub freezing weather for extended periods of time. Having Retired from the U. S. Army. The only modification I would possibly add would be small pit zips under',63,'2020-06-15'),(1892,'Chris',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Silent warmth','The jacket is warm. After walking a few blocks with a sweater underneath, I was almost sweating on the train. The jacket is so light that you wouldn\'t believe how warm it is. In addition to the fabric not making that swishy sound, the fabric has more of a matte finish, which I think makes it look more luxurious versus the shiny alternatives. I',63,'2020-06-15'),(1893,'Gary H.',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,5.0,'Patagonia Hits The Mark','Purchase X-Large in Forge Grey from REI at Boca Park in Las Vegas. The jacket keeps me warm with just a Patagonia Undershirt on all day at 40 degrees. Looked at REI Stormhenge 850. However, no place to put the hood and the Cooper Spice looks dirty! REI technical specs on the date I purchased my Patagonia Silent Down stated no hood at all. Which was',63,'2020-06-15'),(1894,'R.V',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','None',NULL,4.0,'Light, warm and comfortable','It\'s been only a week since I purchased this jacket and it only took 1 full day for me to fall in love with it. I\'d say I have a stocky/slim figure but still have plenty of room for layering. You probably won\'t need much layering due to the amazing insulation the jacket provides. The handwarmer pockets are also incredibly warm and so',63,'2020-06-15'),(1895,'Gus B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'So comfy and warm','Jacket is super soft, warm, and light weight. I can move around easily while wearing it. Also, it keeps me warm in the Mid Atlantic cold weather.',63,'2020-06-15'),(1896,'Rkr',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'A hidden gem','5’ 9” 155 lbs - medium fits perfectly as usual. I bought this for Minnesota winters. A layer or two underneath and this thing will probably handle -15F with no problem. I’ve been wearing a better sweater and a button down for most of the last few winters and decided to step it up. What I did not anticipate was that this would become my 100% GO-TO c',63,'2020-06-15'),(1897,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,4.0,'Silent down jacket','Wore this jacket to Sierras for fishing it was in low 40 degrees under neath I wore a t shirt and thermal top was not cold but would like to find out to what degree this jacket is rated, is very comfortable, wish it was a couple ov inches longer I am 5’ 10” 210 I bought it in x large good fit,it feels that material is not to strong. Please rate tem',63,'2020-06-15'),(1898,'Frank C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,3.0,'Great Value Coat','When my coat came in, it felt very light. I Thought it would be super heavy seeing that it was 700 down and polyester fill. The design is really nice and fashionable but I am not sure its gonna last me this coming winter considering how light and thin it is. This is a great jacket for light use , hopefully it will be warm for New Yorks rough winter',63,'2020-06-15'),(1899,'Dave',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Versatile and light weight','I\'ve owned an older down puffy Patagonia jacket for years. I opted for the NanoPuff Hoody for the hood. I\'ve found that on Spring days, this jacket is much more versatile than my older down jacket. If you wear it unzipped on warmer days, it\'s just right. But if it\'s a bit colder, when zipped up, this jacket will cook! When joggi',22,'2020-06-15'),(1900,'Tevin',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,4.0,'Warm but not very durable','This jacket fits pretty good, I found that the arm lengths are a great size but the jacket is a little too short. Because of the insulation, I like that it can keep me warm in wet and cold weather. Another problem I was having was that the threads keep getting snagged on random things.',22,'2020-06-15'),(1901,'Steve',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','None',NULL,5.0,'Just right','Warm, comfortable, practical, and stylish, the Nano Puff Hoody is excellent. It is ideal for a range of temperatures and for a variety of activities, from strolling city streets to hiking mountains. The medium size is perfect for my 5\'10\", 160-pound frame.',22,'2020-06-15'),(1902,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Light and warm','Great jacket. Might need another in a new color.',22,'2020-06-15'),(1903,'Cem',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'The Best Everyday Jacket','I am way overdue to write a review for Patagonia products. First things first, we are a family of five and all of us has couple Patagonia garments. I am amazed by customer service, quality of products and Patagonia\'s efforts on sustainability. Big thumbs up.',22,'2020-06-15'),(1904,'Ayla B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','0',NULL,4.0,'Warm and Comfy','Super warm and comfortable, I wear my Nano Puff lounging around the house, to work, or in the great outdoors. My only complaint is that there is a hole in the inner breast pocket after two months of light use, so I\'ll have to send it in for repair.',22,'2020-06-15'),(1905,'Matt',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,3.0,'6ft 2in 200lbs and XL is too short and baggy','I love the warmth, style, and comfort it offers, but unfortunately the way it fits me prevents it from being an all-time favorite.',22,'2020-06-15'),(1906,'Rick K.',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,5.0,'A Review on Color','So, as most people know, this is a great lightweight coat. It performs as described and is just the layer and outer layer I’ve needed. My only comment is the Corriander color is a bit off in the description. As soon as I put it on and saw it in the light, it is way more gold than tan or brown. Just a heads up.',22,'2020-06-15'),(1907,'Shawn O.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,4.0,'Love this jacket but...','I love this jacket wear it all the time. But I wish it was a bit longer... I am a 6\'2 skinny dude and for me it fits great in all parts accept the length. I have noticed that this is a problem with many people that are around my height or taller. I have tried on the large size of this jacket as well but it is too big around the belly region fo',22,'2020-06-15'),(1908,'Michael C.',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,1.0,'Nano Puff Hoody is NOT warm!','Have an older version ~4-5 years back which is relatively the same as the current version.',22,'2020-06-15'),(1909,'Charles K.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,3.0,'It\'s the Sizing','Like others have said, the sizing seems...off.',22,'2020-06-15'),(1910,'Holly F.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XL',NULL,5.0,'Perfect!','My husband hates big jackets and will rarely wear a winter coat even though we live in Massachusetts. I decided to purchase him the nano puff in hopes that it would be thin enough and yet warm enough to get him to finally wear a winter jacket!',22,'2020-06-15'),(1911,'Robbie W.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Excellent!','Super lightweight and packable yet a great wind blocker and light rain resistance.',22,'2020-06-15'),(1912,'Joseph C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Nice fit, great for outerwear','Nice fit, great for outerwear or layering',22,'2020-06-15'),(1913,'Christopher P.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Love the warmth','Love the warmth',22,'2020-06-15'),(1914,'Tevin',NULL,'None','XS/S',NULL,4.0,'Keeps warm even when wet','I really like this jacket. It is pretty warm, even when soaked in rain. Nano Puff is really light too. Only problems are that it is not very durable.',22,'2020-06-15'),(1915,'Keith',NULL,'None','M',NULL,1.0,'Arm pit stains','Noticed arm pit stains after short term use. I use natural deodorant and no problem with any other clothes. Tried to wash multiple times and hand wash with Dawn/baking soda.',22,'2020-06-15'),(1916,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'perfect fit','Light weight, warm, perfect fit, size medium mens',22,'2020-06-15'),(1917,'Jane B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Receiver Loved !','Great service as always ! Jacket arrived in just a few days. As a Patagonia family we have many of your light weight jackets and think this one is probably the best one designed. Love the way the quilting is stitched. It looks more flattering and less puffy with this smaller square pattern. Also like the hood. The forge grey is a great color too. N',22,'2020-06-15'),(1918,'Brian L.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L/XL',NULL,2.0,'I have bought 3 of','I have bought 3 of these puffy jackets and liked them a lot. This year my oldest son wanted one with a hood and I couldn’t find one in local stores so I ordered one from the Patagonia web site. What came was not what I was expecting at all. It was an almost flat, thin jacket with almost no fill at all. Doesn’t look like a puffy at all. I would not',22,'2020-06-15'),(1919,'Lena L.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'All time favorite jacket','This is the second time I have purchased this jacket! The first one is still alive but has many years of used love. So I thought it was time to freshen my look BUT with this trusty jacket. Great to layer or where alone. Great for climbing, ski layer or shopping on a snowy day.',22,'2020-06-15'),(1920,'Sanya A.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket! light weight yet practical','Not only the quality is high and fits through the size, the customer support left me speechless! with the holiday season rush, having such support made a loyal and certainly returning customer! Highly recommended brand. Thanks for being awesome.',22,'2020-06-15'),(1921,'Joe J.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Quality','Quality',22,'2020-06-15'),(1922,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'My favorite jacket','The nano jacket is a perfect jacket.. Works Great In high 30s',22,'2020-06-15'),(1923,'Christi