20-06-15'),(2004,'B C.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'With a couple of refinements','My sleeves are too long and it could use a couple of gromit holes in the arm pits for out venting. Maybe Patagonia would make these adjustments. It’s what makes them a five star company',22,'2020-06-15'),(2005,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Awesome','I waited a long time to buy this coat ... and it was worth the wait.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2006,'jim t.',NULL,'None','L/XL',NULL,5.0,'Comfortable,light,and warm.Adds +10 to hipness.','Comfortable,light,and warm.Adds +10 to hipness.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2007,'Paul R.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket as expected','I’ve always been very pleased with Patagonia products and this jacket is no exception. It’s sized well and comfortable and though it hasn’t been cool enough to venture outside with it the weight and material are what I wanted. Keep up the great work!',22,'2020-06-15'),(2008,'Alexander K.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Awesome Lightweight Workhorse','This is one of my favorite jackets for.....everything. It\'s rugged enough for field use, refined enough for a night out, and versatile enough to be a no-nonsense travel companion.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2009,'John',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,4.0,'Sleeves Too Short','I have two of these now: bright orange for hunting season, and a blue Nano Puff for other times. Like all of Patagonia\'s jackets, the sleeves run a bit short. I\'m 6\'1\" and this jacket would be perfect if it was a little longer in the sleeves and body.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2010,'Scott C.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Great Patagonia Hoody','Fits perfect, great layering piece but also able to wear on its own for fall weather. Go to hoody for this fall',22,'2020-06-15'),(2011,'Paolo M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,5.0,'Perfect.','Wanted something I could use every day, or as a mid-layer snowboarding, without spending a fortune, packable but warm and nicely fitting. I thought the Nano was too old of a design and looked around, but after searching other brands none could match the quality and attention to detail of Patagonia. The jacket feels really light, wears very well and',22,'2020-06-15'),(2012,'Harrison H.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,3.0,'Very Warm but threads have been falling out','I love this hoodie honestly, it\'s warm and extremely comfortable and looks great. However, after less than a month of steady use a good deal of the threading holding the insulation in place has started falling out and getting loose. It isn\'t a big issue yet but I sense more consistent use will wear it down very fast. Altogether disappoint',22,'2020-06-15'),(2013,'Bart E.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Warm, but super-lightweight! The perfect','Warm, but super-lightweight! The perfect layer for a fall hike up Katahdin or on its own while kicking around town!',22,'2020-06-15'),(2014,'Jeff S.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Amazing Lightweight Hoody','It works as a jacket, a mid layer, just about everything I need for my adventures. 60 degree days with sunshine I wasn\'t too hot and felt warm in 40 degree nights.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2015,'JODY M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Bad A','North Carolina weather isnt ready for it yet but its comfort is uncomparable, every Patagonia piece of clothing I own is that way though. I cant really give a honest review on warmth yet.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2016,'George S.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S/M',NULL,4.0,'love this','Perfect weight, great sizing',22,'2020-06-15'),(2017,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'WARM','I bought the Nano Puff Hoody along with a Micro Puff, and I was surprised at how much warmer the Nano puff is. It does a great job of cutting the wind while being light for its warmth factor. I added the nano vest and it\'s just has warm. The nylon rip stop in extremely durable and can take a beating. 6\' 190 lbs and the Large fits perfectl',22,'2020-06-15'),(2018,'Michael G.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'seems great','I\'ve just worn it once so far but it was a 40 degree, rainy day on the mountain. Fit great, hood was perfect, nice and warm.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2019,'Jason S.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,5.0,'I am 5\'6 and 160','I am 5\'6 and 160 lb. Per others reviews, I was expecting this hoody jacket to be oversized and accomodate layers, however, it is a perfect and good looking fit over only one shirt so I\'ll use it for casual use as well as hiking and then layer over it with a rain shell if needed.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2020,'Taylor D.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'The Bees Knees!!!','Wandering in the deep dark woods? Temperature below 32 degrees. Throw this little bad boy on and you will feel the warmth of 10,000,000 fibers hugging your body. Buy this coat!',22,'2020-06-15'),(2021,'George O.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Nano Hoody','It’s the best. Warm, light and compressible. I take it in every trip.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2022,'Virginia J.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'M Nano Puff Hoodie','Love it! Keeping me warm!',22,'2020-06-15'),(2023,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Zippers','Zippers/zippers fail, need better zippers for active -working people gear/clothing',22,'2020-06-15'),(2024,'Robert D.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','NB-7lb',NULL,5.0,'Great sailing layer','Usually I prefer down, but I had a sailing trip coming up and I wanted something better when wet. This thing worked perfect.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2025,'John H.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Reliable','I\'ve been a fan since this piece was first available and have 3. On its own or as a layer. The hoody fit and nonblocking of sight. Great for activity, travel, or a chilly library. In and out of the wash... no problem. Welcome and reliable!',22,'2020-06-15'),(2026,'Jake J.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,3.0,'Ms Nano Puff® Hoody','I love the jacket and hoody, however it\'s a poor fit for me. I\'m 5\'-8\" and 130 lbs. and I\'ve typically worn a size small in the various Patagonia jackets, but this one is just too tight around the shoulders and chest to be functional for me. Size medium becomes too long and puffy around my torso. I\'m keeping it to give',22,'2020-06-15'),(2027,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Nano Puff Hoody','This thing is excellent. Its lightweight and super warm, the willow herb green is awesome. I\'m 6\' 165lb and the large fits me perfectly, not too tight anywhere and room for layers. Get yourself a nano puff, you won\'t be disappointed.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2028,'Craig P.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Perfect Mid-Weight Jacket','I wish my life called for wearing this jacket every day. I would buy it in 10 different colors.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2029,'John A.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Patagonia nanopuff','Overall give it a good. Paid extra for it over the brands like Rei, kept warm most of the time while hiking in South America. Perhaps should have gone with the micro puff but overall satisfied with purchase.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2030,'Carlo A.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,4.0,'great jacket to have in','great jacket to have in cold weather. I really love how light, warm, and compact this jacket is. Normally Patagonia gear fits a size bigger but this jacket did not run big. IM 6\'1 194 ibs. and the large fits like a large. i usually get XL in other brands',22,'2020-06-15'),(2031,'Gerard L.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','NB-7lb',NULL,4.0,'Very lightweight and packable','I purchased the Nano Puff Hoody to take on an Alaska / Pacific coast cruise in September because this unit packs down to a very small size. I hope it proves to be warm enough; it is thinner than I expected but appears to be of very high quality. Here\'s hoping for the best.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2032,'Stephen D.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Fantastic Jacket','This jacket has amazing warmth to weight ratio. It is more durable than other jackets of similar weight. This is now my go-to jacket for shoulder season outings and around town in the winter.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2033,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Nano Puff Hoody','This hoody is the bomb. It\'s a great stand alone hoody but it\'s light enough to layer under a raincoat or shell. Super light weight and awesomely warm. It packs down to a very small package. I take it wherever I go. To the mountains, to the rivers and to the restaurants and night on the town. Highly recommend.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2034,'Charles P.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Surprisingly warm for the weight','I haven\'t worn this in a heavy rain, to test the maximum effectiveness of the waterproofing, or the important (to me) claim of warmth when wet. As advertised, light rain beads on the surface. I wore it while walking at 34 degrees F over a cotton tee shirt and I was cool but not cold for the first mile. The hood was an important part of my comf',22,'2020-06-15'),(2035,'HV',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','XS',NULL,2.0,'So close','I love your Nano Puff vest. Amazing fit and the perfect amount of warmth. However, as much as I want to purchase the jacket, it is cut larger than the vest for a given size. That is, an XS jacket has the body and arm holes of a S vest, and the sleeves are sized that way. I can understand why you would not make a slim version of this jacket, but can',22,'2020-06-15'),(2036,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Nano Puff','Absolutely love this jacket! Great stand alone or worn as a layering piece under a rain shell. Essential piece of gear in the PNW and Alaska.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2037,'Rick B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Nano Puff - Mens','Nice lightweight jacket. I like the hood option. The only issue is that the stitching in the sleeves snags on the pocket zippers. Otherwise very pleased',22,'2020-06-15'),(2038,'Brian L.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'Love the Men\'s Nano Puff Hoody','Very light, warm, comfortable, and pragmatic. I love that it can easily be scrunched down into it\'s own zippered pocket to make it more compact. It does run a bit large. I normally wear a size medium, but could have probably gotten away with a small. The medium does allow space for me to wear a sweater or multiple layers underneath which is go',22,'2020-06-15'),(2039,'Gloria M.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Light jacket','This jacket is very light, I don\'t feel it when I am wearing it. The liner looks very thin, let\'s see how is going to last.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2040,'Bryan W.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Jacket Review','Happy to have traded in some vintage Patagonia for the new tech that has proved itself well through travel and multiple weather conditions.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2041,'Rodney S.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Hooded Nano Puff Jacket','Love my jacket! Fits perfectly and can barely tell I’m wearing it- except it’s always warm!',22,'2020-06-15'),(2042,'Dove G.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XL',NULL,4.0,'Great jacket for layering, fishing, and fun','The jacket is great. Fits well under my waders and keeps me warm in light snow! The fit is a little tricky. I ordered m\'s so the girls would fit but the hips are a little tight.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2043,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Nano Puff Hoodie','Pretty much exactly what I needed and expected. It’s light, warm for the weight, and fits very well for a slender guy.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2044,'Brian K.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Thinly wrapped in warmth','The Nano puff hoody is so thin and so warm. I wear it on its own and as a mid layer under my shell without restricting my movement. I am very pleased with my purchase .',22,'2020-06-15'),(2045,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Nano Puff Hoodie','I must say I was skeptical of the performance ability of this jacket. After 3 months I wear this jacket every day. Windproof, just like it says. Warm, just like it says. Packable, just like it says. I have replaced 3 jackets with one. Perfect for mountain biking, I can pack it away in my hydration pack, wear after and evening ride, wear it in the o',22,'2020-06-15'),(2046,'Jake P.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Almost perfect!','I love the fit o