arding, hiking, and walking the dog, and couldnt be happier. Perfect blend of thickness and',22,'2020-06-15'),(2057,'Steelheader',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Would hate to be without it','Had this jacket for 4 years. I’m 5’-11” and 180 pounds and the large fits perfect. Loose enough to fit a layer underneath and snugg enough to not look baggy. Simply put I have this jacket on hand at all times for when I start to get cold. The instant wind blocking and insulation make it an amazingly versatile jacket. Depending on how cold or wet it',22,'2020-06-15'),(2058,'Jarred M.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,5.0,'Awesome Jacket with one major issue - Long Term Review','Fantastic Jacket, I have owned the jacket since January of 2016 and it has held up fantastically. Warm and well fitted it is my go to jacket when the weather requires it. However, My biggest issue so far has been that the stitching on the jacket has come out in various places. This does not effect the performance of the coat, but it does seem to lo',22,'2020-06-15'),(2059,'Sebastian B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Love it!!!','Love it, Fits super nice the only problem is that the sleeves are to long, but is so warn and pretty comfy in cold days, perfect to wear with anything!',22,'2020-06-15'),(2060,'Yehe',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,2.0,'Size matters','While being a great jacket,looks & built,I think that the M size is too tight. Yeah,the jacket runs on the short side but also too tight under the arms on the side of the body.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2061,'Mike P.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Fits perfect and love the packability','Bought this jacket a couple weeks ago and its been great to throw on for belaying in the shade,blocks the wind really well and is super warm. Also great for walking the dog and low exertion exercises or when its really cold and you want to warm up quick,I am 5\'6 165lbs and it fits perfect. Packs down really small which is great.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2062,'Rob S.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'I love this jacket!','I have worn this jacket all winter and it has performed awesomely. It\'s light weight,keeps me warm,fits good,and looks good.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2063,'S D.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Great every-day jacket.','Big fan thus far. Works exactly as advertised. No problems with the stitching ... which I was worried about,based on other reviews.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2064,'antso',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,3.0,'Nano puff grew larger','I love the nano puff. This is my third one. I am using it essentially year round,from summer hikes to resort skiing. Got a new one (2018 model) to replace a 2 year old one and unfortunately found that the jacket in size medium grew by an inch or so in every dimension except for length. I am 5\'9\"/150 and always on lower end of medium. Unfo',22,'2020-06-15'),(2065,'The P.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Won\'t leave home without it','I\'ve had my nano puff hoodie for about 2 years. It is totally awesome. I am tall and thin and the size medium is perfect on me. Good sleeve length and not bulky at all. The hood is awesome,fits over a hat nicely and seals out the cold. No matter where I go I make sure i have this thing with me. Fishing,Disneyworld,Church.. this thing looks goo',22,'2020-06-15'),(2066,'Tsong',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Great all around!','I have owned this jacket for about a year and a half,and I love it!',22,'2020-06-15'),(2067,'Nateshoe',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Great lightly isolated Jacket...thats pack-able!','I\'ve owned a Nano Puff jacket for a few years now and really love it. It\'s light weight,which I love but keeps you warm as a layering piece or on its own in milder climates. I travel often and really like how this jacket packs up into its own inside pocket. It\'s rare that I take a trip without packing my nano into its own pocket and',22,'2020-06-15'),(2068,'Karen229',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Warm','This thing will keep you so warm! Love this jacket. Does run a little small,usually wear a medium but a large fits mutch better.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2069,'Wise O.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Best Jacket I Own','I have owned this jacket for about six months and I have used it almost every day. I love that it packs into itself so it could be used as a pillow. It will definitely be making my gear list for when I thru-hike the AT next year. Thank you so much Patagonia for being such a wonderful company with great ethics!',22,'2020-06-15'),(2070,'br',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,5.0,'Adaptable','Lightweight,handsome jacket. Keeps you warm and it\'s easy to wear the Nano Puff Hoodie either as a mid-layer or as an outer layer. I got it in the plain black and it works really well with almost any outfit or activity.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2071,'izzym2018',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,4.0,'Great,light,and warm jacket','I received this jacket just yesterday from my girlfriend and it\'s amazing. It\'s light,packable,and keeps you warm. It\'s even a bit water proof. The only problem I have is the drawstring to tighten the waist of the jacket. There\'s no way to hide it inside the jacket and it hangs loose and it\'s visible under the jacket. It&#x',22,'2020-06-15'),(2072,'Tailspotter',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Welcome companion..','Super versatile piece and essentially all I need for three season coverage.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2073,'Jake M.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Favorite Jacket','I have had this for a couple of years now and wear it more than I don\'t. It\'s warm,lightweight,and packs down nice and small. It works well as a base layer too. I can\'t get enough of this thing.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2074,'Sergio N.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XXL',NULL,5.0,'So light weight and then so comfortable and warm','As deer bow hunting season opened in Weatern New York and the weather has been so nice and at the same time crazy I have been using my Nano',22,'2020-06-15'),(2075,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Awesome Jacket','I cant say enough good things about this jacket. Super light and it keep me super warm. I can walk around with temps low in the 40s and I feel fine. Great all around jacket for hiking and hanging out in the mountains',22,'2020-06-15'),(2076,'Dadbod12',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Perfect hoodie','You could either wear this in the fall or as a well insulted jacket with a hoodie underneath it is great I love it. GreAt hiking.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2077,'Bobby W.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,2.0,'I like the jacket I just wish the zipper worked','There\'s something wrong with the zipper it keeps getting stuck it\'s like it was smushed or something',22,'2020-06-15'),(2078,'B52starr',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Perfect layering piece for travel','I bought this for a trip to Svalbard in summer. It is so light and packs well: rolled it up into the hoody and stuffed in my duffle. Always looks neat when wearing ( no wrinkles). I used this as a lightweight layering piece under a mid weight parka. Also,wore it on ship. This is not for very cold situations.....just breaks the wind and takes the ch',22,'2020-06-15'),(2079,'Meatstick',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'nano puff hoody','I purchased this piece about 2 months ago. I\'ve been quiet happy with the fit and its warmth to weight ratio. I bought it as a layering piece for fieldwork in the fall and the occasional wet/snowy summer day,but it has also made several appearances while mountaineering this summer. As with most puffy coats it won\'t stay on for a bushwack,',22,'2020-06-15'),(2080,'Ralph T.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Just the right amount of warmth','I like the light weight and nice fit of this garment. I use it primarily on those cold mornings in camp before the sun comes up. Sleeve length is good and the hood covers the head just right.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2081,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Light and warm','Only got to wear it once in the Alps,was light and warm. Easily packs away into self.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2082,'CHRISTINA V.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'So Warm Yet So Light','Bought this jacket over a month ago and so very happy with it. So warm for just a lightweight jacket!',22,'2020-06-15'),(2083,'Bulk12',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'The perfect piece!','I have three of these and I wear them just about every day during the winter. Super versatile.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2084,'Biff4 B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XXL',NULL,4.0,'Warm and fluffy','Fabric has a great hand,cozy to put on...good shoulder season piece. Most days you don\'t need the shell or the down. This is perfect. I\'d like velcro cuff to adjust.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2085,'King M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XXL',NULL,5.0,'The Nano Puff Hoody does all I ask it to do.','This is my go to grab jacket in Maine & sometimes Canada for about 7-8 months of the year. It keeps the chill off and keeps me pretty dry in the rain or wet snow. It\'s very portable and so light,airy I can stuff it into a 1-gallon Baggie after forcing the air out; and it puffs back up once the air gets back in to act as insulation.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2086,'Fredsled',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,2.0,'Sizing','I ordered a large like my down sweater which fits perfect. This item is definetly smaller. I will have to get a larger one.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2087,'Ed',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Love my Nanopuffs!','This is my fourth Nanopuff - suffice it to say I love the product. The size and fit are just right for me,and the hood makes this my new \"go-to\" jacket for days where I might want a little extra warmth.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2088,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'Light and warm!','This hoodie is incredibly warm for how lightweight it is. It packs down to almost nothing to take up very little space,and it\'s great to not have a heavy,bulky piece of clothing when you need to stay warm.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2089,'Tlyer R.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,2.0,'Great jacket having some quality control issues','I got this jacket at the end of December and its an amazing layer for skiing and great for hiking or snow shoeing in,only thing is im having issues with is the rectangular stitching coming undone,there is two sections where its completely come out and ive had to cut off,and every day I wear it I seem to find a new piece of thread that has come undo',22,'2020-06-15'),(2090,'Cesar J.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'Top of the line Product','I\'ve owned this jacket for about 5 months and am amazed by it\'s superb performance. It\'s weight and thinness make it hard to believe that in most ordinary winter conditions all you will need is this jacket. So far I\'ve tested it in 20 degrees F with a wind chill and real feel of 10F with just a T shirt and felt only a slight chi',22,'2020-06-15'),(2091,'Logan M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Lightweight,warm,and super stylish!','After falling out of love with my Thermoball jacket,for various and horrible reasons,I took a step into the unknown. Little did I know that my journey would lead me to a feverish love for the first of many Patagonia products to come. The NanoPuff Jacket is absolutely perfect for Winter in the Pacific Northwest. If the temperature gets really frigid',22,'2020-06-15'),(2092,'Amdg',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,5.0,'Fantastic Jacket','One of my most treasured Patagonia items. So light,so warm. Excellent mobility. Really does stay warm when wet and protects from wind. In extremely cold weather,I combine with a base layer if I\'m not going to be active (by shoveling snow,hiking,etc.). I wish the jacket were a hair longer in the lower back and arms to provide a bit more coverag',22,'2020-06-15'),(2093,'Ethjryhjgtn',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Too bad it didn\'t fit','I think this is an excellent jacket. I would have kept it if it had fit me better. I\'m 5\'-10\" and 185 pounds. A Large jacket fit in the chest and overall length,but was snug in the stomach. I thought about trying an XL,but the sleeves were already about an inch too long.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2094,'Wasatch B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'The most useful jacket I own','This is a truly killer piece for anyone who lives an adventurous lifestyle.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2095,'Mass',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Some recommendations','This is an excellent jacket - one of the best I\'ve ever owned. I live in Estes Park,Colorado,and this is the outerwear of choice for almost every day (-15 and blowing snow calls for heavy artillery). Two suggestions,though.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2096,'Saltywaders',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,4.0,'Great Insulating Layer','I already own a Patagonia nano puff jacket from a few years ago that I love and use extensively around town as well as an insulating layer when I\'m fishing,hunting or camping. I wanted a jacket with a hood and since my nano puff jacket worked so well for me,the hoody was a no brainer. What I love about the nano-puff series of jackets is that t',22,'2020-06-15'),(2097,'Jaystock',NULL,'None','None',NULL,3.0,'lightweight but not warm enough for N.E. winter','I told the sales staff at Patagonia that I needed a jacket for winter cycling in Boston and they recommended this nano puff hoody because it\'s wind and water resistant. The coat does pretty well considering how lightweight it is,however it is not warm enough for winter in the northeast. Maybe if it is combined with a base layer and outer layer',22,'2020-06-15'),(2098,'Mharren',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Performance to weight ratio','Used for all sorts of activities and is the most versatile coat I own. It\'s so light I forget I have it on! Knowing it\'s made of 55% recycled material is even better.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2099,'Dick',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XL',NULL,5.0,'Love to hate','Ok so finally got to try this sucker out. So today was 50 n with a 20mph wind so with only my R1 underneath we ventured out and can honestly say was very toasty which surprised me. I\'d say ud be ok with tempts into the high 30s maybe 40s with a base layer .',22,'2020-06-15'),(2100,'Michael C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,3.0,'Decent,lightweight hoody.','The XL is true to size but there\'s barely enough room to wear a midweight fleece underneath. I\'m 6\' of average build with broad shoulders and XL fits relatively well.',22,'2020-06-15'),(2101,'Fernandoenlasmontanas',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Must have!!','Wore this jacket for 3 years on all my adventures! Can wear it under or on top of my shell. So versatile! Zipper died,sent it for warranty and ordered a new one',22,'2020-06-15'),(2102,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Amazing','I have many jackets and I must say that I LOVE this jacket. The outer material is smooth and soft, it sheds light water and dirt well. The inner material is loose and fluffy, very warm and comfortable. I work outdoors and I need to trust my gear and it has to prove its worth. Well, after many days backpacking in to study sites and relying on this j',19,'2020-06-15'),(2103,'Naor',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Excellent !!!','Probably the best hoodie I have ever had . Great craftsmanship, great materials and very comfortable. Great technical hoodie',19,'2020-06-15'),(2104,'Steve',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','0',NULL,5.0,'Extremely versatile','Purchased the R2 to be a versatile piece of wardrobe and that is exactly what it does. The Medium runs true to size, with a nice coat length rather than a shorter shirt length. Elastic hem is snug, keeping in heat. Cuffs are snug with a stretch area by wrists that I thought would bother me but they remain warm and snug. Pockets are good sized and z',19,'2020-06-15'),(2105,'Fred B.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'A great addition','The R2 Techface hoody is a great addition to my wardrobe. It is wearable over a wide temperature range. Slim fitting, it is \" fuzzy warm \" on the inside & protects against the wind & briars on the outside.',19,'2020-06-15'),(2106,'Willie',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Wowza, this is hoody is AWESOME!','My Patagonia quiver is deep, and this piece rises to the top and is a new favorite. It\'s warm, extremely comfortable and exquisitely tailored/fitted. Does double duty as a mid-layer (I\'ve even worn it under a Micro Puff on extra frosty days) and an outer layer in milder weather and works when wet. The balaclava hood replaces a beanie if y',19,'2020-06-15'),(2107,'Tyler H.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Shockingly Useful Hoody','Last weekend I took this up to 12,500 ft in the wind and snow. I was skiing hard and didn\'t sweat out or freeze. This thing gives that perfect balance. The hood fits tight and the zipper goes high so it feels like a balaclava when fully zipped. Great hoody!',19,'2020-06-15'),(2108,'Scott A.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Goody Hoody','Mid winter mid layer minimizes cold drafts. Surprised to discover this size L fits under my size L R1 tech Hoody for double breathable protectionism.',19,'2020-06-15'),(2109,'Milestoner',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'so good i bought two!','for reference, im 5’11” and 155lbs. i have a 38 inch chest, 32 inch waist, and this fit perfectly!',19,'2020-06-15'),(2110,'Cory C.',NULL,'5\'0 or less','XL',NULL,5.0,'New favorite thing to wear','I’m a big fan of Patagonia. I am usually wearing something of their’s everyday. During the cold months I usually wear a vest but now this is going to be my go-to item. It is very comfortable and warmer than I thought it would be. It is different from other items I have or have seen by Patagonia. On really cold days it will be good under a warmer ja',19,'2020-06-15'),(2111,'Dave',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'REEEALLY warm.','This is an awesome piece. Possibly the best part of it is that it enables me to wear it alone instead of two or even three layers. It is SUPER warm. It\'s important to remember that this is an ACTIVE piece and being the R grid, wind does get through it a bit, so if you\'re just gonna be hanging & not moving around generating at least a',19,'2020-06-15'),(2112,'Gabriel C.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,4.0,'Very comfortable','Great fit. Looks good. Wore it this morning for the the first time with just a cotton tshirt underneath. Was comfortable walking in 39 degree weather with a light breeze. Hood was a little too snug, but a have a 7 3/8 size head. I can see myself wearing this for a lot of different activities, as well as casually.',19,'2020-06-15'),(2113,'Nic S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'warm, nice colours, but not very versatile...','Early days, but so far this garment has worked well for the particular niche use I bought it for - namely something warm to pull on after getting out of the water.',19,'2020-06-15'),(2114,'Jeff J.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,5.0,'Sweet!','Great piece! Super comfy, nice long cut for harness wear. Does a good job of blocking wind yet breathes great for wear while hiking.',19,'2020-06-15'),(2115,'Paul R.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Versatile','This fleece hoody has already become my go to piece for hiking, biking and all around use. It’s warm but breathable, stretchy in all the right places and looks good enough for a night out on the town. Expecting to use it for cross country skiing as well.',19,'2020-06-15'),(2116,'Robert C.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,5.0,'Perfect Layer','Perfect Layer',19,'2020-06-15'),(2117,'William S.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'R2 techface hoody','This garment has a luxurious feel to it due to the generous nap of the inner fleece layer (unlike the R1techface nap). I wore it with a light capilene base layer snow biking in the upper 20\'s and was quite comfortable. Breathability is good and so is wind resistance.',19,'2020-06-15'),(2118,'Matthew M.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Refined But Simple Multi-Use','A simple hoody but with refined elements like fit, closures, and pockets. The R2 is heavier weight for colder temps.',19,'2020-06-15'),(2119,'Chris G.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Great new piece!','I love the new hooded R2 techface jacket! I\'m 6\'1\", 180+lbs ,athletic build and the size medium pits perfectly. I wish the regular R2 fleece had the same fit. It\'s great for fly fishing, hiking or wear casually around town. It\'s good for temperatures in the 40s and 50s. Now that temperatures are more frequently below 32F I',19,'2020-06-15'),(2120,'Kevin B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,4.0,'Everything but the fit...','This hoody has been great so far. I\'m using it as a base layer here in Antarctica. It\'s warm. The chest pocket is spacious. And the outer material seems burly enough to put up with tough work. My only issue is the sizing. I am 6\'1\" and 185 pounds and wearing a medium. The jacket fits my arms well. The torso is a little short and',19,'2020-06-15'),(2121,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'The best','This might be the best piece of clothing I own. Warmth, lightweight, breathable, wind blocking and beyond comfy. I want 2 more so I can wear them all the time without wearing them out.',19,'2020-06-15'),(2122,'Matthew S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Warmer than the nano-air hoody','I wanted something warmer than my nano-air hoody but not as bulky as my puff or down jackets. This fits the bill. Very happy so far.',19,'2020-06-15'),(2123,'Seldomseen',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Haven\'t had enough time in','Haven\'t had enough time in actual use conditions, but comfortable & fits well. Worked great considering not too cold yet.',19,'2020-06-15'),(2124,'Brody I.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Toasty and comfy','Probably my new favorite jacket. It’s comfy like a hoody yet with the water / wind resistant outer layer you can wear it in almost all weather. I was looking for something that was comfy / warm like my better sweater but with a little more weather resistance. I liked how you can zip it off to dump heat and quickly take off when getting into a car',19,'2020-06-15'),(2125,'Rowan M.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Love the snuggly fit, and','Love the snuggly fit, and soft inside fleece which doesn’t get you too hot.',19,'2020-06-15'),(2126,'James F.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Remarkably Light But Warm','Thanks to some crazy weather (or maybe new-normal), I got to wear this jacket for my couple mile walk to and from work. Worn with just a tshirt underneath, I was comfortable in windy upper 30s F going in and calm almost 60F walking home. Great slim fit. Snuggly fleece interior.',19,'2020-06-15'),(2127,'Kerry H.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'This is a great new','This is a great new piece. The high neck keeps out the cold.',19,'2020-06-15'),(2128,'Steve',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Initial Impression','Still summer, so it will be a while before I actually use the R2. I\'m medium build, 6\'0, 175 and the jacket fit like a glove. First trial proved it to be warm. Hood is snug but not too tight, with good fit around the face. Sleeve\'s and hem are right length. Long term review will follow after winter.',19,'2020-06-15'),(2129,'Urkiola',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'If you run cold and want a insulating midlayer that provides excellent protection, moisture management and superior abrasion resistance, it\'s here!','First off-the design and fit of this are what the R1 techface should be. The R1 techface is designed (both hood, zipper covers and fit adjustment) like a shell. But its more like a quasi softshell/air permeable windshell that would be better suited as a midlayer than as a shell ie worn as an outer layer until conditions deteriorate. Granted, i live',19,'2020-06-15'),(2130,'Nunorsk',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XL',NULL,5.0,'Brilliant piece','I have the regular techface r2 , just got the hooded version in red. It seems like they improved the cut. This is a great piece, as warm as a micropuff but more breathable. I also love my nano air but this has that great soft fleece interior and blocks the wind great.',19,'2020-06-15'),(2131,'Dario',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Worth Upgrading from a Nano Puff','I love this jacket, I have a daily rotation from the Nano Puff and Micro Puff. Although the Micro is more shiny and puffy. I think its worth the upgrade. Its a little warmer in my opinion and the pockets are a bit higher which helps my size. Either way they both look great!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2132,'JD',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,4.0,'So good in so many ways, but the pockets...','This is a great jacket. Its extremely light, very warm, and very comfortable. It blocks the wind, and it handles very light rain easily. The fit is great, the look is great, and the overall function is great. The only thing that isn\'t great is the pocket placement. The two front pockets are positioned mid way up the jacket, starting around the',65,'2020-06-15'),(2133,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Great product','A must have if you live in colder climates. Keeps you warm and is extremely light.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2134,'David',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','None',NULL,5.0,'Just the Bees Knees','Long had I held back from buying this jacket. It is pricey for sure. Then I caved and purchased it.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2135,'Pete',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','0',NULL,5.0,'Lightweight Furnace','The scientists at Patagonia have cracked the code, this thing is inexplicably warm for how thin and lightweight it is. I love this jacket, it is far warmer and much higher quality than another jacket I own from a brand that shall remain nameless. I would say this jacket has a pretty technical fit, I\'m 6ft 160lbs and the medium fits pretty snug',65,'2020-06-15'),(2136,'Ocean',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Perhaps my favorite jacket ever','Since 2008 Ive been wearing my much loved down sweater hoody. This year, despite trying to be a minimalist, I decided to upgrade. While the down hoody was great, over the years it began to have small leaks of feathers, so if I wore a dark shirt or sweater underneath, it looked like it had lint in it. And the small leaked feathers were hard to remov',65,'2020-06-15'),(2137,'Charles',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','0',NULL,5.0,'Amazin warmth to weigh ratio','The micro puff is by far the best lightweight insulation I\'ve worn. Surprisingly warm and packable. I use it for backcountry skiing as a descent layer, climbing as a packable belay layer and causally around town. Pair this jacket with an r1 and you\'ll be toasty all day. I liked it so much I wear it almost every day and had to get a second',65,'2020-06-15'),(2138,'Phill W.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'My new favorite jacket','Replacing my nano puff jacket with with the micro puff. Have used the now one only few times. I still wear the nano puff most often to keep the other looking new and my winter has been very mild this year. The one frigid night we had, I layered them and it worked very well. The drop-in pockets are roomy but I do miss the zippered interior pocket li',65,'2020-06-15'),(2139,'Greg',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','0',NULL,2.0,'Sadly, Mixed Feelings','I have mixed feelings about the Micropuff. It is a beautiful piece and I really wanted to love it because I need something light and packable, halfway rainproof and warm when the temp drops. Thought this jacket would be it. Sadly, it seems a bit on the thin side. It sure looked a little loftier on the Patagonia site. And making matters worse I can ',65,'2020-06-15'),(2140,'Jeremy M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Awesome jacket','Purchased this after my down jacket of 10 years finally gave out. This is a awesome jacket and the hood is a great addition. Super warm and very comfortable. Another awesome jacket from Patagonia! I try to be pretty true and honest with reviews and this jacket rocks!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2141,'Casey K.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'My favorite light-weight jacket!','It\'s hard to believe a jacket this light can be so warm. I wear it more than any other jacket because its so light, packable, sylish and most importantly warm! I\'m usually a minimalist in my clothing but I have three different colors in this jacket because I wear it every day in the cold months.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2142,'mark w.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,4.0,'Almost perfect','I have had my micropuff since December of 2018. The warmth to weight ratio of this jacket is incredible. It compresses very well and hasn’t lost its loftyness after being thrown in a stuff sack 100 times. I use it the most when bringing a belay jacket would be overkill but I still want something more than just my Nano Puff. The face fabric blocks t',65,'2020-06-15'),(2143,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket','This is a pretty perfect jacket. It\'s lightweight but retains warmth like there\'s a little furnace inside. It blocks wind and keeps me dry. It looks great without being too puffy and has a pretty solid silhouette. The hood looks a little ridiculous but is function over form. Highly recommend.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2144,'Patch',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'My most versatile jacket (Period)','The title is a BIG claim and I usually do not write reviews. But, with this jacket, I had to. I lost my mountain hardwear ghost whisperer jacket on a bus in Spain. My wife and I were in Europe for an ultra bikepacking race across the Pyrenees, so I needed a jacket. I decided on this jacket. The jacket is not as warm as my mountain hardwear ghost wh',65,'2020-06-15'),(2145,'Morgan H.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Finally A Coat My Teen WILL Wear','My son would never wear a coat even in the coldest of weather. However, his new Micro Puff coat is so light and comfortable that he wears it all the time!!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2146,'Zev A.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,5.0,'Awesome Jacket!','I’ve had other Patagonia jackets in the past but none are as light and warm as this one. The micro puff is now my favorite jacket all around and my go to for just about any adventure.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2147,'Erin',NULL,'None','XS',NULL,5.0,'This is THE PUFFY','After just over a year of hard use this puffy has continued to hit all the marks. Very light and packable, yet quite warm and windproof. Also the styling is A+, looks great around town too. Only drawback for this gal is the durability, it doesn\'t hold up that well to snags and getting too close to the camp stove. As a 120lb broad shouldered wo',65,'2020-06-15'),(2148,'Lynn D.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Gift for my husband, he','Gift for my husband, he loves it',65,'2020-06-15'),(2149,'Jerry H.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'This Micropuff Hoodie is the greatest jacket I\'ve ever owned.','And I have lots of Patagonia jackets. I have worn this for a year. It is so thin and lightweight one can almost see through the panels. It can pack down into the pocket making a small bundle in my pack. I keep thinking it will fail me, but it is warm enough for our Minnesota winters. Nice arrangement of pockets, especially the inside panel ones tha',65,'2020-06-15'),(2150,'JM',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Best Jacket/Hoodie I\'ve Ever Owned','Quality: This jacket has the durability and quality that we\'re all accustomed to from Patagonia. Whether you\'re hiking Mount Rainier or going cross-country through Afghanistan, this jacket will withstand whatever you have to throw at it.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2151,'Jeremy P.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Great Jacket, would definitely buy again!','Really great jacket, been happy with my purchase. I\'m 5\'8 and 150lbs, normally I wear a medium but after reading the reviews on the fit I went with the small which fits perfectly.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2152,'corey c.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket. Very warm, scary','Great jacket. Very warm, scary light.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2153,'Adrian S.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,5.0,'Just Get It','This jacket is the real deal. It is amazingly lightweight, super packable and surprisingly warm. Bought this for hiking through the mountains in New Zealand (start the hike at 74F and end at 38F kind of thing). Kept me warm all the way up and down. Hoody works (the jacket is very warm with it) but you do kind of look like a bean in in it. In light',65,'2020-06-15'),(2154,'JD113',NULL,'None','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Better Than Expected','It\'s perfect. Light, super warm, very good fitting, very good looking. Many compliments while wearing.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2155,'Zach L.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Great Jacket for Mild Temps','This jacket is great for mild temps in the 50\'s and does a decent job cutting the wind. The jacket fits true to size and provides a surprising amount of warmth for its size. A great feature is the jackets ability to be packed into its own pocket for travel or packing in a suitcase. The jacket looks great, performs well, and is super lightweigh',65,'2020-06-15'),(2156,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket','Light, warm and comfortable. Love it',65,'2020-06-15'),(2157,'Kari R.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Amazing warmth and lightness','Amazing warmth and lightness',65,'2020-06-15'),(2158,'Curran V.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Awesome Weight for Warmth','For the warmth you get out of this jacket, it seems like it be pretty bulky and heavy, however I\'m pretty sure you could use this thing as an emergency parachute... the weight is great and doesn\'t make me feel like a michelin man when I layer underneath. It\'s a sweet coat.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2159,'Paul T.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Love this coat!','Many, many Patagonia costs over a lot of years. This is my favorite. Warm enough to wear in low temps, light brought to wear in the 50’s. Water resistant too. Great coat.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2160,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Good','Good',65,'2020-06-15'),(2161,'Patricia M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Warm and lightweight','I gave this jacket to my son for christmas, and he loved it. It was lightweight but very warm—perfect for everyday use in winter. The hood covers part of the face so extra warm. He will also wear the jacket under a shell for skiing. The jacket was a hit.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2162,'Katie M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L/XL',NULL,5.0,'It was great','It was great',65,'2020-06-15'),(2163,'Ronald B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Perfct!','Love this coat. Light, but warm. Good for everything but the coldest of days.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2164,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Great Product','Love the coat, thanks',65,'2020-06-15'),(2165,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Great product!','Great product!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2166,'mark',NULL,'None','L',NULL,4.0,'Great active insulation','I\'ve been wearing this for a little over a year and enjoyed its light weight',65,'2020-06-15'),(2167,'Adam W.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Lofty Aspirations','I’m lovin’ my new puffy! I’ve owned the Nano Puff Hoody for 2 years (great jacket), but my new Micro Puff is a serious upgrade. It’s incredibly light and significantly warmer. My first real test was out in Joshua Tree this week (low of 34 degrees) for some backpacking and stargazing. It’s one thing to stay warm while moving, but for me, the real te',65,'2020-06-15'),(2168,'Brandon S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'The hood/shoulders bunch up a','The hood/shoulders bunch up a bit when the hood isn’t in use. But it fits great, breaths well when in use. Great in the wind & precipitation.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2169,'Michael R.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Great lightweight jacket','Perfect packable lightweight warm jacket',65,'2020-06-15'),(2170,'Vishal M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Surprisingly light and warm at the same time','This jacket is really light and warm at the same time. So far love it',65,'2020-06-15'),(2171,'Marc S.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XXL',NULL,4.0,'No more Michelin man.','Happy to have this item in the wardrobe. Having used a big NF Down Coat since early 2000, I was ready for modernizing the weather protection. Although not as warm as previous, that is not necessarily a bad thing with proper layering. I love the hood! Completely covers the noggin and is cut so that it does not inhibit proper vision for active moveme',65,'2020-06-15'),(2172,'Richard L.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'too thin','Not the best construction, no inner security pockets',65,'2020-06-15'),(2173,'Donald H.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'I bought the Men\'s Micro','I bought the Men\'s Micro Puff Hoody as an insulation layer for skiing, and also for casual, light weight jacket. It is very comfortable, and works perfectly for',65,'2020-06-15'),(2174,'Trey P.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,4.0,'Great packable warmth','This jacket is great for your layering kit bag, I pair it with a Houdini in the rain, and if I need more warmth a R1 Hoodie. My only ding is that on mine it seems like they didn\'t put any insulation in some of the baffles on both elbows so I get cold spots on both arms right above the elbow. A weird place for cold spots.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2175,'Todd P',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Great coat, fits a little large','Patagonia needs a slim fit/athletic cut for some of these jackets. I love everything about my new coat, except the cut. It bunches up awkwardly in front, and it\'s wide in the sides. I had an older coat that had a better shape to it and it was more form fitting. I\'m not skinny, either. But I also don\'t have a big beer belly, which one',65,'2020-06-15'),(2176,'Sean O.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,3.0,'Unbelievably light, Unbelievably packable, Unbelievably delicate','The micro puff is so light it barely feels like you\'re wearing anything. It packs down smaller than any jacket of comparable warmth. Unfortunately though it is incredibly delicate. I make a point to trim my nails before putting it on because I\'m afraid a stray nail will cause a rip. I will continue to travel with it on planes because it p',65,'2020-06-15'),(2177,'Nofandy I.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'awesome','awesome',65,'2020-06-15'),(2178,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Great for 48 degrees and above!','I loved the jacket. The overall weight and packability feature is unreal! It is super light and great for all around town in warmer weather! I found myself wearing this jacket all the time in many different activities I took part in. Great for hikes or small climbing trips in the fall! Would recommend if you are looking for an extremely lightweight',65,'2020-06-15'),(2179,'Ron J.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,1.0,'MS Micro Puff problems','I regretfully write this I say regret as I am a avid Patagonia supporter but I am very very disappointed for my long awaited purchase of this jacket only to have the filling continually surface through the seams of my jacket. Very frustrating and quit annoying.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2180,'Kent O.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Unequaled Warmth to Weight','Great hoodie. Amazingly light and extremely warm and comfortable. Best light winter jacket ever.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2181,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Just right','The micro puff hoody was just what I was looking for. A bit warmer than my nano, plus a hood.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2182,'Lydia C.',NULL,'5\'1 - 5\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Fits middle school locker','My son loves this. Light and warm. Fits in his narrow locker at school but works for recess etc',65,'2020-06-15'),(2183,'Maryann S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,1.0,'Both jackets ordered','Patagonia has quality jackets years ago. There emphasis on recycled and green focus has damaged the brand . Jackets ordered were black . We’re faded black actually but be environmentally friendly dye lol. As for thickness not warm at all . We have a jacket purchased more than 5 years ago that withstood Alaskan winters these would not . Not going to',65,'2020-06-15'),(2184,'Brian S.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Great fit and super warm for weight.','The only thing you feel with this jacket is warmth. It is unbelievably light. I wear this early in the morning riding my bike to work with just a polo shirt and am warm even in temperatures in the low 30s and wind. This fits on the slimmer side compared to the nano puff which I am thankful for. I like the minimalist approach with the elastic waistb',65,'2020-06-15'),(2185,'Patrick C.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Love it','Love it',65,'2020-06-15'),(2186,'Rachel S.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','XS',NULL,5.0,'Andor10','Love my new jacket.... . Comfortable......warm.....and so stylish.....love the texture of the jacket...and so stylish!!!!!!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2187,'Nick H.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Super Comfy just too small.','Super Comfy just too small. Exchanged for a large. Fits nicely',65,'2020-06-15'),(2188,'Dario K.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Excellent','HAPPY WITH THIS PURCHASE ON EVERY LEVEL! ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️',65,'2020-06-15'),(2189,'Ted K.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L/XL',NULL,4.0,'Nice safety layer','I carry this hunting in the mountains to stay warm when the weather turns bad. Lightweight and small, but warm. So far, so good.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2190,'Brent B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,5.0,'Always on','I’ve been holding out on getting a light weight puff for a while, but have enjoyed it just about every day I’ve had it. Great as a layering piece under a variety of other shells/jackets and also quite warm as an outer layer. Packs so small it will be in my travel bag for at least 3 seasons, if not four.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2191,'Abraham G.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XS',NULL,4.0,'A quality jacket, but I wish it was warmer','The warmth to weight on this jacket truly is phenomenal, but it doesn’t mean it’s extremely warm. The jacket is almost weightless, and will keep you comfortably warm as long as you don’t wear it 55 degrees Fahrenheit and below. Otherwise, excellent quality.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2192,'Anne T.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,4.0,'Good jacket. Look forward to','Good jacket. Look forward to using it',65,'2020-06-15'),(2193,'Mason D.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'10월 10일','Perfect',65,'2020-06-15'),(2194,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,5.0,'Much warmer than it looks!','Much warmer than it looks!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2195,'Brian M.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Mens Micro Puff Hoody','Nice lightweight waterproof insulated jacket for light weather condition',65,'2020-06-15'),(2196,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,4.0,'Contrast color piping – why?','Great jacket, great weight, great colors, but… wait!? Oh no, the carbon color (wonderful green color) comes with a contrasting grey piping that was a deal breaker. I can\'t for the life of me understand why Patagonia adds contrasting piping, particularly at the sleeve cuffs of men\'s jackets. For little girls jackets, okay, but for men&#x27',65,'2020-06-15'),(2197,'Mike M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Better and better','I’ve been using Patagonia gear since before it was Patagonia . The equipment just keeps getting better. This latest puffy jacket is amazingly light and warm. I live in the PNW where it is ideal for wet, cold weather. It’s a must-have in my daypack for long day hikes and for around town.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2198,'Trey P.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,4.0,'Great warmth for weight, cold spots in weird places','I love this jacket for many reasons, the least of which is its warmth. The materials are comfortable enough that I have fallen asleep in it (hood and all) and the fit is athletic without being too slim (layers easily). The one odd thing I noticed is that I have cold spots right above both elbows. I don’t know if that is a natural displacement of th',65,'2020-06-15'),(2199,'George M.',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,5.0,'Layer up or layer down','Love it. Ultralight and great in a variety of conditions. Layer underneath and it is good in wind down to 15 degrees F or so. Below that a shell over the top works wonders. I use it under my ski uniform jacket on cold days. Great product. g',65,'2020-06-15'),(2200,'Michael M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L/XL',NULL,5.0,'great lightweight coat.','great lightweight coat.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2201,'Dan D.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Excellent lightweight insulated hoody','Although assigning a temperature rating to any article of clothing is difficult, this piece generally won’t be appropriate below 40-30 with a baselayer, midlayer, and shell over. It’s sweet spot is above freezing. But for what it is and what it does, it is excellent. It is quite packable, impressively light, attractive, and has an inviting fit. The',65,'2020-06-15'),(2202,'Wm E.',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,5.0,'5 stars but one recommendation','LOVE this jacket. Perfect for mid-Atlantic winters below 3000\'. Below 30F, I need more than a T-shirt or lightweight Capilene base layer. Very stylish and functional. I also love the hoody, but would add maybe an inch of material so it is not so tight at my chin. I love the close fit around my head, but zipping all the way up for more than a f',65,'2020-06-15'),(2203,'Osvaldo C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Awesome coat','Warm, light weight, wicked awesome coat!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2204,'Robert K.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','NB-7lb',NULL,5.0,'My new best friend','I have no idea why it took me so long to order the puff hoody .after seeing others on a offshore fishing trip wearing the hoody and me being miserable I placed a order for one that very night.What a wonderful garment. No more Mr Miserable !',65,'2020-06-15'),(2205,'Brett B.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,5.0,'Extremely light','I am super happy with this coat! Its light, packs into one of its pockets. Also super warm! Looking forward to using for backpacking.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2206,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Punches above it’s weight','Light, warm, comfortable. Hood fits perfectly when snow, wind makes things interesting. Layer a shell and you’re good for what the weather gods give ya. My new favorite puffer.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2207,'Jose B.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,5.0,'Nothing is good','Warm, light, feels study',65,'2020-06-15'),(2208,'Guy L.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'Solid piece','I’ve only had this micro puff about a week or so. I’m liking it a lot. Lightweight, warm and seems showerproof as well. The Mtn weather has been cold lately but this is working well without a shell if out for a bit. Works well with a shell as it’s low volume. Can’t wait to ski in it.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2209,'Jane B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Hooded Jacket','This jacket is so lightweight and compact it can be taken anywhere! Provides incredible warmth without the bulk. Excellent for backpacking and winter activities.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2210,'W. A.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,4.0,'Love everything but the main zipper.','The jacket’s hood is the best hood I’ve ever had on a jacket. The only think I dislike is the main zipper. It occasionally gets caught on the flaps behind it, and I wonder if a larger YKK zipper would preclude this. I’m also worried about the durability of the pockets in terms of car keys.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2211,'Paul B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Sweet new look and feel','This new twist on an old classic keeps me coming back. I\'ve worn a version of this since they came out and this one doesn\'t disappoint.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2212,'Sherman W.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Unbelievable warmth for its weight','Unbelievable warmth for its weight',65,'2020-06-15'),(2213,'Rick K.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Perfect Light Weight Jacket','Bought this for winter and it’s PERFECT! Light weight, yet warm- fits in any bag.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2214,'Stephen B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','12-24m',NULL,5.0,'Micropuff hoody rocks!!','Very warm and wind resistant as promised, the hood seals and protects well. I have worn this as my only layer in 30 degree weather in windy conditions comfortably.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2215,'Aaron K.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Light and warm','This piece is very light and very warm for the weight. The hooded Micro Puff fits great - I\'m 6\' and 175lbs and wear the medium - and it packs down pretty darn small. It\'s going with me on all backcountry adventures.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2216,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,4.0,'Great ‘Just in Case’ Jacket','This jacket slots perfectly into my current lineup of jackets. I’ve used it on a very colD and windy 17-F night biking home with only a tee shirt underneath. I won’t say that I was toasty warm, but I was not cold. Those conditions typically have me reaching for my sub-zero down jacket, which while packable is no where near as light and compressible',65,'2020-06-15'),(2217,'Dale A.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','NB-7lb',NULL,5.0,'Unbelievable','so warm yet so light, fantastic!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2218,'Peter J.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great everyday and work jacket','Great everyday and work jacket',65,'2020-06-15'),(2219,'Gary L.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Cozy vegan','My new Micro Puff is what I was looking for: a lightweight alternative to down. As a long distance hiker, I also like how easy it is to wash, while on the trail.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2220,'Alex T.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','36',NULL,5.0,'Excited about these!','Winter bike commuter in WI, and these suckers will keep me warm for sure. I have had to find a substitute for the not quite as cold days or else I\'ll be sweating when I get to school, even in low 20\'s. These will be a go to for all winter activities. Tossing a shell layer over them to protect them and provide a bit more wind resistance wi',65,'2020-06-15'),(2221,'Greg G.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Lighter, and warmer than my','Lighter, and warmer than my Nano Puff. The hood fits well, and layers well under a shell.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2222,'Curtis M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Warm comfortable and lightweight','Warm comfortable and lightweight',65,'2020-06-15'),(2223,'Jeff S.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Warm and packs well','For a light weight jacket it provides great warmth.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2224,'Kirk J.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Awesome pack-able piece you should','Awesome pack-able piece you should always keep with you.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2225,'Clayton T.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Weight to Warmth Ratio','If you’re looking for a hoody/jacket that\'ll keep you warm (even when wet) and is lightweight, the micro puff is your best bet. Temperature below freezing? Snag a good lightweight or medium weight base layer like the capilene and you’re golden. I’m 6’0 and the large fits perfect. My pops is 5’10 and wears his micro in a medium. Seriously. Don’',65,'2020-06-15'),(2226,'Jan G.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,5.0,'Micro Puff delivers','Lightweight, warm, compressible. Gets it done and has become my everyday jacket in the fall and early winter. Layers well. Stands alone too. Love the inside stash pockets for gloves/hat. I don\'t leave home without it.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2227,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Perfect','Decent level of warmth for being so thin. Works great as a mid layer under a shell or heavy coat. Packs down tightly for convenient storage while backpacking. The size Medium fits me perfectly; I am 5\'9\", ~170 pounds, athletic build.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2228,'Caleb A.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Micro Puff','Light on weight but heavy on warmth. I have several of these jackets and recommend them to anyone. Help shed light rain, while regulating body temperature. Don\'t let the soft outer fabric make you think these jackets cant handle some heavy duty wear and tear. I use and abuse all things patagonia and they stand up!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2229,'James R.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'New go to Jacket for climbing!','This jacket is my new go to jacket for climbing adventures for saving wight and space. I reach for it every time now over my nano puff. Lighter and warmer than my nano puff!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2230,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Very light and warm','Very light and warm',65,'2020-06-15'),(2231,'Kirby S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'The jacket you have to have','Could not be happier with this jacket. Lightweight, comfortable 