2237,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket','Warm, light, durable.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2238,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Almost perfect','Super light weight. First test was a sub 0 degree ski tour with base layer and mid layer. Just put it on for alpine and downhill. Very comfortable except neck and chin are a bit too tight. Was willing to zip all the way. Very happy with warmth.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2239,'Mike H.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'Puff the magic hoody.','Having loved my Nano Puff Hoody over the past number of years, I thought I should try the new, extra-feathery Micro Puff Hoody. With a few weeks of cold weather active use here in Montana, I\'m liking the Micro Puff more for technical use and the Nano Puff more as my towny puff piece. The Micro Puff uses Pertex which, in my experience, offers a',65,'2020-06-15'),(2240,'Mateo B.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Great windbreaker and insulator','I absolutely love this jacket because it is so versatile. I use it as a light windbreaker on my commute to work or as an insulator underneath my raincoat. This coat is very roomy and mobile so I have no problem wearing a light sweater or hoody underneath. It feels baggy, but looks really clean allowing me to climb with it and wear it to work. The o',65,'2020-06-15'),(2241,'Christian K.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,4.0,'Good Lightweight Puffy','Overall this is a good lightweight insulated layer. The fit and weight are nice, the only negative would be the seams across my shoulders. They are noticeable when wearing a pack. they don\'t hurt, you just notice them...',65,'2020-06-15'),(2242,'Matthew L.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'Hooded Micro Puffy','Very warm and cozy. Runs small. Ordered a mens med t shirt and it is longer and bigger than the mens medium hooded micro puffy.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2243,'Justin Y.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'So light!','This jacket is unbelievably light for how warm it is. I like the fit for how well it layers underneath my shell. Overall it is a great jacket. Simple, light, warm and ultra-packable. I\'m 6\'0, 165 lbs and the medium fits perfect.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2244,'Ted M.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'Toats awesome!','Toats awesome!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2245,'Mark A.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'my second one','I love this jacket. Its so comfortable and disappears as a mid layer on cold days. It fits so well. Slightly delicate tho..',65,'2020-06-15'),(2246,'Thomas M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Good fit','Good fit',65,'2020-06-15'),(2247,'Eric P.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,4.0,'Micro Puff Hoody','Coat fits great with lots of good room for movement. Ample stuff pockets inside are great. Big exterior zip pockets outside have the bottom of the zipper too high to comfortably stuff in my hands on a cold evening; it feels like I’m going to tear the zipper',65,'2020-06-15'),(2248,'LeBigShop',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Worth it','This is one of my favorites. It\'s very light, yet keeps me extremely warm. Also very packable and can be handy when traveling. Overall worth it.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2249,'Matthew A.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'So light! Warm too','Love this jacket. Super light and packable. It has also kept me warm with a midweight layer underneath in temps in the 20s (F). Doesn\'t breath as well as my Nano Air, but I can\'t think of anything else that could be improved. I\'m 5\' 8\" 155 and wear a small. It fits fine over a base and mid layer',65,'2020-06-15'),(2250,'Clarence W.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,3.0,'The zipper is too small','The zipper is too small and its difficult to close',65,'2020-06-15'),(2251,'Santiago G.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XL',NULL,5.0,'Light and Warm','This is an awesome Jacket. Love that they are light yet warm.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2252,'Christopher L.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XXL',NULL,5.0,'feather light','super light, still has plenty of warmth',65,'2020-06-15'),(2253,'Fong T.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Micro Puf Hoody','Great versatile hoody. Perfect for travel.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2254,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Micro puff hoody','Excellent overall. Very warm for the weight. Ver light. Like the fit of thr.hood.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2255,'Ryan',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Love it','Best purchase I have made!!!!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2256,'Michael F.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L/XL',NULL,5.0,'Great','Great',65,'2020-06-15'),(2257,'Philippe D.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'My MicroPuff is never far','My MicroPuff is never far and it\'s always in my bag when I travel. Great product that I can wear almost year round. Typically my first layer after my shell when skiing.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2258,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Micro Puff Hoody','Great product with well thought out fit and finish.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2259,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'great jacket','great jacket',65,'2020-06-15'),(2260,'Antonio Y.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Super light and warm','Everything I expected!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2261,'Jeffrey P.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'They fixed the sizing','Super happy with my new Mirco. I had the original season version, but the new color had me stoked. Was even happier to find out that they slimmed it out and streamlined it a bit. The old one was a touch loose.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2262,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'It’s perfect!','Love the warmth and weight. The hood is an excellent addition and adds to the versatility. I also love the interior large pockets. Thanks for making awesome gear!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2263,'Don C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M/L',NULL,5.0,'Micro Puff','Beautiful product',65,'2020-06-15'),(2264,'Burton M.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,4.0,'Very nice','A lightweight, comfortable jacket. One issue - when partially unzipped, the collar annoyingly rubs against the chin/neck.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2265,'Chad W.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Lightweight and warm','Great for most adventures in the cold or brisk weather, can be great used on its own but with a shell in the rain to keep in the heat.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2266,'Jim M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Would buy for my whole','Would buy for my whole family if it was permissable',65,'2020-06-15'),(2267,'Dave D.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Love it!','The hood makes it! The feel is light and comfortable.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2268,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'nice!','nice!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2269,'Adam B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Great jacket. Love the fit','Great jacket. Love the fit and warmth. The under-the-helmet hood design isn\'t my favorite, but it is certainly not a deal breaker. If you don\'t absolutely need the hood, especially knowing the tight fit, I would recommend the jacket version. Otherwise a great jacket.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2270,'Andrew C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great all-around insulation layer','This jacket is wonderful; it has been great for everything I do, from work to play. The only jacket I own which surpasses this new micro puff in warmth, comfort, and versatility is my old Patagonia down jacket. I have always worried about the durability of my beloved puffy, but have never torn it (I\'m highly neurotic about this) and it has nev',65,'2020-06-15'),(2271,'Jason V.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','NB-7lb',NULL,5.0,'Warm, Long, and stretchy','As a taller individual it\'s nice to have jackets that come in a decent length. This puff will not disappoint to keep you warm and look pretty cool doin it. it also has just enough stretch to allow full range of motion for any adventure someone may be on.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2272,'Dane B.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,5.0,'Really, really nice!','Home run on the Micro Puff. Big step up on the last generation. Thank you.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2273,'Scott H.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'So far, Awesome!','Obviously time will tell as I have only worn it once in easy conditions. However, first impressions are great and it\'s just like it has been described. Super light, very compressible and looks great. Hopefully, it will be a long term piece for me.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2274,'Matthew L.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'big performance in a small package','Really impressed with the warmth to size ratio of this jacket. A great all-arounder',65,'2020-06-15'),(2275,'Ian S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'warm and functional','Stoked on this hoodie, and loving its warmth',65,'2020-06-15'),(2276,'Ranbir L.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Micro Puff','Jacket fits great. It’s incredibly light weight and warm, I don’t want to take it off. Still have not yet put it to the test in colder weather but I’m confident it will do well.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2277,'Patrick D.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,3.0,'Great jacket, small hood, no waist drawstring','The jacket represents excellent quality, with great design and features. It would otherwise get 5 stars but there are 2 1/2 slight faults.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2278,'Gene H.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Snuggly as ..','It’s so comfortable, light & packable. I can’t wait for winter temps',65,'2020-06-15'),(2279,'Tim P.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Super lite and warm','Love this Micro Puff Hoody! It weighs nothing, incredibly warm and compacts into a pocket making it easy to travel with. The hood fits nice and snug without restraining peripheral vision like some hoods. I wear this piece from fishing, camping, everyday life and don’t hesitate to wear it out on the town as well.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2280,'Joseph C.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Float like a butterfly, sting like a bee','I am very happy with my micropuff hoody. The jacket is a lightweight, packable and warm. However it wouldn\'t be the first jacket i reach for when temperatures get below 20 degrees or so. A great early season and lightweight summer trips',65,'2020-06-15'),(2281,'Jay S.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket. Light and warm','This is a very simple jacket but is light and warm. It is versatile so it can be worn as a main outer jacket or a mid layer under a shell.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2282,'Jim M.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Versatile piece of outerwear','Hand down the best jacket I\'ve ever bought from Patagonia!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2283,'Scott J.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,4.0,'Good overall; tight hood','Good fit overall. A bit baggy across the front of the shoulders. Also when the zipper is all the way up the opening of the hood is a bit tight; a simple shock cord and cord lock system would have been better here for me.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2284,'Brendan C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Perfect Lightweight Jacket','I love it! Only been wearing this new jacket a week now, but it\'s great. Pockets feel a little high, but maybe I should have bought a size larger. I\'m 5\'10\" in a medium. The snug fitting hood is amazing and my first one like this.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2285,'Andrew B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,5.0,'All around wicked','Even lighter than I expected. Super comfy and versatile. The hood on the small is a bit smaller than id like, but i can work around it!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2286,'Mark S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Micro puff','Always satisfied with patagonia products! Haven’t been able to use my new jacket to it’s full extent yet but when the snow falls I know I’ll have confidence in my new micro puff. Thanks Patagonia for such great gear!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2287,'Sebastien M.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Looking good and comfy','Walking to the crag in the morning cold, or belaying in the shade during Fall, this hoody will be your best friend. When the sun gets warmer, the Hoody is so light you won’t feel its weight on your backpack.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2288,'Bret G.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great Puffy','I am 5\'10\'\' 150 lbs and the size M fit me perfectly. Have worn this jacket a ton since purchasing it and am continually amazed by how warm 