s down into a coffee can size and put it into a pack. I was not going to store the jacket into its own pocket, and put it into a suitcase. I was going to wear it to my daughters hockey game and while going to pick out a Christmas tree. This jacket was too thin fo',65,'2020-06-15'),(2298,'Thomas F.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XXL',NULL,4.0,'Nice jacket','Love the look, color and it fits great through my shoulders and arms, tight on my belly, but I\'ve been laid up for 6 months with two knee surgeries so once I lose that, it should fit right on for an XXL.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2299,'Steve H.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,4.0,'Beautiful coat','A delight to wear and look out - a design masterpiece. 4 stars because I find the outside pockets to be a bit high to comfortably rest my hands in, and it\'s not as warm as I expected. That said, it\'s been my go to coat for the unusually cool fall in the PNW this year since I opened the package. One question - what is the extra placket or',65,'2020-06-15'),(2300,'Marcel G.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,4.0,'Good Fit','Good fit, and nice layer. A little tight throughout the back.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2301,'MJPittman',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,5.0,'Ultralight & Activity Neutral Insulator','I have replaced my Nano Air and Nano Puff with the Micro Puff Hoody. Adept at any application (backcountry touring, fly fishing, hiking, camping, every day jacket) this jacket is an easy insulation piece to throw in your kit. High\'s: super lightweight, water resistant, wind resistant, fit/finish, simplicity, packability. Low\'s: breathabil',65,'2020-06-15'),(2302,'Jeremy H.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Finally got some puff!','After years of seeing them around I finally have my own light-weight, easy to wear, attractive Micro-Puff jacket. So far so good, fits in everywhere from the trails to dropping the kids off at school, Thanks for a great product Patagonia!!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2303,'Thomas D.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,5.0,'Awesome lightweight products','Awesome lightweight products',65,'2020-06-15'),(2304,'Gary H.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Great Purchase','Great fit and addition to my outdoor gear. Warm comfortable and packable. It will get the true test in Finland next month .',65,'2020-06-15'),(2305,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Awesome','This is an amazingly warm and light jacket',65,'2020-06-15'),(2306,'Matt A.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket - highly recommend','I\'ve had a nanopuff for almost a decade and decided it was time for something new. I wavered back n forth between the micro puff and the nano puff. Went micropuff and glad I did. Haven\'t had it in any extreme cold yet, but it\'s kept me too warm and should be perfect for cold days snowboarding or touring, and should pack down nice n s',65,'2020-06-15'),(2307,'Daniel W.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great quality work. Come on','Great quality work. Come on snow!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2308,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Micro Puff Hoody','I love the jacket, but my second day wearing it it got a little snag in the sleeve where the fill started coming out. I may return to get repaired or replaced. I love the jacket though.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2309,'Jacob H.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,5.0,'Unbelievable','So light. So warm. So comfortable. Wearing this jacket is unreal in almost every condition. I\'ve never owned anything so practical.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2310,'Sean M.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Tight and light','Feels good.. You know the drill...',65,'2020-06-15'),(2311,'Mary M.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'the micro puff hoody is a where everywhere, all the time , piece of clothing','I purchased a micro puff hoody for myself last year. I found that I wore it all year round...biking, skiing, backpacking and around town in all seasons. I loved it so much that I purchased one for my daughter and one for my partner. We all love this hoody.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2312,'Andrew J.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L/XL',NULL,5.0,'Light weight and the warmest','Light weight and the warmest puffy I have ever worn',65,'2020-06-15'),(2313,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Love it!','I really like my Men\'s Micro Puff Hoody, and I am looking forward to putting it to the test in the upcoming Montana winter!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2314,'Jan S.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Excellent product','I got this for my husband as an anniversary gift. He\'d suffered from Nano-puff envy ever since I got my hoody several years ago. I debated between nano and micro, and based on reviews, got the micro. He absolutely loves his jacket. No more nano-envy.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2315,'Robin H.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XS',NULL,5.0,'Light, packable, toasty, good piece.','It is pretty awesome to realize that you forgot that this jacket was stuffed in your pack and you have something warm to keep off the sudden cold mist that the Sierra has decided to do in place of actual rain.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2316,'Peter S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Best lightweight insulation ever','I spend a lot of time on the water and the micro puff hoody is my go-to lightweight hydrophobic insulation. Fits true to size and super warmth to weight. Packs down to nothing as well.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2317,'Alex G.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'great purchase','the warmth to weight ratio is incredible. it works perfect to wear around casually but also comfortably and durable enough to wear climbing, skiing, camping, etc.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2318,'Rick L.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Excellent garment for layering','Lightweight, roomy, comfortable and stylish. I have a pullover that I wear exclusively for salmon and steelhead fishing. I intend to wear the full zip I have just purchased for every day activities.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2319,'abel m.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Fits great, and super warm!','Fits great, and super warm!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2320,'Lewis C.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Perfect?','I hate that word-- perfect. It\'s always hyperbole. But I do love this jacket. I broke the jacket in during a week-long trip in the Rockies. The weather was true mountain weather, fickle. Each day (except for the second day, which was beautiful) we experienced near nonstop 15-minute cycles alternating between sun, clouds, wind, rain, hail, ligh',65,'2020-06-15'),(2321,'Christopher Y.',NULL,'None','ML',NULL,5.0,'Lighter than air','What a wonderful garment. So light. So warm. Great color. Fits great. Patagonia is a leader in providing items that last a long time. I expect this one will too.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2322,'Paul S.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Great mid-warmth synthetic down','Has some updates compared to the Nano puff. Handles water relatively well for a \"down\" jacket. Bonus that it is made from recycled materials!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2323,'CAPT (.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Not yet tested, but initial thoughts','Waiting until it went on sale, I was limited to the color choice, and I actually like the Tasmanian Teal...it is closer to a medium spruce green. I bought it for my re-attempt at an AT thru hike next year. Initial thoughts? It is super light—-high quality construction. Whether it will keep me warm - even wet? Still up for discussion....but the qual',65,'2020-06-15'),(2324,'Larry T.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Love This Hoody','I’ve owned Nanopuffs and down clothing, but this one is a favorite. Remarkably warm for its weight, packs small and water resistant so it goes with me everywhere from town to trail. Yes, the face fabric is thin but it appears to be very durable for my purposes plus it would be a tremendous mid-layer. I’m 190/6’ and the large fit me best. This is th',65,'2020-06-15'),(2325,'Jerry C.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Puff jacket','This jacket is so lightweight and comfortable you hardly know you have it on and it dries out fast if you get rained on.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2326,'Rob',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,4.0,'Color \"Carbon\" is misleading and does not show properly on Patagonia Website','The color \"carbon\" is not a black, but a medium green color.... Even at the Patagonia store, when they looked at the image on the website, it appears much darker, like a shade of black (which is the true \"color\" for carbon). Had to swap it out at the store.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2327,'Ben M.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XS',NULL,4.0,'Great jacket but the threads came loose very quickly','I love this jacket and use it a lot, but I\'m concerned because the stitching around the outside of the jacket (the stitches that give it that \"puff\" look) started coming loose within a couple weeks of purchase. For the money we pay, this should happen. Plus, I\'m concerned about releasing errant microfibers into the environment!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2328,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Micro Puff','Lightest jacket I\'ve ever owned and super super warm. I own both this and the nano hoody, and this is easily my favorite of the two. Packs down small. Will go on every trip I take. Love it.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2329,'Sean K.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'I\'d try it on before ordering','It\'s a wonderful jacket. So warm, so light. It\'s gorgeous. I returned mine, though, because the fit in pretty unusual. Very long in the torso, so much so that it covered my whole butt, with an odd amount of bicep space. If you\'re basing your sizing off the Nano Puff, like I did, you\'re gonna have a bad time. I would very much re',65,'2020-06-15'),(2330,'Todd G.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,3.0,'Micro Puff® Hoody','This jacket is a versatile and light option to keep in your jacket quiver. It compresses down really small and is super light. It provides lots of warmth when you need it, especially with the hood. I recommend it for people looking to keep their packs light on the trail or for everyday use. 5 stars',65,'2020-06-15'),(2331,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Great jacket','This jacket is extremely versatile. I switched from the nanopuff which the outer material fell apart. This jacket works great as a layer or on its own.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2332,'Kyle S.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'My favorite puffy','I have been through a half dozen or so puffy jackets. From Mammut, Arc Teryx, and other industry-leading brands. This is hands downs my favorite. SUPER warm, SUPER light, and easily packable. The first day I received this jacket, it was about 35º F out and overcast. I threw this jacket on with just a t shirt on under. I was blown away by how warm i',65,'2020-06-15'),(2333,'Ian',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Great warmth to weight','Bought this as a replacement to my old down sweater (not a size medium anymore...) and couldn\'t be happier. Have used this as an insulating later on a W trek trip to Torres del Paine, for kicking it around camp and as a post-surf jacket over the winter. The warmth to weight is excellent and it packs down nice and small for transport. The quilt',65,'2020-06-15'),(2334,'Stu K.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'M-Puff Surprise!','Well, I finally bought the Micro Puff Hoody, in spite of my suspicions about its warmth and innovativeness being overstated by Patagonia. In my opinion, it would have had to meet or exceed the gen1 Nano Air Hoody, which I’ve been using, principally, as an intermediate insulation layer in the mountains, and a casual shoulder season jacket around tow',65,'2020-06-15'),(2335,'Thomas W.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Perfection is when there is nothing left to take away','I ordered one of these jackets in the Fall and returned it unworn. I was convinced that it was too light to be really useful. Was I ever wrong!. While it\'s not a replacement for a heavy parka or jacket this is perfect for ski touring. I can wear a super light layer (i.e. Nano-Air Light Hybrid Hoody) for the uphill and then add this jacket unde',65,'2020-06-15'),(2336,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great Jacket','The temps are still cold in this part of Colorado at night and this hooded jacket has exceeded expectations.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2337,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Micro Puff','I\'ve been a full time, year round river fishing guides in west Michigan for over 2 decades and RELY on my apparel and equipment for guide trips.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2338,'Rich P.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Love this micro puff hoodie','Fits like I hoped it would and is very warm and I can move freely in it. If there’s one change I could make is that when pulling up the sleeves to wash my hands, they are tight on my forearms, preventing the sleeves from moving up my arm much. This happens with other brand clothing as well. Maybe I have large forearms. That’s the only improvement I',65,'2020-06-15'),(2339,'Mike Q.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Best puffy yet....','super light and warm, awesome jacket',65,'2020-06-15'),(2340,'Ed G.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Jacket M\'s Microsoft Hoody','Jacket is light and comfortable. It was past the cold months in Central New York and can\'t wait to see how it holds up in Winter. As a new Patagonia dealer, I want to use the products we sell and feel I can recommend this product to customers with ease.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2341,'Chris T.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Ideal thin puffy layer','This thing is delicate, as one might expect. Other than that, it\'s hard to find a fault in this jacket. It\'s very functional, and there isn\'t anything that I would change about it. It has nice drop-in pockets on the inside, which is something often skipped for reducing weight. This is a great place to stash gloves or flexible water f',65,'2020-06-15'),(2342,'Peter D.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Most Versatile Jacket','I\'ve had this jacket for a couple months now and highly recommend it. It\'s been an extremely versatile jacket and able to insulate, regulate, and keep me dry throughout the spring weather in Colorado, Utah, and the Midwest.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2343,'Jake D.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Believe the hype','I have a bunch of Patagonia insulated jackets so I wasn’t really in the market to buy a new one. But with all the reviews and write up I’d read I thought let try one out. Well this is an amazing jacket. It’s light, packable and so far so good on durability. Great design once again from Patagonia',65,'2020-06-15'),(2344,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Micro Puff','I have been using the evolving light synthetic insulation jackets for many years from Patagonia. The micro puff is the next great piece of insulation! Very light and warm enough for a broad range of temps. The inside pockets are great for storage and the hood provides that extra warmth when the wind is unrelenting. Well done.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2345,'Hugh R.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Mens Micro Puff Hoody','This is the best piece of insulation I have ever gotten from Patagonia. the weight to warmth ratio and compressibility make it my number one piece of clothing that goes in my pack on every trip!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2346,'Ryan M.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Very quality product, I hope','Very quality product, I hope to use it on trips for years to come.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2347,'Gavin W.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great all around jacket','This Jacket has already traveled across the US and to a few foreign countries with me. I love that it can be packed up really small and is comfortable in really cool for just cool temperatures. Keeps you dry and drys fast with great breathability.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2348,'bradley',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'Warm but fragile','Used this jacket for a few weeks and enjoyed it\'s warmth to weight but it was too fragile for me. It would be cool to see the nano puff with this type of insulation inside of it, or simply a beefed up version of the micro puff. I loved the red with blue zipper colorway that the woman\'s version had, would be cool to see more two tone color',65,'2020-06-15'),(2349,'Lee M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,4.0,'Why such a limited hood?','I\'m probably only one of a few people to hold this belief, the hood on this jacket is too technical and singularly purposed. Why does it have to be this snug? I like to wear a baseball cap when I backpack and I cannot wear this hood over a cap without it looking like a conehead. I want a coat than can transition from the climbing wall, to the',65,'2020-06-15'),(2350,'Theodore K.',NULL,'5\'1 - 5\'3','S',NULL,5.0,'Terrific Jacket','At the writing of this review, I\'ve worn this jacket almost every day from November 2018 to mid-April 2019. I wore it on a two-week trek to Kangchenjunga, a week-long trek in the Solu Khumbu, downhill skiing and backcountry skiing in Jackson Hole, and on a ten-day trip to the Lyngen Alps in Norway. It\'s incredibly light and versatile. It',65,'2020-06-15'),(2351,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Best light weight jacket Patagonia has ever made!','I love the light weight material that this jacket is made out of! It\'s perfect for climbing, ski mountaineering and as a light \'back-up\' jacket for days when you think you might not need a jacket but it\'s worth bringing this one because it\'s so light. Nice work Patagonia!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2352,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Best light weight jacket Patagonia has ever made!','I love the light weight material that this jacket is made out of! It\'s perfect for climbing, ski mountaineering and as a light \'back-up\' jacket for days when you think you might not need a jacket but it\'s worth bringing this one because it\'s so light. Nice work Patagonia!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2353,'Matthew F.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','None',NULL,3.0,'Great jacket with bad zipper','Zipper always gets caught in fabric. Now zipper failing completely. Patagonia customer service is great and totally stand by product. White material comes out of seams. Never once thought about a zipper until I owned this jacket.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2354,'Rick C.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,5.0,'Micro Puff Hoody does the job','Bought this as an insulation layer underneath a ski jacket for those cold, windy days on the chair lift; and it kept me wonderfully warm.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2355,'Brent M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'The absolute best','After I first put this jacket on this piece became a go to in my gear. It’s incredibly versatile and fits great.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2356,'Glen H.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,3.0,'A Little Disappointed but still a great jacket for certain applications','Although this jacket might be great for certain applications.... the shell fabric was just too delicate. It seemed to pick and tear with ease. I really loved the weight and insulation, fit etc... but Patagonia needs to beef up the shell to be more durable. I would be willing to accept a little more weight compromise for increased durability. For th',65,'2020-06-15'),(2357,'Luke',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Absolute favorite','This jacket by far is my go to. I own several nano puffs and down sweaters and this out performs both of them! I use it biking in the winter and the hood fits great under my bike helmet and I also have the non-hooded version for a layer as my snowboard gear. Super lightweight and warm. I will say that nano puff and down sweater are warmer than this',65,'2020-06-15'),(2358,'Steve',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,1.0,'So close, yet so far','Boy, I really really wanted this to work out! This is the only Patagonia product I\'ve ever returned.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2359,'Phong B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,4.0,'Lightest thing ever.','I used to not care about weight. However, after wearing this in a few days I can\'t stop wearing it. Other jacker feels less comfortable. It\'s not the warmest jacket but it\'s warm for what it is. I don\'t have to look like I\'m wearing a big down jacket and more casual. One thing I don\'t like about it is the elastic hem.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2360,'James L.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Deceptively Warm but breathable','I have been using this product most every day this winter in temperatures in the teens & low 20’s, up to the mid 30’s using only a light merino base layer. Even in breezy conditions, I have always been warm and have experienced no moisture problems. This has become my favorite all-around jacket, ultralite & well-made.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2361,'Brett O.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Wow, just Wow!','I don\'t write many review but always look to them for help on deciding if I would buy something or not; YES, I am that person.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2362,'Nick D.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,5.0,'super warm and versatile','great coat overall. Factoring in the weight, it is the best down coat I own. Perfect for cold weather skiing and climbing. very comfortable and high quality materials. I bring it instead of my arcteryx atom lt on camping and ski trips where I cannot bring extra layers because of the increased warmth and versatility. one significant issue I have wit',65,'2020-06-15'),(2363,'Bill',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'How jackets compare','I have a bunch of Patagonia jackets. This is how this one fits in.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2364,'James O.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,1.0,'great insulation, total fail on the fit and drape','The insulation is indeed super light and quite warm, not there with the best down but getting close. The fit of the garment is awful, like Patagonia rushed it to market without sufficient testing. the arm hole opening and the bicep circumference is too small for the size (L). The hood comes down too far on the forehead, there is a huge bunch of loo',65,'2020-06-15'),(2365,'Chris',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','XS',NULL,5.0,'This Jacket lives up to the hype','I bought this jacket because it fit me better than the ultralight down jackets I already own and I like the flexibility that a synthetic gives me in the wet. I was a bit skeptical though based on the reviews I’ve read online. Many of these reviews claim that it doesn’t offer the warmth of down. I guess it depends on how extreme an environment you e',65,'2020-06-15'),(2366,'Jim M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Deceptively Good','I can only speak for myself, but this jacket is surprisingly good. After SO much hype, and having read a lot of negative reviews, I decided to spring for it anyway, and I am not disappointed. Anyone in Utah knows this has been a rougher winter than others in recent memory, and as I student I do quite a bit of walking outside in the 20\'s withou',65,'2020-06-15'),(2367,'Jake M.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,2.0,'Very disappointed','I bought from Landfall, a sailing shop in Connecticut. I have had the jacket for 4 days. I have a rip on the bottom part of the jacket already. For something I paid good money for I’m very upset that it has ripped that easily. I also have multiple threats already coming out. Like I said I have only worn this jacket probably 5 times. On the upside i',65,'2020-06-15'),(2368,'Quinn',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Genuinely lives up to the hype','I had a micro-puff hoody from 2012 that was my go-to winter insulation layer. I read all the reviews when the new one came out and wasn\'t quite convinced - it couldn\'t really be that much better, could it? It is. It definitely is.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2369,'Boris D.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,4.0,'Light','Hoody has many advantages, but has few imperfections. First - stiff zipper line, if you close it and move a little, zipper may arch like a hump, and hoody look not good :) If you wear hood, shoulders of hoody go up in neck area and look strange.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2370,'Ronan S.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Fantastic','Recently got my micropuff hoody. I\'ve used it for hiking and general about town wear so far. Fantastic construction quality and amazing warmth from something that barely weighs anything!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2371,'Chris',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Perfect for winter hiking/backpacking','I’ve tested this jacket this winter in Alaska. I’ve worn it down to 15 degrees and it’s all you need if you’re hiking, if you planned to be stationary in weather 20 and below I’d recommend another layer but if you’re active it’s warm. Materials are very light and delicate, so I only recommend as a technical backcountry piece and not a daily wear ar',65,'2020-06-15'),(2372,'Noah',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'game changer','It\'s incredibly light -- I think I have t-shirts heavier than this. It remind me of my very first gore-tex jacket 30 years ago -- in that it\'s like nothing I\'ve worn before -- a total game changer.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2373,'Edward M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Really AMAZING!','So Forge Grey is more of a darker grey than silver. In some of the YT vids it looked more silver. The Patagonia photo is pretty accurate. It\'s not as shiny as I thought it would be either, shiny, but more matte looking than wet looking. It\'s what I wanted. PERFECT. I\'m 6\'3\" and 225 pounds and XL fits great. If I ever get wi',65,'2020-06-15'),(2374,'Aq',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,5.0,'Super lightweight and warm','Thin and extremely lightweight yet warm enough to wear with just a t-shirt down to low 40s. It\'s water repellent but during heavy rain feels damp underneath. The cuffs are not water repellent and it\'s a little annoying they stay wet (like when washing hands) for a little while. It\'s expensive but very high quality workmanship and mat',65,'2020-06-15'),(2375,'Gc3000',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Good ultralight synthetic insulation layer','I bought the Micro Puff when it was first released and have used it for one year. 5\'10\", 155 lbs athletic build, and as with all Patagonia stuff the size M is right on. I needed an ultralight synthetic insulation jacket for ski touring, hunting, and campus in Western Montana. That\'s what I got. This jacket is minimalist in concept, a',65,'2020-06-15'),(2376,'Pablo H.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Best Winter Jacket Ever','Usually I do not spend too much money on clothing but I took a risk and decided to buy this. I can not even describe how comfortable, stylish and warmth it is! I love it! High quality product as always Patagonia. Thank you!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2377,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Best jacket I’ve bought','This jacket is so packable and easy to take anywhere it’s ridiculous. I’ve used it in New Zealand’s South Island winters and steamboat springs Colorado skiing and hiking and it’s perfect. Fits me good I’m 5’9 and have a M.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2378,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Perfect coat','I purchased this coat for my 24 year old son. He loves it! He is 5\'10 tall and weighs around 160 lbs. He normally wears a size medium. This coat fits him perfectly, the snugness around the waist and wrists is not constricting , he can move easily. He said that the coat holds the heat because of the snug fit at the waist and wrists. No cold air',65,'2020-06-15'),(2379,'Dan S.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Awesome, just Awesome','Strangest material, so light yet so warm. The jacket outperforms my others with twice the loft/thickness in both breathability and warmth.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2380,'Ron',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,3.0,'Strange Fit.','I own 3 Patagonia Jackets, all size XL and love them all. Had to return this Jacket because the sleeves were too tight, Tried an XXL and had the same problem. Too bad because if the Jacket had fit properly it would be a great Jacket.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2381,'Anthony',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,1.0,'The worst patagonia jacket i have ever owned','Sorry patagonia I love my other jackets but this one is trash. I have numerous holes from just casual wear and the synthetic material leaks out at the seams. I\'ve had to bring this in 2 times to my local store where I have been offered tape each time. I never take this jacket backpacking because it is way to delicate. Please resolve this probl',65,'2020-06-15'),(2382,'Robert L.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,3.0,'Technically good but not that useful in reality','While the insulation has promise this jacket is really too light and delicate for an outer layer and quite expensive for a mid layer. Not very practical. Matter of opinion if you like the look of the shiny thin fabric, but there are better options for more useful jackets. Also, the fit is too loose through the body for an active piece.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2383,'Brandiggity',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Whoa','Ive had this jacket for about a month. Its unbelievable. So light it doesnt feel like im wearing anything. Ive been in 20 degree windy weather with only a button down and an undershirt underneath and couldnt feel anything. The fact that the elastic bottom part isn’t adjustable is the only thing id complain about but the jacket is so awesome its sti',65,'2020-06-15'),(2384,'Steelhead A.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,4.0,'Not quite perfect but pretty good','I bought this as a lightweight high comfort cold weather shell for east coast winters as well as a comfortable warm layer under goretex for northwest winter flyfishing. I have only thus far tested it in the former, but am confident it will be fine for the latter provided it can resist conductive heat loss around the shoulders which as others have m',65,'2020-06-15'),(2385,'Matt N.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,3.0,'So close to right.','I love how thin this hoody is and yet still so warm. I handle the cold very well and have already been in the teens in this jacket with only a t-shirt underneath and I would have kept me warm except for the lack of drawcord at the hem. I live in Wyoming and the wind just comes right up the underside. Total deal breaker. If it had a draw cord I coul',65,'2020-06-15'),(2386,'Joel',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,3.0,'Lots of potential','I really liked some aspects of the jackets (e.g. lightweight), but ultimately returned it for a few reasons. 1.) Didn\'t feel any warmer than my Nano Puff jacket - in fact, it felt colder in spots (esp. the shoulders). 2.) Didn\'t care for the lack of a chest pocket. 3.) Hand pocket zippers sit too high. 4.) Lack of a draw cord for the bott',65,'2020-06-15'),(2387,'Frank',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XXL',NULL,1.0,'Horrible Fit','The fit of this jack is awful. You cannot raise your arms at all. The way the area near the armpits are cut somehow prevents you from raising your arms without pulling up the entire jacket. And I\'m not talking about raising your arms to the ceiling, I\'m talking about raising them enough to be level with your chest. How could Patagonia mak',65,'2020-06-15'),(2388,'John W.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,4.0,'Almost perfect - still a keeper','Really a breakthrough garment. Featherweight. Superlight fabric so perhaps a bit fragile. There are burlier jackets in the line if you desire. I guess I\'m old school, 6\' tall (like the model) but I got a XL and it\'s just right. I have long arms and like them loose I guess. Two complaints. It needs a chest pocket(s), preferably inside',65,'2020-06-15'),(2389,'Rich F.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,4.0,'Perfect, lightweight, warm.','I would have given 5 stars but the pockets are too high. Picky on my part, but for 299 dollars I want perfection. It weighs so little, yet is so warm. I live in Maine and we already have had cold nights. It stands up well to low temps. The hood is perfect for having a helmet over it.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2390,'Steve G.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Best insulated jacket I\'ve ever owned','I replaced my 2008 down sweater with this jacket. The down sweater was handed down to my father. By far the best jacket for cold temps I\'ve ever owned.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2391,'Wilson',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,2.0,'Possibly the best synthetic insulation ever...EXCEPT','This jacket is incredible. I love everything about it. I\'ve owned several versions of the Nano Puff and was psyched on the new Plumafill insulation. But I\'m sending it back. The non-adjustable elastic waist band is too tight. Anytime I lift my arms above my shoulders the waist band slides up and bunches up under my rib cage and stays ther',65,'2020-06-15'),(2392,'Juan A.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,1.0,'Too delicate to be of any use.','I wanted to wait until I had tested this piece on a winter mountain environment. After all, that what I got it for, and where some reviews had described it was meant to shine. However, my experience is that this garment is too delicate for any use, with the filling coming out of the stitches.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2393,'The M.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'more nano than a nano ?.?.? Pico Puff?','So far very impressed by the weight, feels like nothing on, fluff factor feels indistinguishable to the touch than down, this is better than the encapsil down (which never made it into a real lightweight jacket other than a special edition down sweater), and may just be the major step in companies moving away from down altogether, since there’s no ',65,'2020-06-15'),(2394,'Ian.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,1.0,'Don\'t waste your money....','After thoroughly testing all jackets in this category for this current season. As a comparison to any other, this jacket is extremely poor quality. The overall craftsmanship is very cheap feel. complete amateur sewing. Lacking quality control. For the actual product that\'s delivered it is extremely overpriced!! Just food for thought Patagonia',65,'2020-06-15'),(2395,'Mpls',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Warm and lightweight','I recently took this jacket with me on a bikepacking trip through Kyrgyzstan. It was excellent. It is warm and easily packable. When packed it is not quite as compact as a down jacket. However, the peace of mind that it will stay warm when wet, unlike down, is well worth the slight increase in bulk, especially when traveling through an area where m',65,'2020-06-15'),(2396,'John',NULL,'6\'7 or above','L',NULL,4.0,'question','will this jacket be available in a hoodless pullover, similar to the nano puff?',65,'2020-06-15'),(2397,'Ryan',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,4.0,'Cut is strange (for me)','Love the concept, but sadly returned mine because of fit issues. The L is a tad too tight in shoulders and upper arms, the XL too blousy through torso and too long down my body. Hoping Patagonia changes the fit on the next version because I\'d love one of these in my pack.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2398,'Rod K.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Perhaps my favorite piece of Patagonia gear ever','After nearly 40 years of wearing Patagonia clothing,this piece stands out. It is simply superb. Wearing it is akin to being enveloped by a temperate cloud. It is extremely comfortable,almost not there. Great for extended wear. I find it suited to a wide range of temps and activities,seemingly always just right. Put it on and forget it,which I think',65,'2020-06-15'),(2399,'Guido W.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,4.0,'Love it but...','I purchased the jacket 2 month ago and I have been wearing it in San Francisco and on a few hiking trips. In my experience it works very well when the temperature is below 50 F (10 C). Above that temperature I sweat a lot on my forearms. I love the lightness of the jacket and that it packs very small. I have also noticed small fibers of down coming',65,'2020-06-15'),(2400,'Willie',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,4.0,'Almost perfect!','Aside from the janky thrift store zipper and boxy fit,I love this jacket and I wear it all the time hiking,backpacking,skiing,naturalist work and go-to midlayer in cool weather. Better than expected wind resistance. Extremely comfortable,I hardly notice it. There\'s no reason to not have this jacket in your pack - it weighs nothing and compress',65,'2020-06-15'),(2401,'Lue L.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XL',NULL,5.0,'Excellent Jacket','Bought this 2 days ago. Tried it on and was amazed how warm it was for the weight. This jacket will be perfect for Montana spring and fall. It fits so perfect and unlike my other Patagonia jackets this one has plenty of room in the shoulders. It will be perfect for fly fishing. Patagonia nailed it with this one! If I had the cash I would get a seco',65,'2020-06-15'),(2402,'CraigAFrey',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Amazing Jacket!!','This is my sons review and on the strength of opinion got one for my self. Worn mine every day. Very warm when used as an insulated layer,better than down,when used like this. Can\'t wear anything over it unless it\'s sub 5deg. Great when it gets funky,machine wash,quick dry. So practical. Also works as wind blocker when cycling,but also br',65,'2020-06-15'),(2403,'John M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Windproof & Warm!','I\'ve used this hoody every day for 6 weeks,the thing is extremely versatile whether you wear it as an indoor sweater or on cold,windy outdoor 6-mile dogwalks. I\'m 5-11/160 pounds,the Medium fits with enough room for 2 layers underneath. It\'s not the least bit stretchy (not a NanoAir),but it doesn\'t have to be \' the \"Re',65,'2020-06-15'),(2404,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Great Lightweight Jacket','I received this coat as a Christmas gift,and I really love it. First off this coat is more of a lightweight coat,but it is surprisingly warm. I have worn this coat for two months and have worn it many days in subzero temperatures. On those subzero days I have worn a sweatshirt or quarter zip with a vest with the micro puff as the top layer. I have ',65,'2020-06-15'),(2405,'Ed R.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Great tech evolution,works as advertised,but ...','I bought this Hoody sight unseen in September during the customer advance preview. Since then I\'ve taken it backpacking in Yosemite and the Eastern Sierra. Also all-around everyday use. Amazing piece of gear. Instant warmth as soon as you put it on. Feels great on naked skin when worn with a short sleeve shirt. I\'ve used it with my R1 jac',65,'2020-06-15'),(2406,'Dphill',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'The future','Plumafill is the future of ultralight outdoor products! Would love to see Patagonia make a ultralight plumafill sleeping bag.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2407,'Protector',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Ultralight jacket','Cool ultralight product. It is really warm in around 6C and i dont feel any wind cut through it. Warmer than my old nano puff. The fit is perfect. i am 172cm and wear S. Will buy the jacket version again if there is favorite color',65,'2020-06-15'),(2408,'Castel',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XS',NULL,5.0,'I really love this jacket!','It has convenient warmth,for layering during winter and wearing it as a jacket for the rest of the year.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2409,'SeldomSeenSmith',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Ultra-lightweight,dependable,insulation','I could barely contain my stoke when Patagonia released this piece. An ultra-light synthetic puffy,(more specifically a synthetic puffy that is lighter weight than any other puffy I own) would be a really awesome addition to my kit. While it isn\'t as warm as my beloved ultra-light down hoody,it is more weather resistant and lighter. Here is Ut',65,'2020-06-15'),(2410,'Mike123416846513210',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,1.0,'Fragile','I have many Patagonia products,and love all of them. This jacket looks great and is warm for its weight. If you want a jacket to wear around town this is awesome! However if you want a jacket for any outdoor activity,this is a fragile jacket. It ripped day one.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2411,'Jedininji',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,4.0,'Best synthetic insulation ever!','I was fortunate enough to be able to try the first generation of this product out over the last few months. Overall this is an outstanding product with minor issues that Patagonia surely will resolve.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2412,'Boulder B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,4.0,'Great Jacket,questionable stitching','Bought this jacket a couple months ago,and it is amazingly warm for the size/weight! Packs great,and the hood is great for blowing snow. Only issue I have had is the stitching seems to unravel more than other Patagonia jackets,and I am not sure why. I find myself trimming the loose ends almost daily. Otherwise,a great product that is seemingly stan',65,'2020-06-15'),(2413,'Ephraim',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Why have I been forsaken!','Let me start by saying the 5 star review is based on a feel and squish of the micro puff at a patagonia store yesterday. It\'s a nice jacket - so nice patagonia should just scrap the nano which I have. I went to the shop because my 6 year old micro puff (18 oz with primilaoft fill) zipper died... a noble death and I loved her- but she died.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2414,'Danaco',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,2.0,'Almost great !','I bought this for its light weight to warmth ratio and ability to work while damp or wet as well as having a hood. I am however very disappointed and frustrated with their zipper choice,it\'s far too stiff for how soft and compliant the garment is. The zipper bulges out annoyingly even while standing. I may return this for this issue alone. The',65,'2020-06-15'),(2415,'Dave W.',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,2.0,'Great comfort, unsure on construction','This is one of my favorite jackets to wear, mostly on the way to work, I haven\'t tested it for anything heavy duty yet, but honestly I am worried to. On the third day of owning the jacket I had to put some gear repair tape on the inside of the jacket because I noticed a leake. There\'s also some leaking at seams which I never experience wi',65,'2020-06-15'),(2416,'Hughster65',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'As light as the thought of warmth','I love this jacket. I didn\'t want to take it off the day I received it. It weighs about as much as a plastic garbage bag and keeps you warm without feeling bulky. I\'ve never experienced a better-fitting hood. It has excellent moisture resistance. It looks great on. Granted,I\'ll only be wearing this to brave the howling winds of urban',65,'2020-06-15'),(2417,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Amazing Jacket','After learning what Canada Goose does to animals like geese,wolfs and coyotes I had no choice but to get rid of my CG vest. And wow,was I excited to find this animal-friendly jacket!! It\'s really warm in cold weather,yet you don\'t get overheated (like with dawn jackets) when it\'s 50F+ outside. It looks really good,I mean I got so man',65,'2020-06-15'),(2418,'Jhdr',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Fantastic Jacket','This is a superb jacket which delivers on all that is advertised. The weight to warmth ratio is exceptional. I used this jacket across Europe through the month of November and December. Even in the occasional snow,sleet and sideways rain it kept me warm and dried very quickly. The only negative which seems to be a rarity or defect on my jacket was ',65,'2020-06-15'),(2419,'Andy D.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Total awesomeness!','This is BY FAR the most versatile lightweight insulated jacket in the Patagonia line. I\'ve had it for about 2 months and have literally worn it every day. It is so light weight it works for mild fall days,but also warm enough to perform exceptionally well once winter takes hold. On cool/windy days (between 35-40F) I add a Nano Air vest underne',65,'2020-06-15'),(2420,'Beninak',NULL,'None','M',NULL,3.0,'Nice but not what I expected','This jacket is incredibly light,which is great for packing and comfort while moving around. However,the insulation is very thin and it\'s just not very warm. I\'m comparing it with the previous generation Micro Puff jackets and they were quite a bit warmer (although thicker and heavier). I appreciate the highly efficient insulation they&#x2',65,'2020-06-15'),(2421,'Renato R.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Folding it','Where do u fold to make jacket smaller to travel? It\'s amazing and is love it just got it today for my trip to Nepal but still have to find the way to fold it into a litttel bag',65,'2020-06-15'),(2422,'Chris',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,5.0,'Favorite Patagonia jacket to date','This has become my go to jacket for everything from early morning surf checks to back country hikes and more. Unbelievably light weight and warm with a great fit. I\'m 6\'5\" 230lbs and the XL fits perfectly.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2423,'Dana',NULL,'None','M',NULL,2.0,'Sent mine back','Sometime in the past several years Patagonia started catering to the fashion market. I\'ve noticed it in the cut of several different items.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2424,'Northman',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'My favorite Patagonia piece so far','I\'ve owned a lot of Patagonia stuff over the years,but this one really tops them all. Ultra lightweight and goes with me everywhere,even in the laptop bags on business trips. Soft enough to wear over a t-shirt but cut generously enough that you can wear it over a big fleece-jacket,but not too bulky. It is warm enough to provide that critical h',65,'2020-06-15'),(2425,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Almost perfect','I Just got this jacket a couple weeks ago and have tested it in high 30- low 40-degree weather thus far. I am comfortable with just a t-shirt on under the jacket at these temperatures but any colder and additional layering might be required,my initial impression is that this jacket is not quite as warm as my ultralight down jkt but likely comparabl',65,'2020-06-15'),(2426,'Dave C.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Puffy LOVE','After traveling with my super packable Micro Puff and wearing it on a few early season XC skis,I sold my previously favored Nano Puffs and bought a second color. I like the synthetic fills as no animals need to be sacrificed for my warmth and they work great in our damp Oregon climate. I am 5\'7\",140 pounds and wear a small.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2427,'Brian S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Micro Puff not micro in size','Just like others have mentioned,quality,look,and warmth is top notch. However,I had to return it based on its baggy size. I have mediums in all other Patagonia products including the \"regular size\" nano puff. This fits like one size larger around the torso and arms. Arm length and jacket length are spot on,otherwise,I would say size one d',65,'2020-06-15'),(2428,'Ron M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'So far SO GOOD!','Relatively new piece,but loving the lightweight and warmth. Comfortable down to 44 F with light shirt so far. And not to warm on cool but not cold mornings. By the way,ordered a LARGE and I am 6\'0\" 180 lbs.',65,'2020-06-15'),(2429,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Love it!','This has to be the finest jacket I have ever owned. It wears like a windbreaker,but the warmth is astounding! So light! I also love that it all rolls up into the left pocket. Great job,Patagonia!',65,'2020-06-15'),(2430,'Dad J.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Specialty jacket','This jacket serves a very niche purpose: to be an ultralight,synthetic jacket that still keeps you warm. This is not a down jacket,and the differences you\'re going to get from a synthetic and down should be obvious. No real need to knock it for not living up to your ideas of how a down jacket should perform. Neither is this a hard shell jacket',65,'2020-06-15'),(2431,'Trail M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Best Jacket I have owned','I actually traded in a few Patagonia \"puffies\" to the Wear Worn program to go out and get this one. Best decision ever. Fit is great. Color is sweet (I got the orange). I was a little nervous at how light it was until I took it to the mountains. I had a t-shirt and this and was toasty warm. Others around had large coats,layers,etc and wer',65,'2020-06-15'),(2432,'Tniii',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,4.0,'Micro Puff Hoody Fit Review','Recently received a Men\'s Medium that I ordered. The materials,and finish details looked excellent. Weight,or lack there of was very impressive,but something was just off with the fit. I realized it was Patagonia\'s \"Regular\" fit,but I was hopefully it might be a bit more athletic than some of their other \"Regular\" fit',65,'2020-06-15'),(2433,'I O.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'I am very impressed!','I bought my Micro Puff at the Patagonia Seattle store last weekend while in town for the Coldplay concert. I had searched everywhere for the new Micro-Puff because I wanted to try it on before buying. I thought it might just be a more expensive Nano Puff jacket. While I like the Nano Puff,this jacket is way different. It is lighter,puffier and feel',65,'2020-06-15'),(2434,'Chris B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Love This Jacket','I ordered this jacket two weeks ago and have used it everyday. I took this out the other night to chase the northern lights and it was perfect. Light and comfortable it allowed me to layer under the jacket. The best part is that is is warm and kept me dry during the storms this week. This will easily replace my down jacket and become the new staple',65,'2020-06-15'),(2435,'Ian W.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Super Soft','Perfect fit. Super soft, but not too heavy. On the lighter side of fleeces I\'ve had. Perfect for a cool summer night',40,'2020-06-15'),(2436,'David',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','None',NULL,5.0,'Just Dandy','Would you like to own a cloud? Well now you can! I am 63 and 215 pounds. Purchased a Large and it fits well. If it didnt, Id just return it. But wouldnt review it poorly because it didnt fit my body. Patagonia is not a one size fits all. They try to be, but thats a very hard/challenging task to accomplish.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2437,'Rahni R.',NULL,'5\'0 or less','0',NULL,5.0,'Keeps me warm and toasty','This is one of my favorite items. Keeps me warm in the winter. Definitely a must-have for camping.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2438,'Mark D.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Everyday happiness','I\'m 6\'0\" and 190, and usually somewhere between the fit of a Medium and Large in men\'s fleeces and better sweaters. This one finally nailed it in shoulder width and length (longer torso, and usually need a slim/tailored fit). Can even fit a button up underneath comfortably, to snaz up for a day at the office.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2439,'Ace R.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,4.0,'Great Pullover!','This is a great option for those shorter fellas that don\'t like how the Synchilla Snap T gets baggy on the sleeves. I\'m a 5\'6 guy and the small fits perfectly! 4 stars just cause I\'m not too crazy about the spandex on the waist, other than that it\'s a great piece!!!!',40,'2020-06-15'),(2440,'Estille C.',NULL,'5\'1 - 5\'3','XS',NULL,5.0,'Comfy','Very comfortable and fitting.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2441,'Julie W.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Looks nice, fits nice','I bought this for my boyfriend who is an outdoors guy and it fits perfect. Not too snug, and looks so put together with any outfit, and not to mention, keeps him warm.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2442,'John M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Always comfortable','Just the right weight. These are my favorite. With they were available in lighter colors like feather gray',40,'2020-06-15'),(2443,'Jeanne C.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','3-6m',NULL,1.0,'Not as good fabric that','Not as good fabric that I expected for the money I paid',40,'2020-06-15'),(2444,'Danny R.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Great versatile layer','Great versatile layer',40,'2020-06-15'),(2445,'None',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,1.0,'WAAAYYYY too small','I have a Patagonia down jacket and fleece vest that fit just fine. So I was surprised when I could hardly get this fleece on. Perhaps I was sent a women\'s or children\'d XL?',40,'2020-06-15'),(2446,'Alexander T.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Fits the bill!','Needed a good layering piece as the season cools. I’m a bigger guy - the length and fit on the XXL are perfect.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2447,'Grace T.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket!','I bought this for my fiancé and he loves it! Fits a little baggy on him, but he likes that. Super soft, easy to layer.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2448,'Jessica T.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'A staple item','Bought this for my husband who is a sports medicine doc. He can wear it to work & look professional or after a surf at the beach & be cozy- perfect. He’s 6’1”, wears a size Large in this item.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2449,'Gabrielle M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,1.0,'New material??','I got this thinking it would be just like my synchilla but it is so much thinner and loose at the bottom. It was like a dress that flared at the bottom.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2450,'Mariama C.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'V soft','Bought this for my BF and he loves it! Very soft and a different kind of feel than the usual ones. Very very cute',40,'2020-06-15'),(2451,'Robert C.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,4.0,'A little tight across shoulders','This is a very nice pullover that I want to like a lot. The sizing is a bit \"neat\" across the shoulders for me.... and the bottom a bit too wide. The fabric is fine, exactly what I wanted for Fall. It\'s raining and 48 degrees here in Arkansas today and the product is just great over a light shirt. I\'m not sure that a merchant ca',40,'2020-06-15'),(2452,'Kristina G.',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,5.0,'Great fit and quality. Color','Great fit and quality. Color as pictured.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2453,'Zachary B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,4.0,'Very comfortable','I really dig the color and the materials as it is very comfortable, only critic would be that the fit is a bit more generous than desired. But overall I like the 2 pullovers I purchased.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2454,'Beverly J.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L/XL',NULL,5.0,'Great fabric and colors. I','Great fabric and colors. I bought two of them.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2455,'Doug S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'warm and light','Unlike some of Patagonia\'s other sweaters, this pullover is pleasantly roomy in the forearms and shoulders--more of a classic fit. Warm, soft, and light. A good addition to any climbing pack. Stylish too.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2456,'Zak',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Super cozy fleece for when it\'s not that cold','This fleece is super cozy and soft. Never want to take it off. Love the wacky colorways. Warm for me in the 50s with just a t-shirt. Definitely has a baggier fit like most other Patagonia casual clothing.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2457,'John L.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'The perfect cool weather pullover','This has become my go to layer for cool and damp days here in early fall in Maine. The only thing I’m not crazy about is the waist. It would be better without the spandex trip - I think this has been updated in the new design.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2458,'Karol K.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Warm, good looking and comfy.','Warm, good looking and comfy.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2459,'Kevin Y.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Great lightweight pullover','I’ve been wanting the lightweight pullover for some time. It’s very comfortable and perfect for fall mornings or all day wear on cool days. Can layer without an issue as well.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2460,'David',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Snazzy Snap-T','This is a great fitting, feeling, and looking pullover! Perfect weight and thickness (thinness!) for summer nights and fall days; cozy around the house and office too. I’d like to have a dozen of these in different colors!',40,'2020-06-15'),(2461,'Aaron G.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Tufff and good looking','Tufff and good looking',40,'2020-06-15'),(2462,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Just what I needed!','Jacket is perfect for spring and fall. Easy to throw on and off as the temperature changes. Only thing that prevented 5 stars is that I’m stuck between the medium and the large on fit.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2463,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','ML',NULL,5.0,'Perfect for layering!','Love this pullover. It is soft and warm, but lightweight. Perfect for cool weather with a T-shirt or for cold temps paired with a thermal of sweater. Would definitely buy again!',40,'2020-06-15'),(2464,'Teddy W.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XXL',NULL,5.0,'I like the high collar','I like the high collar and fit of the body. Perfect lightweight fleece for the early mornings on the coast.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2465,'Burke M.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','NB-7lb',NULL,5.0,'Perfect Warmer Weather Fleece','I have had a lightweight synchilla fleece for a few years and have frequently thought, I wish this was a bit lighter weight. Along comes this MicroD Fleece and its exactly what i wanted for spring/fall/cooler summer days, or for airport commuting where the thicker fleece would have me sweating. Great fleece!',40,'2020-06-15'),(2466,'James A.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'comfortable and warm','The material is great. It\'s really soft and comfortable. It\'s great for fall weather',40,'2020-06-15'),(2467,'Michael G.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,3.0,'Like the style. Find them','Like the style. Find them hard to on and off. They bind any undergarment.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2468,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','ML',NULL,4.0,'Sheds a bit, otherwise very cozy!','I’m usually between a men’s M and L so I got the L because I tend to like my sweaters bigger. Fits perfectly, with a bit of room for comfort! Very soft, very cozy, only complaints are that it sheds a bit of fuzz and that it doesn’t have pockets :(',40,'2020-06-15'),(2469,'Aj S.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,1.0,'Unfit at any size','You might reasonably expect clothing sizes and the customers they fit to conform to a bell curve, where the most frequently ordered sizes fit most of the population. Patagonia seems to take the approach that sizes should fit fashion models in a variety of heights. If you\'re of average size you can expect the Large in this product to be sloppy',40,'2020-06-15'),(2470,'Matthew G.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Super comfortable','It is light weight, super comfortable and soft! But it still keeps you very warm!',40,'2020-06-15'),(2471,'William K.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,5.0,'Micro D','The best of my fleece pullovers. Perfect fit and weight. Great for cool northwest fall mornings.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2472,'Jesse C.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,4.0,'Excellent fit and quality','My son loves it... it’ll be great for layering during snowboard season!',40,'2020-06-15'),(2473,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Just right','Light, warm, colorful, it is the go to pullover for a chilly start to the day.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2474,'Max V.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Amazing','I love this fleece so much! I bought it because I live in the PNW and it is perfect for those cold days when it is not raining, and when it is raining just pop a light rain jacket over it and you are all good.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2475,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Love it!','Soft and comfortable, roomy without being large. Excited to wear this fall!',40,'2020-06-15'),(2476,'Jon S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Micro fleece','Awesome, light weight, thin and incredibly warm.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2477,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'One size larger was perfect fit !','Love the feel and weight of this lighter version Snap D pullover. I have the heavier version, and so far love it...the lighter version is good for Fall or Spring, as well as winter with long sleeve base layer underneath. I order Large, but felt it was a bit too snug. Decided to try the xl and the fit was so much more comfortable . I have wider shou',40,'2020-06-15'),(2478,'joseph g.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,1.0,'get your sizing together','Select any Patagonia product, and you\'ll find the same comments: \"sizing is totally inconsistent. get it together!\" Different colors, different sizes. different models, different sizes. I own a medium LT Synchilla that fits great. This - terrible. It\'s cut like a small in the chest and an XXL at the waist. This is my last purcha',40,'2020-06-15'),(2479,'Jonathan F.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Nice thin cut fleece top','I have been trying to replace a well one light weight quarter zip fleece for several years now as my old one is becoming quite tired.… This fits the bill and is extremely well-made. My wife loves the pumpkin color.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2480,'Nancy W.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Dudes love to wear Patagonia','My dude loves all his Patagonia vests, sweaters, tees, and jackets. His Grandchildren think he’s cool.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2481,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Love','Super soft material! Perfect to wear all year long. My boyfriend is 5 foot 8 and 160 pounds and the medium fits perfect',40,'2020-06-15'),(2482,'Gerald D.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great products from a great Company','As always, products that will be in my closet for years.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2483,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Micro D® Snap-T® Pullover Is A Perfect Early Fall Fleece','I have worn my new micro D Snap-T pullover twice since receiving it 2 weeks ago, and it is comfortable without being too heavy. Its flexibly when stretching is just what I was looking for. I highly recommend it.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2484,'Terrell T.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Micro D Snap-T','I love this Snap-T! It is the perfect weight - light enough for early summer mornings/late evenings in Colorado...',40,'2020-06-15'),(2485,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great Fleece','I bring it with me everywhere, its light so it can be worn during the late summer/early fall months. Would definitely recommend buying one.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2486,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'So comfortable!!','Love this thing!! So soft, so light, and a great addition to any collection. 5\'8\" 150 and a medium fit perfect for me.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2487,'Jon L.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'A handy garment.','packs small and adds warmth when needed.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2488,'Patrick N.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Micro D','This pullover is awesome! It’s soft and warm yet still super lightweight. Really hope they come out with another line of these next season!',40,'2020-06-15'),(2489,'Oliver L.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'So versatile','This is the thinest fleece I ever owned, so I can wear this pretty much all seasons. So light and super soft.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2490,'MARY M.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Good fit','Fits well and as always, washes up just like new each time. Recommend!',40,'2020-06-15'),(2491,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great Fleece','Perfect for cool mornings, cool autumn days or as a layering piece. Just wore in Maine for a morning hike and it was prefect.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2492,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Excellent','I love the micro snap T pullover. It being lighter allows me to wear it a lot more in the summer, fall, and spring.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2493,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,3.0,'Snap T','I am 6\'3 with a 34 inch inseam- so I have a short torso',40,'2020-06-15'),(2494,'Dave',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Great Cool Weather Fleece','This fleece is perfect if you want the Synchilla aesthetic without the heat and bulk. That\'s exactly what I got it for. For me, 50s and low 60s is too warm for most fleece, so this has become my go-to. The material is crazy soft and comfortable. There are no pockets, which took some getting used to, but that\'s fine. This is just a cozy th',40,'2020-06-15'),(2495,'Sahaj',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,2.0,'Quality not so good','I own 2 pairs of jacket from Patagonia and they are awesome. But this particular one is not so good quality. The package came in a dirty cover, and when I started rubbing the material lint started coming all over the place. For $95 cost I felt the product is not of good quality. U shouldnt get lints just by moving ur hands on the product. Also when',40,'2020-06-15'),(2496,'Kevin B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,4.0,'Comfortable/Durable','Great for work or a casual hike on the weekend. Can be worn in the office for a professional look if that\'s what you\'re looking for. Very durable. Great in the wind. Plenty of breathability. Wash on cold and dry on delicate cycle. Minimal shrinkage if any at all.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2497,'Lil C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'A1','This thing is snazzy. Four season piece. Make more like Stone Blue w/ Dam Blue. I found the other colors hideous.',40,'2020-06-15'),(2498,'M T.',NULL,'None','L/XL',NULL,5.0,'Everything You could ask for','This is the perfect layer for cool coastal winter days. I was searching high and low for a lightweight layer that could keep the damp chill of coastal Southern California winters off me and this jacket has surpassed my expectations. As a stand-alone outer, I would say that the jacket’s ideal temperature range is from the high 40s up into the low 60',74,'2020-06-15'),(2499,'Charlie',NULL,'None','L',NULL,4.0,'Awesome technical piece, weird sleeves','This jacket is a go-to for hiking under 40 degrees, casual wear, travel, and ice climbing. This and the R1 jacket were fantastic pieces for a September trip to Iceland with weather that varied with the hour. However, the fit of the sleeves is weirdly puffy around the biceps, and a bit bunched around the armpits. It’s especially odd given the fitted',74,'2020-06-15'),(2500,'Charlie',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Wonky collar, awesome jacket','I’ve been using this jacket for hiking and climbing around 30-45 degrees and while skiing under a shell 30 and lower. It’s got just the right mix of breathability, wind blocking, and warmth to keep me comfortable when steaming uphill but not freezing on the downhill leg. Really appreciate the stretch and semi-soft shell hard face, both of which mak',74,'2020-06-15'),(2501,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Love this!','Makes me look very slender too!',74,'2020-06-15'),(2502,'Ethan P.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'So far so amazing','I am pretty tough on my fleece and demand a lot from my layering systems. As a river guide I work in a lot of conditions and need my layers to be light, warm, breathable and comfy. The R2 totally delivers. From Maine in January to Panamanian rain forest this layer has kept me warm, well regulated and fits in on just about any adventure.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2503,'Calvin Q.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,3.0,'Great material but fit is a bit too long','I am 6’2” 170 lb and got the medium. It is beautifully constructed with great material. I’m sure it was intended to be long for cold winds etc, but I almost always have the sleeves rolled up a few inches and the bottom of the jacket prob covers 1/3 of my butt.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2504,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Great fleece jacket! Very comfortable!','Great fleece jacket! Very comfortable!',74,'2020-06-15'),(2505,'Ga챘l C.',NULL,'None','XS',NULL,5.0,'Great for layering and running','I\'ve done 4 UTMB with similar products from Patagonia and this new one has already kept me warm and safe in the mountains when I trail run. It\'s not the most breathable or packable but it\'s warm and soft. It makes me feel safe.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2506,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'I love it!!','I love it!!',74,'2020-06-15'),(2507,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Ms R2® TechFace Jacket','Very comfortable and perfect midlayer for winter. Also works as a standalone jacket in the fall with just a t-shirt underneath. Super comfortable and would definitely buy again (but hope that this one lasts long enough that I don\'t have to). My only complaint is that the sleeves are just a bit long, but that\'s a very minor issue.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2508,'Michael L.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,4.0,'Awesome, just a little long','This jacket is excellent. My only criticism is it seems a little long and the mid section is a little roomy.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2509,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','NB-7lb',NULL,5.0,'It\'s great!','Fits great for a slim person like me. Like how thin it is. I only wish it were a tad bit warmer.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2510,'Robert B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Great jacket for active could be warmer','I’ve worn this jacket almost daily for two months trekking and traveling. It is great as a layer and when active it holds up in colder weather but doesn’t keep the amount of warmth I would like when I stop moving even with additional layers. The fit and comfort are nice for everyday use.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2511,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Best fleece yet!','I grabbed this fleece for my husband after I fell in love with my own R2 TechFace Jacket. We both love the warmth - and it\'s really warm. Great all-around fleece jacket for cooler days. Two thumbs up!',74,'2020-06-15'),(2512,'Joshua R.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Great all around jacket','Awesome jacket, comfortably warm, the cuff design is next level. The only thing I’d say about the jacket is that the fit is on the larger side. So I’m a 185 6’ male and large is definitely a little too big, the medium was a much better fit.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2513,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket','Love my OG R2, by itself or with a shell, probably the most versatile jacket I have. When the new TechFace came out I was super interested, and after trying on M and L, because if you know the brand you know the size can vary year to year. I’m 5’11 190 lbs 42 chest 33 waist and the medium fit great, the large was way to big, the jacket is stretchy,',74,'2020-06-15'),(2514,'Edward R.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Another Great jacket','I love this jacket, it’s fall in Minnesota and I can wear this jacket every day. I can wear it on its own on warmer days, and layer it when the weather changes.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2515,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,5.0,'AWESOME JACKET','THIS JACKET IS SUPER NICE AND FITS WELL!',74,'2020-06-15'),(2516,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Great Jacket! Deceivingly warm','Great Jacket! Deceivingly warm',74,'2020-06-15'),(2517,'Lon R.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Great layer','Super comfortable, lightweight and warm. I\'m 5\'8\", 165 lb and the Medium fit me well.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2518,'Leif E.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'great jacket very warm.','great jacket very warm.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2519,'John-Paul M.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket','Great mid-layer jacket.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2520,'Dean R.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'R2 Review','Fits true to size. We live in Minnesota where fall through spring can be very cold. The R2 is a good stand alone layer for fall and is a great mid layer for the winters here.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2521,'Scott A.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Significantly warmer than R1','I didn’t need it. Family told me not to get it. Already own two R1 Tech face hoodies. And yet, I covet this piece like no other. Luxurious interior instantly warms with only a cotton or light merino layer in chilly temps. Love the exterior texture and pattern.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2522,'William R.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,1.0,'The fit is off','I tried both the medium and large. I\'m 6\'1 and weigh 175.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2523,'Michael D.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'I like the large jacket','I like the large jacket and the size is a good fit but it is long. I was replacing a Nano air hybrid that was stolen and it had a better fit in the Medium. This was too small in the medium. I would have ordered the hybrid again but it was not available in black.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2524,'Michael P.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Too early to tell....','I just got the jacket a couple of days ago and did were it on a cool morning. Fabric felt nice, has some stretch to it. Will definitely wear it a lot. Seems to run slightly long but no biggie. Bought this to replace a really worn R1 jacket and it was on sale.....and this stuff is pricey even on sale. As a long time Patagonia customer I have noticed',74,'2020-06-15'),(2525,'Edward L.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'warm and durable','Perfect jacket for camping and going to the ball game. Great fit (size medium for 5\'8\" 155 lb). The wind, water, and wear resistant surface is awesome. I expect this jacket to last through the next ten years.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2526,'Alex M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Extremely comfortable','This jacket is so soft and pliable, you\'ll never want to take it off. The tapered sleeves are snug so the fabric never gets in the way. You wouldn\'t want to wear several layers under this jacket. Maybe a thin shirt or long underwear base layer, then this jacket. I wouldn\'t call it waterproof, but it can fend off a light rain easily.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2527,'Nilo T.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Ms R2 TechFace Jacket','I ordered the large fits perfect and so comfortable and i can move freely. This jacket is perfect were i live whole year round i can wear it.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2528,'Kyle Y.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,4.0,'Great jacket, poor seams','I am 6\'2\" 185, broad and long limbed. I bought the Medium and the fit is a tad snug in the chest but otherwise good. The arms are long as they should be. A Large might fit better up top, but Patagonia designers unfortunately think taller and broader people are fat, so most of their Larges have balloons of fabric around the middle. This is',74,'2020-06-15'),(2529,'William C.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'R2 techface jacket','I haven’t worn it in cold weather yet, but it seems like the waffled lining will trap air as an insulator to keep you warm. The fit and quality are excellent.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2530,'Gus W.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'R2 Tech Face Jacket','I got this jacket at the start of the summer, so it hasn\'t been through the ringer yet, but I have worn it enough to know that it will be a staple for years to come.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2531,'Craig V.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Versatile Midlayer','Purchased this jackets in early April. In the first month, I wore it as a mid layer for snowboarding, under my waders for the opening day of fly fishing in Michigan, to mass on Easter Sunday, and to work a few days too! I’d call that a pretty versatile piece. For reference I am 5’11” 175lbs and the medium is perfect. Still enough room to wear a nan',74,'2020-06-15'),(2532,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'M’s R2 TechFace Jacket','20-some years ago I had a grey, quilted-looking Patagonia snap-closure pullover. Wore it everywhere, everyday. It still lives in multiple old Polaroids. I literally scraped pennies together to save up for that thing. Got this R2 hoping to replace my long, lost love. I am wealthier now. I got the blue one. Love is anew. So much so that I will also g',74,'2020-06-15'),(2533,'Harleydog',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,2.0,'Fit for a select few','My climbing guide son-in-law has owned one of these for years and loves it, so I thought I’d try one. I only weigh 130. A medium fit close around the chest but the sleeves hung down past my fingertips. Good jacket if you’re 5’11 and skinny.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2534,'Brannon F.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,2.0,'bad stitching placement','The large stitching in the arms runs directly down the back of the arm and over the elbow making for a very uncomfortable garment, especially one that is designed to be worn during athletic pursuits. The medium fits like a large or extra large in comparable brands',74,'2020-06-15'),(2535,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,3.0,'Where\'s the hood!!!','This jacket has potential to provide exceptional warm from everyday to mountain use; however, it plain and simple needs a hood option. For a jacket designed for the option of mountain use, this jacket would have much more versality if it had a hood option.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2536,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Awesome','so I used to have an r3 when they made the older styles 09-11 and that had a furry inside and fleece outside and they used to have it tagged as a laminate less windbreaker because how it was sewn. Well this is as close to that jacket they have ever made and its awesome. Now it even has water repellency. The inside is very similar and the fit is gre',74,'2020-06-15'),(2537,'Stephen L.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'hoody option in this?','Would love to see this with a hood',74,'2020-06-15'),(2538,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Great Jacket','So it is a bit pricey, but it is a great one. With a hoodie underneath, this jacket can easily keep you warm at high 30s to low 40s temperature. Water repellent works excellent. Walked 5 blocks in pouring rain in Portland and about 15 minutes in the car the jacket was all dry. Also looks very stylish and sleek.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2539,'Lance',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great Soft Shell Alternative','#NAME?',74,'2020-06-15'),(2540,'Robert M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Love this jacket','I got this in a medium to replace an older medium R2 that I thought was a bit too snug in the neck and body. I am 5\"10\" and 170Lbs. This is a better fit all around and warmer. My one complaint is that the sleeves are longer than I like but that was easy to fix by tucking them inside and then sewing new seams. They don\'t even look lik',74,'2020-06-15'),(2541,'Jay H.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'One of the best','I think this may have become one of my favorite Patagonia fleeces! I used to wear the normal R2 fleece all the time, but this just is a bit more \"jacket\" I guess because it blocks that extra bit of air and a bit of precipitation and is nice and warm. I miss the soft fluff on the outside, but sacrifices must be made for function sometimes',74,'2020-06-15'),(2542,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Love it','Love everything about this jacket. The exterior surface is awesome. Easy to layer over but tough enough to not worry about it snagging. Plenty warm. A little extra length in sleeves, waist, and collar are nice as you stay covered in motion. True to size but it is a little slim fitting. However, it stretches really well.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2543,'Natural H.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','M',NULL,5.0,'Incredible Jacket','I wanted to provide a quick review to hopefully help those who are considering this jacket. I purchased this jacket about 2 months ago and it has become my daily jacket / layer. Listed below are the key things I like about the jacket. For reference I am 6’5” and weigh 190lbs. and sleeve length is 16.5”.',74,'2020-06-15'),(2544,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'GREAT in-between jacket!','Grandma? Maybe so...my grandma chops firewood and climbs mountains and rides horses. I wear this jacket while trying to keep up with her!',74,'2020-06-15'),(2545,'Zayabons',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Badass','The last guy must care what people think of him. I got the same size, in black, and it\'s handsome as hell. There is nothing \"grandma\" about this jacket. It stretches with your body when biking or playing with the dog and keeps you warm while not making you sweat a ton',74,'2020-06-15'),(2546,'Sf B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'r2 techface','On the whole this is a nice jacket. It is very warm, almost too warm. The sleeves fit nicely -- I\'ve recently had problems with Patagonia sleeve length being too long, but not on the R2 techface. The divets of the jacket provide an interesting texture, but I was told it looks like a grandma\'s quilted jacket, so that was not ideal. If it i',74,'2020-06-15'),(2547,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Nailed it!','Patagonia nailed it with this top. I\'ve been wearing the R1 TechFace Pullover all spring through variable New England weather. Sometimes cold (30\'s), sometimes chilly (40\'s-50\'s), and even in the warmer 60\'s. Sometimes a little wet... and often windy. This top is awesome for a wide range of temps and conditions. I choose a',24,'2020-06-15'),(2548,'Todd',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Finally got it right','Patagonia finally got the R1 right. The cut is roomy but not baggy. The lapel over the zipper creates a nice clean look (and nicely hides the chest pocket), The sleeves aren\'t crazy long like the R1 Techface hoodie. This has become my go to mid layer. At this time they only have 3 color options and would be nice if they had more.',24,'2020-06-15'),(2549,'Zachary',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'One of my favorite outdoor gear pieces','I bought this at an outlet. It was a good deal. I wasn\'t sure what I was getting, but it has quickly turned into one of my favorite pieces. It\'s durable. Great ratio of weight to warmth. It\'ll keep wind out to a point and has some water resistance. I even like wearing it in some casual situations. All around my favorite Patagonia ite',24,'2020-06-15'),(2550,'Bojan',NULL,'None','None',NULL,1.0,'Disappointing item','This product is calmed to be abrasion resistant so it won\'t shred against rock... I had backpack clipped on my waste while hiking and garment on this so called abrasion resistant shirt showed some serious damage. This is brand new shirt. I am extremely disappointed in this item, don\'t buy this.',24,'2020-06-15'),(2551,'Justin H.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'The R1 Perfected','The original R1 pullover has become one of my most versatile shirts. I’m 5’8 145-lbs and a small fits me perfectly. I wear it trail running when temps dip down into the 40s and also use it as a base layer when skiing. The only problem is that it looks ‘worse for the wear’ with all of the use it gets. It easily snags on briars when running and piles',24,'2020-06-15'),(2552,'James P.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'great golf top','It will be great for those cool golf days in Ireland',24,'2020-06-15'),(2553,'Jesica R.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Nice','Nice shirt. Love the subtle pattern for my husband, makes it different from all the other 1/4 zips out there. The navy is really dark. My husband is 6’2” and wears a large generally. This one is slightly tight in the upper chest, and I do wish it was an inch longer. He still loves it, and has worn in twice in the last three days.',24,'2020-06-15'),(2554,'Nicholas R.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'TechFace','Love it! I already had a different color.',24,'2020-06-15'),(2555,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Great Product','I have been using the R1 Techface for a few weeks now and it is performing awesome. I like that is less stretchy than the regular R1 and has the DWR finish.',24,'2020-06-15'),(2556,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'A mew favorite!','My new favorite piece of kit. It\'s super thin, super light, just the right amount of stretchy. But it\'s also shockingly resistant to wind for its weight, and I\'ve been out riding on several 30F days with nothing more than this and a t-shirt and some gloves. More warmth than I\'d expect from something this lightweight. Very versat',24,'2020-06-15'),(2557,'Austin',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XXL',NULL,5.0,'The perfect pullover','Tough and stretchy with water/rain wind resistance.',24,'2020-06-15'),(2558,'Matt U.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,4.0,'Why not just a Techface version of R1?','I wish it had the athletic cut of the traditional R1 hoody. It’s cut more baggy and is missing thumb holes to keep the sleeves down with my gloves.',24,'2020-06-15'),(2559,'David C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Tech face R1','I have worn it twice. Mountain biking and hunting. It worked perfect.',24,'2020-06-15'),(2560,'Robert B.',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,5.0,'My New Go-To Gravel Riding Piece','I often struggle on the question of outwear for morning gravel rides that start at 40-45 degrees (no rain); base layer, jersey, and light shell (to cut the wind), or base layer, jersey, light fleece (like a traditional R-1, of which 2 in the gear closet). Cyclists know the importance of starting cool and bringing up the comfort/temperature level to',24,'2020-06-15'),(2561,'John',NULL,'None','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Great addition to R1 line','Purchased this 