t. Hence, 4 instead of 5 stars. The sizing for me means it works better as an outer jacket and not for close to the body. I am glad I got it and look forward to cooler weath',56,'2020-06-15'),(2643,'Rosalina D.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'This was a gift','My son liked the jacket and it fit perfect',56,'2020-06-15'),(2644,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,1.0,'Patagonia... just a name!','When North Face came out, years ago, I initially thought it was just a name until I tried it. Then I realized it was more expensive than Columbia, but was of better, long-lasting quality. So, when I first heard about Patagonia I dismissed it as another name, but then decided to give it a shot. I was expecting a much higher quality than the Columbia',56,'2020-06-15'),(2645,'Cynthia W.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XL',NULL,5.0,'Patagonia quality is great','I\'ve owned numerous Patagonia fleece tops over many years. None have ever failed. Zippers, snaps, material will be going strong it seems like forever. I treat them with care, and they have held up over 20 years in some cases. I seldom need to buy anything made by any other company.',56,'2020-06-15'),(2646,'Joshua R.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,1.0,'Poor quality','I bought this sweater in late August/September and by December the product is already showing signs of being badly pilled. The garment has never been washed, I would expect a product of this price to last long.',56,'2020-06-15'),(2647,'Rahul',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XL',NULL,5.0,'LOVELY JACKET','VERY SOFT AND COMFORTABLE',56,'2020-06-15'),(2648,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Awesome','Much prefer the synchilla jacket to that of the pullover synchilla. I love this jacket very much and especially the thickness.',56,'2020-06-15'),(2649,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,2.0,'Not bad but NOT wind resistant!','Had a synchilla jacket for many years and it\'s best for cool temperatures to 50s.',56,'2020-06-15'),(2650,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Awesome Jacket!','Just received this jacket and its great! Sizing is bigger than my previous Patagonia gear,longer and bigger all around but I like it this way. Im 6\' 175 and got a large. Zipper pockets and Nickel colorway sold me.',56,'2020-06-15'),(2651,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'My Go To','Love this jacket and its by far the one I wear the most since purchase. Layers wonderfully under my ski shell if its cold on tours and works great as my outer layer during the mud season.',41,'2020-06-15'),(2652,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'My Go To','Love this jacket and its by far the one I wear the most since purchase. Layers wonderfully under my ski shell if its cold on tours and works great as my outer layer during the mud season.',41,'2020-06-15'),(2653,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Extremely versatile, insanely comfortable jacket','Couldn\'t recommend this jacket more for many reasons. I wear this as a layering piece on colder days in the winter (big snowboarder) under a shell and even as an outerwear piece with the R1 pullover. Seriously, that combo has kept me warmer than my insulated jacket has with no layering. The R1 / Nano-Air combo lets in ZERO wind and is supremel',41,'2020-06-15'),(2654,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Extremely versatile, insanely comfortable jacket','Couldn\'t recommend this jacket more for many reasons. I wear this as a layering piece on colder days in the winter (big snowboarder) under a shell and even as an outerwear piece with the R1 pullover. Seriously, that combo has kept me warmer than my insulated jacket has with no layering. The R1 / Nano-Air combo lets in ZERO wind and is supremel',41,'2020-06-15'),(2655,'Emil',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S/M',NULL,2.0,'Poor Quality','The jacket is quite light, but even as a mid-layer, fails to live up to the advertised level of warmth. I wore the jacket fishing during a rainstorm in Deschutes and had to add a down vest over the jacket and under my rain shell to keep sufficiently warm. Most disappointingly, after only about a half-dozen wears, the fabric began pilling around the',41,'2020-06-15'),(2656,'Colin',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,3.0,'Could be the perfect jacket','I purchased this jacket in the navy blue color in September 2019 and immediately fell in love. While I sometimes wear a medium in Patagonia tops and jackets (depending on fit), a small in the Nano Air was a perfect fit for me. I wore it on a few hikes the first week or so that I had it but primarily used it as a casual jacket in the city. In either',41,'2020-06-15'),(2657,'Ted',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,4.0,'The most comfortable jacket','Wow, this is a seriously comfortable jacket - by far the most comfortable I\'ve felt. Its hard to describe, its not quite cotton hoody type comfort but more of if you could wear your favorite pillow. The next to skin feel when wearing this with a t-shirt is outstanding.',41,'2020-06-15'),(2658,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','0',NULL,5.0,'Outstanding!','Dittos to the other ski patrollers here - and thank you Patagonia for your support for the stylish and functional NSP uniforms! These jackets (Nan-Air and Nano-Air Light) are awesome, and I don\'t care about a little bit of pilling.',41,'2020-06-15'),(2659,'merrick',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','0',NULL,2.0,'Would be 5 star except the pilling/wear.','Love the jacket, it\'s a go to for hiking in our mild, but windy New Mexico climate. The only issue is wear. With just a few months each season when I wear it, it is extremely pilled. Instead of looking like a jacket worn fairly often over maybe 4 chilly months, it looks far older than my regular Patagonia fleeces I\'ve been wearing more ye',41,'2020-06-15'),(2660,'Matt W.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,4.0,'Slim fit, super functional','Im 61 and 190lbs. and the medium fits perfect as a slim outer layer. I often need a large-size jacket but wanted something slim fitting that would work great over just a shirt or base layer. Theres no room for a sweater underneath. Its a close fit but the jacket moves with you and doesnt bind up. I love that it doesnt have those elastic cuffs that',41,'2020-06-15'),(2661,'Justin H.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,3.0,'Excellent Jacket, sub-par Durability','Without question, the Nano-Air is the most versatile jacket I own. I wear it trail running during winter in Tennessee, under a shell skiing in Colorado, and as a mid layer for work in northern Alberta. It’s warm, breathable, light weight and extremely packable. It’s also cut perfect - allowing for good mobility without excessive material. My only c',41,'2020-06-15'),(2662,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Fantastic Mid-Layer!!!','I ski patrol at 10,500 feet. I sweat through the nano-air many times during the day. It dries super quick and keeps me toasty on long lift rides. I\'ve tried just about everything (down, synthetic, fleece) as a mid-layer and all pale when compared to the nano-air. In 18+ years of patrolling, I\'ve never had a better mid-layer than the nano-',41,'2020-06-15'),(2663,'nathaniel h.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,4.0,'Sweet Jacket for Exercise','I bought this jacket for around half price and I absolutely love it. I use it for nordic skiing, everyday wear in the winter, and I use it as a layer for snowboarding. Unfortunately, after just about a year of use the fore arm area as well as the lower back area are pilling pretty bad. Other than that it is a great jacket.',41,'2020-06-15'),(2664,'Yulin Z.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Such a versatile layer','I have worn it as a outer jacket with a T-shirt in about 50 degrees and as a mid layer in the 20s with a hard shell and Merino wool base layer, it was great in both occasions. I think it\'s treated with DWR because I used it in some light rain and the rain beaded up, I could easily shake the water off before I got into my car.',41,'2020-06-15'),(2665,'Mike',NULL,'None','M',NULL,4.0,'Awesome for exercise','This is perfect for exactly what Patagonia advertises it being good for: staying active outdoors– hiking, XC skiing, etc. The breathability, compactness, and lightweight are awesome.',41,'2020-06-15'),(2666,'Matthew C.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'Mighty fine jacket for everyday','Mighty fine jacket for everyday wear. Warm without being bulky and it moves with you nicely. Cinching around the wrist and waist keep you draft free without feeling tight or constructing.',41,'2020-06-15'),(2667,'JD113',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,5.0,'Awesome Jacket','Using the 2019 Forge Grey with red accents with matching Galvanized Shell and it an absolute perfect combination for skiing. Love the look, feel, but more importantly the performance of the Nano Air as a midlayer. It\'s simply great.',41,'2020-06-15'),(2668,'Jonathan L.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'The greatest jacket in all of history','I never take time to review clothing, but this thing is something else. It\'s incredibly light, stretchy, soft, warm, and breathable. It\'s even quite good at repelling water. The only thing it doesn\'t do well is block wind, but that\'s intrinsic to the breathable design. Pair it with a shell for &lt;30 degree days, and your fall,',41,'2020-06-15'),(2669,'Zachary J.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Favorite Layer','Stretchy comfortable and breathable. Seems to run a little larger than the previous version, but this could be my imagination. It\'s not an extremely warm layer, but it isn\'t supposed to be. Easily paired with a vest when it\'s truly cold out. New exterior material looks resistant to pilling, which was my only gripe with the old versio',41,'2020-06-15'),(2670,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Works as advertised!','A great mid-layer that can also be worn on chilly days as outer layer. Warm even in windy conditions.',41,'2020-06-15'),(2671,'Mark R.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Nano-air jacket','Great material perfect for layering on cold days on the ski hill. Doesn’t feel bulky. Love it!!!',41,'2020-06-15'),(2672,'Mike',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Great piece','Rarely do I use a layer without a hood, but when I do (mechanized skiing with a helmet and under a hard shell), this is the perfect piece. If you are looking for a breathable active layer without a hood, look no further!',41,'2020-06-15'),(2673,'Sean E.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Nano','Great for everyday wear.',41,'2020-06-15'),(2674,'Wiley R.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','None',NULL,5.0,'Nano air','Never write reviews and I think my impression of this jacket is the only reason I just started. Looks super clean while also being light and warm and just the perfect all around jacket for moderate climates. Absolutely in love with it and haven’t taken it off since I got it.',41,'2020-06-15'),(2675,'Jonathan L.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,5.0,'So light, so comfortable, so warm.','Absolutely the most comfortable jacket I\'ve ever owned. So breathable it\'s hard to find reasons to take it off.',41,'2020-06-15'),(2676,'Jim R.',NULL,'6\'7 or above','L',NULL,5.0,'Perfect','Great layer piece in cold weather but also versatile for use everyday. Awesome fit, jacket is a more slim fit but moves with you and does not constrict.',41,'2020-06-15'),(2677,'Tate C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'NANO Air no equal','This is my second nano air jacket that I’ve owned. They are the most comfortable, breathable and lightweight layer I’ve had the pleasure of owning. I like this jacket for brisk walks, layering for BC skiing and bike commuting. The fit is snug for me (medium, 5’11”, 165lbs) but that was what I was going for. I have pretty long arms and the jacket is',41,'2020-06-15'),(2678,'David E.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,5.0,'Nano-Air','I have had a lot of Patagonia layers over the years, and each one has been special. I can honestly say that the Nano-Air is like nothing I\'ve owned. It is strangely comfortable and I just want to live in it. I can teach 2nd grade in it, and wear it skiing, and I would wear it to bed but my wife won\'t let me.',41,'2020-06-15'),(2679,'Samuel M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'A fun jacket','The jacket feels quite soft, and the zippers operate quite well. The pockets are in ergonomic locations; they are where my hands naturally want to rest. The sleeves feel a little tight in the upper forearm area when I bend my arms. Although the waist doesn\'t look particularly baggy, it feels like the jacket could be tapered a more from the rib',41,'2020-06-15'),(2680,'Russell S.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'I bought the Nano-Air for','I bought the Nano-Air for a winter mountain biking layer. Needed some breathable insulation that I don\'t need to take off and put on repeatedly.',41,'2020-06-15'),(2681,'Christopher L.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,5.0,'Excellent Jacket','Was extremely surprised how warm this jacket kept me! Wore it all night outside with temps in low 50s - was great. Sizes def run slim though. I wear small in everything but had to get a medium in this jacket.',41,'2020-06-15'),(2682,'Bryan W.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,4.0,'Daily driver with one major flaw','This jacket is warm as is or a great base layer for colder days. The fabric is soft and quiet and it has become my go to for everything. That said, the fabric is so soft that the inside of the collar, when zipped up, gets absolutely thrashed by my beard. I think I have an average beard and I shave daily but the fabric still gets caught in it and is',41,'2020-06-15'),(2683,'Lisbeth S.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Handsome jacket','It was a gift for my son, he was very pleased and looked great in it. He bikes a lot, so I am sure it will come to good use.',41,'2020-06-15'),(2684,'Brian L.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Love it.','Love it.',41,'2020-06-15'),(2685,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Awesome','So far have just used as a casual jacket to walk the dogs, but I am looking forward to using it as a layering piece for the mountain. Extremely comfortable and moves with you!',41,'2020-06-15'),(2686,'Joey R.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XLM',NULL,5.0,'Great Jacket','Love the jacket ...wish that it was tailored for and athletic fit.... bought to play golf in',41,'2020-06-15'),(2687,'Josh',NULL,'None','L',NULL,1.0,'Great jacket .. awful durability','1st generation of this jacket was phenomenal. This version is awful. Whatever new fabric they\'re using for the shell is very prone to wear. I\'ve had mine for 10 months and the outside is covered in pills and resembles an old pair of socks. Really sad considering Patagonia\'s commitment to sustainability.',41,'2020-06-15'),(2688,'Daniel G.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','NB-7lb',NULL,4.0,'Basically a better version of the Nano-Puff','I love this jacket, it fits well, it\'s a really comfortable material, great level of warmth for fall days, and it has enough room (especially with the flexible material) that I expect to be able to layer under it for colder days this winter. I say it\'s a better version of the Nano-Puff primarily because of the material. They are both fant',41,'2020-06-15'),(2689,'Leigh',NULL,'None','XS',NULL,4.0,'Good jacket but don\'t like 2019 modifications','A very good jacket, but 3 changes this year which I don\'t like - they are :',41,'2020-06-15'),(2690,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,4.0,'Warm functional jacket – with the (usual) caveat','Took this on an alpine hike recently and wore it under a waterproof shell in temperatures just above freezing. Was the perfect pair. The fit is on the slim side, but not constricting. One star off for the fabric retaining odor after only two uses (by comparison I can wear my Patagonia synthetic down jackets, or anything merino, for weeks without a ',41,'2020-06-15'),(2691,'Sarah T.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Love the nano air jacket','I love how lightweight it is and the comfort of the fit. The material is super comfortable and the style is dope too',41,'2020-06-15'),(2692,'Blake',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Lighter version of the Retro Pile, but runs short.','Really nice finish and style. Overall the pullover is a lighter version of the Retro Pile Pullover from year\'s past.',60,'2020-06-15'),(2693,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','None',NULL,4.0,'Runs Small, get one size up!','Runs Small, get one size up!',60,'2020-06-15'),(2694,'Bryce S.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,1.0,'Runs very short','I am 6’ 1” 170, so tall and skinny. I have always been a medium in Patagonia, the lashes always have to much width to them. This sweatshirt is by far the shortest piece I have ever ordered from Patagonia. It doesn’t even cover my belt.. I’m sure it’s good for some people, but they need to make a long version or something for taller people.',60,'2020-06-15'),(2695,'Matthew H.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'3 Season win for Patagonia','Nice work.',60,'2020-06-15'),(2696,'WENDY V.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Comfy','Bought for my husband. He says it is warm and comfortable.',60,'2020-06-15'),(2697,'Joel C.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,2.0,'Size runs samll','While the product is fine, it runs very small compared to other purchases I\'ve made. Have to return it(them).',60,'2020-06-15'),(2698,'michelle u.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Fleece','Very comfortable and warm for Portland weather.',60,'2020-06-15'),(2699,'Markus R.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,4.0,'Very warm but some pilling','Much warmer than the 100% poly fleeces and in a pleasant way, the elasticated cuffs are not an issue though i don’t see why it needs them.',60,'2020-06-15'),(2700,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Excellent product!','Excellent product!',60,'2020-06-15'),(2701,'david w.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,1.0,'Bad, bad, bad','The fleece i received was terrible in so many ways:',60,'2020-06-15'),(2702,'Carlos M.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','L',NULL,5.0,'Great Product','This is an exceptionally comfortable product of top quality . I highly recommend it .',60,'2020-06-15'),(2703,'MALCOLM M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Fleece Pullover','Medium is too small even though I generally wear medium from Patagonia. Need to exchange for Large.',60,'2020-06-15'),(2704,'Boris D.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,4.0,'Warm and light','Pro\'s: lightweight and warm fleece layer',60,'2020-06-15'),(2705,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','None',NULL,5.0,'Love it! Very comfortable','Love it!',60,'2020-06-15'),(2706,'Shyam P.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Warm and looks great','Great jacket and looks great. My only gripe is that it does have a more boxy look versus a tapered fit. If you order 1 size down, you risk the bottom being too high.',60,'2020-06-15'),(2707,'Tara C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L/XL',NULL,5.0,'Comfy pullover','Love the color, looks and feels comfy cozy',60,'2020-06-15'),(2708,'Kenneth M.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Another winner','Replacing an old friend, have enjoyed this for years and glad that they still make it.',60,'2020-06-15'),(2709,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Fantastic','I love this pullover, it’s become one of my go-tos since I purchased it. The fit is just right, the fabric is comfortable, and it keeps me warm without overheating. Only complaint would be the strange weaving pattern I noticed in it when I received it, but only because I’m unsure if that’s meant to be visible or not...I honestly like it.',60,'2020-06-15'),(2710,'Alec L.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Breathable yet warm','Great material - breathes yet warms',60,'2020-06-15'),(2711,'Alex',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Warm and comfortable','Very warm and comfortable to wear around the house or outside. Even wear it to the office sometimes.',60,'2020-06-15'),(2712,'Al',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Comfortable Double Duty Sweater','For reference I\'m 5\'9\", 200lbs., wear 33\" length dress shirts, and I bought size Large which fits perfectly. I have rated it True to Size because for me it does, however taller men or those with longer arms may want to consider going up a size (I didn\'t check to see if there is a Long size).',60,'2020-06-15'),(2713,'Rick',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Soft and Warm','I recently received a Woolyester fleece pull-over, and have found it to be very comfortable to wear as a sweater indoors, or under a lightweight down parka outdoors on very cold days. I have not found it to be any itchier than a wool sweater. It is soft and warm - the perfect companion for a Vermont winter.',60,'2020-06-15'),(2714,'Eddie',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,3.0,'Looks great but itchy','Love the look and fit. I\'m a short guy, so I appreciate the shorter length many people note. It sheds quite a bit and attracts quite a bit of anything that would like to attach (lint, dog hair, dust...). I also notice this material is quite itchy to me and it irritates my neck since the collar stays up and is in contact with the skin. Would lo',60,'2020-06-15'),(2715,'David',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Cozy','This pullover is really warm and cozy. The wool adds a nice texture and extra level of warmth but manages to not be itchy so it’s very comfortable. It also has a slightly more professional look so it is perfect for the office while still looking casual. The only cons are the fit- I did size up. I usually wear a small but could tell from looking at ',60,'2020-06-15'),(2716,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,1.0,'Can’t recommend','I love Patagonia products and own several. However I would not advise purchasing this one unless you plan on never washing it. Because when you do it “sheds” and unless you want “fuzzies” all over everything you own don’t ever wash it. Very disappointed in this one. Look elsewhere.',60,'2020-06-15'),(2717,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Love it','Way softer than wool, but somehow still just as warm as my wool jackets. Also, the fit is really cool. It fits like vintage patagonia gear, with the hem hitting at the belt line. Because it\'s legitimately warm, its solid on the trails, but also has a tailored enough fit for the office. It\'s one of my ne