to early spring . Now what I don\'t like is lack of manly colors,why not navy,dark grey,green,red,solid navy blue',66,'2020-06-15'),(2911,'HC1990',NULL,'5\'1 - 5\'3','XS',NULL,3.0,'Comfy; but cannot work as a base layer','I agree with others that this pullover is very comfy. Part of this is because it leaves (more than) sufficient space in your arms. Unfortunately,this factor also makes it very uncomfortable if you put a jacket on it. I recommend this pullover only if you plan to wear this alone as a top without any jacket/vest on it.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2912,'Beggarman',NULL,'None','M',NULL,4.0,'Not as good as my old synchilla pullover','I have a synchilla pullover (black) that I bought over 20 years ago. Only noticeable difference is it has a zipper instead of the buttons, 2 side pockets instead of the 1 chest pocket, embroidered logo on the back and sleeves have no elastic.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2913,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Very warm!','I have secretly been coveting one of these for a few years and just decided to bite the bullet. It\'s great and probably the only fleece I\'ll ever wear! Very warm and wind resistant. I like the high neck and the cuffs on the sleeves and the waist--all these features keep me toasty warm.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2914,'NCToad',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Nice and warm,but a few caveats','These fleeces,both the lightweight and the heavyweight versions,are very comfortable and extremely roomy,with lots of room for layering underneath. No pockets for your hands,so think of them more as sweaters than as jackets. The biggest criticism I have relates to the patterned versions--even the ad photos here illustrate the problem--the designs j',66,'2020-06-15'),(2915,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,5.0,'Can\'t live without this!','I\'m a twenty something woman and I\'ve grown up stealing my dad\'s older version of this pullover. I wore it so much it basically became mine until the winters here in upstate NY got even colder and I felt bad borrowing it from him - so I decided to get my own and what a good call on my part!',66,'2020-06-15'),(2916,'Ngates',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Love this sweater','I bought my snychilla hoping I would get a good quality product for the price,I absolutely love it. I wear it to work all the time and it keeps me warm unlike most of my sweaters. My work has the ac running 24/7 and i am right under a vent. I have taken it camping a few times in 40 degree weather and it keeps me more than warm. Fits well and a tad',66,'2020-06-15'),(2917,'JCharlson',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Unreasonably Comfortable','As I wrote this,I was sitting,watching TV,with a stupid grin on my face due to how comfortable this fleece is. As other have mentioned,it is very generously oversized. I am a very large guy,like 280lbs large (granted a ton is muscle and people think I\'m more like 220),and the XL is way too big for me. However,that does not take away from how c',66,'2020-06-15'),(2918,'Kevin',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Love it.','I\'m now officially a big Snap T guy and this is one of my favorite things to wear on a cool morning.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2919,'learningbyheart',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'winter soldier','This synchilla fleece is fantastic for regulating heat. I can stay comfortably warm wearing just a t-shirt underneath. Or if I am sweating it vents the excess heat,yet I am staying at a comfortable temperature.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2920,'Christopher',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'Perfect warmth and versatility','Warm,easy to move around in,I\'m super happy with my snap-t!',66,'2020-06-15'),(2921,'UKRx2K2',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,2.0,'Typically great quality. Cut is huge.','I have an XL that\'s 22 years old and it is smaller than this L. I was disappointed in how huge this was,but it would have cost me more than what I saved on the order on sale to send it back. I love the quality and color,but won\'t ever feel 100% comfortable in this bulky jacket. I\'d make sure to order down a size if you don\'t wan',66,'2020-06-15'),(2922,'PONSbythesea',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Quality product','I\'ve wanted one of these Patagonia fleece pullovers for years,and am more than pleased with it. The weight and weave are just what I expected--slightly heavier and a tighter weave than others on the market. Very well made. This one will outlast any I\'ve ever had.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2923,'Kateysj',NULL,'None','XS',NULL,5.0,'Love it','This is my favorite thing in my closet right now; so warm and comfortable with a super cool pattern. I\'m an 18-year-old girl,but since these were on sale I just ordered an x-small and it fits me perfectly; i\'m usually a small in women\'s.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2924,'Badass92',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Awesome','Bought it. Love it. All I ever dreamed of............',66,'2020-06-15'),(2925,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Good color,met high expectations!','I bought these jackets,one for me and one for my husband,for our 18th wedding anniversary. I had had one 30 years ago for 12 years and knew what to expect. My husband and I re-tapped into each other\'s strengths this year and these jackets symbolized our union-- a couple who stays warm together stays together. Thanks!',66,'2020-06-15'),(2926,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,4.0,'Fits great!','Looks great! Very warm perfect for fall walks or hanging out in the chalet!',66,'2020-06-15'),(2927,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Very Comfortable. Runs Big!','This is the most comfortable sweater I own and I highly recommend buying one. I spent most nights in November thru February in this thing (I\'m in southern CA). However,it runs very very large. I\'m 5-10,165 lbs,and depending on the cut of a jacket/shirt,I\'m either a medium or a large.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2928,'tmritter',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,5.0,'Favorite Patagonia Product','I have been an avid patagonia customer for a while now,and after the 20 or so products I have from them,the synchilla is my favorite. It is simple,yet versatile. I wear it around my house,out hiking,at school; just about everywhere. It\'s warm enough to be worn solo in 50 degree weather and is good at protecting you from moderate rain. Both the',66,'2020-06-15'),(2929,'Henry H.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Go to Winter Sweater','I\'ve had this sweater for a year and it is great. It is very warm and cozy and great for winter time in Colorado. I\'ve had no problems with it what so ever.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2930,'mrgerbik',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great in cool/cold dweather','First off,ordering a size down is most likely what you want to do. I am 5\'10\'\',215 lbs and sized at an XL using their sizing chart. The XL fit was way too loose for my liking. Got a L instead and it fit much better. You have enough room to move around (arms specifically) without there being a lot of extra fabric nor feeling like you&',66,'2020-06-15'),(2931,'Danger B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Warm fleece for chilly evenings','Great fleece for hanging out on the porch or the dock on chilly evenings. Its very soft and very warm. I wore it last night outdoors in 60 degree F weather wearing shorts,and it kept my whole body warm. It is also the warmest fleece I own. It can do down to 50 degrees F no problem. Note that it does not cut wind very well,so expect to bring a shell',66,'2020-06-15'),(2932,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Good for wearing.... Always','I\'ve barely taken this off since I got it. I wear it over my uniform at work,when I\'m chilly when I get up in the morning... and just about any time I reach for a sweatshirt. I\'m a female,5\'11,160lbs. A men\'s small fits about perfectly. The weight is warm,but not so heavy it\'s uncomfortable. It\'s baggy enough to w',66,'2020-06-15'),(2933,'Satokad',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Outstanding','The day my Synchilla came,the temps were in the 30s. I put this on and instant warmth. This piece is comfortable,warm (but not too hot),fits very well,and looks good. I had to put Other for recommended activity because living in it was not a listed option.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2934,'Torogoz',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Nice materials. Very comfortable. I','Nice materials. Very comfortable. I got an XL because I am a regular XXL guy and I wanted a sweater a little fit but this XL is like a XXL. Maybe because it is a retro style,I still like it but I am not using it for work because it fits too big! So just to relax!',66,'2020-06-15'),(2935,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Good for wearing.... Always','I\'ve barely taken this off since I got it. I wear it over my uniform at work,when I\'m chilly when I get up in the morning... and just about any time I reach for a sweatshirt. I\'m a female,5\'11,160lbs. A men\'s small fits about perfectly. The weight is warm,but not so heavy it\'s uncomfortable. It\'s baggy enough to w',66,'2020-06-15'),(2936,'Formula',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'I love my Snap-T\'s','I have two of the Synchilla Snap-T\'s and one of the lightweight versions...this review is for the regular Synchilla Snap-T. I love them and highly recommend them. Like everyone says they run a little big,so size down for a better fit. They\'re extremely soft and comfortable,and definitely warm. But be aware that they do not block the wind,',66,'2020-06-15'),(2937,'Chazzz',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'A Perfect Everything Jacket','I have lots of fleece. Why do I need another one? Well... \'cause the fleece has improved since I bought my first piece 30 years ago, a Patagonia shelled synchilla that won\'t quit, and because the fit of this thing is so ideal for me.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2938,'Pwplante',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'I could wear it everyday','So I bought this around january, during the coldest days of Quebec winter, in Canada. This shirt is so comfortable and warm, it was all that I looked for. I could wear it all time. It\'s cleary a must in wardrobe. It\'s perfect to wear around the house or at university library when temperature get a bit colder, and it does a nice job as bas',66,'2020-06-15'),(2939,'Ty1975',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Wish they made Oatmeal in Lightweight','I\'m a slim guy,6 ft 165 lbs. However,I\'d also really love to get a Synchilla in Oatmeal/Navy. Unfortunately,they only make that color for the regular Synchilla,which is far too boxy for my build. I dream one day that Patagonia designers will either make a slim-fit regular Synchilla,or will make an Oatmeal/Navy Lightweight Synchilla (which',66,'2020-06-15'),(2940,'Kurtastrophe',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Quintessential Pullover','Primary thoughts: This pullover is absolutely fantastic. It is incredibly warm, soft, and durable. The elastic hems keep in heat like no other fleece I\'ve owned. I am 6\'3 and 180 lbs and the large fits pretty well, although I have long arms, so the arms are admittedly too short. This is my only complaint-- I have a lightweight snap-T on w',66,'2020-06-15'),(2941,'Kirkwood',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Nice Fleece','Great fleece for fall/spring weather in the Upper Midwest. Provides plenty of warmth when you want to pop on a light yet warm layer for hiking,working around the yard or just walking around the city. Depending on how you like your fit the fleece runs pretty big. Slim/Athletic builds should definitely size down to achieve just a normal fit. At 6&#x2',66,'2020-06-15'),(2942,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great fleece','Great quality and warm. I\'m 6\'0\" 185lbs and went with the Medium based on reviews. I normally wear a large,but glad I went a size down. Medium fits perfectly',66,'2020-06-15'),(2943,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'good','comfortable. but fit\'s pretty weird. it\'s also very shiny. maybe i\'ll stick to solid colors from now on. it doesn\'t look like as it\'s shown in the pictures. also anyone know how to get the collar to spread apart (in a vshape so it doesn\'t hit my face)',66,'2020-06-15'),(2944,'Daniel E.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Best fleece ever.','Patagonia makes by far,hands down,the best fleece products on the market. There is something about them,especially this piece,which is the best one of them all for casual,every day use,that just emanates quality. It just feels solid,and it\'s unique,and you can just tell that care and passion was actually put into making it,and you know when yo',66,'2020-06-15'),(2945,'Ryan B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'The original, and still the best','I\'ve worn fleece jackets and pullovers most of my life (I developed an appreciation for the functionality of fleece while in Boy Scouts), but only recently did I discover the Snap-T. Over the past couple years, I\'ve come to own 4 originals and 2 lightweights, and my wife owns two (she only started buying them after seeing how much I loved',66,'2020-06-15'),(2946,'Ryan Z.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great for everything.','This is hands down the most comfortable item of clothing I own. It was a gift for christmas last month and even in Florida I have been looking for excuses to wear it as much as possible. I agree with other comment\'s that it runs a little large size-wise,I normally wear a L (6\',175,40-42\" chest) but upon seeing other comments I went w',66,'2020-06-15'),(2947,'Stani',NULL,'None','None',NULL,3.0,'Short Arms','This is a nice fleece,but the fit isn\'t quite what I would expect from Patagonia. I have patagonia shell jackets that are size M and fit me well,with plenty of length in the arms. I\'m 6\' 175lbs. I tried this on in the store and ended up buying a M. It fits great in the torso,but the arms are just too short and it\'s really annoyi',66,'2020-06-15'),(2948,'Jhnk',NULL,'None','None',NULL,2.0,'not \"relaxed\" this year','The Snap-T I bought this year is not my first or only one. I used to love the cut: hard-to-come-by,genuinely-baggy relaxed fit,loose through the arms and chest and sides so that it doesn\'t pull across the shoulder blades when you reach forward or hug around your own chest,and with enough give in the midsection not to pull or ride up even layin',66,'2020-06-15'),(2949,'Will M.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Best Fleece Ever','I got this for christmas and I have worn it everyday since. That is how great it really is. Keeps me warm down into the teens without wind and with a hoodie under it it is unstoppable. In Jonas (Blizzard of 2016), I wore it with a hoodie underneath and it kept me very warm. This thing is the best piece of clothing a person could ever by, plus it&#x',66,'2020-06-15'),(2950,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Perfect fleece for every day!','I received this fleece as gift for Christmas from my dad,and I absolutely adore it. I am about 5\'6\" and 150lbs and a small fits perfectly,not too big but not too small. He got me the Cave: Underwater Blue pattern and I adore everything about it. The sleeves are long that I can cover my hands,which I always do. We took a trip to the Nether',66,'2020-06-15'),(2951,'Z2000',NULL,'None','None',NULL,3.0,'Super warm but don\'t try to sleep in it','This is by far the warmest fleece I have ever owned. Only drawback is the thick seam lines around the upper rib cage which will dig into your side if you try to sleep on your side wearing it. I wear it around the house and it keeps me warm on cold winter days, but have to remember to take it off before I go to bed.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2952,'Brookelp',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'I got this fleece for','I got this fleece for my brother as a Christmas present and he loves it. He\'s around 6ft tall and 175 lbs. In most clothing he wears a large but after reading the reviews I got him the Medium and it fits perfectly! If you are normally a size Large looking for a more relaxed fit and for it to be a little big then I would recommend going with th',66,'2020-06-15'),(2953,'Sarah A.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Best fleece for interior AK','I\'ve lived in Fairbanks for the last 6 years and this jacket is by far the best fleece I\'ve owned. I commonly go for walks with a shirt and this fleece and I\'m perfectly comfortable down to 0 deg F (no wind chill). I have a big soft shell I put over this when I go snow machining. It\'s too warm for strenuous activities (ex choppi',66,'2020-06-15'),(2954,'Sunseed',NULL,'None','None',NULL,3.0,'Fine, but very \"relaxed\" fit','The materials and workmanship are, of course, great, but I wish the \"relaxed\" fit would have been more emphasized in the description. It will definitely limit my use of the jacket as it looks at least a size too big.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2955,'Jake D.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Very warm, but odd sizing','I wanted a very warm fleece, and this certainly fits the bill. If it\'s sunny and calm, this can keep you warm through the 40\'s if you are active. The sizing is a challenge, though. The \"relaxed\" fit translates into a very loose fit around the chest and shoulders. I normally wear large in Patagonia (and even then, some jackets ar',66,'2020-06-15'),(2956,'Fleece F.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Best sweater ever','This sweater is sooo comfortable, I feel like I\'m wearing a pyjamas all day! I don\'t feel like wearing anything else since I got it! This fleece is perfect under a shell as a winter coat, super toasty warm! I would love to have small pockets or a kangaroo style pocket for my hands. People say downsize but I love the fact that my medium is',66,'2020-06-15'),(2957,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Super Comfortable','Just got mine yesterday and it\'s super super comfortable and warm, makes me feel like a giant toasted marshmallow. DEFINITELY SIZE DOWN! It\'s huge. I\'m usually an L and bought an M, but even then it\'s rather roomy. Great for biking to class, walking around campus in the fall, and it could definitely handle the windy winters in t',66,'2020-06-15'),(2958,'Snowshark',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'SO COMFy','Bought this for my boyfriend as a gift in the arbor green pattern. I had no idea it would be so successful! He is about 5\'9 and 160 pounds with big shoulders. He likes his clothes to be roomy so he bought a large. It fits perfect, he is not swimming in it but it is roomy and unbelievably comfortable and soft. He has worn it backpacking and out',66,'2020-06-15'),(2959,'Betterthannew17',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Perfect Year Round Piece','This product is by far my favorite piece of gear I\'ve had the pleasure of owning from Patagonia. Truly one of the most versatile pieces you can own for all year round. Perfect for throwing over a t shirt on cool summer or spring nights, a great all day piece for fall, and great to throw over a sweatshirt or other base layer in the winter. I ow',66,'2020-06-15'),(2960,'Seth344',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Everyday pullover','Don\'t normally do this unless product is great. This product is great. I have one I bought years ago and just recently bought a second. I wear them everyday in the fall and winter. This is better than your favorite hoody. Worth the price.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2961,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'You are missing out! It\'s a must have.','I haven\'t ever written a review on any product but for this purchase, I had to. I just purchased 2 of the original Snap-T pullovers. I did quite a bit of research to see what other people were saying about them and they were swearing by them. I had to find out for myself. I purchased two with all intentions on only keeping one because of the p',66,'2020-06-15'),(2962,'Wildtroutchaser',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Minimalistic Comfort','Classic Patagonia. So comfortable, from hanging by the fire when temperatures drop yet able to use for layering when needed. Minimal in all the right ways.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2963,'Scoutworkz',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket perfect for fall','Great jacket and i love mine for walking to and from classes in the fall. Be aware though, in past seasons it has been recommended to buy down a size as they fit really big. However, this year this is not the case. BUY TRUE TO SIZE i bought one size down like my other jackets and it fit really tight, fit, but tight so i exchanged it for a size up, ',66,'2020-06-15'),(2964,'That G.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Do it','This sweater is amazing. I am rather short (5\'6\") but my shoulders are very broad and I usually have to wear a large. I fit perfectly in a medium. there is so much room in the chest and shoulders that I can move freely with out the sweater restricting my movements. Just buy one.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2965,'Gman337',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Perfecto','Purchased this bad boy in black and this thing is Amazing! Very comfortable and stylish while being simple and low-key and definately a lot thicker than I thought it would be. It Became one of my favorites after its first use. I wear a size Large for most Patagonia fits, and extra large for most slim fitting garments (5\'10\" 200lbs., 43&qu',66,'2020-06-15'),(2966,'Enforcey',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Runs large','I wear a size large for everything, however I just received my Synch Snap-T today and it is way too large. I am 5\'9, 195lbs. Reordered a Medium.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2967,'Patagoniy',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'I ordered this as a','I ordered this as a present for my boyfriend. Although I thought it was a different shade of green, he still ended up loving it and wearing the heck of out it! Thanks Patagonia for succeeding again!!',66,'2020-06-15'),(2968,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'best ever! (18yr old boy)','I freaking love this sweater. Its nice, warm and comfy. My girlfriend loves it to when im wearing it. Im wearing it all the time. Buy this fleece sweater!',66,'2020-06-15'),(2969,'Gmu S.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great Multipurpose Fleece','The Synchilla Pullover is a great multipurpose fleece that will keep you warm. Whether if its walking to class or going hiking in the mountains, it will keep you warm while wearing it standalone, or with a jacket like a wind breaker over it.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2970,'Patagonian2',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'It\'s beautiful','This fleece is amazing. Comfy, perfect fit, avid colors, and much more. This jacket will meet all of your needs. But I kinda wished that it had hand pockets but it\'s ok cause the warmth that stays in this fleece makes up for it. Buy this.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2971,'Photoguy94',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Awesome jacket.','This is my first Patagonia jacket purchase and I am so happy with it. Love the new pattern I got (but I liked the one from last year better...). This is ridiculously comfy and warm for a jacket that size and thickness. My one and only complaint is that it does not have pockets for my hands and that why I\'m giving 4 instead of 5 stars.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2972,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Most usable item I have!','I have had over a dozen Snap-Ts since they came out many years ago. Why so many? Several reasons: they are very portable, you can pack them into anything, they are warm, but not too warm, and I keep several different colours at different locations to insure there is one when I need it! One of the biggest reasons I have had to keep buying them is, t',66,'2020-06-15'),(2973,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Incredible!','With the Polar Vortex visiting yet again, I have not taken it off. It is super warm and crazy comfortable.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2974,'Tom N.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'snap T fleece','I wear a fleece almost everyday from fall to spring. I love the look and feel of the Patagonia fleece. It\'s a great layering piece and keeps me warm!',66,'2020-06-15'),(2975,'South T.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Men\'s Synchilla','This throw-over fleece is a great go-to when it\'s getting cold. I bought mine a size larger than my average t-shirt size specifically to be cozy and long enough when I\'m doing something physical (I\'m an AL, bought an XL). It\'s great. South Texas gets maybe two cold fronts every winter however I travel around and this fleece has',66,'2020-06-15'),(2976,'National',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Synchi Time Three','Well - this definitely was an eye catcher from the start. First my son saw it hanging up high in one of your stores and pointed to it and said - That\'s the one I want. Then a week goes by and my other son orders one on online. Then my husband says - Yeah - I want that too - So - we have 3 of the same synchilla sweater !!! It\'s warm and ju',66,'2020-06-15'),(2977,'Jesse97',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'oh so soft','this product keeps me real cozy on the sideline during games and practice',66,'2020-06-15'),(2978,'Maxamillion',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great Overall Piece','I have worn my fleece almost everyday since the first day they were in stores and I have to say it has held up to every challenge I have thrown at it. Whether it\'s being used as an outer layer to hold heat in and protect against wind, or as a mid layer to keep dry and stay warm, the Patagonia Synchilla Snap-T Pullover is the best fleece for an',66,'2020-06-15'),(2979,'Tmcc',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Overall Good','my only complaint is the sleeve holes were different sizes and i have to take it to the tailor.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2980,'Eque',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'still the go to pullover','A little lighter weight, a little different shoulder cut and the snap front doesn\'t hang collarish like in past year\'s models...that being said, if this had not been purchased to replace my long-time favorite that got ripped off, I\'d be lovin\' it for 5 stars...still my \"go to\" but miss my old friend...',66,'2020-06-15'),(2981,'Wmco',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Duribility and Warmth','I got my Patagonia Synchilla Snap-T over 20 years ago and I still wear it whenever it gets cold out, like today in Colorado. 11 F and I have my Patagonia pullover on over a t-shirt and doing my Christmas shopping. It keeps me warm in the cold and breaths inside so that I am always comfortable. You\'d think after 20 years I would need a new one.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2982,'Zozz',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Even Better than Expected','This jacket is beautiful. I purchased for my son and the quality and design are amazing. He hardly takes it off, so this purchase was even better than I expected. Patagonia is one of my family\'s top picks every year.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2983,'K P.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'In time for cooler weather','Excellent for layering and thus comfortable in a wide range of temperatures. Actually gets too warm if walking a long distance in weather over 45 degrees. Cheers.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2984,'Nick A.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Somewhat Pleased','I was very pleased with my purchase of the Synchilla, HOWEVER I was rather disappointed when after the 4th wear the stitching on the bottom started to come undone. I can now no longer wear the pullover with pear it will fray and the hem will come down. I have bought products from Patagonia before and am slightly disappointed with this malfunction.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2985,'Carey G.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'A true classic, but...','I love everything about the relaxed warmth of the Snap-T Pullover, and still having my first Snap-T from the early 90\'s (amongst a few newer models of the Snap-T) is a testament to it\'s design and construction.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2986,'Susancbmd',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Long lasting awesome','I\'ve had my warm and beautiful Snap-T since the early 1990s. My teenage son started \"borrowing\" it and so I had to get a new one for him. He\'s very happy with it and it looks great along with being well-made, toasty and comfortable. And durable!',66,'2020-06-15'),(2987,'Arthur F.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'M\'s Synchilla','Bought due to old time styling. Fits right and the pocket is useful. Colors pop for me and its not your same old standard looking pull-over.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2988,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great fleece','this is great for mildly cool weather. it\'s very comfortable and i get lots of comments on its looks. I\'m 5\'9 180 lbs with very wide shoulders and a large fits perfectly.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2989,'Scott V.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'My wife keeps poaching them','I purchase at least one every year (unless I can\'t find a color that I like). They are warm, comfortable, and are useful both for everyday use and for ski trips and climbing as well.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2990,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great pullover','This was an replacement purchase as my son \"stole\" my old one when he left for college. It does not disappoint. The same trusty quality and comfort you can always expect from Patagonia.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2991,'Still B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,2.0,'sizing not consistant with older fleece','I\'m a petite female that owns two of these pullovers in size XS. I\'ve worn them for years and felt I was overdue to acquire a new one. I was extremely disappointed to receive a new XS to find that the size is NOT equivalent of my old ones. The shoulders width is the same but it narrows considerably towards the waist. I had trouble getting',66,'2020-06-15'),(2992,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Looks Good!','I bought the Molten Lava size LG. I always take a size LG, but was a bit worried with some of the reviews saying it basically swallowed them up and to down size.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2993,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great pullover','This pullover is light but will also keep you super warm! It looks great so you can wear it out and also to work outside etc. I would definitely get this-it makes a great top layer in cold conditions and great under layer when it\'s super cold!',66,'2020-06-15'),(2994,'Dugefresh',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Very Heavy Fleece','Though this is much heavier than anticipated, it is well made and warm in cold weather. Very bulky for packing on a road trip is my only complaint. Runs a little large but looks great and keeps a dude real warm.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2995,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great pullover','I dig the throw back cut and the material is very cozy. It\'s a great layer to have while commuting.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2996,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great Fleece','I saw this Synchilla Snap T go on sale so I immediately ordered one. Even though I got mine on sale I would definitely pay the full price for it! I bought the Yanaba Molten Lava color variation and it looks awesome! Totally retro but still hip, that might be an oxymoron though. The collar is great, the pocket is great, the elastic sleeves and waist',66,'2020-06-15'),(2997,'Tx O.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'A classic','Had several over the years... Going on two seasons with this one, looks new and super comfy. Great for everything, and is my go-to around the house in winter since its so soft. Find myself wearing it mostly for casual use (have more technical pieces for active duty), though I\'m sure this would work great in any environment. Great mid-layer for',66,'2020-06-15'),(2998,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,1.0,'Disappointed','My snap t was worn once. The trim along the bottom is already starting to pill. I have been a life long customer and this garment was not up to standards. I am hoping the store will make it right.',66,'2020-06-15'),(2999,'Lpbob3',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Great color, warmth but two','Great color, warmth but two things, the loop to hang the fleece was so itchy had to cut it off and the pocket could be easier to go in and out of.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3000,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Well worth the price!!!','A great fleece! Very warm. Cuts the wind very well. I have worn various fleeces over the years. Not having pockets at the waist seemed a bit odd at first but I soon got used to it. The snap pocket is small, but is perfect for keys. Great quality.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3001,'Mini O.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Nice alternative to a sweater','Well made attractive alternative to a sweater. Matches up well with my black jeans.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3002,'Little M.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'50 year old\'s first Patagonia','I got this for my husband who has never worn patagonia before. He wanted a wool jacket but I knew better. I am not sure he has taken it off since Christmas day when he received it. The temperature has been between 8 and 25 degrees F. and he said the jacket is perfect for feeding horses, chickens, goats, dogs, and cats. Warm and still very movable.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3003,'Ariel1331',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'patterns','I love the pattern, but I wish it was available in female and kid sizes as well',66,'2020-06-15'),(3004,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Best Gift!','I bought this for my boyfriend for christmas and he absolutely loved it! I knew he would seeing as I\'ve had nothing but excellence with all my patagonia attire :)',66,'2020-06-15'),(3005,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Best Pullover','This is warm. looks very cool. Comfortable. Fit is good....not bulky.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3006,'A99879',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Size down','This is a very warm sweater that is super comfortable but it has a very odd fit. The sleeves are giant and bunch up underneath the armpits. I have a Patagonia Snap T from maybe about 8 years ago and it had a more normal cut. Regardless, this is a very comfortable fleece, but consider sizing down when ordering.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3007,'Nnn717',NULL,'None','None',NULL,1.0,'Super Baggy','I have ordered two Snap T\'s in the past and this year\'s version is extremely baggy. I am 6\'3\" 180 pounds and the large swallows me alive. I have two larges from a few years ago and they fit fine. This year\'s sizing is out of whack in comparison to past years. Not even sure if sizing down would be sufficient.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3008,'Jessmain',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'I Feel Like A Polar Bear','Although I\'m a lady (a quite small lady at that) I ordered this jacket in a medium and I couldn\'t be more happy with it. It\'s a bit baggy which is good because I can layer with it. The only problem is, this thing is hot as heck! Maybe I\'m just impatient for winter.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3009,'Gee G.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'An old favorite','I have been wearing your snap-ts for decades. Simply incredible!',66,'2020-06-15'),(3010,'Bluewater795',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'same old solid patty','Patagonia has this one right and constantly produces a very solid product. this is my third of this fleece and all of them have been put through a lot and always rise to the challenge. It stays quite warm when wet which is a huge plus',66,'2020-06-15'),(3011,'Stefjob',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'nice clothes','fashionable, useful and colorful.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3012,'Savage H.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,3.0,'Very, Very Baggy','I used to LOVE the Snap-T, but this year\'s version is very, very baggy. I\'m 6\'0\" 145 lbs. and ordered a small. The torso length and sleeve length were both great, but the chest and arms were so loose it was basically unwearable. Even with a heavy sweatshirt underneath it, I had 6-8\" of extra arm fabric, which bunched up aro',66,'2020-06-15'),(3013,'Luuuuukkkkkeeeee',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Warm & Snuggly','I realized that, living in San Francisco, I needed something warm and versatile. I have definitely found that in this fleece. It\'s super warm and comfy. What people say about the fit is totally true: it runs very big. I\'m usually a Medium and so picked that up but, if I were to buy again, I would go for the Small.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3014,'Dan K.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Wonderfully warm','This pullover puts every other fleece item I have to shame. It is wonderfully warm, and comfortable. I would prefer a zipper to the snaps on the opening - the snaps can be a little difficult to close. But otherwise, a great item.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3015,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Love it!','This pullover is like a cozy hug! Just the right thing to come home to when it\'s chilly. I teach skiing at Squaw Valley and look forward to cuddling up in it at the end of the day',66,'2020-06-15'),(3016,'Gregory S.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Very warm, versatile','This jacket is very warm, yet breathable. It\'s ideal for spring or fall (if you live in the Midwest). The snaps are so great for allowing more or less air depending on the temperature.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3017,'Erumbaugh',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'One of my favorite fleece garments.','I\'m outdoors a lot and generally have a fleece with me either on me or in my bag. I\'ve owned several competitors to this fleece and keep coming back to this one. The \"denali\" is often too heavy, and expensive. The \"tech jacket\" is great with it\'s wind blocker if it\'s windy but leaves me wanting in the warmth',66,'2020-06-15'),(3018,'Thatch',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Absolute Quality','I LOVE this fleece and look forward to wearing it the rest of my life. Well until i pass it down to my kid (lol not even married yet but all the same, looking forward to it). I remember my Dad having a patagonia fleece and for some crazy reason he through it away after many years of faithful service. I never plan on getting rid of mine. Annnndddd m',66,'2020-06-15'),(3019,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great Fleece','I bought this fleece about a month ago and I have rarely taken it off since. It breaths well and yet keeps you very warm. The fleece is also incredibly soft and the fit is roomy and comfortable. My only complaint is that it does not do all that well in wind, but that is to be expected with any fleece really. Amazing product, I am sure I will be buy',66,'2020-06-15'),(3020,'Oakley',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Warm and comfortable','Wearing this fleece is like putting on your favorite sweatshirt...its warm, cozy, and comfortable. If you are looking for wind protection, this fleece is not what you need but for a warm layer underneath or a cozy fleece between seasons, this is a great item. Love it.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3021,'Patrick J.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great but awaiting first washing','Color: Red. Really really bright red.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3022,'Brendan M.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'all good and future feedback','i dig this retro reissue peice - but i do wish it had hand pockets in the update of the design',66,'2020-06-15'),(3023,'Arnie',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Warm comfortable and looks good','great, It wears like iron and is warm and looks good',66,'2020-06-15'),(3024,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Snap T','Great shirt/sweatshirt. The fleece is very dense. You could wear this as a jacket in cool temperatures, or use it as a layer in very cold temps.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3025,'Retired2007',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Snap-T','Have owned several snap-t\'s over the years. They don\'t wear out, just get passed along to another when I think I need a new one. Each new version seems to be better than the previous version. I\'m a ski patroller and this is the best mid-layer. Keeps me comfortable in a whole range of conditions and weather.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3026,'Dagtheturntable',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'M\'s Snap T Pullover','The reliable standby Patagonia classic used for anything. My original (L) is still going strong after 20 years. NOTE: I purchased a new one this fall and the sizes have gotten much larger. I returned my (L) for a (M) and the (M) fit fine and is the same size as my 20-year old (L). I am 5\'10\", 170 lbs with lean athletic build, wide shoulde',66,'2020-06-15'),(3027,'Vicky S.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Perfect in every way','I am a huge fan of the newer version on the Snap-T. I have one for myself, one for my daughter and one for my husband. Everyone loves it! Beautiful. Washable. Cozy. And long-lasting. I love the complimentary trim as well. Highly recommend for sitting by the fire, taking long fall walks, cross country skiing, etc.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3028,'Brain D.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'I thought you guys were outta business forever...','I\'m 19 and my father has a sizable collection of Patagonia apparel. Until about five years ago, I thought (with dread) that Patagonia was out of business because me father never purchased anything new from them for as long as I\'ve been around!',66,'2020-06-15'),(3029,'Mrawesome',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Its awsome','Warm an fuzzy. Nice look. Makes you look rich and important',66,'2020-06-15'),(3030,'Collinss',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great gift','Purchased this as a gift for my 16 year old son. He loves it. It is great on dark cold mornings while waiting for the bus, after swim practice and while reading a book. I can\'t wait till he out grows it so it can become mine.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3031,'Chana F.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'M\'s Synchilla\' Snap-T\' Pullover','OMG!!! The color of my son\'s M\'s Synchilla\' Snap-T\' Pullover is ELECTRIC but he loves it. So glad we bought the Glowing Ember jacket. In his words . . . \"I got SWAG now\"',66,'2020-06-15'),(3032,'Marys',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'great christmas gift','very warm and comfortable and stylish- great fit- this was a gift for my daughter',66,'2020-06-15'),(3033,'Cod S.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Snap-Ts over the years','I bought my first Snap-T in the 80\'s. I still have it, it\'s egg plant with green trim. I\'m wearing it now. Since then I have bought 5 more. If I need to wear a sweater, it\'s a Sanp-T. The one I bought last month was for my wife. I get her men\'s because she likes the pocket. She now has 3 of them going back back to the 80&#x',66,'2020-06-15'),(3034,'Lydia P.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'warms you up','I bought this top for my son to wear in my large house that gets quite cold in the winter- 64 degrees! He loves it and it keeps him very warm!',66,'2020-06-15'),(3035,'Kallen71',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Go-to gear that keeps going...','I bought my first Snap-T Pullover 17 years ago. It is starting to show some signs of its regular go-to use (and abuse?) but still still looks, wears and feels great. Kudos to building such a durable and functional garment. I hope to still be wearing it in another 17 years! Everybody should have one of these versatile layers in their wardrobe.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3036,'Elfederiley',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Classic','Patagonia\'s classic layer.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3037,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great Classic!','I had one of these for at least 10 years until I unfortunately left it on a train last Spring. Over the years it had been my main winter garment, and I decided that I just could not do without it, so I replaced it recently with exactly the same one, color and all! I find it to be cozy, warm, and universal. In black it can even serve in a dressy sit',66,'2020-06-15'),(3038,'Chickaree',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'soft and comfy','i bought this because i love patagonia fleece, it keeps me warm even when the material gets a bit damp, and the bright blue color is really the thing to spruce up my wardrobe.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3039,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Best jacket','Have been wearing the synchilla pullover since I can remember and they last forever. Whether your running around town or going out you can always wear your pullover....I recommend this to everyone!!!',66,'2020-06-15'),(3040,'Hoosfan224',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Couldn\'t Be Happier','I bought this pullover primarily to wear for crew, but it has quickly become my favorite piece of clothing out of anything I own. Super warm, super durable, super dependable, and the best part is that it looks great. I can\'t even count how many compliments I\'ve gotten over the past few weeks. The bottom line is that I know this fleece wil',66,'2020-06-15'),(3041,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Excellent','I own three of the snap-t\'s and love them. I also own a similar snap by llbean, but I must say, the snap-t outweighs the llbean by far. During the winter, I wear one of my three every day, and I am planning on buying more as I go off to college. Not only are they warm, but they are comfortable as well and can be worn with anything! I also love',66,'2020-06-15'),(3042,'Scott F.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Might be the best product ever','Seriously, has there been a more perfectly designed and executed piece of clothing than the Snap-T? I\'ve got two of them. One is about 20 years old. It is ratty and threadbare and beloved. My wife ordered a new one for me, so I\'d look more presentable in the winter, spring and fall (or as I call it Patagonia Fleece season). Don\'t tel',66,'2020-06-15'),(3043,'Anonymous',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Synchilla Snap T\'s','I bought both a black one and a blue one 10-12 years ago and have worn them all over the world. I love them. So I finally got around to adding 2 more colors. I wear them to work, to play, to travel. And when it snows, you simply need a shell. Perfect!',66,'2020-06-15'),(3044,'Anonymous',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Quality for Generations','This garment was purchased for my daughter for Christmas. She starts the 3rd generation of Snap T wearers in our family! This is a real keeper in the Patagonia line. Typically the colors are better in the men\'s line so we adjust the sizes to buy for our female family members.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3045,'Burgerz',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Absolute Clothing Staple','This pullover is fantastic. It is exceptionally warm, yet still light enough to wear under a shell. This is something everyone should have in their closet.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3046,'Donn',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'I have three','...and it may be enough. This is as influential a piece of clothing as has ever been made. I got my first the first season they were made, when pile (scratchy, drafty) and bunting (the pill-i-est fabric ever) were the only other \"fleeces\" there were. I got my second not long after; then my third...it\'s the first thing on when I hit t',66,'2020-06-15'),(3047,'Alexm',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'After 20 years, buying my second one','You could say I\'m a little tight with a buck, but when I spend them I prefer quality. I\'ve had my first snap t fleece for almost 20 years I think. It\'s travelled through many many adventures, and with the exception of one small hole I tore on a nail, and a cuff finally beginning to fray, it\'s perfect! This is one quality piece o',66,'2020-06-15'),(3048,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great Pullover','Excellent pullover. Great for staying warm on a crisp autumn day. You will definitely find uses for this fleece all throughout the winter months. The Snap-T is comfortable and is sized to be worn over a heavy sweater.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3049,'Sib H.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Always On','This is the best piece Patagonia makes. I live in an old drafty house so first thing in the morning it\'s freezing until the fire gets going. I put this on first thing, the cold is gone. I use this as my primary gear for hiking in the winter and skiing on sunny days. The only issue is my dog sheds and the hairs are hard to remove. My next one w',66,'2020-06-15'),(3050,'Ne F.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Awesome Fleece','I really love these Snap-T fleeces. This is my second and I wear it almost daily. Thicker and warmer than you think and I get compliments regularly. I fish for winter steelhead in this and then wear it to work. Looks great with jeans.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3051,'Herm',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Still good as ever','I own about half dozen of this garment.I love the new colors and try to stay abreast of the new ones.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3052,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Amazing','This is the best fleece I have ever owned. It stands up to the chilly Colorado nights, works great for layering, and the snap pocket is perfect for holding an extra beer. I have had mine for almost two years and it still seems brand new even though I wear it daily. This is a style and a product that is very versatile and stands the test of time. Bu',66,'2020-06-15'),(3053,'Tbvaden',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Truly Great Product','As with many on here...the Synchilla Snap-T was the first of many Patagonia items I have owned over the years. I have 4 of them, and the original is just as good as the day it was bought (1995?). Timeless, classic Patagonia style, comfort, and quality. Everyone should have at least one of these.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3054,'Balmer B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Make sure you like the color you choose','I bought mine in 1993 and it\'s still going strong. Very versatile, I sleep in it, wear it out and about, etc. and it seems to fit in in all situations. The fit is a bit on the bigger side, so if you like a more trim fit and are on the border, I\'d size down.',66,'2020-06-15'),(3055,'Dhosk',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great piece','The Synch Snap-T Pullover is a Patagonia Classic. It can be used as a sweater, coat, and as a great layering piece. It\'s stylish enough to wear around town and tough enough for abuse in the mountains. It traps in the heat very efficiently and wears well over the years. It\'s so comfortable and toasty you never want to take it off!',66,'2020-06-15'),(3056,'Maxwell',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'AK approved','The jacket works super well in Anchorage, AK winter casual, and primo for extra insulation on hiking trips. Warm, light and breathable make this one of my go to jackets. Pros; exceptional material. Now Cons. Sewing cut little holes for direct air currents outside to in, not ideal for retaining heat during cold AK wind snaps. Not as compact compared',32,'2020-06-15'),(3057,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,3.0,'Perfect color !','Whats up with the pockets location in this jacket? Feels weird! Is that normal ?? Or Something is wrong with mine that I just received today !',32,'2020-06-15'),(3058,'Alan',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,3.0,'Not very durable','I\'ll start by saying this is a great jacket that is warm and very comfortable however it isn\'t as durable for heavy use during climbing or hiking. I\'ve owned this for one season and already have three holes from catching on briers while hiking and brushing up against rock during cold climbing sessions. The material the shell is made',32,'2020-06-15'),(3059,'Mike D.',NULL,'5\'0 or less','NB-7lb',NULL,4.0,'Better for layering than by itself','A good warm, lightweight and breathable under layer for cold days that packs down well. But I prefer my old Nano Puff for casual or everyday wear. The pockets on this higher than normal to reduce bulk if you have stuff in you puffy and your shell pockets. That makes them less functional for everyday use. I also have issues with the collar always st',32,'2020-06-15'),(3060,'Frank',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,3.0,'Sweet jacket in serious need of a redesign','This is a great lightweight, warm jacket but the neck and bottom hem are in serious need of a redesign. I bought a M which fit great except for two things:',32,'2020-06-15'),(3061,'Glenn',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','18-24m',NULL,5.0,'The BEST lightweight warmest jacket','Best lightest jacket ever owned. So warm for being so lightweight.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3062,'Lukas',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','0',NULL,5.0,'Micropuff','As a big mountain ski coach I find myself standing still on the mountain during competitions and line scouting for long periods of time (anywhere from -5 degree F days to 25 degree and windy days). On the flip side there are times I am hiking for long periods of time. I needed a light weight, ultra pack-able, toasty warm jacket that I could pack aw',32,'2020-06-15'),(3063,'Sprezzaturamoda',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Warm synthetic jacket with style','This jacket is no thicker than a sweater, but it warms the body like a down jacket and blocks the wind like a breathable soft-shell, and it looks stylish. It can handle temperatures down to low forties by itself without any layers with just a cotton t-shirt, and with a layer it can definitely handle temperatures down to subzero, and maybe a little ',32,'2020-06-15'),(3064,'Kimberly W.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L/XL',NULL,5.0,'Great design','Very warm. Perfect weight and interesting quilting design.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3065,'Matthew H.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,3.0,'Super warm but awkward neck','This is by far the warmest Patagonia jacket I’ve owned but the neck pokes me in a strange way that has become bothersome. The neck sides sit straight up and become irritating. I should have spent $50 more and got the hooded version.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3066,'Stephen G.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'perfect weight and fit. I\'m','perfect weight and fit. I\'m 5\'11\", 155 pounds wearing an M',32,'2020-06-15'),(3067,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'love it','So light and soft I could wear this all the time, makes me sad to take it off. It is expensive but with a lifetime warranty and excellent customer service it\'s well worth it.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3068,'Tom C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Very warm jacket','I would give it 5 stars but the collar is a bit uncomfortable as it won’t fold down.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3069,'Josh F.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Very warm, and extremely light','Very warm, and extremely light and compact',32,'2020-06-15'),(3070,'Michael m.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'awesome light weight jacket that','awesome light weight jacket that packs great and is very warm. great for those trips during the in between seasons.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3071,'John W.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Another Awesome Patagonia Jacket','I bought this jacket to replace a my favorite jacket that was damaged by a very exuberant and very large puppy with sharp claws who was happy to greet me. I\'ll have to thank the puppy because this jacket is better than the one I\'m replacing! Great fit (although a little tight in the chest), warm, super light, comfortable and stylish. I&#x',32,'2020-06-15'),(3072,'Paul L.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XS',NULL,5.0,'Good product','Good product',32,'2020-06-15'),(3073,'Michael L.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Micro Puff Jacket','This jacket is light and super comfy, very warm for its weight. I have a very well-worn nano puff jacket that I love and will still use for work, but this piece feels warmer for same weight. The Micro Puff holds shape better, not as loose, I hardly know I have it on. The one complaint: the collar. It\'s a bit stiff up against the chin, and if n',32,'2020-06-15'),(3074,'Milestoner',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'i love this jacket','I’m 5’11” and 155lbs. I purchased the medium sized peppergrass green, to act as an insulator/mid layer to my galvanized shell. fits perfect! nice and warm, and allows lots of movement too. i haven’t worn it much to give it a good review but my first impressions are positive. definitely satisfied with the purchase.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3075,'thomas w.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Super light.','A technical wonder. Wish there were a few more pockets. I am 6’ 175 pounds and returned the medium for a large which I am very happy with.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3076,'Nicholas K.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','NB-7lb',NULL,1.0,'Poor Quality','The jacket I received was poor in quality, lacking proper zipping functions, as well as having multiple strings come out of the stitching of the fabric.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3077,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Love it!','Love it!',32,'2020-06-15'),(3078,'Neal K.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,3.0,'May need to exchange. Size','May need to exchange. Size M has 2 chest sizes but couldn’t select the larger one when ordering online. It’s a little snug.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3079,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Love it!','Love all your products but this one is exceptional',32,'2020-06-15'),(3080,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Light and warm!','Absolutely love this jacket! Very light and warm and not restrictive! I wish the collar was a little different however. Love everything else other than the collar.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3081,'Mike H.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,2.0,'Changed size of medium jacket','Neck is cut way to high and I do not have a short neck. Jacket should be labeled medium extra long neck and potbelly due to excessive room in stomach area. Gave it 2 stars instead of one since workmanship was good just fire the designer.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3082,'Kaan G.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,4.0,'Great Product, but can be awesome','I love the Micro Puff Jacket! Warm, wind/water resistant, and stylish. One thing I noticed was if you overheat in it for any reason (mine was biking) since the jacket isn\'t super breathable it is hard to release excess heat. I know wind resistant products compromise breathability, but maybe as a design suggestion, you could try pit zips to qui',32,'2020-06-15'),(3083,'Eric V.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,1.0,'Tiny arms','Love the jacket. But the arms are too tight to wear over a t-shirt. Literally was squeezing my elbows to the point of discomfort. The rest of the jacket fit great though.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3084,'william w.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,4.0,'Great jacket could be cheaper','I like the jacket a lot but it\'s mighty expensive. Should be cheaper like common',32,'2020-06-15'),(3085,'Sathyan M.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Awesome, functional and fashionable.','Awesome, functional and fashionable.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3086,'Mike H.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M/L',NULL,5.0,'Very warm for its weight','Very impressed with the warmth of this light weight puff. After dealing with a Denver snowstorm followed by a Bend snowstorm, I couldn\'t be happier with my purchase. Kept me warm even in windy, cold conditions!! I\'m 6\' 1.5\" and 175 and wear a large.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3087,'Ben S.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'Great Lightweight Warmth','Great jacket for layering on cold days. Tested under a PowSlayer shell and over a base layer/t-shirt for for 3 days of alpine skiing in BC with temps hovering in the mid-teens to low-20s. Lightweight/no bulk. Really comfortable. Breathed well, kept dry inside. Fabric is deceptively sturdy - despite opportunities, did not snag, etc. Definitely a new',32,'2020-06-15'),(3088,'John F.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Only missing one thing','If it had a chest phone pocket it would be supper',32,'2020-06-15'),(3089,'jackson l.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,5.0,'Perfect Lightweight Warmth & Layering for Cooler Temps','Comfort, warmth, style, versatility and easy care are top priorities for me and the Micro Puff Jkt hits all those points for me. The water and wind resistance is a total plus and it\'s great for layering beneath a shell like the Quandary Jkt.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3090,'Jose O.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Micro Puff Jacket (Hoodie)','Great all around jacket, warm and very comfortable. Also there\'s enough room to wear a base and mid layer to keep you warm in 0-30 degree weather.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3091,'Scott C.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,2.0,'Weird Fit','Not sure exactly what they did with the design but it has a strange seam running up/around the arm/shoulder, which made it uncomfortable to wear. Loved everything else, but had to return it for the poor fit.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3092,'Bella Z.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,5.0,'This is my 4th purchase','i have 2 of these jackets myself, i also bought one for my highschool kid and 1 for my husband. They are so light and yet so warm. i\'m wearing it in 25 degree wisconsin weather.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3093,'Mark B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Micro-Puff Jacket As per the description','I have owned a number of Patagonia down jackets over the years. This I would rate right up there. It is indeed exactly as described - a lot of warmth in not a lot of bulk. Fits really well - I bought a size L and am 6ft tall and 200lbs. Ripstop fabric and the panelling make for a stylish look too!',32,'2020-06-15'),(3094,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Great Jacket','Super comfy and warm, packs down small and layers very comfortably under a rain jkt. It fits slightly big but I am between sizes.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3095,'Jeremy S.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','NB-7lb',NULL,5.0,'Love It So Far','This is my first ever Patagonia Jacket. I love the Micro Puff so far. It\'s lightweight and warm. I have worn it in temps 20-50 degrees and been comfortable. I recommend it!',32,'2020-06-15'),(3096,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Quickly became my “go to” when the temperature dropped.','Very surprised at how warm this light weight and comfy zippered sweater really is!. The design has elastic cuffs that seal out the cold and the neck zips up snugly to my chin. I own a small coffee roasting company and have been enjoying the non restrictive feel while driving and the cozy warm it offers while outside delivering to customers during r',32,'2020-06-15'),(3097,'Jeffrey S.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Great fit & warmth','This jacket is a great jacket on it\'s own or a layer under another jacket. Warm and fits perfectly',32,'2020-06-15'),(3098,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Perfect Jacket','The most versatile warm jacket. My most recent hiking trip took me through temperatures between 55 and 27. This jacket kept me warm in the cold, and packed into a light item clipped to my bag while it was warm. Patagonia nailed this one.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3099,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Very light and warm','Very light and warm',32,'2020-06-15'),(3100,'Daniel P.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Light weight and great warmth','Light weight and great warmth makes for unbeatable combination. Bonus - takes minimal space when packing!',32,'2020-06-15'),(3101,'Myrna C.',NULL,'5\'0 or less','S',NULL,5.0,'Micro puff jacket','Size and color are great. Live in Montana so it\'s great by it self in this fall weather and I\'ll use it as a layer under an outer shell as it gets colder. Also like how easy it is to pack into backpack. Thank you!',32,'2020-06-15'),(3102,'Arash B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket, size a bit funky','Great jacket, runs a little large. I\'m always a medium but this one was a bit too long for me so I opted for a small. It\'s a bit tight but I\'m keeping it because it\'s such a great jacket',32,'2020-06-15'),(3103,'Harold M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Men\'s Micro Puff Jacket','A lightweight comfortable, warm jacket that can be worn either as a base layer or as an outerwear.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3104,'James E.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','ML',NULL,5.0,'I can\'t believe the warmth','I can\'t believe the warmth for the light weight. Keep getting compliments from my friends in the outdoors crowd.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3105,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Nice!','Totally new Puff and better in everyway than the previous version. Significantly warmer, lighter and a slightly better pattern. Well worth the up grade for me.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3106,'Eddie W.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Light weight warmth','This is my second Micro Puff jacket. I wear it to work, hiking, skiing, and out for beer. If it weren’t bright RED I’d probably wear it to Church on Sunday. Durable, comfortable, light weight and warm. And as always Patagonia quality.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3107,'Clare G.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Perfect for everything','bought for my grandfather and he can\'t take it off. lives in the unpredictable weather of colorado front range; it\'s his go-to everything jacket in snow and in cold, but sunny weather too.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3108,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,5.0,'Super light!','Wondered about this - being so light I wasn\'t sure how it would compare to my Nano Puffs. Seems to be very close in performance and quite a bit lighter! Excellent piece for the pack as a spare layer with near zero weight penalty.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3109,'Tim G.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XXL',NULL,5.0,'So warm n light.','It\'s amazing how light n warm this thing is!',32,'2020-06-15'),(3110,'Brad G.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Great price and efficiency of','Great price and efficiency of ordering was awesome!',32,'2020-06-15'),(3111,'Kevin B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Now my favorite','For the comparison, I own a Nano Puff jacket—same size and purchased the same year. I was so happy with the Nano that I decided I wanted to try the Micro.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3112,'Jarek P.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Cool color','Very nice, light and packable item. Great colors.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3113,'Larry',NULL,'None','S',NULL,4.0,'Poetic Color Naming Gets in the Way (of an otherwise great coat)','I’m a slim guy who wanted a light puffy for general use and additional packable insulation to bring when crewing on a sailboat club races. I think it’s a great coat with minimal features and bulk. BUT when I ordered a “carbon” color, I expected some shade of gray. NOPE! It’s green. Let’s just do away with “poetry” in color naming and just use plain',32,'2020-06-15'),(3114,'John S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Lite layer','Fits, looks good. Not to puffy looking in cold.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3115,'Victor T.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,1.0,'Bring back the old design','New jacket arms are super narrow at the elbow. Unbearable. Set it back for a refund.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3116,'Robert A.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Love the light weight and','Love the light weight and warmth',32,'2020-06-15'),(3117,'Dino B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Nice light, packable jacket','Good jacket, ideal for temperatures in the mid 40\'s to mid to low 30\'s Fahrenheit (0 to about 10 Celsius for the rest of the world). If you are in extreme cold conditions, could be used as a layer with heavier jacket on top.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3118,'Sean V.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Currently only had the jacket','Currently only had the jacket for a month. I have worn it for hiking and casual walks. When hiking it\'s way to warm to wear during the fall months here in the PNW. It\'s almost too warm for a casual walk also. I took it out in 20F temps the other day and it was just about right. I\'m amazed at how warm this jacket keeps me while still',32,'2020-06-15'),(3119,'Jake B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Micro Puff Jacket','Minimal, fits under or over most clothes. Nice warmth. Runs hot in the armpits. Stash pockets on inside are a plus. Everyday wear.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3120,'Kyle A.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Great Balance of Heat and Cool','This jacket doesn\'t make you hot to the point where your sweating in it just wearing it. It does a good job of keeping you not cold. This allows you to wear it for long times inside without having to take it off and its very good outside in the cold. I wear it almost every day.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3121,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Micro Puff','Great jacket and fit. Best of all is the customer service',32,'2020-06-15'),(3122,'Seth M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,1.0,'Ugly','Material looks like a shiny trash bag and quilted weave pattern doesn’t flatter the style. It looks like Patagonia is trying to differentiate themselves from competitors to much. When holding the jacket up to light, you’re able to see light through the poorly sewn stiching.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3123,'Alex M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Awesome puffy jacket','I purchased a new puffy jacket from Patagonia and it is everything my friends made it out to be. Such a warm and cozy jacket in such a small package.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3124,'Larry G.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L/XL',NULL,5.0,'Micro Puff is awesome','The Micro Puff jacket was everything I had hoped it would be. Super light and comfortable. I will use it primarily as a mid layer for skiing. The less bulk the more freedom of movement. I look forward to many years of use.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3125,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,5.0,'What the Puff!?!','Micro weight ✔️',32,'2020-06-15'),(3126,'Brad S.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,4.0,'Nice Coat','Great color, seems very warm, hasn’t been real cold yet. The neck takes some getting used to, not sure I like it as it’s very long. Zipper is up on my cheek all the time. I thought that was fixed based upon reviews I had read?',32,'2020-06-15'),(3127,'Brendan R.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,2.0,'Sizing','Unfortunately, with the large, the sleeves are too short despite the torso and shoulder sizing being perfect for my 6’3” stature. I have had this common problem with most long sleeve Patagonia products except for the nano storm stretch jacket. I was hopeful it would work as I’ve heard great reviews. I’ll be exchanging it for a vest.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3128,'David E.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Puff the Magic Jacket','Very nice. Love it.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3129,'Thomas B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Nice Jacket with just a couple of minor design flaws for ME','Ok to specify, this is likely the perfect jacket for a wide range of people. In my case it was almost perfect. It is light, easy to pack, warm when on, etc... My only recommendations would be to widen the arms at the elbow. When I am driving or have my arms bent more than 20 degrees, the jacket becomes constricting at my elbow. the rest of the arms',32,'2020-06-15'),(3130,'Marcel G.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,4.0,'Good addition','Nice light weight layer that is good on the go.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3131,'Patrick F.',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,5.0,'The warmth is real.','6\'2\", 205 lbs, athletic, XL fits great. An incredible piece, so much warmth. Moves with my body without being made of stretchy material. The red is a such an attractive shade.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3132,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Wonderful purchase. Using it on','Wonderful purchase. Using it on trip to Spain and Portugal. Love it!',32,'2020-06-15'),(3133,'David R.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Best piece of gear made','Best piece of gear made by Patagonia',32,'2020-06-15'),(3134,'Greg B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Great fit','Great fit',32,'2020-06-15'),(3135,'Timothy C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Great jacket but collar','The jacket is amazing for weight and warmth. But the collar is always popping up, which is nice on the slopes but not for everyday activities. Either Way I would buy Again and recommend to others.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3136,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Updated Men\'s Micro Puff® Jacket Fits Perfect','I had purchased a Fall 2018 version of the Micro Puff and had to send it back due to the tightness of the collar when zipped all the way up. It actually was chocking me and was a bad design. Many other reviews had stated the same thing. After seeing some new colors available I called customer service and they said the 2019 version addressed the tig',32,'2020-06-15'),(3137,'Chris H.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Micro Puff Jacket - Excellent','Extremely comfortable and easy to wear. Love it!',32,'2020-06-15'),(3138,'Johnathan Y.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Love the new jacket','I get compliments on it all the time from nano puff jacket wearers. They love the design for the insulation. The jacket is my go-to this fall. Highly recommend.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3139,'Roam Y.',NULL,'None','L/XL',NULL,5.0,'Very Nice Jacket','I love almost every Patagonia product I’ve purchased, but I’m really fond of this jacket. Light, warm, sturdy, it does it all!',32,'2020-06-15'),(3140,'Ryan G.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XXL',NULL,1.0,'Micro puff jacket','I wore this coat to a 50 degree soccer game and froze. Not nearly as warm as advertised.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3141,'Gail M.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,4.0,'Micro puff jacket','Love the sleeve design and the pockets. Do not like the neck design, it does not drape well when worn part way open',32,'2020-06-15'),(3142,'Saul P.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Nice and light and warm','Only complaint is that the collar is a little high when zipped up.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3143,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Micro Puff','So far so good. Extremely light weight and packable. Haven\'t had cold weather yet to test the warmth.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3144,'Eunji L.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Haven\'t worn yet, but loving it','I bought Star Pink color. color is so pretty. Wanna buy the light Violet color too! it fits well and I instantly feel warm when I wear it.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3145,'Kenneth H.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XXL',NULL,3.0,'Neck Too Tight','Tried this on and neck was uncomfortably high and tight. Put it back in the bag and returned it. I love Patagonia gear but they need to rethink design on this one.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3146,'K J.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'lightweight and warm','typically wear women\'s S (5\'7\" and 138) -- but with Patagonia\'s trend to run smaller and desire to be able to layer sized up to M. Its a bit loose around chest, but overall good. Husband\'s jacket was typical size M and fit well.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3147,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Men’s Micro Puff','Great fit, love the jacket.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3148,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Always on call!','My Micro Puff won\'t last long. It\'s my \'GO TO\' for all occasions jacket, and I can always find it in one of my cars, if it\'s not on my back. I wore out my Nano Puff and this is it\'s replacement, and is fully employed. It fits just right for an all-around!',32,'2020-06-15'),(3149,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'excellent jacket','The quality of the jacket feels amazing. Cant wait till its gets colder to really put the jacket to the test',32,'2020-06-15'),(3150,'Paul J.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'micro nano-puff jacket','great piece to add to my work and travel collection',32,'2020-06-15'),(3151,'Chad C.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Micro puff jacket','The weight to warmth ratio is the best i’ve so far. I spend most of my time in a damp environment so down is not ideal. Still warm when wet and paired with a nano air light provides plenty of flexibility if your worried about being to cold or too warm.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3152,'Gavin M.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'The perfect jacket','I love everything Patagonia makes but this one \"it took us ten years and we came up with nothing\" is really perfect. SUPER light weight and yet warm and cozy, packs down into nothing and fits perfectly. Used it for just about all my flights during the Red Bull X-Alps, the \"toughest adventure race on Earth\" for nearly two weeks i',32,'2020-06-15'),(3153,'Christopher D.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Terrific item.','First and most important to me, the representative was terrific in helping me pick the right shell from among the variety of similar garments. Second, the shell fits, works, breathes and garners compliments for its appearance. I am completely satisfied.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3154,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Awesome jacket','Have loved this jacket so far. Fits well and has convenient pockets on the inside and outside. Great color too (dark green)!',32,'2020-06-15'),(3155,'Bill K.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Producyt exceeds the hype','With the ever changing climatic challenges in the Northern Rockies, the Miocro Puff jacket manages most anyu of Mother Nature’s tricks. From early mornng chills on the water fly fishing to all day hikes that challenge you to our 4 season days - cold, rain, snow and chilly sun… this feather light jacket packs up super small and its very tough outer',32,'2020-06-15'),(3156,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,3.0,'Micro Puff','I love the color. I do like the jacket overall.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3157,'Luong522',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Warm & Stylish','The micro puff definitely fits the bill. Lightweight, keeps me warm and not too bulky.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3158,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Nano puff','Great light weight jacket',32,'2020-06-15'),(3159,'Chris L.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Easily my favorite jacket ever','I bought this jacket having only owned one other down sweater. I don\'t know that I have ever put on something more comfortable warm, and lightweight than this jacket. This jacket is awesome.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3160,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,5.0,'What a jacket!','Just took this on its first trip, a shoulder season trek in NZ (Kepler Track). I am so impressed with this jacket. It is incredibly light and unbelievably warm for its weight and bulk - I can scarcely believe it\'s not down, except it somehow seems even warmer than a down jacket of this weight. It was perfect for the single-digit (celcius) lows',32,'2020-06-15'),(3161,'Allen H.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,4.0,'When not in use lives in my backpack for those times I need an added layer','I have been using the micropuff for the past 3 months predominantly as a layer for ski patrolling in PNW. Love the compressibility since it’s off and on and in and out of my pack with changes of weather. As far as warmth by itself I find it a bit light probably best in mid 40s plus but then I run cold. I also have a nano puff which I love. I would',32,'2020-06-15'),(3162,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,1.0,'Collar way too restrictive and high. Check the model picture, fully zipped this is the most uncomfortable thing ever! I bought the vest as well and wo','Check the model picture, fully zipped this is the most uncomfortable thing ever! Even without it zipped it just sits too high. I bought the vest as well and wore them both before really realizing that this is just really poor design. So bummed, since I owned the nano puff previously I didn\'t give the collar a thought. The jacket would be aweso',32,'2020-06-15'),(3163,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,1.0,'Collar way too restrictive and high. Check the model picture, fully zipped this is the most uncomfortable thing ever! I bought the vest as well and wo','Check the model picture, fully zipped this is the most uncomfortable thing ever! Even without it zipped it just sits too high. I bought the vest as well and wore them both before really realizing that this is just really poor design. So bummed, since I owned the nano puff previously I didn\'t give the collar a thought. The jacket would be aweso',32,'2020-06-15'),(3164,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,4.0,'Men’s Micro Puff Jacket','Sizing and weight are great, and it’s just right for the cold weather activity (or not!) that I do. The one drawback is no drawstring at the waist; it would be nice to be able to make it a bit snug at my waist when I want it.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3165,'Mbeltran',NULL,'5\'1 - 5\'3','XS',NULL,4.0,'Works as exciting expected','As most reviewers said, it is very light weight and warm especially for our SoCal winters. Haven’t worn it when it’s rained so I can’t speak to how effectively it stays warm and dry. Bought it for s trip to Spain where it’ll be in low to high 60s. Pack ability was a high priority since space is at a premium in my carryon and back pack. I couldn’t f',32,'2020-06-15'),(3166,'Steve T.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,1.0,'Poor design and fit','Ordered the jacket and was completely disappointed. Heed the reviews that this is just poorly designed. Did anyone at Patagonia zip this thing up all the way? Completely chokes you at the neck and is tight at the chest. I have been a die hard paddy customer for decades and this without a doubt is the worst designed piece of equipment I have ever pu',32,'2020-06-15'),(3167,'Jeff O.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Excelled while backpacking Europe for 42 days in the late fall','First technical piece of Patagonia gear I\'ve owned and I love it. Specifically went for the Micro puff for compressability, weight savings, and warmth. Touring 16 countries in 6 weeks with a 25L backpack. This thing rocked. When not in use it packed down to next to nothing. When in use (which it was for the most part everyday), it was comforta',32,'2020-06-15'),(3168,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'HIGHLY recommended!','My fellow campers. I cannot highly enough recommend the Patagonia puffer jacket. I just went outside and 26° weather with that jacket and a T-shirt underneath, and only had a very slight chill. I am completely blown away by how thin the jacket is, yet how warm it is. My north face puffer which is significantly thicker is not nearly as warm or light',32,'2020-06-15'),(3169,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Amazing little jacket!','I haven\'t owned this jacket long enough to find any flaws, but it performs far beyond my already high expectations in keeping me warm and dry with hardly any weight or volume. It',32,'2020-06-15'),(3170,'Jim L.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,2.0,'Mr','Really wanted this jacket, but resisted after reading early reviews. Then the 50% off sale on prior year models tempted me and I took the bait. I\'m 5\'9, 145 lbs, average build. All of my several Patagonia garments are size medium and fit well. This jacket in size medium fits me well … except, of course, for the collar and neckline. It&#x2',32,'2020-06-15'),(3171,'Matt M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,2.0,'Fit is off & not that light weight','being eyeing the Micro puff for over a year due to it supposedly being light weight. It\'s not much lighter than a regular Nano I don\'t think. The fit is just off too. pretty tight for an XL and the collar is GIGANTIC. the high collar doesn\'t make it comfortable to wear as an everyday jacket. Will be returning it.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3172,'Patrick',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Warm, light, and well-fitting','I\'m a 5\'9\" 180 lbs athletic male. The jacket fits well, with enough room to wear a sweater and/or baselayer underneath. It also fits perfectly under a torrentshell rain jacket. My only issue with the fit is that it\'s a little tight on the neck, though my neck is fairly thick. Not a big enough problem to buy a size up, but I prob',32,'2020-06-15'),(3173,'Jeff F.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,1.0,'jgf','I also found the neck to be extremely uncomfortable. When zipped, the neck is tall enough, and the zipper stiff enough, that it is basically spearing me under the chin. When unzipped a bit, the stiffness of the zipper and the height of the neck mean that each side of the zipper brushes me on the cheeks in a very annoying fashion.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3174,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket!','Bought it at Snowmass, and must say the product is very satisfactory, used as a down jacket.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3175,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'I love this coat!','This is my first purchase of merchandise from Patagonia. This Patagonia men’s Micro Puff coat is so warm, yet incredibly light weight! And Baltic Blue is a color that really is attractive to wear out in public. I am very happy with this purchase!',32,'2020-06-15'),(3176,'Jonathan C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,1.0,'After a month, stitching in body coming out, along with insulation','I spent a long time researching what lightweight jacket to buy, and went with this one despite there being some other great ones out there. After a month of light use (commuting to work), the stitching in a few seams in the body of the jacket is starting to come out. It appears the internal insulation may also be coming out. This is most disappoint',32,'2020-06-15'),(3177,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'It’s “weird sizes” are for a reason...','So lots of people are reviewing this jacket negatively because of the way it fits— I really do think it is just suppose to fit snugly as it is a light-weight-thermal jacket. If it’s not tight, you will not be warm... I recommend going to a store to try the jacket on. I’m 5’9” and 210 pounds, a large chest and wide shoulders. I liked the fit of the',32,'2020-06-15'),(3178,'Nivaun',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,2.0,'I Agree With Reviewers About Fit','The fit of this jacket is not at all what one would expect from Patagonia. Medium too small, large too big. Neck is small with the body comparatively huge and unfitted. Sleeves are too short for size of jacket.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3179,'robert s.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'I was sceptical that a jacket that was so thin could keep me warm. I am sceptical no longer,','Before I purchased a micro puff jacket in mid-December, I read all the reviews. In particular the ones that said you can’t zip up the collar all the way. Yes, that is true for me as well. However, there is a trade-off. The collar is taller than the collar on my 8 year old Patagonia down sweater. A nice feature when the wind is at my back. I was sce',32,'2020-06-15'),(3180,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Dont know what all the fuss is about! This thing is the BEST!!!','OMG, THIS thing feels invincible, it\'s honestly the best warmth to weight ratio I\'ve ever seen from Patagonia. I\'ve read complaints about the fit on the neck and sleeves, but uhmmm I honestly do not see or feel any issue AT ALL. People must be either super picky or built like Rambo. I\'m 6\'3\" 230 (athletic build) and an',32,'2020-06-15'),(3181,'Reeree P.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,2.0,'Could be an awsome jacket but...','I was so hesitant to spend this much on a jacket but have had your products in the past and been very pleased so I figured “why not”. It looks really appealing and was super excited to get it in the mail! I’ve had had it 2 weeks and one of the seams has the down stuffing coming out. I looked (but know NEVER to pull it out) and on of the seams has a',32,'2020-06-15'),(3182,'Skip',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','None',NULL,2.0,'Terrible fit. Period','I really want to like this jacket but the fit is head-scratchingly puzzling. Medium way too tight and large way too big. And don\'t get me started on the collar!!!!!!',32,'2020-06-15'),(3183,'Tom H.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Superb','My wife and I have worn our micro-puffs in the backcounty for 50 days and nights including a nine day ski tour in Yellowstone last March. Theses are superbly designed pieces. The collar fits so well with my balaclava tucked in that I no longer carry a neck gaiter. The fit through the body is uncannily good -- it is fine over a single base layer or',32,'2020-06-15'),(3184,'Tom B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,1.0,'Sorry guys, back to the drawing board.','I am average in size. 5\'10\" medium build. I buy medium-sized things off any rack and they fit. This. Jacket. Has. Design. Flaws. The medium neck was absurdly small. But I wanted to love the jacket. Love the color, the weight, the concept. Ordered the large. The neck fit perfectly but the body is a sack. Please fix this jacket and let us k',32,'2020-06-15'),(3185,'David C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,2.0,'I hope Patagonia revises fit','I\'m a gear hoarder but rarely write reviews, however some feedback for Patagonia is needed on this jacket. This jacket is has a great combination of materials in an awesomely light weight package. I was stoked to find a jacket that I could wear a lightweight standalone in cool temps (30-50) and then use as a midlayer on frigid backcountry days',32,'2020-06-15'),(3186,'Frank',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Just a great jacket that will not disappoint','Patagonia sizing can be a challenge so thought I would share my specs. I’m 5’ 10” weight 137 33 waist and the medium fits quite well. I can add a classic synchilla fleece underneath and not feel strangled. Get it!',32,'2020-06-15'),(3187,'David G.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,2.0,'Expected Better','I have purchased a lot of Patagonia base layers and outer layers over the years. Included down jackets, rain jackets and wading jackets. I purchased this jacket last week and It fit well through the body but not at all in the neck area once zipped up. I cannot understand why Patagonia would cut it this way. I will unfortunately be returning this ja',32,'2020-06-15'),(3188,'Tl22',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,2.0,'Huge cuffs','Purchased my third Nano and this one came with huge cuffs that fell completely over my hands. Had to return. Quality control problem.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3189,'Casf',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,2.0,'One more vote to change the fit','These same reviews have been up for a while and I never thought to chime in on this--but I wonder how many people like me have tried it on but also found the neck fit to be strange. I know everyone is different so maybe some people love the neck but it fits like no other jacket I\'ve ever tried on. I have a 15.5\" neck btw and can;\'t z',32,'2020-06-15'),(3190,'Willykins',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Extremely light and warm. Well made.','I\'ve read a few negative reviews about the fit,but I think it fits great! I\'m 6 ft 180 lbs with broad shoulders and a 32 inch waist. It\'s longer than most light jackets in the torso which I like,but the sleeves seem ALMOST too short; still acceptable though. I think when the fabric relaxes and I wear it more the sleeves will be perfe',32,'2020-06-15'),(3191,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Great lightweight puffy!','I previously purchased the hoody version of this jacket. Honestly,I was a little disappointed with how \"thin\" it was as an insulating layer (although it is probably equal to a Nano Puff Jacket). I had planned to pack the hoody as a backup warm layer on long (10+ mile) day hikes in the Tetons. My first thought was that I will also need to',32,'2020-06-15'),(3192,'Wailupe3',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Great travel jacket','I brought the Micro Puff Jacket for a trip to Japan. It is light weight and packs into the left pocket. I was surprised how warm it was and water resistant during a rain storm there. I have 3 Patagonia Down sweaters and this is more warm. The fit was comfortable for me. I am 5-8 170 lbs. and bought a size M. It was a great purchase for me.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3193,'Jah B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,2.0,'So close','I was pretty psyched about this jacket. I have the hoody and absolutely love it,despite totally flaming it when I first saw it on the site (sorry). I\'ve pretty much retired my UL down hoody in favor of this newer tech \' but back to the jacket. For me the fit is kind of a deal-breaker. I\'m 6\' and 170 or so,pretty slim,and typical',32,'2020-06-15'),(3194,'Kia',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,1.0,'Super odd fit','I love Patagonia. I really wanted this jacket to work,I even forced myself to wait for the release of the hoodless version. I\'m a minimalist,and I take pride in loving everything I own,especially my clothing. I was really bummed to see how poorly this jacket fit. I have tried on everything Patagonia,and have owned some of their best sellers an',32,'2020-06-15'),(3195,'NoahS',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,1.0,'Terrible fit','This jacket doesn\'t appear to be designed for humans. The collar is significantly taller in the *front*,but it\'s not big enough to fit over your chin,so it just crushes down on itself instead of wrapping your neck. I\'m 5\'8\',175#,size 32 waist - so,not a professional athlete but also decently fit. Instead of contouring to my',32,'2020-06-15'),(3196,'Zimick',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,1.0,'Flawed','I have had a Micro Puff hoody from when first offered and use it close to everyday as a carry layer for backcountry skiing etc.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3197,'Greg',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'More than expected','There are times when a technical piece transcends its roots and becomes an instant favorite piece of kit. You can unmute the advertising hype for this new gem: the micro puff will attain a coveted status in your packing list.',32,'2020-06-15'),(3198,'Gary67',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Fantastic Jacket','I have been wearing this jacket for several months now and it is great. Very light-weight and warm and compressible for packing. A must buy for hiking and even casual wear. I do have a suggestion for using this material. Make it into a blanket. I would make it into a light-weight blanket for back-packing and other purposes. I am a Vietnam Vet and o',32,'2020-06-15'),(3199,'Eric',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,3.0,'6-Year Review','Currently lounging in my 2014 purple/red Nano-Air, looking at one of several tenacious tape patches.',16,'2020-06-15'),(3200,'Josh',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Great Mid-Weight Jacket','5\'8\", 160lbs. I am typically warmer than the average person and this is perfect. I bought this jacket because i needed something more than my R1 as a skiing underlayer and would vent extra heat when i went hiking. Performed perfectly for hiking and I can\'t wait to try it out skiing next season. I went with the hood as none of my othe',16,'2020-06-15'),(3201,'Erin E.',NULL,'5\'1 - 5\'3','XS',NULL,5.0,'4 seasons favorite','Working in the mountains I don\'t have a lot of space for superfluous doodads, I like to keep it simple. This jacket has seen me to many summits and through cold jungle nights. Feels almost like an old cotton hoody but manages to be warm even when wet, and looks cute at the bar after a long trip. Only drawback is I\'d love to see a little m',16,'2020-06-15'),(3202,'andrew',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Most Versatile Layer, Period','Have owned and worn the jacket regularly since 2015. Arguably my best purchase of outdoor gear in the last several years - well worth the price. A number of design choices have changed over time, but the basic function is the same. For me, this is the best insulating layer on the market because i can wear it in such a wide range of conditions. unde',16,'2020-06-15'),(3203,'John',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,2.0,'What happened to the zipper storm flap?','A few years ago, I bought the original version of the Nano Air hoody and fell in love with it. It instantly became my favorite all around jacket due of its combination of excellent breathability, soft stretchy comfort, warmth, decent wind resistant, good looking, style, light weight, and the quality construction and attention to detail that I have ',16,'2020-06-15'),(3204,'Jeremy M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Nano air hoody','Honestly I’m sad it took me so long to purchase this jacket. I’ve owned a lot of Patagonia jackets over the years and this is suddenly my “go to” jacket. Most comfortable/practical jacket I own. Buy one!',16,'2020-06-15'),(3205,'Jeremy G.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'My second skin','My favorite outerwear, from climbing icy chutes to the office, this thing is the overall best outerwear I have owned. It will take pretty significant branch strikes when skiing with no tears. Soft and comfortable keeps you just a tad warm but not hot. Drys in minutes it seems like. Perfect slim fit. I got the large, 5\'10\" 175 probably cou',16,'2020-06-15'),(3206,'Kyle C.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'Favorite Daily Jacket','If you’re looking for daily hoody or jacket that is warm but light, this is it. It’s incredibly comfortable and has a bit of stretch to it. During winter I alternate between this and my M’s Down Sweater Hoody, but this one is a lot less puffy and looks better with jeans and stuff. You could easily use this as a fall/winter running jacket as well, a',16,'2020-06-15'),(3207,'Joe',NULL,'None','L',NULL,4.0,'What happened the the hybrid version','Why did Patagonia stop selling the hybrid version of this hoody? And why did they do away with the thumb hole slit in the cuff?? I thought that was the best design ever for a thumb hole. I was ready to buy 3 more so I would always have one in case they stopped selling it!! Guess I was too late. I have the hoody and non hooded version and I wear the',16,'2020-06-15'),(3208,'Randall',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,5.0,'Warm for what it\'s meant for, no sizing issues','Very warm late spring/summer/ jacket. Great for running in the fall/winter as well due to it\'s great breathability. No sizing issues with the forearms or tightness in the shoulder. Got my normal size and was fine and I have especially broad shoulders.',16,'2020-06-15'),(3209,'Tim',NULL,'None','M',NULL,3.0,'The sleeves/cuff on this are not stretchy.','Great jacket, but my biggest peeve about it (still deciding if it\'s a dealbreaker or not) is that the cuffs on these are not stretchy. Which means it\'s a pain in the butt to pull the sleeves up, even just to wash your hands. Hot and want to roll up your sleeves? Forget about it. Definitely try it on before you buy, especially if you typic',16,'2020-06-15'),(3210,'Martin B.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'My Go-To Jacket','This is my main go-to jacket for almost every trip. I wore the heck out of this thing recently in Antarctica climbing Vinson Massif. It’s awesome for those days when you’re working hard and need something breathable with good range of motion and a nice hood. I layered the Grade VII on top when it got super cold and it worked out to be a perfect sys',16,'2020-06-15'),(3211,'Rolf R.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Good, But...','Another great product ! The only negative is that the hood is not large enough to fit over my ski helmet.',16,'2020-06-15'),(3212,'Lauren B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','NB-7lb',NULL,5.0,'Success','My son likes the fit and the HOOD!!!!!',16,'2020-06-15'),(3213,'Brian S.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,2.0,'Not a fan','Love Patagonia - never had anything negative to say about any of their stuff Adore the company. However, had a night and day experience when comparing the prior nano air hoody jacket I had from 2016 (which I unfortunately had stolen and required replacing) and now. This jacket is just really unsatisfying. Less insulation, really tight - almost unco',16,'2020-06-15'),(3214,'John R.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Why does Patagonia discontinue their great products?','I\'ve had the non hoodie version for years and it has been amazing on tracks throughout the world as well as just using as a regular coat at home. Start looking at the hoodie version for my Kilimanjaro hike and discovered that it seems to be discontinued without a viable new alternative. the weight comfort and rehability of this jacket or great',16,'2020-06-15'),(3215,'Dean C.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Love this Jacket','Great mid weight piece to wear alone or layer with a shell and baselayer. I wear my Nano Air Hoody everywhere, very warm for the weight but what makes this piece so great is how well it breaths. I never feel over heated or clammy. If i layer with a shell (Snowdrifter Jacket) I\'m comfortable at 40 degrees down to below zero temps.',16,'2020-06-15'),(3216,'John B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'SANTA could use this on his many journeys','Totally satisfied with its insulating and breathable qualities.Its only Achilles heel is no drawcord at waist.Super lightweight and of course a little pricey but since its recycled it works for me in my beliefs and practices.Good Job TEAM PATAGONIA!!!!!!!!!!!!',16,'2020-06-15'),(3217,'Nicholas M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Fantastic','I\'m really happy with this jacket. It\'s very light, very comfortable, warm down to 30F wearing just a t-shirt underneath. I\'m 6\'3, 175 and the M fits great - long and a comfortably trim fit.',16,'2020-06-15'),(3218,'Lee B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Awesome layer. Works as intended.','Awesome layer. Works as intended. Can keep it on for strenuous uphill and layer up on top of it when reaching the top. Wide temperature range performance and a great casual wear piece to cap it off!',16,'2020-06-15'),(3219,'Abbott A.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'My go-to Layer','I wore this jacket for over 100 days of skiing last season, as well as over 40 days at sea. It regulates warmth better than any layer I have used and performs even when wet, drys fast. When I start to warm up on the hike up I take off my shell layer and rock the Nano-Air. Its able to keep me warm from the cold air, yet is supper breathable and keep',16,'2020-06-15'),(3220,'Jonathan T.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'A do everything kind of jacket','I have been using this jacket for at least 5 years now and the material is soft and breathable, yet durable. Very impressed and it\'s a favorite of mine. It really lives up to its active use comfortability. I’ve used it countless times now from cross country skiing in 5 degree weather, alpine summits, bike commuting on cold mornings to being my',16,'2020-06-15'),(3221,'Thomas D.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','SM',NULL,5.0,'Perfect for active use in a chilly environment','This hoody does exactly what I need it to. I don\'t overheat when hiking a gnarly approach, and I don\'t get cold when I\'m belaying. Very comfortable material, not nearly as crinkly/crunch as other Patagonia Puffys I\'ve owned in the past. Unfortunately, it already has a small hole on the cuff, but I\'m hard on gear and knew th',16,'2020-06-15'),(3222,'JDPT',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,4.0,'Lightweight and comfortable but a little too snug (order up a size for a muscular frame)','If you have any bulk (muscle or fat) on your torso and arms, you will want to order up a size. The jacket is lightweight and comfortable. I prefer this material over the nano puff jacket (which I also have) but the cut of the nano puff is much better.',16,'2020-06-15'),(3223,'Kyle S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Exactly right','Light enough to fit under a raincoat and warm enough to wear alone. This has been my daily fall jacket and can even hike without getting overheated.',16,'2020-06-15'),(3224,'SR',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Wow','This jacket is insane. The fit is insane. The warmth it provides is insane but you won’t overheat. I own a nano and micro and those serve their purposes in their own way but this is now my go to jacket.',16,'2020-06-15'),(3225,'Mitchell R.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Just what the doctor ordered','I absolutely love this jacket. The price is outrageous, but I was able to couple a gift card into the budget and I haven\'t been disappointed.',16,'2020-06-15'),(3226,'Christopher',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'I\'m VERY happy. I had','I\'m VERY happy. I had a previous version of this jacket, but it got completely destroyed from wearing a backpack. I\'ve worn this near daily for the past month, and no pilling or rips on the back anymore. Great job fixing that issue, Patagonia, and thank you for making such a wonderful jacket.',16,'2020-06-15'),(3227,'Sandra W.',NULL,'5\'1 - 5\'3','M',NULL,4.0,'Love it but...','To me the Patagonia sizing seems a bit slimmer this year. I love the Nano-Air but wish it weren\'t quite so long.',16,'2020-06-15'),(3228,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket','Great jacket',16,'2020-06-15'),(3229,'Ryan L.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Great fit. I particularly like','Great fit. I particularly like the fit. It\'s warm, but not hot, and the fabric is soft, but doesn\'t feel light duty.... I\'ve worn it quite a bit now and love it.',16,'2020-06-15'),(3230,'Christopher M.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'great mid-layer...believe the hype','I\'m really impressed with this current iteration of the nano-air. More durable, more weather resistent, but yet still super breathable. I\'ve worn it in a variety of conditions, and only really needed to unzip and take off once during a particularly warm and strenuous scramble',16,'2020-06-15'),(3231,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket!','This is a great jacket for rock climbing and hiking in! It kept me warm while I was belaying and taking a break and let enough heat out while I climbed and hiked. My only minor complaint is that granite is not very friendly to the material so I already have a small tear but it was easy to patch up!',16,'2020-06-15'),(3232,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Great Product','By far one of my new favorite pieces of clothing.',16,'2020-06-15'),(3233,'John H.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,2.0,'Another one bites the dust','I loved last years version. The only problem with it, was that it pilled. I purchased this years model and was disappointed at the changes. The hood and hem no longer had a tight seal. Very key. The fit was boxier and the insulation seemed thinner. Took away a zippered chest pocket as well. I shipped it back and hope they revive last years version.',16,'2020-06-15'),(3234,'Michael B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Great mid layer for the','Great mid layer for the mountain or causual wear for town.',16,'2020-06-15'),(3235,'Guenter S.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Perfect Hoody for cooler temperatures','While the purpose is to be a mid layer hoody, I have quite often worn it without a jacket and it kept me warm in cooler temperatures and was excellent against cool breezes. It does feel like a very nice sleeping bag as one other person wrote.',16,'2020-06-15'),(3236,'Justin R.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','NB-7lb',NULL,4.0,'Nano-Air Hoody','I absolutely love Patagonia products, and what they stand for as a company! The new Nano-Air is a great jacket, but there\'s one thing that puzzles me. There\'s no drawstring at the waist. For the life of me I cannot understand why they would have removed them since my previous Nano-air\'s all had them. Fit is much better than previous',16,'2020-06-15'),(3237,'Mainer',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Great Cold Weather Piece','I live in Maine. We get good winters. This is one of the most used pieces in my winter wardrobe. Great stand alone from 30-50F if I want temperature regulation and breathability, as long as the weather isn’t too gnarly. I never feel too hot or too cold in this. It moves moisture away more than any other moderately insulating piece that I’ve used wh',16,'2020-06-15'),(3238,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XS',NULL,4.0,'Perfect mid layer!','Just spent a few days climbing in the high Sierras with this jacket, and it does it’s job perfectly! It kept me warm but still breaths nicely (breaths a tiny bit better than the arcterex version, which I used a couple months ago to summit Mt. Whitney). It’s not only great for mountaineering, but I’ve been wearing around San Francisco and it looks g',16,'2020-06-15'),(3239,'Aaron',NULL,'None','M',NULL,4.0,'Good Layer for Winter Climbing','This jacket is a great layer. It\'s the right level of warmth without being heavy or un-breathable. Additionally it\'s very comfortable, likely wearing a cozy synthetic sleeping bag on your upper body. I\'ve used this jacket primarily in the desert during the winter for climbing – it\'s a perfect jacket to throw on when belaying in',16,'2020-06-15'),(3240,'maxwell m.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Super versatile','Great layer, super versatile. I use it for everything from a skiing mid layer to belay jacket. Couldn\'t be happier',16,'2020-06-15'),(3241,'Colby C.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','XS',NULL,4.0,'Great updates from the past Nano Air model','I have the old model of the nano air and I loved everything about it besides the fact that it was quite bulky when I wanted to pack it away into a backpack or duffel. With the new improvement of being able to stuff the jacket into the chest pocket was a major reason why I decided to purchase the new model and it does not disappoint. The addition of',16,'2020-06-15'),(3242,'Dave M.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Favorite Jacket','I love my Nano Air jacket. This jacket took all the greatest features of the Nano Puff and elevated them with stretch fabric, softer on skin feel yet crazy durable as outer wear and obviously a terrific layering piece. Get one, you won\'t regret it!',16,'2020-06-15'),(3243,'Kyle J.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great Hoody','The quality and warmth of this hoody are great. I would recommend 100%.',16,'2020-06-15'),(3244,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Great Jacket','This is a great lightweight cozy jacket. I gave it to my son and he loves it. I got the stone blue color and it looks great on him. Perfect! He lives back East and this is a wonderful jacket for layering.',28,'2020-06-15'),(3245,'Derrick S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great warmth.','Great warmth.',28,'2020-06-15'),(3246,'Eddie',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,2.0,'Itchy','I am surprised no one has commented on how itchy and scratchy the material. Granted I am wearing a short sleeve underneath, and I realize it is a wool blend. Can\'t comment on piling since I will be returning due to inability to wear it comfortably. Love the fit, love the look, love the light weightedness too.',28,'2020-06-15'),(3247,'Abel',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,4.0,'I love it, but noticed pilling after a month','This is my favorite jacket, Its warm, soft, and is a great mid layer for the midwest winter! Its also a nice casual jacket as well. But I just noticed pilling on the arms, I am not mad about the pilling but rather like Dad disappointed at the jacket. Other than that, its my favorite jacket I own.',28,'2020-06-15'),(3248,'Steve',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,2.0,'Pills badly','It pains me to leave a bad review for a Patagonia product as I really love the brand and what the company stands for in terms of sustainability. That said, I’ve had this woolyester jacket for about 8 weeks and it is pilling like crazy after only a few wears. This just isn’t acceptable or what I expect for a product at this price point. I have many',28,'2020-06-15'),(3249,'St',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Love the Feel','I bought one of these and like it very much but I\'d like it more if if had a zippered pocket somewhere in or outside. The pockets on the from aren\'t much good other that for hand (which are important!) and the rib-knit size of the cuffs is a bit much for me, i.e., too large. It is warm and stylish though.',28,'2020-06-15'),(3250,'Mikey',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'I love the looks','Looks (mostly) awesome. I came here to buy one, but then saw the elastic waistband...get rid of that, and I’ll definitely get one!',28,'2020-06-15'),(3251,'Asim K.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Asim Khan','What an amazing jacket! The fit is great- a much welcomed tailored fit which still gives if required. However the real star of the show is the exceptional Woolyester fabric. It demonstrates incredible warmth yet allows you to breathe at the same time demonstrating superb thermo-regulating properties. I read the other review of someone stating that ',28,'2020-06-15'),(3252,'Laughinggull',NULL,'5\'1 - 5\'3','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Woolyester is my new favorite','When I first read about Patagonia using recycled wool for a fabric my first reaction was not positive. But all of that changed when I got an opportunity to try this jacket on. Wonderful and unique!! I didn’t think anything could replace my love affair with Polartec. or R1 fleeces. But this has. Woolyester is thinner, denser, has this very cool weav',28,'2020-06-15'),(3253,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Finally. Perfect!','It’s currently laying over my grandmother in the emergency room. Blankets in here are not warm enough (she’s warm now). Figured I’d write a review! Purchased this while in Chicago last weekend and was perfect with a T Shirt while the temps were in the low 40’s. It fits snug (which I like). Not bulky. And gets the job done. Being wool, it can also g',28,'2020-06-15'),(3254,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great fleece','Nice looking fleece and performs even better. Toasty!!!',28,'2020-06-15'),(3255,'Jordan D.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'Super warm, a little itchy though','Just got this today and it looks sharp, is super warm, and has a nice fit, but the inside is a little fuzzy because of the wool so naturally it is a little itchy on the arms. Other than that it\'s great.',28,'2020-06-15'),(3256,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'So comfortable!','The texture of the fabric is like a knitted sweater rather than fleece. It’s toasty warm and soft.',28,'2020-06-15'),(3257,'Todd',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,3.0,'Great Jacket - Too Long for Some Reason','I\'m 5\'9\" and always order large jackets/fleeces, etc. from Patagonia. Until this one, they fit perfectly. This sweater/jacket is unusually long and I can\'t figure out why. I had to check to make sure I didn\'t order a tall size but I didn\'t. It\'s just longer than normal. Otherwise the product is great. Unfortunatel',45,'2020-06-15'),(3258,'David',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,2.0,'Fabric needs improvements','I have owned the jacket for five months. I really like the fit and color of the jacket. Unfortunately the outer surface of the fabric is now rough with pills. A soft roughness like an old teddy bear. The arms have deep creases and washing won\'t remove the creases. Which is strange. Not at all what I was expecting in a Patagonia jacket.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3259,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Christmas gift','Warm, comfortable and attractive',45,'2020-06-15'),(3260,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Great Product!','Very happy with it. :)',45,'2020-06-15'),(3261,'Nick T.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,1.0,'Never again','Bought a \"Better sweater\" in November of 2019. By the end of January 2020 it is pilling badly. And... the thought that I am releasing micro-sized bits of plastic into the environment every time I wash it is unbearable to me now. I veered off the track of natural fibers to purchase this product and really regret it. The pilling is so bad I',45,'2020-06-15'),(3262,'Marsha Z.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Wonderful style and fit','I always like Patagonia for its variety of colors and excellent style. I bought several family members sweaters and vests. They all loved them.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3263,'Matt O.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Happy with the full-length zipper','Happy with the full-length zipper version of this sweater. It is comfortable, the tight-knit fleece performs well, and I like the color pattern. I\'m 5\'10\" 175 lbs and a Medium may have been better fitting (but the Large works fine, just a little long).',45,'2020-06-15'),(3264,'J