10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great fit and quality','Great for colder days 30 plus degrees 0 Celsius. Fit is very comfortable and material is pretty thick. A medium fit perfect as I’m 5”11 and about 150Lbs.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3378,'Kevin P.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Very warm','The jacket is great and the pockets are huge! I can fit my whole hand in there and still have room. It is also very soft and thick and fits well',45,'2020-06-15'),(3379,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,5.0,'My son loves it!','I got this for my 13 year old son. He loves it! He wants it to be cold everyday so he wear it. The fit is great too.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3380,'Raul P.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,5.0,'Great sweater.','Love the fit and feel. Wear it to work at a hospital. Looks casual yet professional. Many compliments from coworkers.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3381,'B Y.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Now have several Better Sweaters...using','Now have several Better Sweaters...using almost daily. My \"go to\" clothing item for every function!',45,'2020-06-15'),(3382,'Charles M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Quality fleece','Fits perfect. Good quality as expected from Patagonia.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3383,'Chris M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Instantly my favorite.','One word: Cozy. Looks great. Love the color (I got the green). I have a few BS, but this is my first in the full zip jacket-form. I like it better than the pullovers. On my Xmas list for sure.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3384,'Kyeong Y.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Very nice fit and I','Very nice fit and I love the color!',45,'2020-06-15'),(3385,'Ziyad I.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,4.0,'Great comfort but loosely fit','This is jacket is very comfortable and cozy but I feel the sizing chart was inaccurate. I’m 6’0 tall and 160 pounds and the medium I purchased runs a tiny bit big. Overall, great quality!',45,'2020-06-15'),(3386,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,3.0,'Great Jacket but just didn’t like the fit.','Quality and look of the jacket are perfect, I mean, that’s why I bought it! But I really hoped it would have more of an athletic fit. Maybe if I planned on wearing a hoodie underneath?',45,'2020-06-15'),(3387,'Karin L.',NULL,'5\'1 - 5\'3','None',NULL,5.0,'Perfect','I bought this for my Dandy 95 year old Dad- he loves it and looks so great in it. He\'s on the small side 5\'4 and about 120 lbs. He got a medium so he could wear layers under it. It\'s perfect!',45,'2020-06-15'),(3388,'Dennis M.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'better sweater is a great','better sweater is a great lightweight cover',45,'2020-06-15'),(3389,'Sandra M.',NULL,'5\'1 - 5\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Best not better','Love this jacket for cold fall morning in the mountains',45,'2020-06-15'),(3390,'Eileen M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,5.0,'Sweater Jacket','This jacket was a gift for my grandson. He is 17, slim and about 5’ 10”. The fit is perfect and he is thrilled with this sweater jacket',45,'2020-06-15'),(3391,'Isayra A.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','XL',NULL,5.0,'Honestly unisex','I just bought the men’s because I like things to go down to the bottom of my butt, and to give me some arm room for sweaters and stuff. Fits great and so toasty!',45,'2020-06-15'),(3392,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Very nice! Warm, but not','Very nice! Warm, but not bulky',45,'2020-06-15'),(3393,'Viviana P.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great item ... warm and','Great item ... warm and easy to care',45,'2020-06-15'),(3394,'Pete A.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Warm, fits great, use on the trail or can wear in the office','This is my second Better Sweater Jacket. I commute by bike so sometimes have doubles of go to items that I leave at work. I can wear this jacket around a chilly office or use as a mid-layer on the trail.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3395,'Isaac H.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'High quality fleece','Excellent jacket, worth the price. Compared to the Columbia fleece jacket, this seems to be a much higher quality. The fleece in the pockets doesn\'t catch on my hands the way the Columbia did.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3396,'Benjamin C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Better Sweather Jacket (Matcha Green)','Great jacket, very comfortable. Not as \'fitted\' in the midsection and around waist, so feels like it runs a little large. Returning / exchanging for a medium.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3397,'Robert N.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,3.0,'Very nice and warm sweater','Only problem is that I will be returning it because it is too heavy and warm for where I live - southwest Florida. It’s well made as expected but I just can’t see getting enough use out of it. Thought it would be good lot take on trips when going to a colder climate and it would be but it’s a little too bulky to pack in my luggage.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3398,'Brian S.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,1.0,'Too short','Been wearing Patiginonia for 30+ years. I have a closet full of favorites. But the sleeve length on these two “same size” garments was a good 1 1/2” short.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3399,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Better Sweater Jacket','Love the Better Sweater Jacket. It is super warm and with a zipper it opens up if it gets too warm!',45,'2020-06-15'),(3400,'Dave C.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Go to coat/sweater','This jacket will get more use than any other item I own. It is comfortable, stylish, and most importantly, effective. This company knows what they are doing.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3401,'Jodi',NULL,'5\'1 - 5\'3','SM',NULL,5.0,'Best Jacket for cool weather','This jacket is comfortable, easy to pack, and perfect thickness for cooler weather.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3402,'Arcadio R.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Never disappointed','Practical, well made and comfortable. What more could I ask for.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3403,'Adrian D.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,2.0,'Sleeve length','The sleeves are built for someone with extremely long arms and I’m still confused that they came with a M sized sweater. Returning was not an option as the size and color was already sold out.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3404,'Michal G.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XS',NULL,5.0,'Awesome sweater','Looks very professional, I wear it to the office and look like a VC guy lol. It has high collar that matches well with a shirt.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3405,'Robert G.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Incredibly comfortable but 0 wind protection','This is the PERFECT jacket to wear indoors if you are a little chilly or to layer with a wind breaker when you go outside. Only complaint is that other fleeces I own from Patagonia (synchilla) are all much better at breaking the wind. Would definitely recommend if you’re looking to layer this with other jackets.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3406,'Myung S.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Perfect for cold weather between','Perfect for cold weather between fall and winter.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3407,'John W.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,5.0,'Very happy with the sweater.','Very happy with the sweater. Thank you. As always a quality experience.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3408,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Perfect!','Jacket is perfect in every way. It is also extremely versatile.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3409,'Jason T.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Awesome product, awesome people, awesome service','It just doesn’t get any better than Patagonia. From the people to the products and everything in between they just do things right. The Patagonia Better Sweater has been my go to fleece for years now. So of course when it came time for our surgical trainee group to get branded fleeces, there wasn’t any other option in my mind. Already, just a week ',45,'2020-06-15'),(3410,'Erwin S.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Got this for my husband.','Got this for my husband. He wears it all of the time! Perfect for evenings and cooler days. It is very flattering.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3411,'William S.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Bester sweater','fits great! Since most Patagonia gear is slim fit, this one has a bit of room to move.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3412,'Ian',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,4.0,'Great casual sweater','Love these as a more dress up looking sweatshirt. The style gets lots of compliments (esp the heathered colors - I have grey & green) and the fit is perfect for me. Only qualm is the pilling after about a year or so of regular use. It doesn\'t get washed very often and isn\'t used as a technical piece by me so the abrasions aren\'t',45,'2020-06-15'),(3413,'Mitchell',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,1.0,'Poor in nearly every category.','I wanted...tried to like the Better Sweater, but just couldn\'t. Mainly, its just not comfortable. Putting on a lightweight puffy is like heaven in comparison. Its heavy, bulky [esp. for travel], doesn\'t regulate temperature well - either too hot or too cold, smells easily, loose fit in the body especially at waist with no cinch equals dra',45,'2020-06-15'),(3414,'Andrew K.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Overall great product. Would prefer','Overall great product.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3415,'Lucas C.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,2.0,'Ms Bettersweater','I don’t like the heathered material. The color wasn’t truly black and frays easily.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3416,'Marie L.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Sweater for my husband','This is the 3rd sweater for my husband and he loves it. Comfortable and long lasting. Great product.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3417,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Nothing Better than the Better Sweater!','I got this for my boyfriend for his birthday and he loves it! The sweater can be worn for pretty much any occasion; date nights, walks, sweater around the house, anything! So far it\'s held up nice and I would definitely repurchase again!',45,'2020-06-15'),(3418,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Better Sweater Jacket','Awesome jacket. This is my go to when I need something comfortable and warm. Only reason I gave it 4 stars instead of 5 is because of the fit in the forearms. Too tight to fit a long sleeve shirt under it. Fits great everywhere else.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3419,'Brendan R.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','MS',NULL,5.0,'The Daily Driver','The better Sweater Jacket is my daily driver. It\'s the super comfortable medium warmth top that I can wear seamlessly inside my office and outside in the field, while being durable enough to take the beating of my on the go hands-on lifestyle, and formal enough I can walk into a business meeting and play the part. This top washes well, and sti',45,'2020-06-15'),(3420,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Awesome jacket!','It was a gift for my husband and he loves it! He wears it so often we need to buy him another one for sure!',45,'2020-06-15'),(3421,'Diego E.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','NB-7lb',NULL,5.0,'Super soft and cozy. VERY WARM','This sweater is no joke. It\'s a warm jacket and can only be worn in fall or summer. 60 and below',45,'2020-06-15'),(3422,'Spike',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,1.0,'I hate this \"jacket\"','Better Sweater Fleece is worthless if you step outside. I find that the material is so porous that walking on a cool day is enough to let the breeze in and cool me down. Forget it if there is an actually breeze. If you doubt what I say, hold the material up to a light, and you will be amazed at all of the light that comes through. The material is a',45,'2020-06-15'),(3423,'Bill S.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Better sweater','They don’t call it better sweater for nothing!!!',45,'2020-06-15'),(3424,'Hans',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,2.0,'Cheap quality that I would expect to find at Target for 1/4 the price','My wife & I both bought these & they \'pill-up\' so bad that she constantly has to use a \'clothes shaver\' on them. She says the quality is no better than one of the big box stores. For the exorbitantly high prices you guys charge for your gear I\'m very disappointed in the quality.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3425,'Nirbhay',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Nirbhay','My mom got me this for my birthday and this is utterly amazing. I love the unique design and the comfortable fit.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3426,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'So far so good!','Just got my sweater at REI and I absolutely love it! I\'m 5\'7, 170 lbs using a size Medium. Love the look of it with a tshirt or a flannel underneath, and if its really cold i\'ll use my North Face rain jacket. Keeps me warm and looks great! I\'ve been using it for a few days now, and I hope it lasts for awhile. All in all, I love',45,'2020-06-15'),(3427,'Steve',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Steve','My dad got one for Christmas and I tried it on and immediately fell in love with the jacket! Told my parents I wanted one for Christmas next year! 2 months later they surprised me on my Birthday with one!! I will never buy anything else, EVER!!!',45,'2020-06-15'),(3428,'Zach',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,2.0,'Strange fit','At 5’11” 180 lbs, I’m usually always a medium. Ordered the medium, and while the arm length fit as expected, the rest was way too short and very snug. Sent it back. Didn’t even bother trying the large, though.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3429,'Sammy T.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XXL',NULL,3.0,'Not For Me','I am 6\'4\", 40\" waist, 230#, 37\" sleeve length. I purchased the XXL. I am a tall guy with a thin to medium build (no beer gut). I can see why others had comments on the jacket length, sleeve width and ill fit. The jacket body is long and goes well below my waist. The body fit is ok, however the sleeves are narrow and somewhat dif',45,'2020-06-15'),(3430,'JAMES R.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,1.0,'Meant for tall and lanky','I\'m 5\' 9\" with an athletic build. Jacket had a nice fit through the chest and biceps that allowed for an athletic build. The arm length was the issue. At 5\' 9\", my arms hang mid thigh. In other words, I have normal length arms yet the sleeves for this sweater are VERY long and come past my fingers by 4\". Needless to sa',45,'2020-06-15'),(3431,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Everyone should have this!','I purchased mine at a authorized retail store. The fitting is perfect fit and snugs close to the body. Just keep in mind that this jacket isn’t windproof so have a thermal or long sleeve shirt underneath to keep that cool air at bay.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3432,'Julie',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,3.0,'Nice jacket BUT too THIN','Hi, I just want to say I love Patagonia as a company, and would love to continue supporting its business. That said, I am utterly disappointed with the recent fit (in both men\'s and women\'s), as well as color choices (this season\'s colors seem dull and boring). I bought this better sweater for my husband to replace his older one, thi',45,'2020-06-15'),(3433,'Ray',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,4.0,'Great sweater, but runs large','This was my first better sweater and i fell in love with it immediately. It\'s very comfortable and warm. The only downside is that it runs a little on the large side. I\'m 6\'1\" and normally wear a size large, but this sweater is a little baggier and longer than I\'m used to.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3434,'Joe A.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,4.0,'Love it. Not so much in the wind','Just got my new Better Sweater. I appreciate the regular fit as it seems like all Patagonia products are slim fit. The XL fits me nicely. I like the color and the fabric and ordered a Sweater Stone from Amazon the same day as the sweater to keep up with the pulling that I have been warned is coming. The sweater is warm but the wind cuts right throu',45,'2020-06-15'),(3435,'Dale W.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,2.0,'Love the looks, not the fit','I just got this and LOVE the looks and fabric, at least on the outside. Because the inside is fleece it is really, really difficult to put on as nothing will slide on a shirt-against-fleece setup. Also, the sleeves are somewhat tight from elbow to wrist which only multiplies that difficulty. Maybe because it\'s called \"sweater\" it is',45,'2020-06-15'),(3436,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Love it!','Bought it in black, but almost more of a charcoal gray (which I actually really like). I’m a medium in everything and the medium in this jacket fits perfectly. I really love the way this thing fits, but be aware that wind does cut right through it. That said, it’s a great under layer or a cool fall day jacket that is crazy comfortable.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3437,'Mrd888',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,2.0,'Warm,comfortable but has pilled substantially','This a great staple for your wardrobe. I have it in black,but it has pilled substantially even though it has only been lightly been worn. I would go for a different color. Will definitely keep you warm and is classic enough that you can wear it in business casual environments.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3438,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Great!','The jacket is perfect. The only criticism is that the jacket look way darker and different in person than in the product photographs. Other than that it is a good sweater jacket and it\'s worth the money.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3439,'James M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Simply great','Hooray for the 3XL Better Sweater. I\'ve managed to land three of these in my closet and keep telling myself they\'re really zip cardigans so I can wear them at the office with a tie. They are super versatile and comfortable.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3440,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket','Ive received 2 of these as gifts in the past few months. Its as comfortable as a hug. Stylish...dresses up or dresses down and can be your outer layer most of the time.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3441,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'Fair Trade! Hurray!','This is my first Patagonia purchase and I\'m happy wit it. I bought it in support of Fair Trade,and I\'m glad Patagonia has made a move to support a Fair wage for the workers who make their,and our,clothing. One thing to be aware of with this sweater is that it does not provide warmth in windy conditions. It\'s best worn around the hous',