ed denim. Another disappointment is that the sleeves are too tight,so that putting the jacket on over shirt sleeves is quite difficult.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3535,'Just J.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XL',NULL,5.0,'BEST sweater Jacket','I love my \"better sweater\" it\'s definitely one of the best purchases I\'ve made this year,premium quality,comfy and washes really well.. Patagonia products always stand the test of time.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3536,'Steve T.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Fashionable & Warm','I bought this item a month ago before traveling to the Maritimes. During our 3 weeks there I wore this sweater constantly. It warm incredibly warm yet breathable. I enjoyed it and raved about it so much that my wife bought a red one for herself while we were in Halifax! Now we\'re both toasty and good lookin\' at the same time!',45,'2020-06-15'),(3537,'Klk7125',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,5.0,'Dad\'s first Patagonia','Bought this for my 84 year old Dad (6\'4\",200 lbs) and he loves it! It delivers a smashing look as well as being his new very favorite piece of clothing. He says,\"It\'s so light you don\'t even know you have it on.\" Bought a L and it fits like it was custom-made (love the long sleeve length).',45,'2020-06-15'),(3538,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Excellent in all respects !!!!','just back from a beach vacation .... perfect for cooler nights and mornings',45,'2020-06-15'),(3539,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Love it!','I bought this for my boyfriend and he absolutely loves it! It\'s so warm and comfortable. We both have one and we love to wear them on those chilly days when we are running errands or just hanging out! Totally worth it!',45,'2020-06-15'),(3540,'J G.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Awesome sweater','Bought it for a trip to Idaho,kept me super warm during nights with avg temp of 35.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3541,'Patrick J.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Office sweater; trail mid layer.','Another great find for my Patagonia collection. 123',45,'2020-06-15'),(3542,'Seth K.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,2.0,'Enormous drop in quality over past versions','Replace my 2013/14 version (which I lost) with a 2015 version and found it to be much much much lower in quality.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3543,'Sierra S.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'I wear it every day','I really like this jacket. I use it almost every day. Have used it hiking/camping in the Sierras,around town,and after I get out of the ocean at night. It is warm and durable and low maintenance. Super comfortable too. I have read the other reviews,and for me the longer arms and bottom are perfect. I have tried previous years better sweaters on and',45,'2020-06-15'),(3544,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Love It','I bought this product just about a year ago and I\'ve really enjoyed it. The weight is perfect for late fall to late winter/early spring. Great product.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3545,'Evvrick',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Anytime Wear,except for snorkeling.','This fleece is Awesome!',45,'2020-06-15'),(3546,'Windyhill3',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Nice jacket,one flaw','This is a really nice jacket,but as others have mentioned,the sleeves are much too long. The jacket body fits me well,but the sleeves are designed for real knuckle-draggers. The people at the store said it was designed for active wear,and the sleeves had to have enough length so they wouldn\'t pull up in use. There is no way I could reach far e',45,'2020-06-15'),(3547,'Donald K.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Still an essential','I have had several better sweaters over the years, and this year\'s version is more \"performance\" oriented than in the past. All around, it is definitely a must-have. You can wear it around town as well as for short walks in the forest on a cold morning.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3548,'Rastanif',NULL,'None','None',NULL,1.0,'Change is not always good','Don\'t understand why you changed the way this is made. Bought an XL which is the same size I bought of the better sweater in past years. The sleeves and length on this new version is way too long. The feel is not there either as it feels like cheaper material. Don\'t start doing like other companies please and sacrifice the product you mak',45,'2020-06-15'),(3549,'TheMapper',NULL,'None','None',NULL,3.0,'Why change something that ain\'t broke?','Just upgraded to this from a 2014 Better Sweater. Not particularly satisfied with this 2015 model because of a number of aforementioned reasons. The 2015 Better Sweater overall feels boxier,has longer and wider sleeves,and is made of a thinner material than the 2014 models. Also,it\'s missing the premium nylon facing on the zipper track and the',45,'2020-06-15'),(3550,'Elizabeth M.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Great weight for SoCal winters','Based on earlier reviews,I ordered a size down for my husband,who generally wears a Large in everything. The Medium was much,much too small,and had to be exchanged. The Large fit is a bit slimmer through the torso than other fleeces he owns,but the sleeves were not too long - they were perfect for his 34/35 shirt sleeve. I gave this jacket to my hu',45,'2020-06-15'),(3551,'Nomad360',NULL,'None','None',NULL,3.0,'Slipping on the detail quality','I just purchased a third \"better sweater\" and was surprised to see that the quality had slipped with the recent version but the price had not changed. I have two older versions of both the jacket and vest. The details like the nylon facing on the zipper closure and piping on the collar are gone. It is the little things like this that make',45,'2020-06-15'),(3552,'Nm S.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Best Sweater','The best Better Sweater design yet. Just received my 2nd color. The full zip version is versatile enough for any demand. I can wear it under a shell for warmth on the slopes or as outerwear in town. Sizing is spot on perfect. It\'s not as boxy as previous models. You can tell this one is for the more athletic types - slimmer in the sides and wa',45,'2020-06-15'),(3553,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great Jacket','I see a lot of people are complaining about the sizing of the latest Better Sweater Jacket but I didn\'t have any issues. I looked at all the colors online and when I got to the store tried on the color I wanted in the size I thought would fit me best and it was a perfect fit. I got the XL, I\'m 6\'5\" and 220 lbs. This is my first',45,'2020-06-15'),(3554,'Billy N.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,2.0,'Improper Fit','I vetted this product with several friends and acquaintances as well as read other reviews and the 2015 Better Sweater is not of the same quality, as a whole, as earlier models. The sizing was off as I tried on a friend\'s Large that fit perfect and when I received my order it was long in the torso and sleeves (almost like a 40L instead of a 40',45,'2020-06-15'),(3555,'Mikey S.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,3.0,'What\'s going on at Patagonia regarding fit/sizing?','Hi everyone. I\'m a longtime Patagonia wearer. Male,5\'8\",160lbs,fit build,mid-40s. Something has gone off the rails,and not in a good way,in the design department of late (2015-16 Winter). Fleece jackets and 1/4 zips no longer seem to fit probably or comfortably. Either they are too tight in the body (small for me) or way too long in',45,'2020-06-15'),(3556,'Chickenjoe',NULL,'None','None',NULL,2.0,'bitter pills to swallow','I want to love this fleece. And I did for several months. Its super comfortable and really really warm. I\'ve worn it from 50 degree weather down to freezing and it\'s plenty warm (not super good against the wind though).',45,'2020-06-15'),(3557,'Todmorden',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Inconsistent sizing','I really like the jacket. It\'s comfortable and warm, great as a sweater or midlayer.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3558,'Don G.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,2.0,'what gives?','My second Better Sweater however,this one\'s arms /shoulder are very tight,too long sleeves and seems longer in the body than my 3yr old version. Pretty disapointed.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3559,'Nyc1234',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great trading desk fleece','I work as a sales analyst on Wall Street and this really helps me fit in with the traders on my desk. Once I saw that a trader bought one, I went out right away and got one for myself. I even got the same color as him (gray)! I thought about buying another color but it wasn\'t worth the risk.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3560,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,2.0,'Sizing is off!','I\'ve been a big fan of the Better Sweater for years and decided to purchase a new one this season and to my disappointment the sizing is way off from previous seasons. I\'m 5\'10 about 165 lbs and typical wear a Medium in Patagonia. This sweater model\'s arms are about 1/4 inch longer than my old one and the fit is slightly boxier.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3561,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'What can I say... love it!','I absolutely love this jacket from the material to the design. The pockets make sense as much as I hate to carry a cell phone the front chest pocket makes it easy to access when the kids are calling. I have had no issues with size and like to layer because of constantly changing temperatures and conditions in the mountains. I ware this jacket for e',45,'2020-06-15'),(3562,'Ricklaw',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket; normal Patagonia sizing','These Better Sweater jackets and pullovers are the best. They are warm, good-looking and well put together. They may fit more trimly than similar products from other manufacturers, but the fit is not tight or constricting if you know how Patagonia products are sized and buy accordingly. The fit in the Better Sweater is what I have come to expect an',45,'2020-06-15'),(3563,'John P.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Unique Fit','As other reviews have mentioned, the arms are longer. Also, unlike most Patagonia jackets, this one has a trim to it. So instead of the massive waste of fabric meant for fat American bellies, the larger sizes broaden the shoulders and waist proportionately. The fabric is thick, durable, and extremely comfortable. Great coat all around.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3564,'Mongo',NULL,'None','None',NULL,1.0,'Arm length and sizing just wrong.','I tried a size L, my usual size, on in a store. Too tight all over and the sleeve length was ridiculously long. I could possibly live with that if the cuffs had some kind of elastic or Velcro closures but they don\'t.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3565,'David V.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Quality still good','Not sure what the fuss about sizing is, the jacket is true to size. This 2015 version is a little longer than my 2011 better sweater, but the extra length is welcomed as I\'m 6\'3\". The sleeve length is pretty much the same',45,'2020-06-15'),(3566,'Gavster',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Sizing is one size too large','Unfortunately this sweater is one size too large. I am 6\'2\" and pretty slim and I am almost always a medium so I got the medium but it\'s at least one size too big. Just about to order a small so hopefully that one does the trick. I would recommend going to a store to try on before buying. That\'s my experience, hope it helps you',45,'2020-06-15'),(3567,'Spacegoat',NULL,'None','None',NULL,2.0,'Sleeves Absurdly Long','I typically wear shirts with 33\" arms. I bought a Medium and the sleeves are about 4\" too long. Almost completely cover my hands. Also, the length of this jacket could stand to be shortened by a couple inches. I\'m 5\'-11\" and this jacket feels like it was designed for a much taller person...with unnaturally long arms. Whoeve',45,'2020-06-15'),(3568,'H P.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Perfect for tall men','My husband is 6\'4\" and 190lbs and has a difficult time finding jackets that are long enough in the arms and torso. This fits perfectly. Really well made product.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3569,'Austin T.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,3.0,'Very nice, definitely my style','Very nice, definitely my style as far as looks go - however, the sleeves are too long. I got a Large and had to send it back, even though I wear a large in everything else. Got the Medium today and the sleeves are still to the middle of my hands',45,'2020-06-15'),(3570,'Jay073',NULL,'None','None',NULL,1.0,'Had high hopes, sizing failed me','Overall build and quality of the jacket is the best out there - but the sizing is completely off. Ordered down a size and still sleeve length and jacket length was too long. Traditionally wear the same size in all other items by Patagonia, but for some reason the sizing is completely off with this product. Looks like many others have had this same ',45,'2020-06-15'),(3571,'Josephtate',NULL,'None','None',NULL,1.0,'Strange sizing.','To chime with others: the sizing is strange. I have a large Better Sweater vest. Fits great. But the jacket version? A full 3-4 inches longer in the torso. Arms gorilla-length. Tried a medium. No luck. Too tight. It\'s as if the large was mislabeled since that vest version of the large fits fine.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3572,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'So Far ,So Good!','I recently bought this to \"update\" a simple Synchilla Full-Zip, that was an excellent piece, and what a treat this is. The red color looks great, the fit (on a smaller build) is spot on, though the sleeves are a little long on my short arms. I have not had it too much, nor have I put it too lot\'s of abuse, but take that for what you',45,'2020-06-15'),(3573,'Johnny U.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,3.0,'Good jacket but pilling. Size is goofy.','I may have an older model but I\'m looking to get a new version and wanted to pass on my feedback. I\'m 5\'11\", 190lb, muscular chest, short torso w/ crazy long legs. 17\" x 34\" slim / tailored dress shirt.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3574,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,1.0,'Huge!','I am 6\'0, 200lbs, 35 in sleeve. I ordered a large and it felt like I was a kid wearing an adult\'s clothes. Length of the garment was down below my crotch and sleeves almost covered my entire hand. Looks good but sizing is seriously off.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3575,'Mazinger',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Light, Warm and Oddly Sized','I like this sweater a lot. It\'s light, yet very warm. I purchased it to wear at home and work during those cool autumn days. I really like the material and workmanship that is typical of the Patagonia brand. The only complaint has to do with sizing. I\'m 5\'10\" and 196lbs and I had originally purchased a size large. However, upon',45,'2020-06-15'),(3576,'Hey L.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Works for me','It\'s like a sweater only better, just as the name says.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3577,'Casual O.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,1.0,'Not Better','I own a Better Sweater from last year (2014) in size medium. I am 5\'11\" and 170 lbs. I just tried on the new version of the Better Sweater with the added Napoleon pocket in size medium. Unfortunately, the sleeve length is now two or more inches longer and covered half of my hand whereas the old version fit me perfectly. Too bad!',45,'2020-06-15'),(3578,'Dbs1',NULL,'None','None',NULL,2.0,'hate to be a pill...','Surprised to see that Patagonia has deleted old reviews of this product! I wrote last year that the Better Sweater Jacket I had was a nice fit, comfortable wear and satisfactorily warm BUT the fabric pills something fierce! After just a few months of casual use -- mostly indoors! -- the front and arms looked awful from pilling.',45,'2020-06-15'),(3579,'James',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Good work jacket','I am 6\'0\" 210lbs and ordered this jacket as a medium. Even so, I usually wear a t-shirt and a micro-fleece vest underneath comfortably. It is not very warm in the chest area but has a comfortable cut. I have been wearing it through some serious chores and found it durable and comfortable.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3580,'Lee',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,3.0,'Pocket seam tore out in first season','So Ill start off by saying I truly love this coat!! Ive worn it primarily around our farm and while working in the shop. The coat is so warm and the insulation inside is soft and slick unlike other brands so that dirt/sawdust doesnt get caught in or stick to the inside. The hemp fabric is very',54,'2020-06-15'),(3581,'Michael K.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'The Last Work Coat I\'ll Buy','I\'ve had this jacket a few years now. One of the best work jackets I\'ve worn, and the last one I\'ll buy. It has weathered time and use really well. It has enough space for layering during deep cold, so is great for all seasons. The pockets are deep and warm. It\'s sharp enough to wear right out of the shop, so it\'s a corners',54,'2020-06-15'),(3582,'Jacob',NULL,'None','M',NULL,4.0,'Great jacket made better with beeswax','I love this coat. It’s simply the most durable piece of clothing I’ve ever owned, and the seams and cut make moving around and doing real work easy. I made mine waterproof and windproof with bee’s wax. Simply melt the wax, paint it on with a cheap brush, and soak it in with a heat gun or blow dryer. The wax makes it stiffer, though it will be ready',54,'2020-06-15'),(3583,'JASON C.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Awesomeness','I’ve had mine about a year now with a couple of washings (ink black is beginning to fade which looks great). The durability is outstanding! Tough as they say but you can wear it in dinner date with your significant other. Really goes well with just about anything. Originally I ordered a small seeing how the cut is relaxed fit but it was too tight i',54,'2020-06-15'),(3584,'Zachry P.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Warm and Big','Got this for Christmas. Much larger and warmer that I expected. I was thinking it was going to me more along the lines of a shirt jacket. Its not it much thicker and warmer than one. I have yet to be cold in this, and can tell it is durable to work in. I wasnt looking for a new warm work coat, but I got one and I am happy as can be. Now I hope one ',54,'2020-06-15'),(3585,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'Home Run Patagonia!!','OMG, got this coat for Xmas and it is fantastic , the quality and craftsmanship is amazing. It really is the best coat i have ever owned.....the urge to put a big peace fabric sign on the back is huge but it’s just perfect the way it is. So I’ll add the peace sign to my Patagonia fleece jacket instead!! In fact i already have!!',54,'2020-06-15'),(3586,'J. V.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','NB-7lb',NULL,5.0,'Tough and Cozy','Love this jacket! It keeps we warm with very few layers needed underneath. Love all the pocket options as well!',54,'2020-06-15'),(3587,'Joshua B.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Love this jacket','This jacket is great. Well made and super warm. I originally bought a large but exchanged for a medium. I\'m 6\'0 190lbs.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3588,'Matt O.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'My new favorite jacket','I wanted to try something non-fleece for a change, and this is my new favorite jacket for everyday use. It\'s very comfortable, it\'s warm but not so warm that I am constantly having to take it off to avoid overheating (as I would be with a medium to heavy weight down jacket), and it seems durable. It\'s not meant to be a high-performan',54,'2020-06-15'),(3589,'JD',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Worth the price','I used to work in Alaska where Carhartts\' rule, but this jacket beats any of my Carhartts coats hands down. It is far more comfortable and has way more attention to details that make it a pleasure to wear, not just \'work clothing\'; and it is warmer. The fit may be a bit tricky, but once dialed in correctly, it is damn near perfect.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3590,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Excellent Jacket!','I ordered this jacket on 11/4 and it arrived 11/6 -- which funnily enough was my birthday (thanks for that @Patagonia!)',54,'2020-06-15'),(3591,'William B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Solid Jacket','I own many jackets, but I am so glad I purchased this jacket.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3592,'Pamela P.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,5.0,'Amazingly light, flexible yet warm','Size S fits my 5\'10\" 147 lb husband well. He can still wear a medium layer underneath for when our Montana winter gets chillier. The outer canvas is nubbly, yet flexible, not like the duck canvas on similar-looking coats from that other company. This is also lighter weight than those other coats which he also appreciates.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3593,'sarah r.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','None',NULL,5.0,'The coat seems well made,','The coat seems well made, but ran a bit large in my usual medium so I went down to a size small. Not real roomy but comfortable to chop wood.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3594,'KATHERINE L.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','L',NULL,5.0,'The jacket is great and','The jacket is great and I love it. It had to be exchanged, though, for a smaller size as it runs large.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3595,'john w.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'Pretty Good','I like this jacket. Wife doesn\'t, everyone else says nice jacket. It\'s possibly not the warmest. I have a wanaca down jacket. It\'s not that jacket. The cuffs are the only problem I have with it. Making gloves not the easiest to fit and put on. I\'m a fatty, usual size large shirt. But the medium fits me. If I upped my donut intak',54,'2020-06-15'),(3596,'Melinda W.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','MS',NULL,5.0,'Good looking jacket and warm, too','Bought 3 of these jackets as Christmas presents. My gift recipients love them! They are the perfect amount of warmth for snow or cool weather in California. Good looking jacket as well. My son normally wears a Mens Medium and my husband wears a Mens XL. But I read the reviews that the jacket runs large so I bought a size smaller for both and they f',54,'2020-06-15'),(3597,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket!','My husband loves it and wears it everywhere! Quality is typical Patagonia...amazing!! Very soft, warm and durable! The fit runs true to size and not bulky!',54,'2020-06-15'),(3598,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Awesome Jacket!','I purchased the ink black color and have gotten numerous compliments on the great casual look/style of the jacket. I am 6 ft., 165 lbs. and the medium size fit is perfect. Take note that the fit of this jacket is a little relaxed which makes it great for layering. The jacket is also very well insulated…. I have worn it in 20 to 30-degree temperatur',54,'2020-06-15'),(3599,'Wolf',NULL,'None','M',NULL,4.0,'Warm Jacket','Great jacket, and very warm. The only issue is the sleeves run small around the wrist area. This results in discomfort if you wear a watch (Garmin).',54,'2020-06-15'),(3600,'Kathleen C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L/XL',NULL,5.0,'Bought for my son and','Bought for my son and he loves it',54,'2020-06-15'),(3601,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Love it!','This jacket is perfect to keep warm without being too bulky. My husband has worn it everyday since Christmas. Couldn’t be happier with the quality, fit and design.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3602,'Brandy G.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Warmest jacket','My husband loves this jacket! He wore it on our recent trip to NYC and didn’t change jackets the entire time. It’s the warmest jacket he’s ever owned, and it paired well with his outfits. He only wishes there were some type of hood on it, but it’s still a wonderful jacket. He also noted it’s not as heavy as he would expect a jacket that warm to be.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3603,'Nathan B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'very warm and fits comfortably','very warm and fits comfortably but sleeves are a touch too long.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3604,'Tom R.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'More then expected','Of course Patagonia has always offered great looking clothing. That’s why I purchased this jacket. But once I put it on, the warmth and durability became immediately obvious. This will be my go-to jacket for my harsh Chicago winters.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3605,'marc p.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Tough and soft. Kinda like','Tough and soft. Kinda like me ;). Love the jacket. Really have no complaints but if your looking for a suggestion perhaps right side inner vest pocket.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3606,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Soo comfy!','This jacket is awesome! Bought it for my boyfriend, he had never even tried it one and it fit true to size. Great fit and look. The upper back has the extra folded fabric that allows for more arm movement without lifting up the jacket and without looking odd in the back. Zippers and pockets are crafted very nicely. Dress it down, dress it up or go ',54,'2020-06-15'),(3607,'Brian M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Well made, comfortable everyday jacket','Fits well, tough to date, roomy fit, perfect for sweatshirt underneath. I’m 6’0” and a svelte 220 (LOL) and wear a XL',54,'2020-06-15'),(3608,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Perfect','Very good quality. I never Wright reviews but I am now because it is that good of a product. I am 5’9. 220 and I ordered a large. The sleeves are a little long but the stretch cuffs at the end make up for it.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3609,'Justin S.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'If you\'re on the borderline between Medium and Large, try Medium first','I find a lot of Patagonia clothes fit pretty tight and I was debating between Medium and Large so I first ordered a Large. I ended up swimming in the Large so I exchanged it for a Medium and it fits perfectly.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3610,'Kevin B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Iron Forge Hemp','I’m not the only one that loved this jacket; I have 3 friends that are ordering the same for work!',54,'2020-06-15'),(3611,'Marie B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Amazing quality in every sense.','Amazing quality in every sense. Durable and heavy. Would recommend to any and all',54,'2020-06-15'),(3612,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Better than expected!!','You can never go wrong with Patagonia wear! Decided to splurge for my 15 year old and provide him with some warm wear. So happy to say my son loves the jacket and it will surely keep him warm during the winter! Thank you bunches!',54,'2020-06-15'),(3613,'Lori G.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Durable','Durable',54,'2020-06-15'),(3614,'Cory K.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,5.0,'Iron Forge Ranch Jacket','This is my new favorite go to jacket. The canvas is soft, durable and the jacket is warm for north east winter weather.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3615,'Adam K.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Best coat on the planet','Best Montana jacket I have bought!! Bout to buy the pants too!!',54,'2020-06-15'),(3616,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great Jacket','Well made jacket. I’m 5-10, 185 and wear a large in Patagonia micro puff and all other jackets. However in this jacket, a medium fits perfectly. I understand their workwear line is made to fit layers underneath, so take that into account. Very warm and only wear it on &lt;40ish degree days.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3617,'Steffen H.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,4.0,'Since I read the reviews','Since I read the reviews before buying, it’s worth chiming in for the next person. I’m a broad shouldered male, pretty much a medium always, but the medium for this jacket was generously cut. Baggy and the trunk was like a bell. Good for layering a lot of things underneath, but without a waist cinch it was too big. More like a carhartt jacket, comf',54,'2020-06-15'),(3618,'Dalton F.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Absolutely in love, better in','Absolutely in love, better in person.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3619,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'Great jacket!','I don\'t normally write reviews, but I really like this jacket. It feels sturdy, and the fit is great. It does, though, feel like a \"California winter\" jacket - in that it is insulated, but not the equivalent of a Carhartt bomber winter farm jacket. I would love it if Patagonia made this jacket with 2x or 3x the insulation for folks w',54,'2020-06-15'),(3620,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Love it!','I bought this for my husband and he told me it was the best jacket of his whole life. It\'s very sturdy and fits great. I would definitely repurchase again but probably won\'t have to since it\'s great quality and very durable. I will most definitely recommend this jacket to friends and family!',54,'2020-06-15'),(3621,'Heather w.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Phenomenal Jacket','While we are far from farm owning - wood chopping - barn building - cattle wrangling folks, we loved the look of this jacket online! I bought it for my husband (6ft 185lbs - bought medium) because we liked the cut and color of the black. This jacket is an absolute rockstar! Feels so incredibly well made and super super warm. While we\'ll mainly',54,'2020-06-15'),(3622,'Douglas C.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Heavy, durable, well-made coat. Lots','Heavy, durable, well-made coat.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3623,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XL',NULL,5.0,'Perfect','Best jacket I have ever owned. It is super heavy and warm. The wind does not even come close to cutting through this fabric. Money well spent',54,'2020-06-15'),(3624,'Jb S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Order the smaller size','The hemp jacket is absolutely amazing. Quality is phenomenal. However, I am 6 foot tall and 190lbs and the medium size fits loose. Do I really need a small?',54,'2020-06-15'),(3625,'Leo P.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'Iron Forge Hemp Ranch Jacket','Great jacket, durable abrasion resistant hemp material.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3626,'Jeff H.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Exactly as advertised','It is a tough, warm coat. Perfect for working outside in New England winters. Normally a medium in Patagonia but sized down to a small based on the reviews and it fits perfectly while still being able to add a layer underneath.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3627,'Kevin M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket. Looks good and','Great jacket. Looks good and warmer than expected',54,'2020-06-15'),(3628,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Perfect Jacket','Warm, comfortable, and enough room for a layer underneath.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3629,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Love it','As always Patagonia delivers. Very warm. I love the weight of it. It’s heavier than it looks, but great for it’s function as a work jacket.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3630,'Nathan B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Awesome Jacket!!','I\'m 6\' 2\", 250lbs and after reading reviews I reluctantly went with the XL. I had planned to get the XXL since I rarely find anything in XL that fits properly. Well I\'m glad I went with the XL. It fits great. I don\'t know that I\'d be able to wear a think layer under it that comfortably but that\'s ok for me because',54,'2020-06-15'),(3631,'Di T.',NULL,'5\'1 - 5\'3','XS',NULL,4.0,'M\'s Iron Forge Hemp Canvas Ranch Jkt','I got this jacket as a small originally and switched to an extra small. I am a little chubby with a BMI of around 28, if that matters. the extra small could be a little smaller still. There is another review which is true about watches getting caught by the cuffs and that is a little annoying. The jacket pockets are nice, they are big and even when',54,'2020-06-15'),(3632,'Cory S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Amazing Products','I’m always pleased with Patagonia’s quality and attention to detail. Also, being a leader in ethical eco responsibility. You can’t go wrong with this company. Mom, you know what I want for Christmas this year :)',54,'2020-06-15'),(3633,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','XS',NULL,5.0,'Love it!!','Great jacket, warm and durable. Love love love it!!',54,'2020-06-15'),(3634,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'It\'s amazing!','I was somewhat hesitant about this item because I wasn\'t sure it would be warm enough for Wisconsin in winter. So glad I decided to pick it up! My new favorite jacket, bar none! Fits great, looks amazing with everything, warmer than expected, deep, functional pockets, overall a stellar design!',54,'2020-06-15'),(3635,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Durable and warm! I’m a','Durable and warm! I’m a wildland firefighter and use this jacket on cold days around the garage and working in the field. I’m 5’10 and the medium fits perfect with room for a hoodie underneath as well.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3636,'Nathan B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'I Love This Jacket','Despite Patagonia\'s poor marketing message with this jacket (you\'ve surely read the comments across social from working men and women.) this is an awesome piece of gear.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3637,'Clayton M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,4.0,'Almost great','Love the jacket. Nice fit and look. Bought it for the field cruising rough terrain with lots of bramble. Only issue so far is the interior cuffs were sewn in asymmetrically so the right one is way out compared to the left which bugs me a bit and also gets snagged on thorns. We\'ll see how it holds up over the winter.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3638,'Caleb O.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Heavy Duty Warmth','Pleasantly surprised with this jacket. This jacket is heavy duty, warm, and looks pretty darn good. The jacket has a good \"heft\" to it and seems like it will hold up over time. Great casual jacket that still looks great enough to wear for a night out!',54,'2020-06-15'),(3639,'Ann A.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Just what I wanted','Fits well, thick enough but easy to move in.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3640,'Andrew H.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','XS',NULL,4.0,'Love it.','The material is really sturdy, yet soft.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3641,'Michael M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'This Works...','Excellent jacket with great build quality.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3642,'Cary D.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Fantastic New Addition','I\'ve been searching for a more rugged jacket that is warm and yet functional. I could not have asked for better from Patagonia. The quality is what you\'d come to expect and the pictures on the model don\'t do it justice.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3643,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','SM',NULL,5.0,'Excellente!','This jacket is a lifestyle of comfort and warmth. Used to hate going outside, but now I hate going inside. With this jacket, you\'ll think you can conquer anything and look good while doing it.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3644,'Patrick O.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket. Weather still to','Great jacket. Weather still to warm to wear outside but had to wear it anyway.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3645,'Saul B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Great cold weather jacket','Perfect blend of warmth and rugged construction for outdoor work or play. Looks great too. Size is on the larger side.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3646,'Brandon W.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Ranch jacket','The picture really doesn’t do this jacket justice. When ordering I had no clue how durable and heavy it actually was. It’s an amazing jacket fits true to size and very comfortable. Would definitely recommend to anyone looking for a awesome jacket!',54,'2020-06-15'),(3647,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Great coat!','Nice fit, great attention to detail. Finally an XL size coat that is just right for me. The sleeve length is perfect and the collar lays just right when zipped all the way up. The insulation is perfect for these frosty mornings. I\'m quite impressed. Great Job Patagonia!',54,'2020-06-15'),(3648,'garret k.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Solid Jacket','Solid Jacket',54,'2020-06-15'),(3649,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Awesome Jacket!','I am very happy with this jacket. It has a great feel and fit and I know it will be with me for a lifetime.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3650,'Kiley M.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','XS',NULL,5.0,'Sweet jacket for chicks to','Awesome jacket been wanting one like it for years. I’m about 5’6 with broad shoulders/arms & a men’s xs fits great, a small would’ve been perfect over my lady hips :-). I love Patagonia men’s stuff. I actually just love Patagonia.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3651,'Nate D.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,4.0,'Durable, warm, and true to size','I am 6\' 4\" and 200lbs and after reading all the reviews that said it runs large, I decided to get a medium which turned out to be way too small. Had to return that one to get a large which fits me perfectly. I wear a large in everything and this jacket was not an exception. The sleeves are a bit tight and can be tough to get a big watch t',54,'2020-06-15'),(3652,'Angelo L.',NULL,'5\'1 - 5\'3','XS',NULL,4.0,'I like it.','It is a little large for me. I chose the smallest size, so if it can be made smaller, it would be great.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3653,'Joe Q.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Sweet Jacket','Fits great. Very warm. Lots of Style',54,'2020-06-15'),(3654,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Great Jacket','Very impressed with this jacket. It’s much warmer than I expected and the material is supple, while also seeming very strong. I’ve been wearing it for a lot of chainsawing and brush clearing and it shows no signs of wear. A game pouch on the back would be a nice addition. I am 6’-2” and 220, the large fits nicely.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3655,'Daro H.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,5.0,'Great. Jacket,perfect fit','Great. Jacket,perfect fit',54,'2020-06-15'),(3656,'Micheal B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Heavy duty, warm and good','Heavy duty, warm and good pockets',54,'2020-06-15'),(3657,'R.M.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Dream Jacket','I work in a field where I\'m outside a lot. Tree plantings, river and stream observations, and working on riverbanks. I\'ve found that clothes that are able to perform in those conditions, and help me look the part in the office are not a dime-a-dozen. This jacket is the highest quality of this standard that I\'m looking for. Its kept m',54,'2020-06-15'),(3658,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'6’3 195lbs','Hey, So I was hesitant on buying this. But Im glad I did. Sizing is off so order one size under. Im 6’3 195lbs toned body, so the Medium fits me perfect. Not to loose and baggy and not balls tight. I own 4 carhart canvas jackets that have a similar look to this one but with the sherpa lining. Weight wise they match up, warmth wise not sure yet....T',54,'2020-06-15'),(3659,'J T.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','None',NULL,5.0,'Forge hemp jacket is insulated','Forge hemp jacket is insulated it is not cardboard leak and I have many many help work wear shirts and pants. I’ve been wearing them five days a week as a tile layer and they stand the test of time. 3 yrs to date. My other pants get holes in the mean within six months. Keep making hemp please.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3660,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','NB-7lb',NULL,5.0,'Forge Hemp® Canvas Ranch Jacket','Love it. Very warm yet doesn\'t fill heavy on you. convenient pockets. Perfect for working outside on a cold day. It\'s my number 1 coat in my rotation.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3661,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Love This Jacket!!!','This is the jacket I’ve been searching for! It’s rugged and well made, fits true to size, and looks good too! I wear it constantly to work (I own a construction company and spend a lot of hands-on time working in the field) but I can also brush off the diet and wear it out on the weekend.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3662,'Ron T.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','NB-7lb',NULL,5.0,'Good value for the price, but too large','This jacket seemed like a quality product. It just ran large in size and needed to be returned.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3663,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','3XL',NULL,5.0,'Ms Iron Forge Hemp-In Singapore!','Great jacket, Very hard wearing and absolutely fantastic speedy service to Singapore! obviously the jacket is not for here! Ive sent to a local seamstress and had the cuffs removed just because I want to wear other items under my jacket and the cuffs would be an irritation. Love it.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3664,'Gaspar',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Great for any situation','Amazing for any sort of situation. I´ve had mine for the past few days and I haven´t taken it of once. Im 6,2 92kg and the L was perfect for me, It is kind of loose but in a good way, I can fit an extra layer beneath it. I am waiting to take it to the Crag and see how it does with the elements.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3665,'Stephen T.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Love this jacket. It comes','Love this jacket. It comes exactly as advertised.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3666,'Arlo D.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,5.0,'Very comfortable','This jacket is very comfortable and warm with a good fit to wear a hoodie or long sleeve under when it’s cold. The arms/ forearms are a little tight but it helps keep the sleeves out of the way. Definitely sized big but knowing that it’s okay. I’m about 5’10 and weigh 165 lbs.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3667,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great Jacket','I purchased the ink black in medium. I am 5’11 185 with a 42” chest. Fit perfectly. The hemp fabric seems robust and will likely hold up just as well as my other cotton duck work clothes. I think I will have to purchase it in the tan as well...',54,'2020-06-15'),(3668,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XS',NULL,5.0,'Durable, comfortable, looks great!','I\'m loving the Ranch Jacket! The insulation provides just the right amount of warmth when working and the hemp is super durable. I like the shorter cut as it allows some heat to escape from the bottom when I\'m more active. The fit allows for some layering when it\'s real cold or windy and the collar is great for some extra protection',54,'2020-06-15'),(3669,'Evan L.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'3 Season Jacket','Contemplated this for awhile, loving it so far. Warm, easily a winter jacket here in SW CO when layered. Bought it for the warmth and the sutainable materials and lifetime guarantee. Whether you\'re outside moving firewood, tending horses or enjoying natures beauty, this jacket will keep you warm',54,'2020-06-15'),(3670,'Ross N.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'True to size','I sized down and that was a mistake, the jacket is true to size unless you want something my slim fitting. It is however workwear and should be slightly oversized for movement and layering. Very warm and high quality construction. Should have included a snap button on the sleeve for it is very tight getting your hand through.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3671,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,4.0,'Prawly gonna wear it every day it’s above 15','Ordered online, and my first impression was that it was bulkier than I wanted. I’m 6’2” 180lbs with a lean torso, and I got spooked by other reviews. But I tried it on a second time and decided actually I did like it, and would give it a shot. I haven’t taken it off since then, except to sleep. I’m mostly a medium in jackets and that’s what I got.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3672,'James D.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,5.0,'Love at first wear.','I received this as a gift upon drooling over it for months. I put it on and fell in love straight away. I am a 180cm tall 67Kg climber. I have average shoulders, small rib-cage and particularly long arms. This jacket fits great around the shoulders and general length. The only downside for me is that I feel it could do with 1cm more on the arms for',54,'2020-06-15'),(3673,'William C.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Comfortable fit','Nice looking, rugged. Comfortable fit. Other reviewers were right - they seem to run large. I bought medium because I\'m sure a small would have been to small (I am a 42 chest, but short 5--7\"). But it\'ll do. Note - this jacket is heavier than I expected - which is great - will make a nice fall/winter spring coat in all but the most f',54,'2020-06-15'),(3674,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XS',NULL,5.0,'Love this jacket, the pictures don\'t do it justice!','I am 21 years old, about 5\' 11\" and just under 160 lbs. I typically wear this jacket for casual wear.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3675,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great Jacket','Sizing- I’m 6’0, 200lb, and I normally go in between sizes for Patagonia, M and L. I took a M in this jacket, and I think it was the right way to go.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3676,'Otf',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'Great 3-Season Jacket','I\'m not a fan of the elastic inner cuff, but I can get used to it. Otherwise the jacket looks great out of the box, looks like I\'ve owned it for years without looking worn out. It fits well, and roomy enough to allow for light layering on the colder days.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3677,'Devin W.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XS',NULL,5.0,'Great Jacket','Love the jacket. Wish it were slightly smaller. It fits a little baggy. I\'d go one size smaller than you need. (but not sure if it would be too small)',54,'2020-06-15'),(3678,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Nice stuff!','Outstanding quality. Accurate sizing. Nice company as well.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3679,'Vincent B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Cuffs','The cuffs on this jacket should be buttoned or snap. It is a tight squeeze trying to get my hands through that snug opening. Otherwise an excellent comfortable work jacket. But there is not a time I put this jacket on with out wishing for a buttoned cuff.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3680,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Excellent','Perfect fit, solid construction with thought given to details. No nonsense.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3681,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Love it','Had to return for a smaller size, that was a first. Great quality and very comfortable. Embroidering our logo was difficult but still looks sharp. Coat works well for the weather in Alaska.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3682,'Timothy S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Iron Forge Hemp Canvas Ranch Jacket','This jacket I know will outlast me! tough, strong and fits great! Could not find any washing instructions. Unfortunately as soon as I got the Jacket it became too warm to wear it but I have had everyone who comes over to put it on to feel the warmth and strength of this jacket!',54,'2020-06-15'),(3683,'Lee I.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Love it.','Bought it late in the season so haven’t had the chance to work in it. But it is super comfortable and exceptionally warm which I wasn\'t expecting. It could pass for a light winter coat. I would downsize. I am 5’6 160 lbs and the small fits perfectly',54,'2020-06-15'),(3684,'christopher l.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','L/XL',NULL,5.0,'Dressin\' it up','Everything I own is either puffy or made of synthetic filling and very functional for everything from skinning to biking to fly fishing, and they are all awesome and keep me warm. But, sometimes you need to dress it up a little. This jacket is very comfortable and very well made. The pockets are where you want them and the zippers are heavy duty. I',54,'2020-06-15'),(3685,'David D.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Don\'t let the look fool you','It looks like a stiff solid jacket it the photos. Don\'t believe it! it is a very great fitting, tough jacket that I wear on the farm daily. It is really soft and flexible, more so than some of my worn in jean jackets. When I let people know that it\'s made out of hemp, they are all surprised and want to touch the fabric. A great jacket, an',54,'2020-06-15'),(3686,'Bryan M.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Hemp Jacket','So thankful for this purchase. While I haven’t had a lot of opportunity to wear it yet, I can already tell it’s going to be a close companion for a long time.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3687,'Ben',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Great Jacket Overall--except for the cuffs','I\'ve had this jacket for six months now, and it has spent a cold winter in Bend, OR. I\'m 6\', 180 lbs and like most people, sized down and bought the medium, which fits great. The jacket is overall very warm, especially with a layer or two underneath. The material is durable and wears nicely. So far its held up great to bushes, rocks',54,'2020-06-15'),(3688,'Chris G.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Solid coat','I\'ve had this jacket for over a year now and I\'m very satisfied. The canvas exterior is very, very strong and fits comfortably over a hoodie or other lighter jacket. The front hand pockets are very deep but don\'t bulge out like other jackets. The buttons and zipper on this thing are insanely sturdy. Still looks like when I bought it',54,'2020-06-15'),(3689,'Peter',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XS',NULL,5.0,'Great Farm Jacket','I\'m so impressed with this jacket. I love the quality and broken-in feeling. After reading all the reviews, I too purchased one size smaller and took a chance (usually a SM in this brand) and it fits perfectly. Even in the smaller size, I can still wear a shirt and hoodie underneath (layering is important over here in WA). I\'m so impresse',54,'2020-06-15'),(3690,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,5.0,'Great!','I purchased this about 4 months ago and waited to write about it until I’ve put it through the ringer. First off, I’m 6’4” but really lean and ended up with the L as a perfect fit. Based on other reviews I started with the M and had to swap it out (without any trouble) because the length in the arms wasn’t quite there. I live on a farm and work in',54,'2020-06-15'),(3691,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'My Favorite Jacket','My parents got this for me as an incredibly considerate xmas gift, and I\'ve worn it nearly ever day for the three months since then. I\'m outside a lot for both work and hobbies and this bundle of warmth has exceeded my expectation. I wear a size Large, and at 6\' 200lbs it may be just slightly big on me, but more by puffy-ness and not',54,'2020-06-15'),(3692,'Dusty',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Can\'t Say Enough (A++)','As great of a purchase I\'ve made to date through Patagonia (big statement there). This jacket is fairly loose fitting (I prefer size L), so those of you who may prefer something more form fitting, I\'d consider sizing down yet bear in mind that while this jacket is highly fashionable, the intention is more work related. That said, the extr',54,'2020-06-15'),(3693,'William L.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Best coat I have for ranch work','I am considering stockpiling. This is hands down the best coat I have. Feeding horses, fixing fences, putting up hay, clearing brush, harrowing pastures, this is my go to coat. Yesterday filling water troughs I got a lot of mud on me, this coat barely gets dirty and wet mud just beaded off. Love it.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3694,'earl',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,4.0,'A suggestion','A true \"ranch jacket\" only has pocket that have a flap over them to keep such things as hay and dirt from filling them up. Great looking jacket but not for a working ranch, or yard for that matter...close but no cigar...This is a comment only, I do not own this jacket but just noticed the pockets. Every item made by Patagonia that I have ',54,'2020-06-15'),(3695,'Produce F.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'ProduceFarmer','Literally best work jacket you could ask for! Well done Patagonia.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3696,'Roman Z.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,4.0,'Long Lost Jacket','I was skeptical about buying this jacket as it is fairly expenisive. I read every review about 2-3 times to get an idea of what others thought about it and to help me decide. This was one of the best jackets I have owned in my life. The fit is larger, I usually wear a medium in patagonia but a small in this style fits me almost too perfect. For ref',54,'2020-06-15'),(3697,'Brian',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XXL',NULL,3.0,'fit not write','I have always done well with Patagonia\'s XL jacket sizing in the past. I am 6\'4\", 240lbs. and athletically built. So I was surprised when I had to return my XL and request a XXL. The new work wear line is not the same sizing as traditional Patagonia sizing, so consider this when you purchase. My XL was too short in the sleeves and sh',54,'2020-06-15'),(3698,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,4.0,'Very warm!','I\'m 6\'3\", 180 and am routinely in-between an M an an L, so I ordered both (and kept the better-fitting one). The M fit great in the body and sleeves, had room for a hoodie underneath, and was *just* long enough. The L didn\'t add much in either sleeve or overall length (maybe a half-inch, at most), but was absolutely *massive* in',54,'2020-06-15'),(3699,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Great Jacket','I bought this jacket mainly for casual use but It definitely is not restrictive if mobility is needed. The jackets materials feel durable and high quality. I love the hidden cuffs in in the sleeves as well as the pencil pocket in the top that I use to hang my sunglasses off of when indoors. Overall, this jacket is well made with many convenient fea',54,'2020-06-15'),(3700,'Conrad F.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Absolute Unit','Went through many jackets from Carhartt and Walls but was never satisfied. Finally landed on this one and I\'m blown away. I build wooden furniture outside year round in Louisiana. I wanted something that was warm but flexible in our constantly changing weather. I wanted something that looked awesome. I wanted something that I could use for man',54,'2020-06-15'),(3701,'tyler d.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,3.0,'Classic Look with the Toughness to back it up. Needs better design for warming pockets.','Cons first: Zipper needs to be upgraded and fleece lining needs to be removed from pockets. Hay likes fleece more than a magnet needs steel. The \"Hand warming\" pockets are pretty much useless until each piece of hay is plucked from them. Sleeves need to be widened for layering and the elastic cuffs don\'t fit with a watch. Suggestion',54,'2020-06-15'),(3702,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Awesome Jacket','I went to my local retail store to try this jacket on as I’m usually between a medium and a large. I’m 6’1 175lbs. Ended up going with the large to accommodate my broader shoulders plus I knew I wanted to layer underneath. The medium definitely fit better in the body (I have a 32 waist) but was just too tight across the back and shoulders. Given th',54,'2020-06-15'),(3703,'JASON C.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Incredible Jacket','5’9” 174 lbs Athletic build. Got the small - which fits but it too tight thru the chest and going back for a medium. That said, the gusset back opens wide for range of motion (even though it’s too small on me!) Sleeve length was perfect on the small so medium may be slightly too long. Due to tightness there was no room for more than a tee shirt und',54,'2020-06-15'),(3704,'Robert A.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Nice jacket','This is a really nice jacket. I like the weight and fabric. The only thing I can hit it on so far. Is the zip up pocket on the inner left side of the jacket. If it could be made with a wider opening so my hand does not get caught in the zipper. I would like to keep my cigarettes in that pocket.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3705,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'A Perfect Winter Jacket!','I have one of the older Patagonia canvas barn coats (uninsulated), so I got this one for winter wear. I need a durable bomb-proof warm jacket as getting firewood is a daily chore. The insulation is perfect for our cold New England winters. Using zippered front (plus buttons) is a great idea which blocks wind and makes closing the jacket faster and ',54,'2020-06-15'),(3706,'Peter',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','XL',NULL,3.0,'Forearms','I love this coat... BUT... As this line is aimed at the construction industry, it would be good to widen the forearm area. My forearms are sausaged into the sleeves when I\'m only wearing a T-shirt. Every other part of the coat fits well and leaves room for layering, but the forearms are so narrow I cant wear it when it\'s cold outside. I h',54,'2020-06-15'),(3707,'Barton C.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,1.0,'Not for ranching.','First off I am a big advocate of all things Patagonia and a significant percentage of my wardrobe have been your clothes for decades. I bought two of these \"Ranch\" hemp jackets as gifts for two friends who are actual cattle ranchers in North Dakota. Within a couple months of daily use on the ranch both zippers blew out. Ranching involves ',54,'2020-06-15'),(3708,'John',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Like a warm blanket','Put this jacket on felt like it was a long lost jacket found again, amazingly flexible for canvas, now i will sit here eagerly hoping the make some insulated bibs with the same construction.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3709,'Rastanif',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Awesome Coat','Love this heavy duty coat. Very warm and durable for the long haul. Also a generous cut to layer when working outside in freezing temperatures. Would highly recommend this to anyone looking for a great coat.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3710,'Guest',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'It fits really reallly good','My wife bought me this jacket and it fits really good. Like I’ve been missing this jacket my entire life good. Enough room to layer tough/heavy enough to work in when I’m milling/woodworking/choring. If the rest of the jackets in this collection fit this good I may buy another.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3711,'Ian S.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Excellent Work Coat','I purchased this coat to replace an old Carhartt work coat. I am a carpenter and work outdoors during the cold Northeast months. The ease of movement with the hemp fabric has been a huge upgrade over the stiffness of the Carhartt duck canvas. Based on the fit of the Farrier shirt I ordered a large which is a size down from my usual XL',54,'2020-06-15'),(3712,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket','I got a small. 5 11\" 168lbs. climber build. Fits perfect with a tee shirt. If you want to layer go up a size. Super soft..',54,'2020-06-15'),(3713,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'A solid 4.5 star!','Before buying this jacket i read most of the reviews and they were right on the money for quality and fit! As a contractor i need a \"Carhartt\" jacket but they just dont fit me right, and leave me feeling restricted. Iam 5\'8\" 180lbs athletic build, and the Patagonia Ranch jacket fit PERFECT in a Medium. First thing i noticed slip',54,'2020-06-15'),(3714,'Doug',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'This may be my new daily','5\'9\"/180. Fits great. Works well even with a light weight hoody underneath. Multiple shirts and a heavier hoody would make the fit a little tight for me, but i wear my weight in my mid section.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3715,'Adam K.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Great coat, Iron Forged indeed','Once I received the coat, it was much heavier than I anticipated which was a good thing. I really like the ribbed elastic wrist feature which allows for easy hand movement and keeps the cold out. Overall great jacket for working, hiking and stylish enough to wear out on the town. It goes without saying that Patagonia is the market leader in making ',54,'2020-06-15'),(3716,'Dp',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'New go-to jacket','5’11”/175 lbs and the medium fits almost perfectly. Arms a little bit long, but otherwise it’s one of the best fitting PTG jackets I’ve had and it’s way more insulated than expected. Looking forward to pairing it with some jeans for the perfect backcountry kit.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3717,'David M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket.','First off great service! Ordered on Election Day and they were closed but able to order online. Really appreciate the value the company places on good stewardship. Ok the jacket review. Ordered a M and fit is perfect. I’m 5’10 and an athletic 170. Usually wear a large so sizing down a size worked great. The quality is excellent as you would expect',54,'2020-06-15'),(3718,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,5.0,'Great Jacket','Excellent jacket. Fit is a little wider through the middle, but is appropriate given the utility. Materials and fabric looks like it will hold up well for years of use.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3719,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'ImagesM\'s Iron Forge Hemp® Canvas Ranch Jacket, Coriander Brown (COI) DEFAULT-EXCLUSIVE M\'s Iron Forge Hemp® Canvas Ranch Jacket, Ink Black (INBK) DEF','Just received this jacket. At 5\'11\", 160 lbs I generally would go large, but ordered medium based on other reviews. The medium fits great, if anything it\'s a little roomier than I\'d like, but will be good for layers. Overall great first impression.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3720,'James M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,5.0,'Great Jacket, Great Fit','I really like canvas workwear jackets, they\'re stylish and they last a long time. The problem is I\'m a thin guy. I\'m 6 ft and weigh 150 or so. Most workwear is constructed with a really broad back, which looks goofy on a guy with narrow shoulders. I was worried that I might run into that problem with this jacket even if I sized down',54,'2020-06-15'),(3721,'Daniel M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Runs very large.','I love the jacket, however it\'s just too big. I used the sizing guide, and it said i need a XXL. I am 6\'3\" 260lbs and it is just 1 size too big. I live in Germany however so I have to figure out how to exchange it for a smaller one now.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3722,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket!','Just received this jacket for my husband yesterday. He is not easy to please with the clothes. But he was happy with this one like a child, he almost slept in it :-) He says he loves how soft the material feels, the pockets are deep and lined with soft to touch material. You can put the collar up for a fancy look. The sleeves have a sock like mater',54,'2020-06-15'),(3723,'Everts',NULL,'None','None',NULL,3.0,'Not a real work jacket','I like this jacket but I feel that a real work jacket like this needs a hood. If you\'re actually using this to work in the outdoors then you know how nice a hood is when it begins to rain or snow. I don\'t know if I can use this as a real work jacket now.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3724,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'I dig it.','I\'m definitely buying the hemp hype. I bought this jacket late in the season,but still had time to put it through it\'s paces as winter lapsed into spring here in New England. It was warm,tough,and flexible - the three things I hoped for most out of this jacket. On days when I didn\'t need a full waterproof shell,this piece was a trust',54,'2020-06-15'),(3725,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'I dig it.','I\'m definitely buying the hemp hype. I bought this jacket late in the season, but still had time to put it through it\'s paces as winter lapsed into spring here in New England. It was warm, tough, and flexible - the three things I hoped for most out of this jacket. On days when I didn\'t need a full waterproof shell, this piece was a t',54,'2020-06-15'),(3726,'Zerbekw',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XXL',NULL,4.0,'Good fit,warmer than expected','I\'m an ecologist and do field work all year long. My old cold-weather work jacket proved inadequate this very cold winter in the Northeast,so I figured I\'d give Patty\'s new workwear line a go. This jacket is heavier/beefier than I expected,and much warmer. It feels like it\'ll hold up to field work for a long time to come. Good f',54,'2020-06-15'),(3727,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'The Answer','Like others,I owned a Carhartt jacket for heavy work before being given this beaut for Christmas.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3728,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'The Answer','Like others, I owned a Carhartt jacket for heavy work before being given this beaut for Christmas.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3729,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket','I\'m very happy with my canvas ranch jacket. It\'s great in the yard or with jeans,but I can also wear it with a slightly dressier outfit (I got the dark grey color). Compared to a similar jacket at Filson,the quality seems fairly even and the price,therefore,is great value.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3730,'Miles M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Good fit and mobility.','The large fit me great 5\'10\" and 180. The arm rotation is great. Looking forward to putting this to the test.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3731,'NickCO',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Great working and looking jacket','I bought this jacket and have been thoroughly impressed with its fit and warmth. I\'m big across the shoulders and usually wear an XL in Patagonia coats and jackets,but the large was good in this model. The jacket is a lot better looking work casually than I expected too in the black.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3732,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Finally!!','Received this for a Christmas present to replace a Carhart that I gave to my son because I hated it. The fabric has a wonderful hand to it and has none of the stiff abrasiveness of the Carhart. So far,it\'s held up to everything I\'ve thrown at it,from the workshop to walking dogs to re-stacking firewood to burning brush. Warm and exception',54,'2020-06-15'),(3733,'Kyco4',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,4.0,'Dig it. Only 2 suggestions..','First Ill start off by saying I dig the jacket. I have put it through the ringer these past 5 months or so and it has held up quite well. I work on a Vineyard on the western slope of CO and it has handled the cold and all Mother Nature has thrown its way. I only have two suggestions that would improve the design of the coat..',54,'2020-06-15'),(3734,'JDnAZ',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Better watch out Carhartt','I have owned the the most popular brand of work jackets for almost 40 years.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3735,'Dave',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Excellent work jacket worth the price.','I\'m glad I picked this up. It\'s going to be my new daily work jacket in the colder months. The material is softer than it looks but you can tell it\'s strong. All the stitching is rock solid and it feels broken in right out of the box. The zipper is substantial and I like being able to button up the front as well. The collar is one of',54,'2020-06-15'),(3736,'Patagonialoverman',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,2.0,'Rare miss','This jacket is a rare miss from Patagonia for me. I\'m 6\'2\" / 185 lbs and the large was very ill fitting. The arm and body length was fine but the chest and internal volume of the coat was ridiculously large. Even with a thick hoody on I was swimming in it.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3737,'Lee M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,4.0,'Exciting piece','Overall I am very pleased with this jacket. It is definitely well built and the fit and features are well thought out. I give it four stars because of the fleece lining in the pockets. Micro fleece has a tendency to catch on dry skin or cuts; also,why add a synthetic material when you don\'t need to? This jacket is proof that natural materials',54,'2020-06-15'),(3738,'Toni22',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Amazing jacket- super warm','I love this jacket and wear it daily. It was a bit heavier than I was expecting but it is super warm,looks great as a casual jacket and most important is super warm. The lined pockets are probably the best feature. It does run a little big but not too large.',54,'2020-06-15'),(3739,'Big J.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,3.0,'Not exactly what I was expecting','Nice jacket,and a well designed set of features. The pockets are great. As mentioned it does run large. At 6\'6\" and 215 lbs the large fit really well. But I ended up sending it back. I don\'t really like the material. I wish it was stiffer and not so soft/pliable. The material was shedding little bits of stuff. Maybe it needed to be w',54,'2020-06-15'),(3740,'Paul',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Tough,transitional coat,but heavy','Great for Fall and Spring temps,and warm in the winter,with some layering. Very tough work coat; toted several bags of mulch on my shoulder recently,and no slippage or damage. I followed the advice of other reviewers and got a smaller size than I would normally get,that worked 