6-15'),(3917,'Peggy C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Recipient loved it.','Purchased quarter zip sweater. Looks like a heathered blue. Very soft, comfortable and true to size.',15,'2020-06-15'),(3918,'Ben I.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Most comfortable sweater I own','Most comfortable sweater I own',15,'2020-06-15'),(3919,'Dana M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Pigeon Blue Better Sweater','Nice high quality sweater that runs a tad big. Love the color. Can wear w jeans, navy pants or kahki’s. Heavy enough to keep u warm but not too bulky.',15,'2020-06-15'),(3920,'Laura M.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','L/XL',NULL,5.0,'Perfect','Whether a girl (like me) or a boy, this sweater is roomy, soft, cozy, and will DEFINITELY keep ya warm without overheating. The zip up neck allows you to feel free to cool down or warm up a bit more depending on where youre off to. Im only mad my fiance has this and ai didnt buy it for myself.',15,'2020-06-15'),(3921,'Michael O.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Great item and service','I have a quarter zip Better Sweater of my own and ordered one for my dad for Christmas. It is such a high-quality shirt: warm, comfortable, well-fitting and durable through many wash cycles.',15,'2020-06-15'),(3922,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Perfect !','These sweaters are as functional , comfortable and durable as they come. Best sweaters I own !',15,'2020-06-15'),(3923,'courtney L.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'We all love the better','We all love the better sweaters. It is an outdoor staple. They wear so well, i can pass them down to my nephews too.',15,'2020-06-15'),(3924,'Kaileen D.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'I love my 1/4 zip better sweater','This sweater is so warm. Definitely order a size up. I am 5\'7\" ~140lbs and got a medium and it was perfect. Considering sewing on my own pockets though.',15,'2020-06-15'),(3925,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Excellent','Fuzzy and what I wanted.',15,'2020-06-15'),(3926,'Peter W.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Excellent quantity as always from','Excellent quantity as always from Patagonia. Fits true to size.',15,'2020-06-15'),(3927,'Lynette K.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Man Wearing Patagonia','Great addition to wardrobe.',15,'2020-06-15'),(3928,'DIANE D.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,4.0,'Nice feel a little snug','Nice feel a little snug in shoulder at first but okay during wear.',15,'2020-06-15'),(3929,'Zachary M.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'I ordered the two tone','I ordered the two tone and love it. Ordering more colors soon.',15,'2020-06-15');
INSERT INTO `reviews` VALUES (3930,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Perfect','Got this in the mail and immediately put it on! It’s super soft and fits perfect. I am 6 foot 1 and wearing a medium and it’s size is spot on. It makes a perfect sweater for around the house and going out in the town.',15,'2020-06-15'),(3931,'John J.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','3XL',NULL,5.0,'Great Sweater','I love these sweaters they are warn, look good, and are very comfortable.',15,'2020-06-15'),(3932,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Great quality and fit!','Great quality and fit!',15,'2020-06-15'),(3933,'Cristina M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great fitting, true to size','Great fitting, true to size 1/4 zip.',15,'2020-06-15'),(3934,'Cindy M.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Wears great and looks great','Wears great and looks great love it',15,'2020-06-15'),(3935,'Jeffery H.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Awesome Sweater','Fits true, very warm. A staple in my weather rotation.',15,'2020-06-15'),(3936,'Dan b.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'OV DANNY','Great fit',15,'2020-06-15'),(3937,'David R.',NULL,'5\'0 or less','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Men\'s Better Sweater 1/ 4 Zip','These have become a staple of northern living. They wear like iron, are warm, comfortable, and look great.',15,'2020-06-15'),(3938,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Great!','Received my order a bit later in the day towards nighttime but it was well worth it. This jacket is the warmest I have had in a while and it is very comfortable. It is the first Patagonia product I own and certainly won’t be the last. Thank you for the great quality!',15,'2020-06-15'),(3939,'Omri Y.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,5.0,'Keeps being my top choice for everyday top','Insane quality, never wears out. Keep me warm and agile :)',15,'2020-06-15'),(3940,'Ben K.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','None',NULL,5.0,'Perfect','Perfect',15,'2020-06-15'),(3941,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great Product','Warm, Comfortable option for the cold winter days.',15,'2020-06-15'),(3942,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Comfy, soft, quality piece from Patagonia!','Great product. Very versatile!',15,'2020-06-15'),(3943,'Shad H.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','3XL',NULL,5.0,'Good quality','Nice color, feels soft',15,'2020-06-15'),(3944,'john g.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Super comfortable and a little shrinkage','Love this sweater perfect for temps in the 40’s. I ordered a size up so I could dry it and it shrunk down perfectly.',15,'2020-06-15'),(3945,'Nps V.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'A Michigan High School Cross-Country Officials New Favorite Piece of Clothing.','This Better Sweater fits very well and it is very warm. I have used the sweater under my rain gear. I received the sweater just in time to wear it to a high schoolState Regional at which I worked as an official. I was toasty and dry for six hours of outside activity.',15,'2020-06-15'),(3946,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'7 or above','XL',NULL,5.0,'Fits perfectly! Runs true to','Fits perfectly! Runs true to Patagonia size, whatever you normally are make sure to grab in this!',15,'2020-06-15'),(3947,'Kevin R.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Great midweight piece','Great midweight piece',15,'2020-06-15'),(3948,'Shane I.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,1.0,'Poor fit','I bought two of the the sweaters in different colors size large (6’1” 190#). One fit great and one fit like a tarp, one was correct length and width and the other was longer in the arms and wider in the body. The fit in the arm pits was bad also, bunched up like a gas station fleece and cut off circulation. Sent both back due to fit and quality.',15,'2020-06-15'),(3949,'Miles M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,5.0,'1/4 zip','Its sexy and warm. Highly recommend. I am 160 lbs and 5\'11\" and the small fits perfectly',15,'2020-06-15'),(3950,'Sean M.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Dual purpose','Works great as a layering piece or a sweater for casual wear.',15,'2020-06-15'),(3951,'Rod D.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Better Sweater','Great warmth with this product. Works great in the field as well as casual wear. Latest version seems to be sized a bit larger than my previous versions.',15,'2020-06-15'),(3952,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Love this!','Lots of compliments on my Better Sweater. Maybe it\'s the color, but it feels very \"woolly\".',15,'2020-06-15'),(3953,'Judy H.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,5.0,'Fit to a T','I bought this for my boyfriend who is 5\'6\' and on the fairly skinny side. Typically he wears size medium for tees, sweaters, etc., but the small fit him perfectly, so be wary that this product does run a bit small. Other than the sizing, its super comfortable, warm, and a very simple, clean look. He loved it.',15,'2020-06-15'),(3954,'Robert W.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Layers','I bought a black XL on sale for layering under a shell when skiing. I liked it so much, I bought a couple more to move away from \'the big ski parka\' to simply layering this under a shell or with a vest under a shell. This item is also great just over a T around the house, over an extra layer for outside when it\'s chilly, and of cours',15,'2020-06-15'),(3955,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','0',NULL,5.0,'The Best of the Best, Hands Down! Get it? Lol','I purchased my first ever Down Sweater Hoody about 3 weeks ago and couldn\'t be happier. Patagonia stands behind their products for a reason. Couldn\'t beat the price that I paid, because ya know, discount codes are awesome :) The down is recycled and does have a scent, BUT that\'s mainly due to it not being treated or coated like most',62,'2020-06-15'),(3956,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Great product','This coat is exactly what you expect to get. Its warm, super lightweight and provides all the comfort you need. Perfect for wearing in commute to work or to any sporting event or even skiing. Recommend to all. It is nice to have a hood as opposed to the non-hooded version. Got mine for Christmas, best gift I have gotten in a long time.',62,'2020-06-15'),(3957,'Ben',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','0',NULL,5.0,'Best Around Jacket','This product has been with me on so many adventures. It was my go-to warmth creator during our 6-week truck camper trip in Alaska. It is a great outer jacket, but I\'ve used it frequently as a layer under my ski school uniform jacket on those cold days. It fits true to size. I like it a little bigger as it allows me to layer underneath or just',62,'2020-06-15'),(3958,'Michael C.',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,4.0,'Decent down hooded sweater','Have both the hooded and non-hooded version and already left a review on the non-hooded jacket version.',62,'2020-06-15'),(3959,'Scott D.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Warm, light, packable','Excellent for 30-50F temperature. I use this as my main commuter jacket in Minneapolis during the months of September thru December and March thru May. It’s warm, comfortable, and easy to stow away.',62,'2020-06-15'),(3960,'Barbara P.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'BEST EVER JACKET','There is nothing better - this is the epitome of a warm, attractive, and awesome jacket.',62,'2020-06-15'),(3961,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Best jacket I’ve ever owned!','Went hiking in Zion, Bryce and Grand Canyon right after Christmas. This jacket was amazing. Lightweight and warm. Completely worth every penny.',62,'2020-06-15'),(3962,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Great sweater','Bought this as gift for son, he loves it! Really warm and comfortable',62,'2020-06-15'),(3963,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket !','Great jacket !',62,'2020-06-15'),(3964,'Ruthanne W.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','LM',NULL,5.0,'Great down jacker','Between my husband and myself we have about six of these from over the past few years, and they are still as warm and awesome as ever!! Love this product',62,'2020-06-15'),(3965,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Great Every Day Jacket!','So happy with this purchase! Very compact, easy to move around in, and warm.',62,'2020-06-15'),(3966,'Jennifer J.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Awesome coat','Love the color - and the fit - perfect all around winter coat.',62,'2020-06-15'),(3967,'Vince F.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,3.0,'Nice but a step backwards','This is one of the nicer down hoodies on the market but it does not live up to the older ones, which were just about perfect for what they were. I am outside in the weather a lot doing nature photography in the high country and I have been using my current Patagonia jacket successfully for more than ten years. This new hood design just doesn’t keep',62,'2020-06-15'),(3968,'Aimee M.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,1.0,'Hole','It came with a hole and we didn’t realize it right away. So on the first day of wearing there were feathers falling out. Which didn’t help when it’s cold outside.',62,'2020-06-15'),(3969,'Jenni',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Best jacket','So light and warm',62,'2020-06-15'),(3970,'Luke P.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,5.0,'Third time\'s a charm','This is my third down sweater, the hood is great, and adds a good deal of warmth. Also, it seems like the right zipper on the jacket. I have had problems with the spiral zippers in the past, though patagonia has always been great about the repairs...',62,'2020-06-15'),(3971,'Mark S.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'This was a gift for','This was a gift for my son. He would never wear anything that is too bulky so I am pleased that he always has this on. It has been as cold as 20 degrees out, and with only a tshirt underneath, he stays quite warm.',62,'2020-06-15'),(3972,'Nick',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'My go-to','I never leave home in winter without this thing! It\'s light and packs up really small but is very warm. Make sure to keep it at least 3 feet away from granite at all times, though, or it might explode.',62,'2020-06-15'),(3973,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Warm and Comfortable!','I am extremely pleased for how warm this jacket is, especially considering how thin it is. It does not feel too bulky, and it is still very easy to layer underneath of it. I haven\'t stopped raving about it since I bought it.',62,'2020-06-15'),(3974,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','ALL',NULL,3.0,'“Major Sizing Issues”','The formula Patagonia uses for sizing is so different than what they print. I recommend definitely going up @ least (1) size if not (2). I’ve spoken to customer service on numerous occasions & even several of the agents have said the sizing is definitely different that what people are use to. If Patagonia would just note the “actual” sizes it w',62,'2020-06-15'),(3975,'Karen D.',NULL,'5\'1 - 5\'3','S/M',NULL,5.0,'Awesome','This jacket is awesome and the hood is always a crowd pleaser. I have purchased this for my son since he was 2 and now that he is 12, still loves it. The color (red) was just an added bonus for him.',62,'2020-06-15'),(3976,'Tanya H.',NULL,'None','XXL',NULL,4.0,'Had to buy a mens jacket','The jacket runs a little small since I usually wear a mens xl and have room. I bought this in an xxl and the waist and chest are quite large but hips are tight. With that being said I\'m sure ots a fine size for a man. Now if Patagonia would ever bring an xxl in womens I would be ecstatic because I love their stuff but have to buy bad fitting m',62,'2020-06-15'),(3977,'Peter C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'IMPRESSIVE','Warm warm warm warm ! Don’t need layers either! I can wear a short sleeve shirt while wearing this jacket! Keep this in mind I live in Central New York ! Snow capital of America!',62,'2020-06-15'),(3978,'Rick N.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Great service/Great item','Super swift delivery of a great new cozy down jacket.',62,'2020-06-15'),(3979,'anthony p.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Holiday Bliss','I treated myself to this jacket prior to the Holiday, but just in time for the cold that hits the Northeast this time of year. The jacket is fantastic is both style/design and well as functionality. I have been layering it under a Patagonia Gore Tex waterproof shell and I’ve been dry and warm.',62,'2020-06-15'),(3980,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,5.0,'Simply the best!','Best jacket! Looks great too!',62,'2020-06-15'),(3981,'arnold c.',NULL,'None','L/XL',NULL,5.0,'Too big but I still love it.','Got this in at a local outdoor shop. I’ve been wanting this jacket forever and I finally found it. They only had M and XL so I took the XL thinking it would work because I may wear more stuff underneath. Man this thing keeps you warm enough with just a polo shirt with it. So now the jacket is too big and doesn’t fit me like it should. but I love it',62,'2020-06-15'),(3982,'RO',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Lightweight, Comfortable and Warm','I bought one without the hood for my adult son possibly 3 years ago, but he missed one winter of wearing it. Her really likes the lightweight comfort and warmth of this jacket, even in cold Minnesota winter. Last winter, though, he must have caught one sleeve on something that punctured two very small holes, but enough to allow some down to pop thr',62,'2020-06-15'),(3983,'Moira D.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'excellent product','excellent product',62,'2020-06-15'),(3984,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Love it❤️','Love it❤️',62,'2020-06-15'),(3985,'Gregory K.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'sofa sleeper','well done. conforatble, versitile, & functional.',62,'2020-06-15'),(3986,'Augie A.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Best Coat Ever','At first I was skeptical however, after wearing it for about two weeks, I am extremely satisfied with my purchase. It’s very warm, lightweight, and the best part is you can wear it casually or dressed up. Thanks Patagonia!!!',62,'2020-06-15'),(3987,'Claudia D.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,5.0,'Love this jacket. Packs up','Love this jacket. Packs up so small for expeditions',62,'2020-06-15'),(3988,'Thomas M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Nice upgrade from the Micro','Nice upgrade from the Micro Puff in terms of added warmth.',62,'2020-06-15'),(3989,'Stephen G.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Fantastic jacket','Excellent warmth for the weight. Hood is just the right size. Down jackets tend to run just a tad large due to the assumption that you may have multiple base layers underneath including a fleece so I\'m going to say this jacket runs true to size. I recently wore it over a short sleeve shirt in sub 40 degree weather while only standing around in',62,'2020-06-15'),(3990,'Michael D.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Love my down sweater hoody','This is my in-between down jacket. Warmer than a nano or micro but not a big puffy jacket. Love the hood for extra warmth. Haven\'t had it out skiing or hiking so not sure how it will do with moisture management. Does not have vent panels so not sure I would recommend if you plan to sweat a lot.',62,'2020-06-15'),(3991,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,5.0,'I\'m 6\'6\" - Perfect Fit','For any long - armed tall guys out there, you know it\'s hard to find -anything- that fits both your body and your arms. This jacket fits snug to the body and also plenty of length in the arms. There is nothing worse then a jacket too short on the arms. This is not the case with this jacket. I am 6\'6\'\' slim/fit and ordered a Larg',62,'2020-06-15'),(3992,'Dione G.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,5.0,'Warm and Lightweight','I bought the same coat for my two daughters and husband. They love them. Very light- I thought the inner part would be kind a better sweater but it is not. It is warm If layered with other clothing. Perfect for football season.',62,'2020-06-15'),(3993,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'m\'s down sweater','Great fit, medium fits perfectly, room for a sweatshirt underneath if needed. Fits fine without one too. It\'s great against cold wind, yesterday was 35 degrees in the AM and I was cozy.',62,'2020-06-15'),(3994,'Arthur L.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Great Urban Jacket','Great as long as you use it for urban wear and low aerobic activities. Down is NOT a good insulator as many believe for back country and high aerobics use. When wet from the elements and perspiration it will freeze. Everyone in my family has one. I recommend it’s use with this caveat.',62,'2020-06-15'),(3995,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Love It','I bought my first Ms Down Sweater Hoody about six years ago and immediately loved it. After wearing my hoody for many years a bunch of small tears accumulated and eventually my zipper quit working. I reached out to customer support and they had me send it in for a potential repair or credit for something similar. They deemed it irreparable and then',62,'2020-06-15'),(3996,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Perfect!','Awesome jacket! Super warm and even warmer when paired with my R1 P/O. The L fits me great with enough room for layers and not too with just a t shirt underneath. Can handle light drizzle, but anything more requires a shell.',62,'2020-06-15'),(3997,'Ineva W.',NULL,'None','XL',NULL,1.0,'Not warm or worth the','Not warm or worth the money',62,'2020-06-15'),(3998,'Catherine H.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Very happy with my purchase','Very happy with my purchase',62,'2020-06-15'),(3999,'Katerina L.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,5.0,'Perfect everyday winter coat','I love this coat. It’s really warm for its size and the hood is a must have. I’m a tall thin woman (5’11 140lbs) and I ordered a size small. I can layer a thick fleece underneath just fine. I got it in Carbon which is actually a dark green color (not black like the name suggests).',62,'2020-06-15'),(4000,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Fantastic product!','Fantastic product!',62,'2020-06-15'),(4001,'Theodore S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Seems to be as advertised','Seems to be as advertised so far.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4002,'Jessica T.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Excellent','I love the down sweater hoody. I purchased one for myself & when I had the chance got this one for my husband. It is just the right weight and warmth for many conditions. Perfect for chilly northern CA mornings & nights. Throw it on for a quick hike or after a surf. It’s so versatile & goes with everything. Dress it up or casual. This i',62,'2020-06-15'),(4003,'Michael B.',NULL,'5\'1 - 5\'3','S',NULL,5.0,'Love it','Love it',62,'2020-06-15'),(4004,'Franklin S.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'nice','nice',62,'2020-06-15'),(4005,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Love it','Just was I was hoping for, somewhat fitted, not too bulky, and quite warm for those cold and rainy fall and early winter days.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4006,'Cameron C.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Cozy, warm and every day wear.','This is an essential piece of my every day winter wear. I love how light weight it is and how warm it keeps me. I wear it in sub freezing conditions to 50.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4007,'Curtiss O.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','L',NULL,3.0,'Sleeves are,disproportionately too long by','Sleeves are,disproportionately too long by approximately 4 inches, and I\'m not a short fat guy.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4008,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'0 or less','NB-7lb',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket!','I bought the sweater hoodie jacket for my son who goes to school in chilly Chicago and he loves it! Says it’s perfect weight and warmth',62,'2020-06-15'),(4009,'Les O.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Down sweater','Perfect for Colorado weather. Outstanding product. It is more of a jacket than a sweater. I usually take a large size but a medium is perfect. The hood is perfect and keeps out the wind and cold. Get the best.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4010,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,5.0,'Comfortable and Cozy ☺️','Loving the down sweater! Specially with this cold Weather ☺️',62,'2020-06-15'),(4011,'Damon E.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,5.0,'If you care about sustainability','While the production of any consumer product has its associated impact on the environment, Patagonia attempts to minimize it as much as possible. I will happily vote with my money for this company and their initiatives.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4012,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'down sweater','Feels great and looks good. Nice and worm and keeps the wind out. My wife had one she loves so much that I had to get one too.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4013,'Conner M.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Light weight and warm','Super lightweight and warm. Love the simplicity and style. Fits true to size.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4014,'Ethan Y.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','NB-7lb',NULL,2.0,'Too Thin','This jacket is was thinner than expected for the amount of price paid. I wish this product was thicker and had to return this jacket. I have to keep looking elsewhere maybe.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4015,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Scott’s review','Quintessential piece of craftsmanship from Patagonia! I’ve had one for years, wont go on a trip outdoors without it! Thanks for making the quality ! Forever Fan !',62,'2020-06-15'),(4016,'Rick',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,4.0,'Odiferous','Beautifully constructed. I have a 4-5 year old version of this garment and the newer version has stronger zippers, water proofing and bigger and better hood. However when I hung the new ones up in my room and came back awhile later the whole room smelled like cooked chicken! Doesn\'t much matter if you are outside but if it gets wet or you go i',62,'2020-06-15'),(4017,'Peter A.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Ms Down Sweater Hoody','Fits very well. I can easily wear this underneath my Rain Jacket shell as a warming layer. Allowing me to shed layers easily when my body temperature rises. The packable storage capability is nice while hiking, it also duals as a pillow if not in use.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4018,'Benjamin A.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Mens Sweater Down Hoody','Very warm, solid construction and stylish.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4019,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Best coat ever!!','This is my go to garment spring, fall and winter. Keeps you warm in the most challenging Montana\'s winter days. Its light yet warm and never seems to bulkey. I buy a size larger then I might normally wear so I can have a fleece on underneath.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4020,'Rand H.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,4.0,'Like a warm hug (but not clingy)','Loved this jacket. Always warmed me up, and fought off the wind (pretty nasty in winter in Illinois) and light rain. But the zipper gave out after two years; so did the zipper on my Down Sweater. (Patagonia did me solid: accepted my returns and gave me credit.) Suggested improvement would be a way to roll hood when not in use.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4021,'alpine_style',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,3.0,'Decent but nothing special','The fit is on the loose side so if your doing more athletic things it\'s not great. The light tan color I have show dirt very easily. I would wear this for a few week tops and had to wash it at least on a month. The down is good, but it\'s a pretty light fill. Considering the hype it doesn\'t live up to it.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4022,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'I love my down hoody!','I’m on my second down hoody now and with the exchange program I was able to recycle my well loved green one and get a new blue one just in time for more adventures! So far it’s been to the tops of snowy peaks in Alaska and to the windy high altitudes of Peru. Cheers to the next destination, thanks Patagonia',62,'2020-06-15'),(4023,'Scott P.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Perfect Patagonia','I used this jacket almost everyday for two weeks while guiding in Southern Patagonia. Heavy wind, light snow and rain and a smoky asado, the jacket held up beyond expectations. We will be purchasing these for our team in Chile as they are a must have piece of equipment. Thank you Patagonia for making a near perfect garment for these climes.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4024,'Gldpanda',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Goose down gives you wiiiiings','One of the best down jackets I’ve owned. I can wear it by itself in our local 20 degree-average weather, and it keeps me perfectly warm; 800-fill is sooo nice. The wind-proof outer is killer too, it actually keeps the wind out. Additionally, the hood and chin comfort are great. Here’s why it only gets 4 stars: Elasticized cuffs. In my opinion, it w',62,'2020-06-15'),(4025,'D. M.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Fit for Royalty','HRH Prince Harry wore this jacket in black on February 25, 2019 in Morocco. I bought it on line, received it on March 2, 2019 and it\'s perfection. I\'m a senior citizen, 5\'7\" size XXL, 230 lbs, waist 45\" and it looks and feels amazing on me too. You don\'t have to be a young slender Prince to be Royal.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4026,'Alex G.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','None',NULL,5.0,'I\'ve never had a jacket like this','This jacket is simply incredible. I\'ve been wearing the same peacoat for going on eight years, and I still love it, but, man, I completely forgot what it was like to own a warm jacket. This thing has stood up to Ohio\'s brutal 2019 winter––and with ease. I haven\'t gotten it terribly wet, so I can\'t attest to how the down holds up',62,'2020-06-15'),(4027,'Kevin B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Held Up to the Demands of Mount Fitz Roy','This Down Sweater Hoody is awesome whether you\'re in the Appalachian Mountains or on Mount Fitz Roy in El Chatan. This is great for warmth and wind resistance in the coldest months of the year. I\'m 6\'3, 190 lbs and a Large fit very well with just a T-shirt or with several layers. I\'m able to comfortable slide this on with severa',62,'2020-06-15'),(4028,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Tried the micro and nano until I found D’s one ;)','I destroyed both a nano puff and micro while on hiking/backpacking adventures with my dog.....I am very happy that Patagonia allowed me to return my purchases until I found the right puff for me. This jacket is much more durable and less likely to rip as the lighter primalofts/down jackets, the sacrifice are just a few grams that can still fit into',62,'2020-06-15'),(4029,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,5.0,'Best Jacket I’ve ever owned','This jacket has gotten me through just about everything. From the Oregon coast, harsh Montana winters, and summit peaks. I just bought a second one today and I thought I’d share how much I love this thing. Use it by itself, or layer underneath it. I wear a nano air hoody and an R1 hoody underneath the down. It’ll get you through everything up to li',62,'2020-06-15'),(4030,'Nochaser1959',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Best of its kind','I have spent quite an amount of time looking for a versatile midlayer/standalone jacket for downhill skiing that is highly functional and stylistic at the same time. As in all things in life, there isn’t a perfect do-it-all jacket, but this one comes close with a comfromise I can live with.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4031,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,1.0,'Smells Awful!!!','My wife bought me this for Christmas and when I wore it out I noticed an awful smell. We returned it to the Patagonia store in Boston and a new one was shipped. A couple of days later the new one arrived smelling equally as awful. At this point I was done with it but my wife requested another one be sent. It just arrived and it smells like a wet du',62,'2020-06-15'),(4032,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'So Warm, So Light!','I live in an area that gets into the 20s during the winter, and this jacket handles it like a champ. I have jackets twice this size and thickness that don’t keep me as warm. One of the best parts about it is that the Small actually fits me! I’m a male, 5’7 and 145lbs. I like slim fitting clothing, and the small is perfect on me. I can’t even wear a',62,'2020-06-15'),(4033,'Sam',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,5.0,'Please make this in a Slim Fit','First off, this is a great, warm hoody that\'s incredibly comfy. I\'m 6\'4, about 175 lbs though, so in appearance, it looks a bit boxy on me.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4034,'Bobby',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Perfect for pretty much everything','I\'ve worn this hoody for hours in the PNW backcountry and just walking around New York City, and it always performs. It keeps me warm even into the 20s with just a t-shirt on underneath, and into the single digits with a layer on under. With the hood up it\'s basically impenetrable. Sheds snow and light rain like a champ. My criticism is:',62,'2020-06-15'),(4035,'Ben',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XS',NULL,4.0,'Great except fragile','I’ve had the jacket for 12 days now and love how warm and comfortable it is. I’ve been able to wear it in temperatures down to the low 30s (with high humidity so it feels colder) and find that it is sufficiently warm even when worn only with a long sleeve. I compared it to the micro puff jacket and the real down makes a very noticeable difference i',62,'2020-06-15'),(4036,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Great Jacket','I recently purchased this jacket as an upgrade to the micro puff version which I love. This down sweater hoody didn\'t disappoint! My micro puff is a size medium which fits perfectly, but can be a little snug when I try to layer anything more than a t-shirt and a light sweater underneath. The down sweater is perfect for any layer situation I ma',62,'2020-06-15'),(4037,'Brig',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Great fit for tall skinny guys','I am 6\'2 150 pounds and I was concerned that this jacket would be too wide on me (size Medium). I have always preferred well tailored clothing, and I stay away from boxy clothes. I am happy to report that Patagonia has not neglected us skinny folks with the down sweater hoody! The jacket looks great and is easily long enough for my long arms a',62,'2020-06-15'),(4038,'Nick',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,4.0,'Awesome jacket, but easily tears','I personally love my micro green down sweater hoody. I find myself gravitating towards this jacket even when it’s cool outside. It’s unbelievably comfy and warm. Perfect fit even with a better sweater underneath for extra warmth. Definitely not the lightest jacket, but not as heavy as other insulated jackets and parkas. Wouldn’t change a thing abou',62,'2020-06-15'),(4039,'Steve',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','None',NULL,5.0,'steve','I actually have the ultra-light down hoody which is very similar to the sweater. I like that it is light, packs ultra-small into the chest pocket or can be stuffed into the left hand pocket and used as a pillow when flying. Based on my experience with Patagonia gear I won\'t be needing a new sweater for many years of hard and regular use.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4040,'Chris707',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Comfy in the backcountry','I primarily use this for mountain west backpacking. It really is a comfortable jacket, and comes with the high quality construction known with patagonia. Very happy with how the hood fits on my skull, and like having the bungee adjustability. This is not the lightest down jacket for backpacking, but I wanted the patagonia brand for this product. So',62,'2020-06-15'),(4041,'Liz',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,4.0,'For the ladies','I am a woman and didn\'t like the color offerings or the fitted look of the women\'s version of this jacket. I ordered the mens in a size small and am thrilled with the purchase. It is slightly tight around the hips but it also fits my brothers and dad similarly. I roll under the bottom for a bloused effect that is nice. Very warm and versa',62,'2020-06-15'),(4042,'Hot C.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,4.0,'Very warm and light but fragile','This very warm and lightweight \"sweater\" is perfect for urban and traveling situations. If worn alone while camping you\'ll need to be reasonably careful or add a stout outer shell. It\'s not what you would want to wear alone to carry an armload of firewood. It is fragile and can snag or tear easily.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4043,'Michael C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,4.0,'Decent lighweight hoody down sweater','Saw it on sale and bought it at a decent price.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4044,'Timothy F.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,4.0,'Good jacket for semi cold conditions.','I live in the mountains and it snows six months out of the year. I bought this to fill in the gap between my down sweater and my DAS parka. It is very warm for the weight and bulk of the jacket,and has become my new go to for cool weather camping.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4045,'Jc200',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'Super warm and great fit','I bought this in November and I have no complaints. All aspects of the jacket were well designed from the fit of the hood to the micro fleece zipper cover near you chin.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4046,'Colorado G.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XS',NULL,5.0,'Better Fit & Performance than its competition','A little background: I have purchased down jackets from Mountain Hardware and from LL Bean. This is my first Patagonia down jacket. This is by far and away the best of all of the down jackets I have tried. The quality of construction is superior: the zippers size,zippered pockets,interior pockets,adjustable drawstring inside the pockets,lined chin ',62,'2020-06-15'),(4047,'Mgvec',NULL,'None','M',NULL,3.0,'I Love It,But...','I have used this jacket as my everyday jacket and mid-layer for just about a year now and I love it!. However,after several washings with Granger\'s the down has bunched up and is no longer adequately filling the sleeve chambers up near the shoulders. I have washed and dried following all instructions and there does not appear to be any missing',62,'2020-06-15'),(4048,'Paul M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Essential gear,light and warm','I love this down sweater jacket. It weighs almost nothing,packs easily,and solves being chilled. It\'s like wrapping yourself in a cozy warm cocoon.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4049,'Colleen J.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'Great Everyday jacket','This is a classic. I like the down sweater hoody because I can wear it by itself everyday and it also fits nicely under a shell for colder days at the mountain. The hood is cozy when the wind is blowing.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4050,'Bryan G.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,2.0,'Love this jacket but.....it does not hold up','I loved this jacket. The fit of it is amazing and it\'s pretty warm. But....After just under a year,I noticed that the sleeves would rub against the pocket zippers and over time (less than year),this started to tear the fabric on the inside of the sleeves. After speaking to a colleague with the same jacket,he mentioned he had the same issue wit',62,'2020-06-15'),(4051,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Perfect!','This is by far the best coat that I have ever owned! It is incredibly warm,light-weight,and durable. I\'ve worn it the last few weeks in temperatures ranging from 0* F to 50*F and have never felt more warm or comfortable in a winter coat. I highly recommend!',62,'2020-06-15'),(4052,'Evan',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,4.0,'Great but include a patch','Jacket was great. However,on my first hike the nylon snagged and ripped on the elbow when passing a bush. I then had to order nylon patches off of amazon as there\'s no patagonia store directly near by. Patagonia,given your ironclad guarantee and repair rather than replace motto,why don\'t you include repair patches like many other outdoor',62,'2020-06-15'),(4053,'Deweyphan',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,4.0,'Fit is great','I have got to say the fit is awesome. it\'s not too large or not too slim. i always have problems with jackets being too tight at the pits. It\'s warm and perform well. With a tee shirt underneath and the jacket outside,35 degree and up is comfortable. However I put one star less when I notice the jacket (even though it has 800 fill power d',62,'2020-06-15'),(4054,'Kevin D.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'From Wetsuit to warmth in the wind.','I just spent a couple days surfing on the Oregon coast in typical November weather: air temp: 42 degrees. Water temp: 52 degrees,rain and wind. As soon as I get out of the water and back to the car,I pull my wetsuit down to my waist,dive into my down sweater hoody and then my Torrentshell jacket. In a few minutes,I\'m toasty and my fingers are',62,'2020-06-15'),(4055,'Bart3',NULL,'None','M',NULL,1.0,'A Fragile Disappointment','I was really looking forward to this coat getting me through Beijing winters. I\'ve worn it to work maybe five times and yesterday found two small tears in the outer fabric. Ridiculous to spend this much on a coat that can\'t hold up on the subway. Will update with pictures when I get home.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4056,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,5.0,'Another Dandy!!','For over 30 years I have been a regular customer of Patagonia. My closets are full of Patagonia gear that won\'t wear out! In 30 years,I have return one item. It was quickly replaced no questions asked. My new purchase,a down hoody sweater,is amazing! I can\'t wait to test it out in some deep back bowl powder stashes!! Whoohoo!!! Thanks Pat',62,'2020-06-15'),(4057,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Keeps you warm but doesn\'t overheat your body!','You have to love down feathers,they keep the cold out but also allow for heat to escape',62,'2020-06-15'),(4058,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'Great coat','Only drawback,packing it into its pocket is near impossible for me. Other than that it\'s awesome. I\'m 5\'10\" 185 lbs. L fits well. I have only been down into the 40s with it. I suspect if you\'re moving around it\'s good down into the 20s or below depending on wind etc.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4059,'Kesling',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Best All Around Jacket','The best all around jacket. I use it for; sailing especially when going to Catalina,camping,hiking,and traveling. Packs small and comes with me anywhere I go.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4060,'Jct69',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Shwinng','I had this exact same jacket for the last 8 years and bought a new one when that one gave out. All I need to say about how much I love this thing. It\'s light and packable enough that you never leave home without it.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4061,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Very good quality,great fit jacket!','Bought this jacket for my husband who is a professional skater.Great jacket overall . Most important- fits great ,TTS. Light,warm and very comfortable.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4062,'Jackfrost',NULL,'None','XS',NULL,4.0,'Awesome jacket','only concern is Patagonia sizing is very inconsistent. Had a mens XS previously and replaced with another mens XS only to find it actually too small. The jacket rocks-all seasons!',62,'2020-06-15'),(4063,'Badger1',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Best Jacket','I am really liking this jacket. Cold mornings,windy afternoons or light drizzle it\'s my go to jacket. I often wear it with just my board short and do not get cold. Perfect jacket to throw on after spearfishing or',62,'2020-06-15'),(4064,'Ajmw',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Best down jacket I ever purchased','A bit more expensive than the other down jackets I was tracking,yet well worth it. Fit is true and not bulky whatsoever. I prefer the hoodie version,incredible warmth in an ultra-light jacket. The hood is the best design I\'ve ever experienced: warmth were you need it (skull & neck & upper chin) and it doesn\'t interfere at all with',62,'2020-06-15'),(4065,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Warm and not too bulky!','I bought the Down Sweater Hoody as a heavy mid-layer or outer layer on cold dry days. It has been great! I\'m glad I went with the hood especially when the cold wind kicks up\'I don\'t think it is too bulky and I barely notice it when it\'s not in use. I am 6\' tall,160lbs,and the medium fits really well.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4066,'R10 W.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Just the right tool for the job','Bought this as a mid layer for under my work shell. I\'m on the hill from 7:30 in the morning until 5:00 in the afternoon. Cozy and comfortable all day and in varying temperatures. Love the hood,which fits over my big head with a helmet on!',62,'2020-06-15'),(4067,'Rick44',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'down hoody','Perfect especially the attention to detail. Thanks for all you do',62,'2020-06-15'),(4068,'Jeremy60',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Toally satisfied.','I have worn my down sweater now on a handful of 20 degree days and I am totally satisfied with its performance. I layered with a polar fleece,which helped stop air flow though the baffle stitching. I have worn warmer jackets,but none whose warmth-to-weight ratio was this impressive. It weighs almost nothing. It\'s a high-quality product and wel',62,'2020-06-15'),(4069,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Great Coat!','I needed a coat for awhile and decided this would the perfect coat for the price. The coat keeps you really warm when it\'s cold out! Would recommend to anyone',62,'2020-06-15'),(4070,'Hot C.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Go for a looser fit','Great between 15F to 50F. Paired under a rain jacket it\'s perfect for icy windy cold rain or sleet. Before you buy be sure to try this on with an undershirt and thick long sleeve shirt as you\'d wear on a cold day. I\'m 6\'2\" 198lbs and the XL is the right fit when wearing layers.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4071,'Darcey',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,4.0,'Great but for one design issue','I\'m very happy with this except for the zippered pocket design. It is a stretch to call it a \"pocket\" as you can\'t place items down into it. It\'s more like a horizontal sleeve. This is an issue with things like keys and wallets,getting in an out of cars,for example. If the pocket is not partially zipped,then items can fall',62,'2020-06-15'),(4072,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket','I bought this a month ago for cold weather trip in NY. It\'s so comfortable and warm.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4073,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'I wear ONLY Patagonia\'s winter Hoodies in Moscow!','once i\'ve chosen Patagonia\'s hoody in Italy and since then I wear only Patagonia\'s hoodies& They are light and warm^ very comfortable but unfortunately not very strong against scratches',62,'2020-06-15'),(4074,'Freddie H.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Great commuting coat with hood','Seam split on first coat and you guys replaced no questions asked wonderful policy ty',62,'2020-06-15'),(4075,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XL',NULL,5.0,'Best coat I\'ve ever owned!!!','I feel like this has been the worst winter on record that I can remember in the Pacific Northwest. That said - everyday I am pretty stoked to get to throw on my Hooded Down Sweater again!!! Rain. Check. Snow. Check. Freezing rain. Check. Chilliaxing on the couch. Check. Happiest customer ever. Double check. Hats off Patagonia - this jacket is a kee',62,'2020-06-15'),(4076,'Jominty',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Great Versatile Jacket','Great overall jacket! Living in the Midwest during the winter means strong wind.. this jacket cuts the wind wile being very light and versatile. I would buy it again!',62,'2020-06-15'),(4077,'Wombat S.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','S',NULL,4.0,'Solid Jacket','I bought this a month ago. It has served me well,as it keeps me comfortably warm in the coldest days of the southeast. It fits well and I can easily fit what I usually wear underneath it: t-shirt,flannel,and even a hoodie if I really need it. So far,the only problems I\'ve had are around 4 or 5 down feathers sticking out on the inside of the ja',62,'2020-06-15'),(4078,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'So Warm!','Wore this with just a light base layer and a shell snowboarding in Tahoe. Temp was in the teens and high winds. Love it!',62,'2020-06-15'),(4079,'Rick B.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,5.0,'Perfectly functional.','I have wanted one of these jackets for a long time and finally bought one,and I couldn\'t be happier. Somehow it is perfectly comfortable in a vast amount of conditions. I\'ve worn it in temps ranging from 10-60 degrees so far and been completely comfortable. It fits great and feels great. It\'s my favorite jacket!',62,'2020-06-15'),(4080,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Great Jacket!','Got this as a Christmas gift and love it. Surprisingly warm for as light weight as it is. Love how compact it is. Double check your sizes. I\'m 6\' 205 and needed an XL. Also highly recommend paying the extra and getting the hood. Great looking jacket too.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4081,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Perfect','As advertised,Patagonia never disappoints. Super warm,comfy with full range of motion.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4082,'Tim S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Been waiting','Did not disappoint! Very warm and cozy. Fits great. I read some neg reviews and I didn\'t have any issues to date',62,'2020-06-15'),(4083,'Ben R.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Crazy Warm,Crazy Soft','First down coat in a long time,and I can\'t believe I waited so long. The hood is tailored perfectly so there is very little peripheral vision blockage. Weight is perfect so I hardly notice the jacket. Collar is great too,zips very high so hardly any cold air can sneak in. I haven\'t worn this skiing yet,but should be good as a midlayer on',62,'2020-06-15'),(4084,'Joshua G.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XXL',NULL,3.0,'Very nice. Small for xxl.','I got this to replace a previous one I had recycled through Patagonia. I was pleased with the color,the new zippers and construction.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4085,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Warm and Light','Used this on several backcountry ski trips already this year and is a great combination of lightweight/low volume and warmth. Love the hoodie-I have the down sweater without the hoodie and may have to retire it. The added warmth of a hoodie compared to a jacket & hat doesn\'t compare. I am 6\',180 and the Medium is a snug fit,but is how',62,'2020-06-15'),(4086,'Colten R.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Warmth without the weight','Exploring the mountains this season? Don\'t leave home without a down hoody. Versatile as a insulation layer or outerwear. This hoody will keep you warm down to single digits. Weather doesn\'t care if you\'re not prepared. So don\'t get caught with out your down hoody.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4087,'Brax',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Cold weather essential','I\'ve been a PNW resident for 10+ years and somehow,I\'ve never owned a down jacket. After the typical extensive research I conduct before purchasing a piece of technical apparel,I selected this jacket.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4088,'Brian I.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Warm and Compact','I\'ve had this for about a month and I\'m still putting it through its paces.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4089,'James W.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Super warm','Great fit. I\'m 6\'3 and sleeves are good length. Very warm and packable.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4090,'My4kids',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Tonya Creel','I. Ought this for.my college son and he loves the hooded quilted zip up.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4091,'Andykot',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Good Quality','I bought it as a gift for my son he\'s 25 years old and he loves it.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4092,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Great All-Around Hoody!','I bought this two months ago for trip to Canada. I am completely satisfied! I wore this in single digit weather with just a t-shirt underneath and was completely warm. I also love the fact that I can pack into the inside pocket for traveling. Definitely worth the purchase!',62,'2020-06-15'),(4093,'LH',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Awesome Product','This jacket keeps me warm and fits perfectly. Very happy with the purchase!',62,'2020-06-15'),(4094,'Capt M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Awesome jacket','Got the Mens down sweater hoody and haven\'t stopped wearing it all year! I have a ton of Patagonia gear and some 10-15 years old but so far this has been my favorite piece. Warm,thin,packable - it\'s everything I wanted and need! Only down side is now all my kids are demanding one!',62,'2020-06-15'),(4095,'Garlic F.',NULL,'None','XS',NULL,5.0,'Pitches and Stitches','I\'ve had this jacket for six years now. It\'s been with me on a month long backpacking course in the Winds,a month and a half of backpacking in the Indian Himalaya,weeklong trips in Glacier NP,Utah,The Beartooths,survived desperate chimney climbing and backcountry ski days in the tobacco roots and bridger range.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4096,'Brian Y.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,2.0,'Not thrilled with it','I have a pretty standard frame and body size and find the lower seam to just be too tight. The bottom of the jacket has a draw cord which is useless as the bottom seems to taper in so much that it is tight in the bottom 2\" but fine everywhere else. Also a few of the stitching separating the down baffles comes out. I returned one jacket already',62,'2020-06-15'),(4097,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,2.0,'Beware of the wet dog smell!','Smelled fine when I unpacked it - wore it on a light walk and by the time I got to my gym,I smelled a strong smell that I can only describe as a wet dog. I thought,that\'s strange - my gym stinks like a wet dog. Put jacket away in locker and no more smell. Wore it home and by the time I was in the elevator in my building,the smell came back. Fi',62,'2020-06-15'),(4098,'Amy S.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Essential Winter Piece of Gear','This jacket has you coverd from head to tail! This is as good as the regular Down Sweater but ups the warmth & coverage level a bit with the addition of a hood.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4099,'Go C.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,5.0,'perfect winter jacket','the best looking/warmest jacket I have worn,true to size (like most Patagonia products) perfect for casual wear and easily layerable with fleece underneath it.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4100,'Daxx',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XXL',NULL,5.0,'EXCEPTIONALLY WARM MID LAYER','I am surprised to experience how warm this jacket is. I have used it for hiking as a mid layer under a Goretex-Pro shell and over a basic merino base layer when the temps have hit below 0 Celsius. I really like it for a couple of reasons; one is the thing is so light for a mid layer that you hardly know it is on. This is huge on an active hike in c',62,'2020-06-15'),(4101,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Very warm and my new go to jacket!','I used to lug around my fleece when hiking and backpacking. With the Down Sweater Hoody I can pack it into itself and it takes significantly less room. I\'ve always heard good things about Patagonia gear,but was concerned about the price point. After a backpacking trip to Second Beach,La Push,WA where we experienced high winds,cold front,and ra',62,'2020-06-15'),(4102,'Duckman',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great daily wear','Great daily winter wear jacket and the hood adds that extra warmth for both head and neck',62,'2020-06-15'),(4103,'Bucket',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Nice jacket. Cuffs could use','Nice jacket. Cuffs could use more stretch,hard to get them over my hands when they\'re warm. Could definitely go for bigger sizes though,6\'7\" around 250 and xxl feels a bit small and short. great if it fits you though.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4104,'Sean L.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,2.0,'Sizing is way off','Bought this jacket and had to return it because I was very unimpressed with the sizing. Large was way too big and medium was way too small on me. Furthermore, the sleeves are way too wide. If you could improve the fit of these jackets to accompany slimmer profiles that would be great',62,'2020-06-15'),(4105,'Warrentotheg',NULL,'None','None',NULL,3.0,'Fleece Lining Needs to Go','The years past had a much more aesthetically pleasing face fabric on the black color. My main gripe is the fleece lining by the face that has been added to this updated version. It makes it an eyesore and honestly the nylon felt good up against my skin. Patagonia is second to none when it comes to environmental practices in the outdoor industry, so',62,'2020-06-15'),(4106,'Kg R.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Great Jacket - A Few Tweaks Needed','This is a great jacket for a variety of dry, cold weather uses. I find the DS comfortable with only a baselayer between 25 and 40 degrees. When the temperature dips below 25, I usually thrown on a shell or layer with something warmer like the Patagonia better sweater.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4107,'Psibarber',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Best Down Jacket','I started years ago buying Patagonia as a suggestion from my son a rock climber in Yosemite. My three Patagonia layers are base, down sweater and down hoody jacket in cold conditions. These products are well built unlike alternate products from LLbean and others which the down flys out everywhere from holes in the seams. Best of all Patagonia repai',62,'2020-06-15'),(4108,'T1cartel',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Warm and great fitting','This jacket is the perfect weight and warmth for year round use in So. Cal. The new, slimmer \"improved\" fit is a real upgrade over the previous, boxier fit. It compresses easily into it\'s own pocket for effortless storage or transportation.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4109,'Quetico',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Zipper Problem','I have purchased two of these jackets and love them for hiking, canoeing and skiing. However when I am skiing I need to attach my season pass to the pocket zipper. Since these jackets have pockets that close upward I keep losing pocket belongings. The problem is the weight of the pass and the speed of skiing pull the zipper open. It would be much s',62,'2020-06-15'),(4110,'Photuris',NULL,'None','None',NULL,2.0,'Good fit, warm, but already coming apart','I would rate the jacket higher if it weren\'t for the fact that after 2 months of wear, a thread on the left sleeve came loose already. I have only worn the jacket for going to work and back, riding in cars--no outdoor activity use whatsoever. I will have to send the jacket back for repair, but not sure if I want to keep the jacket as the same',62,'2020-06-15'),(4111,'Jack B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Love it. Need more Colors','Seriously, awesome jacket. I rocked this guy at Breckenridge last weekend when it was dumping snow, under a shell of course, and it kept me nice and warm the whole time. Popped a few vents on the shell when I was getting warm and closed them when I was cold and it worked perfectly.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4112,'Artlover',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Good, but could be better','I\'ve been a huge fan and purchaser of Patagonia jackets and clothes ever since the business started. I have owned various clothing and jackets that have gone through tons of changes year after year. I have many of your jackets that I use for many different activities. My activities include: running/jogging, walking, car trips, skiing, hiking,',62,'2020-06-15'),(4113,'Lavandrix',NULL,'None','None',NULL,1.0,'Poor Quality Control and Design','So, I ended having to return replace the previous iteration of this hoody, and was looking forward to the new design of this one. I would have to say it was a brief and bittersweet rendezvous. First, the hood closure broke in the wash only one day after receiving it in the mail (1/30/15). Second, and on a completely unrelated note, I was unimpresse',62,'2020-06-15'),(4114,'Dewr41',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Very warm, great fit','I work FT as a ski instructor and I bought this to layer under my outer jacket on cold days. With a couple of base layers, this jacket keeps me warm even when the temps drop below zero. The fit is great around the head/neck, wrists and waist.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4115,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Great Jacket','I wanted a light down jacket for skiing and backpacking. Patagonia is always on the top of my list of brands, so I tried it. I don\'t regret it at all. It\'s incredibly light and warm and I can wear it with a light layer underneath if I want to be extra warm or nothing and I\'m still protected from the elements. I have also wear it as a',62,'2020-06-15'),(4116,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'So hot when it is SO cold!','I purchased this jacket as I was relocating from Seattle to the northwest corner of Minnesota. With sub zero temps for long periods of time as well as windy days, I needed a jacket that would stand up to these harsh weather conditions. This jacket has held up extremely well against these harsh conditions thus far and will continue to do so. The hoo',62,'2020-06-15'),(4117,'Shopping B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Almost Perfect','The Patagonia \"Down Sweater\" series is an excellent choice for a mid-weight down insulator. I\'ve owned the regular \"Down Sweater\" for many years and it\'s the perfect insulator for fall and non-subzero winter days. In fact, I\'m always surprised at how warm it can be.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4118,'Zigzakk',NULL,'None','None',NULL,3.0,'Decent','Good garment thus far. Warm down to about 20 degree for me, and then I need to put another mid-layer underneath. There is a weird fit to it. It is too short on my torso in a small (5\'8\" 135lbs) and I hate the idea of cold wind sneaking in from underneath, so I bought a medium and its a bit bulky in the midsection, particularly if I am wea',62,'2020-06-15'),(4119,'The B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,1.0,'It keeps you warm but...','I bought this in blue back in October and had to exchange it by December because the wrist seam was falling apart and there was discoloration around the opening of the hood (looked like it was wet but really wasn\'t). Upon my exchange, I decided to go with the same color. However, I\'ve only had this new one for a little over a week and the',62,'2020-06-15'),(4120,'Franconia',NULL,'None','None',NULL,3.0,'Very lightweight','I like this jacket, but be warned that it is a very lightweight down jacket. It is pretty warm, but not that warm. It is almost more of a \"sweater\". After a couple of seasons with feathers poking through and coming out and being compressed over and over again, it starts to feel very thin and not that warm. I can\'t imagine the need fo',62,'2020-06-15'),(4121,'Mazer',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'A College Student\'s Best Friend','This jacket is literally the bomb. It looks great, fits the body very well and is extremely warm. It\'s somewhat fragile but is to be expected of a jacket that\'s made with feathers and a polyester ripstop shell. I get compliments all the time (especially from the ladies) and this thing is literally my go-to piece. I own multiple pieces of',62,'2020-06-15'),(4122,'Tx C.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Perfect Alpine Jacket','This jacket is amazingly warm for how small it packs down and how light it is. It\'s been with me on alpine mountain treks and big multi-pitch trad climbs where belays can be rather chilly. If I\'m in the mountains or pulling rock, this jacket is in my pack.',62,'2020-06-15'),(4123,'Sergio',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,5.0,'Warm and cozy','Closest thing to having an actual coat of hair. It produces heat when you wear it, I love it.',132,'2020-06-15'),(4124,'Lyndsay',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,3.0,'Sleeves run short','As a tall woman (510 ), I have frequently bought mens sweatshirts and jackets from Patagonia (Im usually a medium in womens and an XS/S in mens) in order to get extra arm sleeve length. However, I feel like the arm sleeves have gotten much shorter in the last couple years and this fleece is a testament to that as the sleeves are a good couple inche',132,'2020-06-15'),(4125,'Zach L.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Warm Warm Warm','Don\'t let its fluff fool you, this fleece is very warm. It is great for wearing around the house on a cold winter day or for heading outside when conditions are cold but clear. The fit is true to size, however, I will say that it feels tight in the armpits. I wear a Large in just about everything and noticed the fit does feel snuff under the a',132,'2020-06-15'),(4126,'Guillermo M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'So comfy, so warm, so dope','Love this fleece.',132,'2020-06-15'),(4127,'Carolyn S.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Gatos 1/4 Zip','I get a Patagonia every year for my grandson and he lives it.',132,'2020-06-15'),(4128,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Great product','Gift for my son. He loved it!',132,'2020-06-15'),(4129,'Stephanie T.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','L',NULL,5.0,'Love Love Love','Love Love Love',132,'2020-06-15'),(4130,'Ryan C.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Cozy Sweater','I bought this as a Christmas gift for my brother-in-law. They live in Long Island, so naturally, winters are brutal. He’s usually a S, but I sized up to a M so he can fit more clothes under it. He’s able to wear an undershirt, dress shirt, and a sweater under this cozy/fuzzy monster of a sweater. He’s been wearing it every day, so I’d say it was th',132,'2020-06-15'),(4131,'Thomas R.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'This pullover is as soft','This pullover is as soft as I hoped it would be. I have an itchy skin condition and this is the only fleece I can wear now. It is also very warm',132,'2020-06-15'),(4132,'Robert C.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XL',NULL,5.0,'very happy','very happy',132,'2020-06-15'),(4133,'Phil Q.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Comfortable.','Comfortable.',132,'2020-06-15'),(4134,'Vince P.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,5.0,'Overall good experience','Overall good experience',132,'2020-06-15'),(4135,'Colette M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Very warm garment.','Very warm garment.',132,'2020-06-15'),(4136,'Kyrillos T.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Quarter Zip','Ordered a large last time and fit a bit big, so tried a medium and it was too small. Great Sweaters overall',132,'2020-06-15'),(4137,'Sarah B.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,5.0,'So soft and cozy','I’m a women, but I bought a men’s small so the arms would be longer and the length would be longer. The men’s small fits perfect and I still have room to wear layers underneath. If I wanted it to be more fitted with just a thin layer underneath I would have went with an XS. I haven’t tried washing it yet. I bought this in blue since I have two blon',132,'2020-06-15'),(4138,'Anthony V.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L/XL',NULL,5.0,'This style sweater is not','This style sweater is not for daily wear, it gets your body temperature very high. You sweat a lot and in a short period of time. I would recommend wearing for hiking, snow play and extreme cold winters.',132,'2020-06-15'),(4139,'Rodney T.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,5.0,'Better than expected...','Multipurpose, Excellent Material, Soft, Warm & Cozy. I bought this item in three colors. Fits well.',132,'2020-06-15'),(4140,'Kathryn J.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Fuzzy, Warm and Comfy','I would just offer the suggestion that you may want to size up since it’s a bit thick. Otherwise, I highly recommend it since it is all of the above!',132,'2020-06-15'),(4141,'Andrew O.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,5.0,'amazing','very comfortable',132,'2020-06-15'),(4142,'Josh S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Best sweater ever','Love this. Get comments every time I wear it.',132,'2020-06-15'),(4143,'Aaron S.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,3.0,'Odd Fit','I felt like this might be a women\'s cut. I bought a medium and am 5\'9\" with an average build. Getting this thing on and off is a real chore, it looks nice once it is on, but it feels tight on the shoulders and arms.',132,'2020-06-15'),(4144,'Sameer A.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'A wearable blanket that is also fashionable','Literally the best purchase I’ve made in a while. It’s warm, soft, and versatile. I wear it to class, to work, to sleep, and out on the town, and it always works and looks good. 10/10',132,'2020-06-15'),(4145,'Gretchen O.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,5.0,'soft plush pull over','love it!',132,'2020-06-15'),(4146,'Mary M.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Excellent service and products.','Excellent service and products.',132,'2020-06-15'),(4147,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,5.0,'My man loves it!','My man loves it!',132,'2020-06-15'),(4148,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Great product','Great product',132,'2020-06-15'),(4149,'Mike G.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','None',NULL,5.0,'Dope zip','I like it runs nice',132,'2020-06-15'),(4150,'Jonathan D.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,5.0,'So comfy','This sweatshirt is awesome. So soft and comfy. I have two different colors.',132,'2020-06-15'),(4151,'Jory T.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','XL',NULL,4.0,'Warm sweater and great material,','Warm sweater and great material, the fit could be a little better',132,'2020-06-15'),(4152,'Anthony R.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Ms Los Gatos 14-Zip','Nice and warm',132,'2020-06-15'),(4153,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,5.0,'Love my Patagonia!','I love my 1/4 zip top! Fuzzy and warm!',132,'2020-06-15'),(4154,'Fengbin H.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S/M',NULL,4.0,'Ms Los Gatos 14-Zip','Very cozy and warm. It works perfectly as the middle layer in the windy weather condition. Perfect choice as the top layer for the fall season.',132,'2020-06-15'),(4155,'Bethel A.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Amazing fit and very cozy','Amazing fit and very cozy',132,'2020-06-15'),(4156,'Timothy T.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'Amazing Pullover','I love this pullover! It\'s perfect for a gloomy autumn day. I don\'t get cold super easy so it\'s perfect and lightweight.',132,'2020-06-15'),(4157,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'fluffy, soft, excellent purchase!','fluffy, soft, excellent purchase!',132,'2020-06-15'),(4158,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Amazing','Fuzzy and warm inside and out it’s just a little snug in the arms',132,'2020-06-15'),(4159,'Sergey T.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0