 was a little bummed out when it was too big. He had worn it for the day so I cannot return it. It will become loose after a while of wearing it. He loves the fabric and the color. I just wish it was smaller. I will have to try and shrink it. He is 175 and a Large was too big.',131,'2020-06-15'),(4280,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Love it!','I bought this a few months ago and absolutely love it! I am 6\' 190lbs and I wear a large in everything,so that is exactly what I bought. It fits perfect! The material is so thick,I grab it to wear at every chance I get. This pullover is not bulky by any means but you don\'t lose any of the warmth.',131,'2020-06-15'),(4281,'Edward99',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,4.0,'Almost perfect','Very comfy,slightly dressier,cotton version of the classic Synchilla Snap T,but not as warm. Comfier and trimmer than the fleece version,only issue I had was with the cuffs. They are very wide and fall over my hands. I would\'ve preferred a simple elastic cuff like on the original,but I have quite small wrists and hands so your experience may b',131,'2020-06-15'),(4282,'Jlangley28',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Top Patagonia item in my closet','This shirt is everything you want it to be when you finally decide to spend the money to buy it. Not only does it look and fit great,but the quality of the sticking is amazing. I can wear this sweater in 25 degree weather and be at a comfortable body temp,or I can wear it in 60 degree weather and be at a comfortable body temp. Anytime I leave the h',131,'2020-06-15'),(4283,'Jack D.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,3.0,'Great sweater,shrinks immensly','I have two of these sweaters. One from last year\'s product line (2015-2016),and one from this year (the Forge Grey sweater). I am 6\'0\" and 165 lbs. I bought a medium in both sweaters. The sweater from last year fits well,if somewhat short around the waist. The sweater from this year is significantly smaller. I laid both sweaters on t',131,'2020-06-15'),(4284,'Holden',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Super Soft Warm and Light Weight','6\'1 205lbs Athletic build. Fits very slightly baggy but after a wash it fit me perfect. This product is extremely soft and very light weight. Even though it is very light weight it holds warmth very well. My wife loves it on me.',131,'2020-06-15'),(4285,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Love this! But needed to exchange for bigger size','I bought this a month ago,and use it almost daily. It\'s a little dressier than the traditional snap-t pullover,but it\'s every bit as comfortable. I am 6\' tall and 170 lbs,and I have always worn a Patagonia medium. I loved the medium in this pullover - until I washed it! It shrunk severely,even using low heat for the dryer. I purchase',131,'2020-06-15'),(4286,'JayRich',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Perfect','This has to be my favorite piece of Patagonia that I own. I\'m a big guy (6\'3\",280lbs) and built like a NFL center. Pretty consistently,I\'ll have trouble with the length of Pata clothing. This pullover is definitely an exception to that. It fits incredible. It\'s a little bit slimmer of a fit (in my opinion) compared to the f',131,'2020-06-15'),(4287,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'So many complements!','I\'ve had my eye on this for awhile but was waiting for the right color (not blue or grey) and just got it delivered last week. I wore it all weekend and had to figure out how not to wear it to work everyday as well. It\'s super soft,warm,and looks as good in the office as it does in the garage. It goes everywhere and layers perfectly. The',131,'2020-06-15'),(4288,'Chopin',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Beautiful and comfortable','The fit is very well done and exceptionally comfortable',131,'2020-06-15'),(4289,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'So good I went back for more!','I had pondered buying this pullover for about 6 months due to the price. But one night after a few cocktails a decided to make the leap and let me tell ya,Patagonia did not disappoint!! I received it very promptly in the mail and never took it off. I liked it so much I could not resist when Patagonia came out with more colors. I ordered the Forge G',131,'2020-06-15'),(4290,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XL',NULL,5.0,'Awesomeness!','Bought this sweater at a local outlet as well and love it so much I\'m going back tomorrow for another one in a different color. It\'s well made and super soft. Also received tons of complimemts while wearing it. Must have item in your fall wardrobe!',131,'2020-06-15'),(4291,'Nickname U.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Ultimate Comfort','Perusing the Patagonia outlet by my house,I tried this on and instantly knew I had to buy it and that it would be my most comfortable sweater. I have had it for over a year and it has held up and remained comfortable (I do not send it through the dryer). I bought a larger size for comfort. My wife instantly bought one as well. We compare it to wear',131,'2020-06-15'),(4292,'Ryan',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Super comfortable','I love these pants. They are an athletic fit, slim enough not to billow out in the wind when walking, but not too tight that they restrict movement, and they have some stretch to them to help them move really well with you. They are warm, the wind can blow through them though, but that helps them breath well. I have worn them on casual walks and th',136,'2020-06-15'),(4293,'Christopher',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,4.0,'pretty good, with caveats','So, I had a pair of these and they pilled like crazy. I returned them. The second pair pills a bit, as would be expected with this type of fabric (though the r1/r2 techface jackets don\'t pill nearly as much), but you can touch it up easily enough with a sweater stone.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4294,'Bill',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Super quality pants','Excellent product,I use for all activities and daily life.As previously noted ,you neeed to include zippers for pockets and offer additional colors.I have three pairs and Love these pants.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4295,'Andrew',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','None',NULL,1.0,'Awesome, but very disappointed','Just bought these sweatpants and they are very comfortable and keep you very warm. Really like the grid thermal pattern and they fit great, not baggy, but not too tight either. The big issue here is that just wearing these a couple times and didnt even wash them. The outside started pilling and now it is everywhere. For how much I paid for these, I',136,'2020-06-15'),(4296,'Mike V.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Love these pants','They are great winter sweats that look a little nicer - I work from home and wear them during the day, and they\'re warm enough to wear outside walking the dog in winter (whereas with normal sweat pants I need to put on long johns under them). The only thing is I would love more colors (blue, black, dark gray, whatever) - I would definitely buy',136,'2020-06-15'),(4297,'Sam K.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,2.0,'Great for around the house but. . . .','after just a wash or two the fabric shows fraying dimples along the grid pattern -- most prominently on the upper legs. So much for sustainability . . . .',136,'2020-06-15'),(4298,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Love ‘em but they’re big','Love ‘em but they’re big for a size small',136,'2020-06-15'),(4299,'Jimmy',NULL,'None','S',NULL,2.0,'Had high hopes','I own several pairs of older R1 that I wear quite a bit in the winter. They’re more like lose tights, or snug joggers with no side pockets or draw string & a zip back pocket. I was happy to find these had a draw string & side pockets!',136,'2020-06-15'),(4300,'Dave',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'My trusty R1 top....as a bottom.','Been wearing the R1 quarter zip and R1 hoody for years and years, and finally was able to add the R1 pants to my collection. They function exactly as expected: awesomely. Comfortable, nice cut and nice deep pockets. The legs are maybe a touch wider than they need to be, but no big deal. The drawcord on the waist is a bit short though and can be a l',136,'2020-06-15'),(4301,'cheryl j.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','XS',NULL,5.0,'cool weather pants','look great on. slim fit and true to size. great for 40 degree weather here in florida winter. out door tai chi practice and indoor yoga in a cool room. light weight and will be great for travel to cool climates. a bit expensive, even for patagonia.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4302,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Great','Just what I was looking for, very comfortable pair of warm pants. Breathable enough to be active in too.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4303,'Tod W.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'My favorite pants','These pants get more use than any Patagonia product I have. I\'ve worn them as house pants almost every day for over 5 years. Bought another pair a year ago just in case they discontinue at some point. Have yet to wear the new ones but they seem identical in every way. I really can\'t tell that my originals have worn very much but as stated',136,'2020-06-15'),(4304,'Simon F.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,4.0,'Perform as expected','I’ve been mostly wearing these around the house as sweatpants, and a few times under shell pants on especially cold days. They work as fleece sweatpants should. The pockets are a nice addition. No fly makes them less than ideal as a base layer, but it’s not a real problem unless I’m wearing a harness. I’ve experienced the pilling that some others h',136,'2020-06-15'),(4305,'Noel Q.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Excellent pants','Comfy, great fit, and can tell they will last',136,'2020-06-15'),(4306,'Tom F.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Fitted casual pants that are surprisingly warm','Lots of positive reviews here, and I concur. I can’t speak yet to how well they’ll hold up, but with Patagonia’s lifetime warranty, that’s not really a concern. Wear them and see what they do. What do they do? They fit well and are warm. They are billed as a base layer, but you can definitely wear them around casually and not get cold in the Fahren',136,'2020-06-15'),(4307,'Clayton M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Best down time pants for winter','Fit is perfect, super comfy.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4308,'Gary N.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'R1','Perfect for layering or running',136,'2020-06-15'),(4309,'B. A.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,4.0,'These are a hit, but could use some additional development to further refine','These pants are so close to being perfect for a variety of mild, casual conditions and situations. Extremely comfortable, warm without being too hot, and fit well. My only gripe after two months with them is that they started significantly pilling right in the immediate crotch area very soon after purchase and wear. I bought two pair to alternate b',136,'2020-06-15'),(4310,'Justin S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L/XL',NULL,5.0,'Bought these to lounge around.','Bought these to lounge around. I have some R1 pullover tops too, so love the feel of the material. Keeps me warm in and around the house.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4311,'Justin D.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,5.0,'Great pant layer','Great pant layer',136,'2020-06-15'),(4312,'dan m.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'The start of a great pant','Very good pant, waist could be great if they want back to the early Talus pant inside the waist with waist cinch - the best I have seen anywhere ever - I still have some that were made by Fastex (#192) just for that pant.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4313,'Robert K.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,5.0,'Length is great for my','Length is great for my 6’5 height',136,'2020-06-15'),(4314,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'AMAZING!!!','These pants are sweeeeet! Ultra warm and so so comfortable! I\'ve been waiting a long time to get these, bummed I waited this long! Been wearing them around the house, but purchased to wear under my waders for cold weather fishing.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4315,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Love them!','I am a woman who fits better in men\'s pants usually because the hips aren\'t as big. So these men\'s pants in med. fit perfectly. 5\'7\", 150, athletic with long legs. The only gripe is that I wish the front pockets were zippered. They flare out when you bend and things fall out.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4316,'Andrew J.',NULL,'5\'0 or less','L',NULL,5.0,'These are awesome','A friend recommended these to me a year ago and I didn\'t listen. Big mistake. These are my new go-to pants.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4317,'Chris R.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,4.0,'Mens R1 pants','I love that they are recycled, but would have preferred a selection of colors.. the R1 texture is not my favorite, something smoother would also fit my taste also',136,'2020-06-15'),(4318,'Jared L.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,4.0,'Super Cozy','I\'m a sailboat dweller / alpinist, so these are clutch on those crisp cold mornings. The weight & pack-ability is just about right.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4319,'Greg E.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,5.0,'Good old favorites','Whether you are layering for the cold or slipping into them for an evening of couch surfing, you can’t go wrong',136,'2020-06-15'),(4320,'MtnMomma81',NULL,'None','XS',NULL,3.0,'Mens sizing too big for a petite woman','Love the style and R1 materials. I wish you made the R1 pant in women\'s specific sizes for the length and hips! The mens XS is still too big for me at 5\'3\" 130 lbs. Would love if they had the option of the R1 pants in the women\'s sizes with a shorter inseam but the same loose relaxed cut.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4321,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Zippers!!','I\'ve had a pair of these for a very long time and they have zippers on the side pockets. Please make them that way again and I\'ll buy multiple pairs. They are my go to hang around pant/layer under hunting/fishing pants/waders etc.etc. and have been on many trips. Please add the zippers back!!',136,'2020-06-15'),(4322,'Jonathan O.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'R-1 Pants','They fit so well and are so comfortable, I wear them all of the time. They are sufficiently presentable to even wear to some meetings and at night. I have multiple pairs of R-1\'s and would like to see them offered in different colors.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4323,'andrew',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XL',NULL,5.0,'Great update of very versatjle warm layer','Replaced an 12 year old pair of r1 pants.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4324,'Jake',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,3.0,'Best Pants out there -- But Need zippers','I have 3 pairs of these pants. I wear them everyday. To work, everyday things, skiing, hiking, climbing. They\'re incredible, but the pockets are awful. Everything falls out of them. If you\'re driving with keys in your pockets, they will fall out, guaranteed. I can\'t use the pockets while climbing for obvious reasons or for skiing. I',136,'2020-06-15'),(4325,'Orling',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'The greatest pants i own','The R1 Pants are simply the greatest pants I own. So comfortable and fit me so, so well. They are slimmer than other fleece pants, so you can take some liberties with wearing them in public and still maintain some decency. They are unmatched in comfort. There\'s nothing I would rather wear around my cold house in the winter. They\'re great',136,'2020-06-15'),(4326,'Kerry H.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,1.0,'Pilling far too soon','I will start by telling you that I LOVE everything I have every owned by Patagonia. In October 2018 I purchased the R1 pants and new full zip R1 with hood, one week after I received the pants, they started pilling. I contacted the Customer Service and made a report. I had not worn them under Blue Jeans and had not washed them yet. They started pill',136,'2020-06-15'),(4327,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Great Lounge Pants!','I love these pants! They definitely have a slim cut and the inseam for the Medium is probably closer to 33\" (which works great for me!)',136,'2020-06-15'),(4328,'Greg A.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Best cool to cold weather pants','I’ve worn these pants in every type of weather in Colorado for a little over a year . I wear them for camping all year combined with an r1 hoody and can be toasty warm below freezing all the way down to near zero or mild temps to just stay warm . My favorite pants to wear anywhere for any reason!',136,'2020-06-15'),(4329,'William H.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Go To Pants when the weather gets cool','These are my favorite casual pants once the weather gets cool. Wear them around the house, around the campsite, walking the dog, on car trips, to the grocery & under my waders when it really gets cold. Too baggy to wear as any sort of insulating layer though. I\'ve read complaints about pilling but haven\'t experienced any for myself in',136,'2020-06-15'),(4330,'J',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XL',NULL,1.0,'Be careful on your purchase','The pants look great out of the box. After one wear and not one wash the pants began to fray and look like they are years old. For the price you expect a much better material. Beware before you purchase.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4331,'Mdrich',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,4.0,'Perfect lounging pants','Bought these in October and I\'ve worn them at least once weekly since. A little bit of pilling on the front which is disappointing,but the pants are great for cool weather casual wear and an outer layer to ditch once I get into the gym. I love them and may get the top. They almost mimic a military waffle bottom except with loose ankles.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4332,'Jasonn',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'Great material. Very Durable. Way too long','It would be nice to have an 30 inch inseam as an option. even the XS start at 31 inches.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4333,'Lordideme',NULL,'None','S',NULL,2.0,'6 Month Review','I have had these for six months now and been in the about 30 times.I use these as a base/mid layer under my waders.For summer to late summer early fall in upstate ny they worked well.As the water temps dropped below 45 Degrees the pants really didn\'t cut the mustard. I had to go to my nano puff pants for steelhead season with the R1 as a base.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4334,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'Warm and comfortable','I first got R1 pants back in 2003 and really liked them but the elastic finally wore out several years ago. I replaced them,but that version was almost like tights,and I am skinny. I don\'t like tight pants so the 2010s have been challenging for buying men\'s pants,especially stylish ones from places like patagonia. These new R1s are way ba',136,'2020-06-15'),(4335,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,1.0,'Make them for Women!','My second pair of R1 Women\'s pants finally are biting the dust and there is no choice for women in this weight. Patagonia,please go back to making an R1 choice for women in pants. The men\'s version is not unisex enough and the color is so drab. Thank you.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4336,'Mark',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'Not the old one','I had an older model with zippered pockets. I like that',136,'2020-06-15'),(4337,'Meadowdude',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'Nice pants,comfortable','Bought these before a trip to Alaska. Served me well,but they did come with a fraying seam. Patagonia replaced them within three days of my request!',136,'2020-06-15'),(4338,'Help',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,3.0,'Bring back the old style','I had an old pair of R1 pants,lost them on trip recently. They were the greatest. I would love to replace them,but these are more like sweat pants than a base layer. Patagonia,plz help.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4339,'Quinton',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','None',NULL,4.0,'Wish they had elasticized cuffs','These are awesome but I wish they had elasticized cuffs in addition to the waist band. Would be the perfect layer or lounge pants',136,'2020-06-15'),(4340,'skiptahoe',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Base 4 Fish/Ski','I use them as a base layer under my waiters and ski pants...perfect !',136,'2020-06-15'),(4341,'Beau B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Great Fit...more colors!','I\'ve had these for over a year. Turned in to my go-to base layer for skiing. Great for traveling to and from the slopes and then throw on your ski pants. They also have turned in to my sweatpants in the summer. Year-round weekly washings and still look great. Biggest gripe...MORE colors. This is the end of the second season of the same.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4342,'Beau B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'You need these,now!','I bought a pair of these for layering and warmth outside...and now wear almost nothing else inside! Great fit. Warm yet breathable--and so comfortable I just bought two more pairs. An excellent,lasting value.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4343,'Cdnpage',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'Nice fleece pants','They are comfortable and warm. I wear these in my waders over a baselayer during winter months. My feedback on these pants would be deeper front pockets and add a rear zippered pocket.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4344,'Tim F.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Love R1 pants','Love these--great for hanging around the house on a chilly morning/evening. Wear these with an R1 top,and you can leave the thermostat down low. Great as a layer under waders,great as a base layer for skiing. Good for everything. Can\'t get enough of them.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4345,'Beau B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,3.0,'Add a Zippered Fly and Velcro Cuffs!','I wear them under my shell pants and also under waders. I love the fit and feel of these pants,however they\'re in dire need of a zippered fly! When fishing by boat or hunting with a shell over them,there is no fly to match the fly in the shells I wear. That makes things a bit difficult and aggravating for me.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4346,'Chopin',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Comfortable','Some piling over time,but very nice good quality. Worth it.',136,'2020-06-15'),(4347,'Mike S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'great but run small','Great