end this guy enough.',109,'2020-06-15'),(4440,'Stephen J.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Perfect for my use...','The Micro D Pullover is perfect for my intended use. It is light and folds into a small size. I will carry it in the back of my fishing vest on those days when it might get chilly. In addition, I will wear it on those those days when you need it the first thing but don\'t need it as the day warms up. These conditions are frequent in the mountai',109,'2020-06-15'),(4441,'Chad K.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'My favorite fleece','I had one of these years ago and recently bought another. The fabric is quality. I always think the sizes run weird for Patagonia but I’m about 5’8” and 170 and a small fits me perfectly.',109,'2020-06-15'),(4442,'Andrea B.',NULL,'5\'1 - 5\'3','S/M',NULL,5.0,'Perfect','The perfect lightweight fleece I was looking for.',109,'2020-06-15'),(4443,'Willie',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,3.0,'Close to fine except ginormous neck','I love the austerity of this piece, the timeless casual style and the buttery soft comfortable fit. And of course the legendary quality and interesting color selections. It\'s perfect for what it is except ... the collar is way too big to provide any warmth and comfort and is useless unless you have a huge neck (it will not protect you from the',109,'2020-06-15'),(4444,'Stephen M.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'This is an excellent pullover:','This is an excellent pullover: warm, soft, fits just as expected. I ended up ordering two of them!',109,'2020-06-15'),(4445,'Amy S.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Basic Fleece Comfort','Generous relaxed fit & way comfortable. A great mid-weight basic piece of insulation for layering while outside or just getting cozy reading a book by the fire. You can\'t go wrong with the Micro D Pullover.',109,'2020-06-15'),(4446,'By',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,2.0,'Itchy','I bought this as a gift for my boyfriend, but he says it\'s really itchy when he wears it, which is kind of a surprise because I thought it was super soft. It\'s really disappointing with all the high reviews here too. I just can\'t recommend it for people with sensitive skin.',109,'2020-06-15'),(4447,'Rossy N.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Perfect!','I just received my order today and am absolutely thrilled with this fleece. Thankfully it comes in 3XL to fit my broad shoulders. Comfortable, lightweight and provides the perfect warmth. It looks great and has the Patagonia quality I have come to expect. I can see this getting a lot of use and will probably need to add another. Definitely a winner',109,'2020-06-15'),(4448,'Andy',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'This is great, but miss the Hoodie.','I love this pullover, but I only got it because the hoodie was out of stock. The hoodie was my favorite piece of gear... for travel, leisure, anything and everything. It went everywhere. I lost it in a breakup, and honestly, it is probably the reason that we don\'t talk at all anymore. Please bring it back.',109,'2020-06-15'),(4449,'Doug L.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,5.0,'Awesome','The fleece is very soft and keeps you warm yet it’s still breathable and light weight. Patagonia mad another amazing product!',109,'2020-06-15'),(4450,'Harry513',NULL,'None','M',NULL,2.0,'Inconsistent Sizing','The quality of the fleeces are as expected. Soft,breathable,and seemingly durable. However I have a black one,navy one,and a blue one. All size medium and all fit differently. Black fits perfect like a glove. Navy seems to be a little larger,with a little more room in the chest and sleeves are a tad longer. No big deal. The blue one however I canno',109,'2020-06-15'),(4451,'James M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Excellent pullover','So glad Patagonia made this in a 3XL. Not highly technical,but highly practical. A simple,versatile layering piece that works well for casual and active uses. One of those garments I end up buying in half a dozen colors. Excellent fit. Great value for the price.',109,'2020-06-15'),(4452,'Satisfied',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Versatile Fleece','A light layer that is very versatile - in 40-60 degree weather I can wear a short sleeve shirt underneath and I\'m fine. I have even worn these over long sleeved button down shirts. I write \'these\' because I own them in five colors - by coincidence I\'m wearing one now. Highly recommended.',109,'2020-06-15'),(4453,'Rossy N.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,4.0,'Awesome midlayer,watch out for sizing though!','Purchased one of these last year. Got a small that fit more like a medium,but the fit was perfect. Bought another one this year in the same size and I can barely get it over my head. Did notice that one was made in Mexico and the other in El Salvador,maybe that\'s why the sizing is off.',109,'2020-06-15'),(4454,'Merchant M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Perfect layer','I love this fleece more than any other in your line. It\'s not too light and not too heavy. I usually run hot so a heavy fleece simply makes me sweat. This is what I put on over a t-shirt when it gets really cold. It keeps me warm without overheating. I am 6\' tall 170lbs. and the medium fits perfect. I haven\'t noticed any pilling of t',109,'2020-06-15'),(4455,'Bilibili',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XS',NULL,4.0,'Excellent pullover','Great fit,excellent material. Runs a little bit large. I am 5\'11\'\',135 lbs,slender shoulder,size XS fits me well.',109,'2020-06-15'),(4456,'Jawg',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,3.0,'Nice fit','Nice fit. Looks great but it has an oily hand. The fabric is not as nice as recycled synchilla of years ago.',109,'2020-06-15'),(4457,'Ichthyocentric',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Excellent light fleece pullover.','Perfect for cool mornings and evenings in Spring,Summer & Fall! Softest fleece ever; very comfortable.',109,'2020-06-15'),(4458,'Rick M.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Perfect Fleece','It\'s comfortably thin but an excellent weight,allowing for all kinds of wearing. It fits extremely well,trim enough to look good,but there\'s plenty of room. It feels great,it lasts forever,especially if you don\'t put it in the dryer. I wear it over a Merino Daily T-Shirt - from October until who knows when out here in the Oregon Coas',109,'2020-06-15'),(4459,'Lordideme',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'Love it','The Micro D is perfect for when the warmer temp roll in.Its perfect to thickness to ware around the office or layer under a nano for spring time on the river.',109,'2020-06-15'),(4460,'Kwill',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Quality,Soft,Lightweight','Great affordable fleece. Stitching and material feel and look top notch,ridiculously soft,and very lightweight. I could definitely see myself using this in the future as a midlayer while snowboarding,a light layer while cycling in the morning,or for a casual fleece to wear around town. Great product all around.',109,'2020-06-15'),(4461,'Rossy N.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Fantastic Jacket!','I love this jacket. The quality of the build is excellent and it feels like wrapping yourself in a cocoon.',140,'2020-06-15'),(4462,'Rafik A.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'Love this Jacket','I totally love this thing! I can walk in NYC with a capilene cool short sleeve underneath and be quite warm in sub freezing temperatures yet I don’t over heat indoors, just have to unzip. Super cozy jacket and I get many compliments wherever I go. I thought it was just going to be an occasional use jacket for the winter but its become my main jacke',140,'2020-06-15'),(4463,'William B.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Love it. Super comfy and','Love it. Super comfy and warm',140,'2020-06-15'),(4464,'Rolando B.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,5.0,'Perfect fit','Perfect fit',140,'2020-06-15'),(4465,'Dennis V.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Crazy fun jacket','Super quality. Great fit',140,'2020-06-15'),(4466,'Matthew L.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'My new favorite jacket','I love this jacket. It’s incredibly versatile, it keeps me warm down about the teens and isn’t overly hot in milder weather if you unzip.',140,'2020-06-15'),(4467,'Rossy N.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','NB-7lb',NULL,5.0,'Perfect for cold weather!','Purchased for my husband and I must say he loves it! Very warm, we take long walks in the winter, ideal jacket and it looks good!',140,'2020-06-15'),(4468,'Rossy N.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,4.0,'awesome jacket','furry, cuddly and snuggly',140,'2020-06-15'),(4469,'Robert S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Love this coat...','Love this coat...',140,'2020-06-15'),(4470,'Norsang L.',NULL,'None','XS',NULL,4.0,'Color is just little off','Everything about this jacket is perfect. The only thing that made me give four stars instead of five, is because of the color being not same as on the picture. I have mem\'s retro Jacket and it is true to color. I bought retro x jacket in black and was satisfied with it. Bought this Jacket expecting same but when received the color is not as da',140,'2020-06-15'),(4471,'jean-paul f.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Goes well with a La Croix','Have you ever wondered what it would be like to be a bear? Well I now know... It\'s fantastic! Each time I wear this jacket I turn whatever my surroundings are into pure undisturbed nature. Snow, wind, cold, angry people, this jacket protects you from it all. It is fashionable enough to wear to your Grandmas 60th birthday or a New York roof top',140,'2020-06-15'),(4472,'Rossy N.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S',NULL,5.0,'Great jacket','My teen daughter wanted a fleece for winter and this was perfect - so cozy, so warm, great fit - she loves it!',140,'2020-06-15'),(4473,'Rick M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Black Bear Coat','AWESOME! Very Warm',140,'2020-06-15'),(4474,'Rossy N.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Love this jacket!!!','This arrived just in time for the shift into the cold wetness of late Fall in New England, and it is perfect for our recent weather: daytime highs in the 30\'s, wind chills in the mid-20\'s, and intermittent rain on some days. It is also a much better choice for taking our dog out just before bedtime; synthetics feel warmer than down jacket',140,'2020-06-15'),(4475,'Rossy N.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Mens Recycled Fleece Down Jacket = Amazing!','This is so warm and dare I say good looking and fashionable in a bear-is kind of way. Oh and not to mention just plain fun. We need more of that right now.! I am 6 foot 2 and the XXL and it fits! Toasty warm! Great that it is both recycled fleece and down. A conversation starter for doing the planet good.',140,'2020-06-15'),(4476,'Rossy N.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Super warm & perfect fit!','I have had many Patagonia jackets over the years but this one is a step above the rest! Perfect is every way!',140,'2020-06-15'),(4477,'Joseph N.',NULL,'5\'0 or less','NB-7lb',NULL,5.0,'Dopest Jacket I own','I can walk out of my apartment into the cold and stay warm. And then on the subway unzip my jacket and stay cool enough. Perfect blend. Would recommend.',140,'2020-06-15'),(4478,'Spaceman',NULL,'None','NB-7lb',NULL,5.0,'Best Jacket','Only negative is being asked where I got the jacket when I wear it. Eventually everyone in Minnesota will have one.',140,'2020-06-15'),(4479,'Colter S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Outstanding Jacket','This feels like you’re wearing a teddy bear. Immensely warm and cozy, makes me excited to go outside in the cold.',140,'2020-06-15'),(4480,'Win G.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'A fleece/down take on the timeless bison jacket look','Some of the best Patagonia pieces are inspired by the western wilds but meant for civilized use. Like this revisionist take on the classic bison jacket. A gorgeous round town glam item that feels big and warm and looks fantastic. Nice high collar you can zip up and shrink down into when it\'s cold. The coated interior makes it easy to put on ov',140,'2020-06-15'),(4481,'GMack',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Warm, well made, roomy','It\'s the big fuzzy fleece jacket of your dreams. The kind that if you leave around a significant other or climbing partner will quickly disappear. And you definitely will get comments wearing it - judge for yourself whether it\'s curiosity or envy.',140,'2020-06-15'),(4482,'PATRICK',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'One Negative','The thumb holes if you are not using them are annoying, maybe have the option of get the garment with or without the thumb holes.',95,'2020-06-15'),(4483,'Dilley',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,4.0,'hits all the bases','Material feels fantastic. Fit is good for me because the medium runs slim and long. I\'m 6\'2\" tall 165 lbs and 38 chest. It fits snug enough over a baselayer with zip t neck, but also with a baselayer and/or the R1 pullover underneath. The color blue I got pops really nicely and length of arms/hem is perfect. The Hem is even slightly',95,'2020-06-15'),(4484,'Rossy N.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,3.0,'Sizing isuues... AGAIN!','Upon receiving this I fell in love. Then, I tried it on and felt I\'d just put on a tent. It\'s HUGE! I\'m 6ft and 175lbs and commonly wear size large in numerous brands due to broad shoulders, even Patagonia. For example, I have 2 Performance Better Sweaters in Large and they fit perfectly. So why can\'t Patagonia have consistent s',95,'2020-06-15'),(4485,'Rick',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Exactly what I was looking for','About eight years ago I bought a mountain hardwear stretch fleece 1/4 zip that I absolutely love. They no longer make it but I stumbled across this Patagonia Crosstrek 1/4 zip and its very similar. I wanted something with polyester fleece with elastane or spandex materials (stretch fleece). For winter hikes this is what you want. Its form fitting a',95,'2020-06-15'),(4486,'Bob T.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,3.0,'Bad craftsmanship','I bought this product to wear on travel and daily use. The first item I received back in December 2019. I wore less than 3 times and hand washed twice. No problem one the first washes; second time issues with stitching. I contacted Patagonia and get a replace product within days. I wore the item one time to work and washed it after work. Same issue',95,'2020-06-15'),(4487,'RG V.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,5.0,'A nearly perfect piece of clothing/equipment','I own four of these 1/4 zip pullovers and among all of my Patagonia gear, this particular item may just be my single most favorite. First, the fit is perfect; I’m a men’s L. I wear this for late fall or early spring mtn biking, skiing as a base layer and always for Fat Biking. Going out to the woodpile? Yup pull on a 1/4 zip Crosstrek. Cool Maine e',95,'2020-06-15'),(4488,'James P.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'golf shirt for ireland','great for those cool days in ireland.',95,'2020-06-15'),(4489,'Jim R.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Crosstrek 1/4 Zip','The Crosstrek is awesome! I purchased it to wear during winter rounds of golf (30\'s-40\'s). It really easy to swing clubs, plus with a base layer, plenty warm. I have two already, looking to buy a third.',95,'2020-06-15'),(4490,'Dan S.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Awesome for winter runs','Picked it up for running this winter and so far its been perfect, with a light layer underneath, its been the perfect outer layer in temps into the low 30\'s. I\'m 6\'2 195lbs and the medium is perfect for a close fit. I actually prefer it to my R1',95,'2020-06-15'),(4491,'Thomas L.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','NB-7lb',NULL,5.0,'Perfect Added Layer','This is a really nice layer for a cold run. I often run in the early morning and need to layer up to stay warm but also breath. I really like the thumb holes in the sleeves as an option for keeping my hands warm. Love it.',95,'2020-06-15'),(4492,'Alexandra B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Looks good','I bought this as a gift for my husband, and it looks great on him. He likes it very much. It\'s lighter than the better sweater, so good for fall. Even though it says regular fit, I think 