h, it started to pils. The reviews about the pilling are true here.',154,'2020-06-15'),(4614,'Pablo',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XL',NULL,3.0,'Not slim fit','Soft nice blue color, but the fitting is not what they advertised for. I\'m always size L on Patagonia, but when I saw that this product is slim fit, I ordered XL. Way too big. I\'m 5\'9\'\' and 200lb. Order your regular size.',154,'2020-06-15'),(4615,'Milestoner',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'dolomite blue','i picked up a medium size in store, and it’s super nice and comfy. i prefer pullovers versus the full zips, but this has been my go to hoody for lounging and more relaxed days. the dolomite blue is such a calm and beautiful color. plus it’s name after some beautiful mountains! i haven’t experienced any piling yet and this hoodie has been getting us',154,'2020-06-15'),(4616,'Jered P.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Keep it simple','Good fit and comfortable feel.',154,'2020-06-15'),(4617,'Karen S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,3.0,'Nice quality','But, WAY too big. My husband always wears a large, but this sweatshirt looked like a 2X.',154,'2020-06-15'),(4618,'Nathaniel B.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,5.0,'Fit well. Warm.','Fit well. Warm.',154,'2020-06-15'),(4619,'Rossy N.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Great sweater','This sweater is the most comfortable one in my closet, so much I want to wear it all the time and I think I could because of the build quality. The price seemed a little high but now that I\'ve worn it, it was totally worth it!',154,'2020-06-15'),(4620,'Terence S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Excellent quality and fit.','Excellent quality and fit.',154,'2020-06-15'),(4621,'Larry G.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,1.0,'When fully zipped up, it','When fully zipped up, it does not provide protection and warmth for my neck in the collarbone area. Also the hood only works when it is tied up. This is the same problem with your light and variable jackets. They just do not work in the wind and do not provideProtection in that neck area.',154,'2020-06-15'),(4622,'Carol K.',NULL,'5\'1 - 5\'3','M/L',NULL,5.0,'Quality','Patagonia does care about the customer, they take pride in their work, I\'m so glad I found out how great the quality/well made, the clothing is. Thank you, thank you',154,'2020-06-15'),(4623,'Kevin G.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'Immediately Comfortable','Nice and soft. Like most Patagonia items, it runs a little larger than other brands. I\'m 5\'8\" and 145 lbs. A small fits perfectly.',154,'2020-06-15'),(4624,'Corey E.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Good sweatshirt','Casual comfortable',154,'2020-06-15'),(4625,'Rossy N.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','XS',NULL,5.0,'Exactly as described!','Exactly as described!',154,'2020-06-15'),(4626,'Darrell D.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'great hoodie','A bit snug in the fit, but overall worth it, it\'s warmth and appearance make it a great buy.',154,'2020-06-15'),(4627,'Shawn B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Perfect for Warmer climates','Functional and great weight for warmth on cool nights and mornings. Nice feel and true to size.',154,'2020-06-15'),(4628,'JF',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,3.0,'Reviews were right - pils like crazy','I assumed everyone complaining of pils didn’t know how to wash their clothes or didn’t own a sweater stone, I was wrong. I’ve had this jacket for about a week and I have pils along both arms and the wrist cuffs from light use. I’m on the fence about returning it because it feels great and the fit is spot on, but the quality is weak.',154,'2020-06-15'),(4629,'Rossy N.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,1.0,'Lighter weight and fabric pils!','I am really disappointed with my new P-6 hoodie. My original Patagonia hoodie was looking a bit worn so I decided to replace it with a new one. The fabric literally began to pil the first time I wore it and it quickly became too shabby to wear at all.',154,'2020-06-15'),(4630,'haze',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'Very glad Patagonia made this','This is a great hoody. No nonsense, simple, lightweight. I haven\'t experienced the piling that most reviewers mention even though I sleep in mine sometimes. I have the dolomite blue. I would say don\'t change anything about these Patagonia, and just keep pumping out more colors. So bummed that I missed the forge grey! I was a little surpri',154,'2020-06-15'),(4631,'Mark K.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Very cozy sweatshirt','I noticed some of the comments regarding pils but anything that’s woven is going to pil on some level. The pils could be addressed with a sweater stone. I’ve found the material to be extremely cozy. Great for a casual office environment or to throw on over a T-shirt. I’ve only worn it a few times so I can’t attest to how it will last over time but ',154,'2020-06-15'),(4632,'Craig',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,2.0,'Some good/some bad','Fit and color is great. Super soft. I bought it in 3 colors. Unfortunately they all started to pill pretty quick. I can still wear casually and as a mid layer, but can no longer wear to the office or out because of the piling.',154,'2020-06-15'),(4633,'Jonathan D.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'Consistently great','I live in FL so we don’t have any stores with Patagonia. I pickup my Patagonia items while on snowboarding trips or online. Always worth the extra effort to find some Patagonia gear. The quality and fit are worth the price. Great company. Keep up the good work. Only mild recommendation is to make the sleeves a tad longer for us taller people.',154,'2020-06-15'),(4634,'Phillip H.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'P-6 lightweight hoody','Had the sweater for a week and love it. It fits great, the material is very comfortable. I’ve read that this item gets pilled up, so we’ll see what happens once I wash it.',154,'2020-06-15'),(4635,'Rossy N.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','NB-7lb',NULL,5.0,'Great Office Hoody!','My co workers like to keep our office freezing cold! This hoody keeps me warm and comfortable during the work day, while my colleagues attempt to turn the office into the arctic tundra.',154,'2020-06-15'),(4636,'Wade E.',NULL,'5\'0 or less','NB-7lb',NULL,5.0,'lightweight full-zip hoody','Super soft, love the feel, pilled really fast though.',154,'2020-06-15'),(4637,'Nathan W.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,1.0,'Pils, pils, pils','Great fit, soft material. Pils instantly. I wore this under a shell once, and pils (pills) appeared on the elbows and stomach area. I sent it back.',154,'2020-06-15'),(4638,'Shawn T.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Amazing Sweatshirt','Lightweight, well constructed, amazing fit, buy one now!',154,'2020-06-15'),(4639,'Charles B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,3.0,'Comfortable Yet Pills A LOT','I purchased this sweater less than a month ago for a two-week trip. Overall, the sweater is very comfortable, feels amazing on and keeps me warm when I need it, especially here in Utah as it\'s still a bit cool. My only comment is that it has pilled so much around the wrists and waist to the point it\'s become unattractive. This is my first',154,'2020-06-15'),(4640,'Courtney L.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,1.0,'M\'s P-6 Label Lightweight Full-Zip Hoody Pills immediately','I bought this hoodie for a Christmas present and after the recipient wore it 5 times it started to pill. After 1 wash, it was way worse. Very upsetting bc he REALLY likes it, but it is unwearable any longer. At this price, you\'d think Patagonia would have prevented this from happening. So bummed. I would not recommend this product, maybe there',154,'2020-06-15'),(4641,'William M.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,2.0,'Pills quite quickly, leaving a once pleasurable hoodie a disappointment','I purchased this hoodie at the Patagonia store in Seattle less than a month ago. I am extremely picky regarding my hoodies, and this one was perfect. It is very soft, thick enough to warm against chill wind, and has a good hood with enough fabric to not \"pull\" when you turn your head. I do wear it frequently, probably 4-5 