,'Rossy N.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'It’s a great sweatshirt that','It’s a great sweatshirt that looks good and keeps me warm. It’s a little bigger than I intended but it still fits good.',151,'2020-06-15'),(4699,'Michael',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great Sweatshirt','Product was excellent for my purposes. Putting on the shirt is easy and the inside feels soft against the skin. The outside of the garment feels coarse but durable. At first you may find the garment stiff but overtime it breaks in. Fit was great for my slim body build although it could be better. Good for layering.',151,'2020-06-15'),(4700,'Dc G.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Buying More','This is the best sweater I\'ve ever purchased. It\'s the perfect thickness for base layer winter weather, or all through spring/fall as a top layer. I wear it for nearly everything... Climbing, Hiking, Running (although you\'ll definitely sweat in it), grocery shopping, Lounging around the house, etc. It has a great athletic fit.',151,'2020-06-15'),(4701,'Gene T.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,3.0,'P-5 sweat shurts','Excellent fit -great comfort-good color selection and priced right!',151,'2020-06-15'),(4702,'Anthony B.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'no better sweatshirt','If a simple crewneck sweatshirt is what you\'re looking for, this is the best you could ever get. I have two of them, the baby blue color is fantastic. They get softer as you wear them and are the perfect layer for spring. You will not regret this purchase.',151,'2020-06-15'),(4703,'Kevin B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Perfect Fit','I just bought this sweatshirt for the last month of cold weather here in the Blue Ridge Mountains and I wish I had bought it at the beginning of winter. It is a perfect fit every way around and incredibly warm. I\'ve had it four days now and I\'ve wanted to wear it everyday. This morning I had to talk myself out of wearing it to work for th',151,'2020-06-15'),(4704,'Rossy N.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Excellent Sweatshirt!','I love this crew sweatshirt. I read some of the other reviews and was worried a bit that it wouldn’t fit correctly but to my surprise it fits great. I think the key to this is you have to have very broad shoulders or be a big dude. I’m 6’3” 230 lbs and an XL fits me flawlessly. Length is good, width is good. I bought it in the weathered stone and t',151,'2020-06-15'),(4705,'Chris',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,4.0,'Great but...','I found this sweatshirt to be tighter than most of Patagonia’s other items but, after a few wears it stretched out in all the right places and currently feels great! The sweater is very thick and feels of quality, overall it’s a fantastic sweater but if you are in between sizes I recommend sizing up.',151,'2020-06-15'),(4706,'Cs',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Great fit except','I love this sweatshirt, has a little flexibility compared to others I have worn. Stitching is tough and won\'t have any loose areas......I absolutely love it, however around the shoulder area, where the seam is, it sticks up like its been permanently on a hangar. So where the shoulders are, the junction is not smooth...still would buy again.',151,'2020-06-15'),(4707,'Frost',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'New favorite','really excellent sweatshirt, fit is excellent, feel is excellent, party time, excellent.',151,'2020-06-15'),(4708,'Rossy N.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,4.0,'Among best sweatshirts I’ve owned','Super durable materials (heavy weight) makes this my favorite sweatshirt currently. Even using it to play tennis in cold weather. (Instead of my technical gear). I’d say this is a good lifestyle causal piece that has some gears!',151,'2020-06-15'),(4709,'Brandon',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,4.0,'Great Hoody, but a bit big','I am 5\'9\" and about 185 lbs, smalls tend to be a bit tight in the pit/under arm area and a bit short in the sleeve so I purchased a medium thinking it would solve the problem. Well, it solved the problem too well. While there is ample room in the areas listed above, the hoody is a bit loose and baggy every where else. Otherwise, the color',166,'2020-06-15'),(4710,'Conner C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Bison Hoodie','I have bought a lot of hoodies and they all run a little different. Theyre good when you could find what fit you but its hit or miss with a lot of them. What you wear in one brand my be totally different in another. With all that said here is how I would measure Patagonia hoodies. If you wear a large t-shirt youll wanna get an Large in this hoodie.',166,'2020-06-15'),(4711,'Rossy N.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','LT',NULL,5.0,'Bison Hoody was a hit!!','Bought this hoody as a gift for a friend who happens to be tall and thin and always has a hard time finding good fitting hoodies. He loved it and the fitting was perfect. It is a very well made hoodie, loved the material!!',166,'2020-06-15'),(4712,'Rossy N.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Uprisal hoody','Uprisal hoody',166,'2020-06-15'),(4713,'Tonya F.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'This fits great and is','This fits great and is comfy.',166,'2020-06-15'),(4714,'Cara G.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Beautiful and comfortable','This was a holiday gift for my husband and he absolutely loved the design. Well made and very comfortable.',166,'2020-06-15'),(4715,'Kaylee S.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','M',NULL,5.0,'Awesome Hoodie.','Another great gift for my',166,'2020-06-15'),(4716,'Chris N.',NULL,'None','L/XL',NULL,1.0,'What happened','This is my second Patagonia purchase (LOVE the retro x jacket) but it frustrated me very much. I love the look and material quality and tried it on in my size (large (I’m 5’9” 185) and it was like wearing a straight jacket. I reluctantly tried on and purchased an xl (way too long for me) but even then after wearing it a time or two I gave it to my',166,'2020-06-15'),(4717,'Rossy N.',NULL,'None','None',NULL,5.0,'great','great',166,'2020-06-15'),(4718,'Rossy N.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'A hoody that fits!','Finally a hoody that fits. The body is trim, the arms have no excess material flapping around. This hoody is the slim version of your favorite jeans. If you\'re not slim and trim, size up. I\'m 5\' 10\", 145 - most clothes fit me baggy unless they\'re trim fit.',166,'2020-06-15'),(4719,'Rossy N.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Great fit','Love this jacket. I’m 5’10 210 pounds and the large fits great.',166,'2020-06-15'),(4720,'Kathy K.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,4.0,'Great sweatshirt','The hole where your head comes out is a little small but otherwise it fits well.',166,'2020-06-15'),(4721,'Wes S.',NULL,'None','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Hoodie snz','6’1 240 athletic',166,'2020-06-15'),(4722,'Rossy N.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Great all around sweatshirt','Very happy with the fit. I haven’t tried any of the other Patagonia pullovers but it seems to have a nice slim cut. It’s not baggy at all. I’m 6’1 175 and ordered a medium. I would recommend. Wore it in the 60s and found it to be adequate warmth. It’s definitely a mid-heavyweight sweatshirt.',166,'2020-06-15'),(4723,'Joseph',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','None',NULL,2.0,'Terrible quality fabric','The sweater is oversized and boxy and very soft and super cute but it pills almost immediately and went from a sweater I bought to wear to work to a sweater I can\'t wear to work because it looks so crappy in three wears. Awful.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4724,'Torsten',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,3.0,'Great Sweater - but smelly','Beautiful sweater. Cosy material and fits like a glove (6.1 ft and 165 lbs - size M). The blue striped color combination is easy to match with other items and adds a bit of pizzazz. The only downside: it smells like an army surplus store. Dont know if this is the inherent odor of recycled cashmere or is do to inappropriate storage (bought from Pata',176,'2020-06-15'),(4725,'Leana S.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Love my cashmere sweater','I’ve already worn it twice this week!',176,'2020-06-15'),(4726,'CHARLENE M.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','L',NULL,5.0,'Sweater','Great fit and comfort. If it has durability I’d expect from Patagonia it will be worn many times over many more years.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4727,'Carrie S.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'My new favorite piece of clothing.','My wife bought this for me for Christmas. This sweater is so soft and so comfortable I never want to take it off. I will wear this until it falls apart!',176,'2020-06-15'),(4728,'Evelyne B.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,3.0,'Too wide.','I bought this sweater for my husband. He is 6’2”, 175 lb, so I bought a size large, so it would be long enough in the sleeves and waist. This sweater hangs kind of shapelessly off his shoulders, and even on his arms. It lacks definition. Doesn’t hug the waist or wrist.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4729,'Rossy N.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Awesome product! Got it for','Awesome product! Got it for Christmas and it is by far the best gift received!',176,'2020-06-15'),(4730,'John',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'True Patagonia','Can’t say enough good things about the quality, and overall fit and finish of these cashmere crew’s by Patagonia.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4731,'Christine',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Hit','I bought 3 as Xmas presents and they were all a big hit.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4732,'Allan C.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Beautiful','Very soft, lovely texture, looks great at work, on weekends and is nice for travel. Fits true to my size.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4733,'Gretchen A.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','XL',NULL,5.0,'exactly right','My husband loves it. Fits true to size. Soft, warm and stylish. Can’t miss with this sweater',176,'2020-06-15'),(4734,'Verna L.',NULL,'5\'1 - 5\'3','None',NULL,5.0,'Great fit and warm','Great fit and warm',176,'2020-06-15'),(4735,'John W.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Exactly what I was hoping for...','The color was great, fit was perfect, and the sweater is light, yet warm.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4736,'Kendra F.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,5.0,'Love all your products','Love all your products',176,'2020-06-15'),(4737,'Rossy N.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Great sweater!','Very comfortable. great sweater.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4738,'JEANNE B.',NULL,'5\'4- 5\'6','S/M',NULL,5.0,'This sweater is perfect','So soft, so well made, such a great fit. Love the color and everything about it. And it’s made from recycled cashmere!!',176,'2020-06-15'),(4739,'Rossy N.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'great sweater','wearing it right now - love the fit and color blue.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4740,'Tim M.',NULL,'5\'0 or less','XL',NULL,5.0,'Incredible Sweater','Wow, that\'s my first thought with this piece I received, so warm, stylish and incredible comfortable... Cant wait for my next one.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4741,'Gary B.',NULL,'None','S',NULL,5.0,'Wonderful','Feels soft and light and gives a great layer of warmth. I’m 5’7” and 145 lbs and the small was fine. Plus, it’s Patagonia. I actually started to look at other providers, but I realized that Patagonia checks all the boxes: responsibly sourced, well made with a life time guarantee and treats employees fairly. That’s all I need.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4742,'Erich H.',NULL,'None','M',NULL,5.0,'Steez For Days','If your office is having an ugly sweater party, skip this sweater and keep looking. I don\'t want to take the sweater off, which may be problematic when its time to take a shower. The material has a delightful next to skin feel and the beech brown has a pleasant warm autumn steez. Only down side is my neck wants to be cozy like the rest of my t',176,'2020-06-15'),(4743,'Rossy N.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Cozy Cozy Cashmere!','Heavier than my other cashmere sweaters, and less delicate. A wonderful, cozy sweater for chilly nights.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4744,'A. B.',NULL,'None','XXL',NULL,5.0,'Great sweater','I’ve worn it three times so far and have tons of compliments. Best part is that my wife loves when I wear it.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4745,'Tripp W.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Comfortable, soft, warm and looks great','I love the sweater so much that I bought a second one already. I’ve been wearing them a lot for travel because they stay good looking and in shape, even after a red eye, and you can roll straight into the office and still look somewhat put together.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4746,'Garrett C.',NULL,'6\'7 or above','L',NULL,5.0,'Fantastic Sweater','This has become my favorite sweater. Great build quality, and the perfect weight for where I live. The large fits me perfectly, but I\'m 6\'7, and normally wear XL. I\'d suggest getting it a size under what you would normally buy.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4747,'Rossy N.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'My favorite sweaters of all time!','I started wearing Patagonia cashmere sweaters about 20 years ago. I had several and wore them most days during the winter. Those eventually wore out after so much wear. I bought a few more this year and could not be happier! The feel and fit are perfect. They are like having some old friends back. I love the colors this season too!',176,'2020-06-15'),(4748,'Cody P.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Recycled Goodness','Just as soft as any of my other high-end cashmere sweaters, and I feel a lot better knowing this one is recycled! Awesome product! If they make a lighter grey, I’ll buy that as well.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4749,'Catherine G.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Beautiful sweater','Finally! After much searching, we have found a sweater that works. Warm, fit s great, not itchy, and looks fantastic! Thank you, Patagonia!',176,'2020-06-15'),(4750,'Kirk C.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'I love this sweater...','This sweater is insanely comfortable and the cut and fit is spot on. It is warm, cozy and still holds all of the great qualities of wool - what\'s not to love with this one!',176,'2020-06-15'),(4751,'Benjamin J.',NULL,'6\'4 - 6\'6','L',NULL,5.0,'Good size, warm, comfortable.','It’s very light and soft to the touch, my one reservation about it is that it can feel kind of scratchy on my torso and arms. I’m hopeful that will stop after some use as I’ve only had it for a week and worn it 2-3 times.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4752,'DONALD C.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Nice sweater but know the sizing runs large','It\'s a very nice cashmere sweater. Seems very well made. Pretty thick so should be nice and warm. The sizing seems to run quite large. I usually wear an XL or an XXL but in this sweater I needed a L because the XL ran quite large in the body.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4753,'DonC',NULL,'None','L/XL',NULL,5.0,'Nice useful sweater but runs *really* large','This is a very nice sweater which will hopefully wear well. Soft as well as nice and warm. As with most Patagonia gear, well constructed. Runs several circles around the offerings from Arcteryx, which usually has nice gear. Just be careful with the sizing. As noted by one reviewer, this sweater runs very large in the body. I usually wear an XL or i',176,'2020-06-15'),(4754,'Dan F.',NULL,'None','L/XL',NULL,5.0,'Recycled?','Great fit. Great color. Built well. Looks like it will last.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4755,'Ted K.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Cashmere Crewneck','I love this sweater. Very comfortable, soft material, versatile with other clothing. Highly recommend.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4756,'Joseph N.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','S',NULL,5.0,'As expected','Comfortable. Good looking. Who could ask for anything more. I have two other cashmere sweaters from Patagonia over the years and I will say this recycled version is just a titch itchier. But just a titch. Fits me perfectly and I’m 5’8” and 145lbs with slightly broad shoulders and purchased a small.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4757,'xav',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Cashmere crew','An absolutely amazing sweater. So so soft. And incredibly good looking. I got it in wooly blue and adore it. Feels like an old friend.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4758,'Thomas W.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Recycled Cashmere sweater','Good weight',176,'2020-06-15'),(4759,'M. H.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Best ever','I bought this sweater from the SLC Patagonia outlet in 1998. Been wearing it for almost 20 years for everything from dress up to backcountry skiing/mountain biking. My dear (86yo.) mother put patches on the elbows about 5 years ago. I plan to send it back to be recycled when I buy the new one. Buy this sweater! You won\'t regret it.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4760,'Kay B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'A workhorse of a sweater','My husband took this sweater on a 30 day November tour of Northern Europe and wore it almost every day. Over T-shirt’s, dress shirts, with jeans and nice pants. It always looked nice and was warm and comfortable.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4761,'Joe L.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','XL',NULL,5.0,'Excellent','Great relaxed fit, super soft, and high quality.',176,'2020-06-15'),(4762,'Ian W.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Nice investment','A little pricey, yes but worth it if you\'re looking for something warm that you can wear wherever. I found some of the other sweaters ran large but a medium fits good for me (5\'9\"/160lbs).',176,'2020-06-15'),(4763,'Donald K.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Best Sweater you can Buy','Yes, this sweater is a little pricey compared to other Patagonia items, but its worth it. Its unbelievably warm, its rugged enough to wear outdoors, and slick enough to wear to the office. I bought two and wear them a lot. Just waiting for more colors to come out. Also, its a great length some of the other Patagonia sweaters are too long. This one ',176,'2020-06-15'),(4764,'Kevin',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','0',NULL,5.0,'Great Sweater','It feels like a regular wool sweater to me. I wore it yesterday with a lightweight long sleeve t-shirt underneath and, unlike other reviewers, I didn\'t notice any itchiness. It is a comfortable, classic weight sweater with turned-back cuffs (the cuff is held in place by a stitch of yarn). The arms were a perfect length for me, but I tend to ge',174,'2020-06-15'),(4765,'Jennifer S.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L/XL',NULL,4.0,'Well made but itchy','I purchased this sweater for my 20 year old son. It arrived on time for the holiday and the color and fit is just as described. He is tall and thin and I ordered him an xlg & he looks great in it. He did state that he will always need to wear a long sleeve shirt under the sweater because it is very itchy (which is why I have 4 stars rather than',174,'2020-06-15'),(4766,'Jonathan R.',NULL,'None','L',NULL,2.0,'It was great until....','I have an older version of this sweater with the neck zip. Two of them actually. I love them, fit great, warm, dressy enough for work, but not too polished. I realized after owning them for some time, it was probably time to wash them. I always wore them as an outside layer for office work so they never got dirty. I followed the directions to the l',174,'2020-06-15'),(4767,'Matthew B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','L',NULL,5.0,'Amazing as always','I love this sweater and am always impressed with the look and quality of Patagonia products. I only have a few items (mostly due to cost) but those items have been in rotation for years. I am happy to add this sweater to the rotation.',174,'2020-06-15'),(4768,'Norman B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,2.0,'Sleeves Too Long','I wear sweaters all the time. I purchased a medium and found that the sleeves are 2\" too long on me. I a 5\'9\" slim guy and have never had this issue.',174,'2020-06-15'),(4769,'Unknown',NULL,'None','None',NULL,4.0,'Nice, warm, but heavy. What','Nice, warm, but heavy. What happened to your cashmere sweaters, equally warm but lighter to wear?',174,'2020-06-15'),(4770,'Sam G.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,4.0,'Great sweater. Sizing is tough.','I really like this sweater, but had a tough time finding the right size. I wear some things from Patagonia that are men’s size large and some men’s size medium. I originally bought a large, and exchanged for a medium. Still, the sleeves and body are a little long. Otherwise, the sweater is of great quality and design.',174,'2020-06-15'),(4771,'Mark W.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Lightweight and very warm.','Lightweight and very warm.',174,'2020-06-15'),(4772,'Catherine G.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,3.0,'Beautiful sweater, but was too itchy','The color looked amazing, and it was true to size. However, it was a little too itchy, so had to take it back. Giving the recycled cashmere a chance as of this writing!',174,'2020-06-15'),(4773,'Eric O.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','S',NULL,5.0,'Comfy, heavy, and sharp looking','The sweater is perfect for fall/winter! The wool isn\'t too scratchy, the fit is solid (I\'m 5\'10\" 155 lbs and went with a small), and the pattern and colors are very sharp.',174,'2020-06-15'),(4774,'Dustin B.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Amazing Sweater','Where it all the time, is very warm and cozy!',174,'2020-06-15'),(4775,'Trevor K.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','XL',NULL,5.0,'Warm & Soft','Sweater is warmer than expected for its weight. Also, much softer than expected. However, it seems to run a little large/long in the XL. I\'m 5\'11\", 225lbs and it\'s still a little large.',174,'2020-06-15'),(4776,'Rossy N.',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','L',NULL,5.0,'Bought for my pappa!!','I bought this sweater for my pappa for Christmas (my family is fully in love with Patagonia as a company and their values). After he let me try it on I immediately wanted one for myself. It is perfectly oversized and heavy but still hugs the body! Seriously wish I would have bought one for myself.',174,'2020-06-15'),(4777,'Peter B.',NULL,'5\'7 - 5\'9','M',NULL,5.0,'Recycled Wool Sweater','This sweater is perfect for the Pacific NW and our three season dampness. We keep our house cool, so it is great inside and to go outside I add a rain shell and that is usually warm enough. When it does get cold, it is great as a second layer over a long sleeved base which also negates itching on bare skin. I\'m thinking about getting another.',174,'2020-06-15'),(4778,'Rossy N.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Great sweater','I live in Alaska and wear a lot of sweaters. This is a keeper. I\'m 6\'0 160lbs and the the medium was perfect. The sleeve length is perfect- goes just past the wrist a little and because it has a little stretch to it makes it very easy to move around in without it pulling this way and that (would make a good ski sweater I would think..). T',174,'2020-06-15'),(4779,'Rossy N.',NULL,'5\'10 - 6\'0','M',NULL,5.0,'Love this sweater!','I was so excited to purchase a sweater using recycled materials. When I opened my package, I could see right away that the sweater was of great quality. The fit is perfect and the sweater looks high-end. It\'s a great piece of durable clothing that I hope will last for many years. I\'m excited to buy more recycled clothing, such as this swe',174,'2020-06-15'),(4780,'John',NULL,'6\'1 - 6\'3','M',NULL,3.0,'Too itchy','I\'m not sure if it\'s the knit, or the recycled Nylon, but it\'s very itchy. As soon as I tried it on I knew it wasn\'t going to work. I\'m relatively tolerant of wool, owning Merino shirts and socks, and the recycled Cashmere sweater I received at the same time is very comfortable. This sweater fits and looks great I would kee',174,'2020-06-15');
